#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:110
msgid "Points of caution"
msgstr "Ehtiyot bo'lish nuqtalari"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:112
msgid ""
"Owl components are rendered entirely in JavaScript by the browser. This "
"can cause some issues:"
msgstr ""
"Owl komponentlari brauzer tomonidan to'liq JavaScript da ko'rsatiladi."
" Bu ba'zi muammolarga olib kelishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:115
#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:122
msgid "Layout shift"
msgstr "Tartib siljishi"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:116
#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:147
msgid "Poorer indexing by search engines"
msgstr "Qidiruv tizimlari tomonidan yomonroq indekslash"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:118
msgid ""
"For these reasons, you should only use Owl components on the portal and "
"website for specific use cases described below."
msgstr ""
"Shu sabablarga ko'ra, Owl komponentlarini portal va veb-saytda faqat"
" quyida tasvirlangan muayyan foydalanish holatlarida ishlatish kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:124
msgid ""
"When a page initially renders content, and that content subsequently "
"moves (\"shifts\") within the page, this is referred to as a layout "
"shift. When using Owl components in the portal or website, all of the "
"HTML that surrounds the Owl component is rendered by the server and is "
"the first thing that will be displayed to the user. When JavaScript "
"starts running, Owl will mount your component, which will likely cause "
"the surrounding elements to move around on the page. This can cause poor "
"user experience: the user sees an element on the page that was initially "
"rendered and with which they want to interact, so they move their cursor "
"or finger above that element. Just as they're about to click, the Owl "
"component is mounted, and the element they want to interact with is "
"moved. They click and interact with the Owl app instead."
msgstr ""
"Sahifa dastlab kontent ko'rsatganda va bu kontent keyinchalik sahifa"
" ichida siljiganda, bu tartib siljishi deb ataladi. Portal yoki veb-saytda"
" Owl komponentlarini ishlatganda, Owl komponentini o'rab turgan barcha HTML"
" server tomonidan ko'rsatiladi va foydalanuvchiga birinchi bo'lib ko'rsatiladigan"
" narsa hisoblanadi. JavaScript ishga tushganda, Owl komponentingizni o'rnatadi,"
" bu esa sahifadagi atrofdagi elementlarni harakatlantirishiga olib kelishi mumkin."
" Bu yomonroq foydalanuvchi tajribasiga sabab bo'lishi mumkin: foydalanuvchi"
" sahifada dastlab ko'rsatilgan va u bilan muloqot qilmoqchi bo'lgan elementni"
" ko'radi, shuning uchun kursor yoki barmog'ini ushbu element ustiga ko'chiradi."
" Ular bosishga yaqin bo'lganda, Owl komponenti o'rnatiladi va ular muloqot"
" qilmoqchi bo'lgan element ko'chiriladi. Ular buning o'rniga Owl ilovasini bosadi."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:135
msgid ""
"This can be a frustrating experience, so you should be careful when "
"designing your page that the Owl component will not move elements around."
" This can be achieved in various ways, e.g. by positioning it below all "
"other existing elements, not having other interactive elements around, or"
" reserving a fixed space for the Owl component using CSS."
msgstr ""
"Bu bezovta qiladigan tajriba bo'lishi mumkin, shuning uchun sahifangizni"
" loyihalashtirishda Owl komponenti elementlarni ko'chirmasligiga e'tibor"
" berish kerak. Bu turli yo'llar bilan amalga oshirilishi mumkin, masalan,"
" uni barcha boshqa mavjud elementlarning pastiga joylashtirish, atrofda"
" boshqa interaktiv elementlar bo'lmaslik yoki CSS yordamida Owl komponenti"
" uchun ruxsat etilgan joy ajratish."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:143
msgid "`Cumulative Layout Shift on web.dev <https://web.dev/articles/cls>`_"
msgstr "`web.dev saytida Kümülatif Tartib Siljishi <https://web.dev/articles/cls>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:149
msgid ""
"When search engines build their index of the content of the web, they use"
" web crawlers to find pages and analyze their content to show these pages"
" in their search results. While modern search engines are generally "
"capable of executing JavaScript code and should generally be able to view"
" and index content rendered in JavaScript, they may not index the content"
" as fast and penalize the page in search results."
msgstr ""
"Qidiruv tizimlari veb kontentining indeksini qurishda sahifalarni topish"
" va ularning kontentini tahlil qilib qidiruv natijalarida ko'rsatish uchun"
" veb-kriperlardan foydalanadi. Zamonaviy qidiruv tizimlari odatda JavaScript"
" kodini bajarish qobiliyatiga ega va JavaScript da ko'rsatilgan kontentni"
" ko'rish va indekslash imkoniyatiga ega bo'lishi kerak bo'lsa-da, ular"
" kontentni shuncha tez indekslamasligi va sahifani qidiruv natijalarida"
" jarimalamasligi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:155
msgid ""
"Because most search engines do not reveal the exact way that they crawl "
"and index web pages, it's not always easy to know the extent of the "
"impact that client-side rendering can have on your search engine scores. "
"While it's unlikely to make or break your SEO strategy, you should still "
"only use Owl components when they are adding real value over server-side "
"rendering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:162
msgid "When to use Owl components on the portal and website"
msgstr "Portal va veb-saytda Owl komponentlarini qachon ishlatish kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:164
msgid ""
"As explained in the previous sections, using Owl component can slightly "
"degrade user experience if you're not careful and may also hinder your "
"SEO. So when should you choose to use Owl components in these places? "
"Here are some general guidelines."
msgstr ""
"Oldingi bo'limlarda tushuntirilganidek, Owl komponentdan foydalanish"
" e'tiborsiz bo'lsangiz foydalanuvchi tajribasini biroz pasaytirishi"
" va SEO ni ham to'sishi mumkin. Xo'sh, ushbu joylarda Owl komponentlarini"
" qachon ishlatishni tanlash kerak? Mana bir nechta umumiy ko'rsatmalar."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:169
msgid "When you don't care about SEO"
msgstr "SEO haqida qayg'urmasangiz"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:171
msgid ""
"If a page cannot be indexed by search engines because it's not available "
"to the public, e.g. anything in the user portal, SEO performance is not a"
" concern, as web crawlers cannot access these pages anyway. There are "
"also some things that you do not want or care about indexing, e.g. if you"
" want to have a page where the user can choose a date and time for an "
"appointment, you probably don't want search engines to index the dates on"
" which an appointment is possible at a specific moment in time."
msgstr ""
"Agar sahifa ommaga ochiq bo'lmaganligi sababli qidiruv tizimlari tomonidan"
" indekslanishi mumkin bo'lmasa, masalan, foydalanuvchi portalidagi har qanday"
" narsa, SEO ishlashi muammo emas, chunki veb-kriperlar baribir bu sahifalarga"
" kira olmaydi. Shuningdek, siz indekslanishni xohlamaydigan yoki e'tibor"
" bermaydigan narsalar ham bor, masalan, agar foydalanuvchi uchrashuvga"
" sana va vaqt tanlashi mumkin bo'lgan sahifa yaratmoqchi bo'lsangiz,"
" ehtimol qidiruv tizimlarining muayyan bir vaqtda uchrashuv mumkin"
" bo'lgan sanalarni indekslashini xohlamaysiz."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:179
msgid "When you need strong interactivity"
msgstr "Kuchli interaktivlik kerak bo'lganda"

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/frontend_owl_components.rst:181
msgid ""
"The decision to use Owl is a trade-off between the previously mentioned "
"disadvantages and the effort that Owl saves you by making it easy to "
"build richly interactive user experiences. The main reason to use Owl is "
"when you want to build an interface that can react in real time to user "
"inputs without requiring the page to reload. If you mainly want to show "
"static content to the user, you probably shouldn't use an Owl component."
msgstr ""
"Owl dan foydalanish qarori ilgari aytib o'tilgan kamchiliklar va Owl"
" boylikli interaktiv foydalanuvchi tajribasini yaratishni osonlashtirish"
" orqali tejayotgan kuch o'rtasidagi murosadir. Owl dan foydalanishning"
" asosiy sababi — sahifani qayta yuklashni talab qilmasdan foydalanuvchi"
" kirishlariga real vaqtda javob bera oladigan interfeys yaratmoqchi"
" bo'lganda. Agar asosan foydalanuvchiga statik kontent ko'rsatmoqchi"
" bo'lsangiz, ehtimol Owl komponentidan foydalanmasligingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/howtos/javascript_client_action.rst:8
msgid ""
"A client action triggers an action that is entirely implemented in the "
"client side. One of the benefits of using a client action is the ability "
"to create highly customized interfaces with ease. A client action is "
"typically defined by an OWL component; we can also use the web framework "
"and use services, core components, hooks,..."
msgstr ""
"Mijoz amali to'liq mijoz tomonida amalga oshirilgan amalni ishga tushiradi."
" Mijoz amalini ishlatishning afzalliklaridan biri — osonlik bilan yuqori"
" darajada sozlangan interfeyslarni yaratish imkoniyati. Mijoz amali odatda"
" OWL komponenti tomonidan aniqlanadi; biz, shuningdek, veb freymvorkdan"
" foydalanish va xizmatlar, asosiy komponentlar, hooks dan foydalanishimiz mumkin..."

