"foydalanish haqiqatan ham zarur bo'lmasa ORM yordamchilarini "
"ishlatishni afzal ko'ring."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:748
msgid "The recommended way to build SQL queries is to use the wrapper object"
msgstr "SQL so'rovlarini yaratishning tavsiya etilgan usuli wrapper ob'ektidan foydalanish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:755
msgid ""
"One important thing to know about models is that they don't necessarily "
"perform database updates right away. Indeed, for performance reasons, the"
" framework delays the recomputation of fields after modifying records. "
"And some database updates are delayed, too. Therefore, before querying "
"the database, one has to make sure that it contains the relevant data for"
" the query. This operation is called *flushing* and performs the expected"
" database updates."
msgstr ""
"Modellar haqida bilish kerak bo'lgan muhim narsa shundaki, ular "
"ma'lumotlar bazasini darhol yangilamaydi. Haqiqatan, ishlash "
"samaradorligi sababi, freymvork yozuvlarni o'zgartirgandan so'ng "
"maydonlarni qayta hisoblashni kechiktiradi. Ba'zi ma'lumotlar bazasi "
"yangilanishlari ham kechiktiriladi. Shuning uchun, ma'lumotlar bazasini "
"so'rashdan oldin, u so'rov uchun tegishli ma'lumotlarni o'z ichiga "
"olishiga ishonch hosil qilish kerak. Bu operatsiya *flushing* deb ataladi "
"va kutilgan ma'lumotlar bazasi yangilanishlarini amalga oshiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:772
msgid ""
"Before every SQL query, one has to flush the data needed for that query. "
"There are three levels for flushing, each with its own API. One can flush"
" either everything, all the records of a model, or some specific records."
" Because delaying updates improves performance in general, we recommend "
"to be *specific* when flushing."
msgstr ""
"Har bir SQL so'rovidan oldin, so'rov uchun zarur ma'lumotlarni "
"yuvish kerak. Flushning uch darajasi mavjud, har birining o'z API si "
"bor. Hamma narsani, modelning barcha yozuvlarini yoki ba'zi aniq "
"yozuvlarni yuvish mumkin. Yangilanishlarni kechiktirish umuman ishlash "
"samaradorligini yaxshilaganligi sababli, yuvishda *aniq* bo'lishni "
"tavsiya etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:784
msgid ""
"Because models use the same cursor and the :class:`~odoo.api.Environment`"
" holds various caches, these caches must be invalidated when *altering* "
"the database in raw SQL, or further uses of models may become incoherent."
" It is necessary to clear caches when using ``CREATE``, ``UPDATE`` or "
"``DELETE`` in SQL, but not ``SELECT`` (which simply reads the database)."
msgstr ""
"Modellar bir xil kursordan foydalanganligi va "
":class:`~odoo.api.Environment` turli keshllarni saqlaganligi sababli, "
"xom SQL da ma'lumotlar bazasini *o'zgartirganda* bu keshlar bekor "
"qilinishi kerak, aks holda modellarning keyingi qo'llanishlari noto'g'ri "
"bo'lib qolishi mumkin. SQLda ``CREATE``, ``UPDATE`` yoki ``DELETE`` "
"ishlatilganda keshlarni tozalash zarur, lekin ``SELECT`` da emas "
"(u shunchaki ma'lumotlar bazasini o'qiydi)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:802
msgid ""
"Just like flushing, one can invalidate either the whole cache, the cache "
"of all the records of a model, or the cache of specific records. One can "
"even invalidate specific fields on some records or all records of a "
"model. As the cache improves performance in general, we recommend to be "
"*specific* when invalidating."
msgstr ""
"Yuvish kabi, butun keshni, model barcha yozuvlari keshini yoki aniq "
"yozuvlar keshini bekor qilish mumkin. Hatto ba'zi yozuvlar yoki "
"modelning barcha yozuvlarida aniq maydonlarni ham bekor qilish mumkin. "
"Kesh umuman ishlash samaradorligini yaxshilaganligi sababli, bekor "
"qilishda *aniq* bo'lishni tavsiya etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:814
msgid ""
"The methods above keep the caches and the database consistent with each "
"other. However, if computed field dependencies have been modified in the "
"database, one has to inform the models for the computed fields to be "
"recomputed. The only thing the framework needs to know is *what* fields "
"have changed on *which* records."
msgstr ""
"Yuqoridagi metodlar keshlar va ma'lumotlar bazasini bir-biri bilan "
"izchil saqlaydi. Biroq, agar ma'lumotlar bazasida hisoblangan maydon "
"bog'liqliklari o'zgartirilgan bo'lsa, hisoblangan maydonlarni qayta "
"hisoblash uchun modellarga xabar berish kerak. Freymvork bilishi kerak "
"bo'lgan yagona narsa *qaysi* yozuvlarda *qaysi* maydonlar o'zgargan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/orm.rst:836
msgid ""
"One has to figure out which records have been modified. There are many "
"ways to do this, possibly involving extra SQL queries. In the example "
"above, we take advantage of the ``RETURNING`` clause of PostgreSQL to "
"retrieve the information without an extra query. After making the cache "
"consistent by invalidation, invoke the method ``modified`` on the "
"modified records with the fields that have been updated."
msgstr ""
"Qaysi yozuvlar o'zgartirilganligini aniqlash kerak. Buni amalga "
"oshirishning ko'plab usullari mavjud, ehtimol qo'shimcha SQL so'rovlarini "
"o'z ichiga oladi. Yuqoridagi misolda biz qo'shimcha so'rovsiz "
"ma'lumotni olish uchun PostgreSQL ning ``RETURNING`` bandidan "
"foydalanamiz. Bekor qilish orqali keshni izchil qilgandan so'ng, "
"yangilangan maydonlar bilan o'zgartirilgan yozuvlarda ``modified`` "
"metodini chaqiring."

