#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:204
msgid ""
"By default, the profiler enables the SQL and the Periodic collectors. "
"Both when it is enabled from the user interface or Python code."
msgstr ""
"Odatda, profillashtiruvchi SQL va Davriy kollektorlarni yoqadi. "
"Ham foydalanuvchi interfeysidan yoki Python kodidan yoqilganda."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:210
msgid "SQL collector"
msgstr "SQL kollektor"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:212
msgid ""
"The SQL collector saves all the SQL queries made to the database in the "
"current thread (for all cursors), as well as the stack trace. The "
"overhead of the collector is added to the analysed thread for each query,"
" which means that using it on a lot of small queries may impact execution"
" time and other profilers."
msgstr ""
"SQL kollektor joriy threadda ma'lumotlar bazasiga yo'naltirilgan barcha "
"SQL so'rovlarni (barcha kursorlar uchun), shuningdek stek izini saqlaydi. "
"Kollektorning yuklamasi har bir so'rov uchun tahlil qilinayotgan threadga "
"qo'shiladi, bu shuni anglatadiki, uni ko'plab kichik so'rovlarda "
"ishlatish ijro vaqtiga va boshqa profillashtiruvchilarga ta'sir qilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:217
msgid ""
"It is especially useful to debug query counts, or to add information to "
"the :ref:`Periodic collector <performance/profiling/collectors/periodic>`"
" in the combined speedscope view."
msgstr ""
"U so'rovlar sonini tuzatish yoki birlashtirilgan speedscope ko'rinishida "
":ref:`Davriy kollektor <performance/profiling/collectors/periodic>` ga "
"ma'lumot qo'shish uchun ayniqsa foydali."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:225
msgid "Periodic collector"
msgstr "Davriy kollektor"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:227
msgid ""
"This collector runs in a separate thread and saves the stack trace of the"
" analysed thread at every interval. The interval (by default 10 ms) can "
"be defined through the :guilabel:`Interval` option in the user interface,"
" or the `interval` parameter in Python code."
msgstr ""
"Bu kollektor alohida threadda ishlaydi va har bir intervaldа tahlil "
"qilinayotgan threadning stek izini saqlaydi. Interval (odatda 10 ms) "
"foydalanuvchi interfeysidagi :guilabel:`Interval` opsiyasi yoki Python "
"kodidagi `interval` parametri orqali belgilanishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:232
msgid ""
"If the interval is set at a very low value, profiling long requests will "
"generate memory issues. If the interval is set at a very high value, "
"information on short function executions will be lost."
msgstr ""
"Agar interval juda past qiymatga o'rnatilsa, uzun so'rovlarni "
"profillashtirish xotira muammolariga olib keladi. Agar interval juda "
"yuqori qiymatga o'rnatilsa, qisqa funksiya ijrolari haqidagi ma'lumot "
"yo'qoladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:236
msgid ""
"It is one of the best way to analyse performance as it should have a very"
" low impact on the execution time thanks to its separate thread."
msgstr ""
"Bu ishlash samaradorligini tahlil qilishning eng yaxshi usullaridan biri, "
"chunki alohida threadi tufayli ijro vaqtiga juda kam ta'sir ko'rsatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:244
msgid "QWeb collector"
msgstr "QWeb kollektor"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:246
msgid ""
"This collector saves the Python execution time and queries of all "
"directives. As for the :ref:`SQL collector "
"<performance/profiling/collectors/sql>`, the overhead can be important "
"when executing a lot of small directives. The results are different from "
"other collectors in terms of collected data, and can be analysed from the"
" `ir.profile` form view using a custom widget."
msgstr ""
"Bu kollektor barcha direktivalar Python ijro vaqti va so'rovlarini "
"saqlaydi. :ref:`SQL kollektori <performance/profiling/collectors/sql>` "
"kabi, ko'plab kichik direktivalar bajarilganda yuklamasi muhim bo'lishi "
"mumkin. Natijalar yig'ilgan ma'lumotlar bo'yicha boshqa kollektorlardan "
"farq qiladi va `ir.profile` shakl ko'rinishidan maxsus vidjet yordamida "
"tahlil qilinishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:251
msgid "It is mainly useful for optimizing views."
msgstr "U asosan ko'rinishlarni optimallashtirish uchun foydali."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:258
msgid "Sync collector"
msgstr "Sinxron kollektor"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:260
msgid ""
"This collector saves the stack for every function's call and return and "
"runs on the same thread, which greatly impacts performance."
msgstr ""
"Bu kollektor har bir funksiya chaqiruvi va qaytishi uchun stekni "
"saqlaydi va bir xil threadda ishlaydi, bu ishlash samaradorligiga "
"katta ta'sir ko'rsatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:263
msgid ""
"It can be useful to debug and understand complex flows, and follow their "
"execution in the code. It is however not recommended for performance "
"analysis because the overhead is high."
msgstr ""
"U murakkab oqimlarni tuzatish va tushunish, hamda ularning koddagi "
"ijrosini kuzatish uchun foydali bo'lishi mumkin. Biroq, yuklamasi "
"yuqori bo'lganligi sababli ishlash samaradorligini tahlil qilish uchun "
"tavsiya etilmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:271
msgid "Performance pitfalls"
msgstr "Ishlash samaradorligi tuzoqlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:273
msgid ""
"Be careful with randomness. Multiple executions may lead to different "
"results. E.g., a garbage collector being triggered during execution."
msgstr ""
"Tasodifiylikka ehtiyot bo'ling. Bir necha marta ijro qilish turli "
"natijalarga olib kelishi mumkin. Masalan, ijro vaqtida axlat yig'uvchi "
"ishga tushishi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:275
msgid ""
"Be careful with blocking calls. In some cases, external `c_call` may take"
" some time before releasing the GIL, thus leading to unexpected long "
"frames with the :ref:`Periodic collector "
"<performance/profiling/collectors/periodic>`. This should be detected by "
"the profiler and give a warning. It is possible to trigger the profiler "
"manually before such calls if needed."
msgstr ""
"Bloklash chaqiruvlariga ehtiyot bo'ling. Ba'zi hollarda, tashqi "
"`c_call` GIL ni bo'shatishdan oldin biroz vaqt olishi mumkin, bu "
":ref:`Davriy kollektor <performance/profiling/collectors/periodic>` bilan "
"kutilmagan uzun kadrlarga olib keladi. Bu profillashtiruvchi tomonidan "
"aniqlanishi va ogohlantirish berilishi kerak. Zarur bo'lsa, bunday "
"chaqiruvlardan oldin profillashtiruvchini qo'lda ishga tushirish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:279
msgid ""
"Pay attention to the cache. Profiling before that the `view`/`assets`/..."
" are in cache can lead to different results."
msgstr ""
"Keshga e'tibor bering. `view`/`assets`/... keshda bo'lishidan oldin "
"profillashtirish turli natijalarga olib kelishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:281
msgid ""
"Be aware of the profiler's overhead. The :ref:`SQL collector "
"<performance/profiling/collectors/sql>`'s overhead can be important when "
"a lot of small queries are executed. Profiling is practical to spot a "
"problem but you may want to disable the profiler in order to measure the "
"real impact of a code change."
msgstr ""
"Profillashtiruvchi yuklamasidan xabardor bo'ling. Ko'plab kichik "
"so'rovlar bajarilganda :ref:`SQL kollektor "
"<performance/profiling/collectors/sql>` yuklamasi muhim bo'lishi mumkin. "
"Muammoni aniqlash uchun profillashtirish qulay, lekin kod o'zgarishining "
"haqiqiy ta'sirini o'lchash uchun profillashtiruvchini o'chirib qo'yishni "
"xohlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:285
msgid ""
"Profiling results can be memory intensive. In some cases (e.g., profiling"
" an install or a long request), it is possible that you reach memory "
"limit, especially when rendering the speedscope results, which can lead "
"to an HTTP 500 error. In this case, you may need to start the server with"
" a higher memory limit: `--limit-memory-hard $((8*1024**3))`."
msgstr ""
"Profillashtirish natijalari xotira talab qilishi mumkin. Ba'zi hollarda "
"(masalan, o'rnatish yoki uzun so'rovni profillashtirish), ayniqsa "
"speedscope natijalarini ko'rsatishda xotira chegarasiga yetib qolishingiz "
"mumkin, bu HTTP 500 xatosiga olib kelishi mumkin. Bu holda, serverni "
"yuqoriroq xotira chegarasi bilan boshlashingiz kerak bo'lishi mumkin: "
"`--limit-memory-hard $((8*1024**3))`."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:293
msgid "Good practices"
msgstr "Yaxshi amaliyotlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:298
msgid "Batch operations"
msgstr "Paketli operatsiyalar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:300
msgid ""
"When working with recordsets, it is almost always better to batch "
"operations."
msgstr ""
"Yozuvlar to'plamlari bilan ishlashda, deyarli har doim operatsiyalarni "
"paketlash yaxshiroq."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:303
msgid ""
"Don't call a method that runs SQL queries while looping over a recordset "
"because it will do so for each record of the set."
msgstr ""
"Yozuvlar to'plamini aylanishda SQL so'rovlar yuboradigan metodlarni "
"chaqirmang, chunki u to'plamdagi har bir yozuv uchun shunday qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:314
msgid ""
"Instead, replace the `search_count` with a `_read_group` to execute one "
"SQL query for the entire batch of records."
msgstr ""
"Buning o'rniga, yozuvlar to'plami uchun bitta SQL so'rov bajarish uchun "
"`search_count` ni `_read_group` bilan almashtiring."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:328
msgid ""
"This example is not optimal nor correct in all cases. It is only a "
"substitute for a `search_count`. Another solution could be to prefetch "
"and count the inverse `One2many` field."
msgstr ""
"Bu misol barcha holatlarda optimal yoki to'g'ri emas. Bu faqat "
"`search_count` uchun o'rinbosar. Boshqa yechim teskari `One2many` "
"maydonini oldindan yuklab olish va sanash bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:332
msgid "Don't create records one after another."
msgstr "Yozuvlarni birma-bir yaratmang."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:340
msgid ""
"Instead, accumulate the create values and call the `create` method on the"
" batch. Doing so has mostly no impact and helps the framework optimize "
"fields computation."
msgstr ""
"Buning o'rniga, yaratish qiymatlarini to'plang va paketda `create` "
"metodini chaqiring. Buni qilish asosan ta'sir ko'rsatmaydi va freymvork "
"maydon hisoblashini optimallashtirishga yordam beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:352
msgid ""
"Fail to prefetch the fields of a recordset while browsing a single record"
" inside a loop."
msgstr ""
"Tsikl ichida bitta yozuvni ko'rib chiqishda yozuvlar to'plami "
"maydonlarini oldindan yuklab olmaslik."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:361
msgid "Instead, browse the entire recordset first."
msgstr "Buning o'rniga, avval butun yozuvlar to'plamini ko'ring."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:370
msgid ""
"We can verify that the records are prefetched in batch by reading the "
"field `prefetch_ids` which includes each of the record ids.browsing all "
"records together is unpractical,"
msgstr ""
"Har bir yozuv id larini o'z ichiga olgan `prefetch_ids` maydonini "
"o'qib, yozuvlarning paketda oldindan yuklab olinganligini tekshirishimiz "
"mumkin. Barcha yozuvlarni birga ko'rish amaliy emas,"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:373
msgid ""
"If needed, the `with_prefetch` method can be used to disable batch "
"prefetching:"
msgstr ""
"Zarur bo'lsa, paketli oldindan yuklab olishni o'chirish uchun "
"`with_prefetch` metodidan foydalanish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:383
msgid "Reduce the algorithmic complexity"
msgstr "Algoritmik murakkablikni kamaytiring"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:385
msgid ""
"Algorithmic complexity is a measure of how long an algorithm would take "
"to complete in regard to the size `n` of the input. When the complexity "
"is high, the execution time can grow quickly as the input becomes larger."
" In some cases, the algorithmic complexity can be reduced by preparing "
"the input's data correctly."
msgstr ""
"Algoritmik murakkablik - bu algoritmning kirish hajmi `n` ga nisbatan "
"qancha vaqt talab qilishining o'lchovidir. Murakkablik yuqori bo'lganda, "
"kirish kattalashishi bilan ijro vaqti tez o'sishi mumkin. Ba'zi hollarda, "
"kiritma ma'lumotlarini to'g'ri tayyorlash orqali algoritmik murakkablikni "
"kamaytirish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:391
msgid ""
"For a given problem, let's consider a naive algorithm crafted with two "
"nested loops for which the complexity in in O(n²)."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan muammo uchun, murakkabliği O(n²) bo'lgan ikki ichki tsikl "
"bilan yaratilgan sodda algoritmni ko'rib chiqaylik."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:403
msgid ""
"Assuming that all results have a different id, we can prepare the data to"
" reduce the complexity."
msgstr ""
"Barcha natijalar turli id larga ega deb faraz qilib, murakkablikni "
"kamaytirish uchun ma'lumotlarni tayyorlashimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:413
msgid ""
"Choosing the bad data structure to hold the input can lead to quadratic "
"complexity."
msgstr ""
"Kiritma uchun noto'g'ri ma'lumotlar tuzilmasini tanlash kvadratik "
"murakkablikka olib kelishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:423
msgid ""
"If `invalid_ids` is a list-like data structure, the complexity of the "
"algorithm may be quadratic."
msgstr ""
"Agar `invalid_ids` ro'yxatga o'xshash ma'lumotlar tuzilmasi bo'lsa, "
"algoritmning murakkabligi kvadratik bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:425
msgid "Instead, prefer using set operations like casting `invalid_ids` to a set."
msgstr ""
"Buning o'rniga, `invalid_ids` ni to'plamga o'zgartirish kabi to'plam "
"operatsiyalaridan foydalanishni afzal ko'ring."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:435
msgid "Depending on the input, recordset operations can also be used."
msgstr "Kiritishga qarab, yozuvlar to'plami operatsiyalari ham ishlatilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:447
msgid "Use indexes"
msgstr "Indekslardan foydalaning"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:449
msgid ""
"Database indexes can help fasten search operations, be it from a search "
"in the or through the user interface."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumotlar bazasi indekslari qidiruv operatsiyalarini tezlashtirishi "
"mumkin, u qidiruvdan yoki foydalanuvchi interfeysi orqali bo'lsin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/performance.rst:457
msgid ""
"Be careful not to index every field as indexes consume space and impact "
"on performance when executing one of `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, and `DELETE`."
msgstr ""
"Har bir maydonni indekslamaslikka ehtiyot bo'ling, chunki indekslar "
"joy egallaydi va `INSERT`, `UPDATE` va `DELETE` lardan birini "
"bajarishda ishlash samaradorligiga ta'sir qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/reports.rst:10
msgid "QWeb Reports"
msgstr "QWeb hisobotlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/reports.rst:12
msgid ""
"Reports are written in HTML/QWeb, like website views in Odoo. You can use"
" the usual :ref:`QWeb control flow tools <reference/qweb>`. The PDF "
"rendering itself is performed by wkhtmltopdf_."
msgstr ""
"Hisobotlar Odoo da veb-sayt ko'rinishlari kabi HTML/QWeb da yoziladi. "
"Odatdagi :ref:`QWeb oqimni boshqarish vositalari <reference/qweb>` dan "
"foydalanishingiz mumkin. PDF renderlash o'zi wkhtmltopdf_ tomonidan "
"amalga oshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/reports.rst:16
msgid ""
"Reports are declared using a :ref:`report action "
"<reference/actions/report>`, and a :ref:`reference/reports/templates` for"
" the action to use."
msgstr ""
"Hisobotlar :ref:`hisobot harakati <reference/actions/report>` va harakat "
"uchun foydalaniladigan :ref:`reference/reports/templates` yordamida "
"e'lon qilinadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/reports.rst:19
msgid ""
"If useful or necessary, it is possible to specify a "
":ref:`reference/reports/paper_formats` for the report report."
msgstr ""
"Foydali yoki zarur bo'lsa, hisobot uchun "
":ref:`reference/reports/paper_formats` ni ko'rsatish mumkin."

