#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:6
msgid "Security in Odoo"
msgstr "Odoo da xavfsizlik"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:8
msgid ""
"Aside from manually managing access using custom code, Odoo provides two "
"main data-driven mechanisms to manage or restrict access to data."
msgstr ""
"Maxsus kod yordamida kirishni qo'lda boshqarishdan tashqari, Odoo "
"ma'lumotlarga kirishni boshqarish yoki cheklash uchun ikki asosiy "
"ma'lumotlarga asoslangan mexanizmlarni taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:11
msgid ""
"Both mechanisms are linked to specific users through *groups*: a user "
"belongs to any number of groups, and security mechanisms are associated "
"to groups, thus applying security mechanisms to users."
msgstr ""
"Ikkala mexanizm ham *guruhlar* orqali muayyan foydalanuvchilar bilan "
"bog'langan: foydalanuvchi istalgan miqdordagi guruhlarga tegishli va "
"xavfsizlik mexanizmlari guruhlar bilan bog'langan, shuning uchun "
"xavfsizlik mexanizmlari foydalanuvchilarga qo'llaniladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:19
msgid ""
"serves as user-readable identification for the group (spells out the role"
" / purpose of the group)"
msgstr ""
"guruh uchun foydalanuvchi tomonidan o'qiladigan identifikatsiya vazifasini "
"bajaradi (guruhning roli / maqsadini ifodalaydi)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:24
msgid ""
"The *module category*, serves to associate groups with an Odoo App (~a "
"set of related business models) and convert them into an exclusive "
"selection in the user form."
msgstr ""
"*Modul toifasi*, guruhlarni Odoo ilovasi (~bog'liq biznes modellar "
"to'plami) bilan bog'lash va ularni foydalanuvchi shaklida eksklyuziv "
"tanlovga aylantirish uchun xizmat qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:28
msgid ""
"clarify & document special cases & relationship between groups & "
"categories better"
msgstr ""
"maxsus holatlari & guruhlar va toifalar o'rtasidagi munosabatni yaxshiroq "
"aniqlashtiring & hujjatlashtiring"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:33
msgid ""
"Other groups to set on the user alongside this one. This is a convenience"
" pseudo-inheritance relationship: it's possible to explicitly remove "
"implied groups from a user without removing the implier."
msgstr ""
"Bu bilan birga foydalanuvchiga o'rnatish uchun boshqa guruhlar. Bu "
"qulaylik uchun psevdo-meros munosabati: asosiy guruhni o'chirmasdan "
"foydalanuvchidan nazarda tutilgan guruhlarni aniq olib tashlash mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:40
msgid "Additional notes on the group e.g."
msgstr "Guruh haqida qo'shimcha izohlar, masalan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:45
#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:177
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/restrict_data_access.rst:133
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:67
msgid "Access Rights"
msgstr "Kirish huquqlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:47
msgid ""
"*Grants* access to an entire model for a given set of operations. If no "
"access rights matches an operation on a model for a user (through their "
"group), the user doesn't have access."
msgstr ""
"Muayyan operatsiyalar to'plami uchun butun modelga *kirish huquqini "
"beradi*. Agar foydalanuvchi uchun modeldagi operatsiyaga mos kirish "
"huquqi bo'lmasa (guruh orqali), foydalanuvchining kirish huquqi yo'q."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:51
msgid ""
"Access rights are additive, a user's accesses are the union of the "
"accesses they get through all their groups e.g. given a user who is part "
"of group A granting read and create access and a group B granting update "
"access, the user will have all three of create, read, and update."
msgstr ""
"Kirish huquqlari qo'shimcha: foydalanuvchining kirishlari barcha "
"guruhlar orqali olgan kirishlarining birlashmasidir. Masalan, "
"o'qish va yaratish kirish huquqini beradigan A guruhiga va "
"yangilash kirish huquqini beradigan B guruhiga mansub foydalanuvchiga "
"yaratish, o'qish va yangilashning uchtasiga ham kirish huquqi bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:60
msgid "The purpose or role of the group."
msgstr "Guruhning maqsadi yoki roli."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:64
msgid "The model whose access the ACL controls."
msgstr "ACL kirishini boshqaruvchi model."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:68
msgid ""
"The :class:`res.groups` to which the accesses are granted, an empty "
":attr:`group_id` means the ACL is granted to *every user* (non-employees "
"e.g. portal or public users)."
msgstr ""
"Kirishlar beriladigan :class:`res.groups`, bo'sh :attr:`group_id` "
"ACL *har bir foydalanuvchiga* (xodim bo'lmaganlar, masalan, portal "
"yoki ommaviy foydalanuvchilar) berilishini bildiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:72
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The :samp:`perm_{method}` attributes grant the corresponding CRUD access "
"when set, they are all unset by default."
msgstr ""
":samp:`perm_{method}` atributlari o'rnatilganda tegishli CRUD kirishini "
"beradi, odatda hammasi o'rnatilmagan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:83
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/restrict_data_access.rst:198
msgid "Record Rules"
msgstr "Yozuv qoidalari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:85
msgid ""
"Record rules are *conditions* which must be satisfied in order for an "
"operation to be allowed. Record rules are evaluated record-by-record, "
"following access rights."
msgstr ""
"Yozuv qoidalari operatsiyaga ruxsat berish uchun bajarilishi kerak "
"bo'lgan *shartlar*. Yozuv qoidalari kirish huquqlaridan keyin yozuv "
"bo'yicha baholanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:89
msgid ""
"Record rules are default-allow: if access rights grant access and no rule"
" applies to the operation and model for the user, the access is granted."
msgstr ""
"Yozuv qoidalari odatda ruxsat beradi: agar kirish huquqlari kirishni "
"bersa va foydalanuvchi uchun operatsiya va modelga hech qanday qoida "
"qo'llanilmasa, kirish beriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:96
msgid "The description of the rule."
msgstr "Qoidaning tavsifi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:100
msgid "The model to which the rule applies."
msgstr "Qoida qo'llaniladigan model."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:104
msgid ""
"The :class:`res.groups` to which access is granted (or not). Multiple "
"groups can be specified. If no group is specified, the rule is *global* "
"which is treated differently than \"group\" rules (see below)."
msgstr ""
"Kirish beriladigan (yoki berilmaydigan) :class:`res.groups`. Bir nechta "
"guruh ko'rsatilishi mumkin. Agar hech qanday guruh ko'rsatilmasa, qoida "
"*global* bo'lib, \"guruh\" qoidalaridan farqli tarzda ko'rib chiqiladi "
"(pastga qarang)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:110
msgid ""
"Computed on the basis of :attr:`groups`, provides easy access to the "
"global status (or not) of the rule."
msgstr ""
":attr:`groups` asosida hisoblanadi, qoidaning global holatiga (yoki yo'q) "
"oson kirish imkonini beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:115
msgid ""
"A predicate specified as a :ref:`domain <reference/orm/domains>`, the "
"rule allows the selected operations if the domain matches the record, and"
" forbids it otherwise."
msgstr ""
":ref:`domen <reference/orm/domains>` sifatida ko'rsatilgan predikat, "
"domen yozuvga mos kelsa qoida tanlangan operatsiyalarga ruxsat beradi, "
"aks holda taqiqlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:119
msgid "The domain is a *python expression* which can use the following variables:"
msgstr "Domen quyidagi o'zgaruvchilardan foydalanishi mumkin bo'lgan *python ifodasi*:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:123
msgid "Python's :mod:`python:time` module."
msgstr "Python ning :mod:`python:time` moduli."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:125
msgid "The current user, as a singleton recordset."
msgstr "Joriy foydalanuvchi, singleton yozuvlar to'plami sifatida."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:127
msgid "``company_id``"
msgstr "``company_id``"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:127
msgid ""
"The current user's currently selected company as a single company id (not"
" a recordset)."
msgstr ""
"Joriy foydalanuvchining hozir tanlangan kompaniyasi bitta kompaniya id "
"sifatida (yozuvlar to'plami emas)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:131
msgid "``company_ids``"
msgstr "``company_ids``"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:130
msgid ""
"All the companies to which the current user has access as a list of "
"company ids (not a recordset), see :ref:`howto/company/security` for more"
" details."
msgstr ""
"Joriy foydalanuvchi kirish huquqiga ega bo'lgan barcha kompaniyalar "
"kompaniya id lari ro'yxati sifatida (yozuvlar to'plami emas), ko'proq "
"tafsilotlar uchun :ref:`howto/company/security` ga qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:134
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The :samp:`perm_{method}` have completely different semantics than for "
":class:`ir.model.access`: for rules, they specify which operation the "
"rules applies *for*. If an operation is not selected, then the rule is "
"not checked for it, as if the rule did not exist."
msgstr ""
":samp:`perm_{method}` :class:`ir.model.access` dan mutlaqo farqli "
"semantikaga ega: qoidalar uchun, ular qoida *uchun* qo'llaniladigan "
"operatsiyani ko'rsatadi. Agar operatsiya tanlanmasa, qoida u uchun "
"tekshirilmaydi, qoida mavjud bo'lmagandek."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:139
msgid "All operations are selected by default."
msgstr "Odatda barcha operatsiyalar tanlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:149
msgid "Global rules versus group rules"
msgstr "Global qoidalar va guruh qoidalari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:151
msgid ""
"There is a large difference between global and group rules in how they "
"compose and combine:"
msgstr ""
"Global va guruh qoidalari ularning qanday tuzilishi va birlashishi "
"bo'yicha katta farq bor:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:154
msgid ""
"Global rules *intersect*, if two global rules apply then *both* must be "
"satisfied for the access to be granted, this means adding global rules "
"always restricts access further."
msgstr ""
"Global qoidalar *kesishadi*, agar ikki global qoida qo'llanilsa, kirish "
"berilishi uchun *ikkalasini* ham qondirish kerak, bu shuni anglatadiki, "
"global qoidalar qo'shish har doim kirishni yanada cheklaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:157
msgid ""
"Group rules *unify*, if two group rules apply then *either* can be "
"satisfied for the access to be granted. This means adding group rules can"
" expand access, but not beyond the bounds defined by global rules."
msgstr ""
"Guruh qoidalari *birlashadi*, agar ikki guruh qoidasi qo'llanilsa, "
"kirish berilishi uchun *har birini* qondirish mumkin. Bu shuni "
"anglatadiki, guruh qoidalari qo'shish kirishni kengaytirishi mumkin, "
"lekin global qoidalar belgilagan chegaralardan tashqariga emas."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:160
msgid ""
"The global and group rulesets *intersect*, which means the first group "
"rule being added to a given global ruleset will restrict access."
msgstr ""
"Global va guruh qoidalar to'plamlari *kesishadi*, bu shuni anglatadiki, "
"berilgan global qoidalar to'plamiga birinchi guruh qoidasini qo'shish "
"kirishni cheklaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:165
msgid ""
"Creating multiple global rules is risky as it's possible to create non-"
"overlapping rulesets, which will remove all access."
msgstr ""
"Bir nechta global qoidalar yaratish xavfli, chunki barcha kirishni "
"olib tashlaydigan mos kelmaydigan qoidalar to'plamlarini yaratish "
"mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:171
msgid "Field Access"
msgstr "Maydon kirishi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:173
msgid ""
"An ORM :class:`~odoo.fields.Field` can have a ``groups`` attribute "
"providing a list of groups (as a comma-separated string of "
":term:`external identifiers`)."
msgstr ""
"ORM :class:`~odoo.fields.Field` guruhlar ro'yxatini taqdim etuvchi "
"``groups`` atributiga ega bo'lishi mumkin (:term:`tashqi identifikatorlar` "
"vergul bilan ajratilgan satri sifatida)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:177
msgid ""
"If the current user is not in one of the listed groups, he will not have "
"access to the field:"
msgstr ""
"Agar joriy foydalanuvchi ko'rsatilgan guruhlardan birida bo'lmasa, "
"maydonga kirish huquqi bo'lmaydi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:180
msgid "restricted fields are automatically removed from requested views"
msgstr "cheklangan maydonlar so'ralgan ko'rinishlardan avtomatik olib tashlanadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:181
msgid ""
"restricted fields are removed from :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.fields_get` "
"responses"
msgstr ""
"cheklangan maydonlar :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.fields_get` javoblaridan "
"olib tashlanadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:183
msgid ""
"attempts to (explicitly) read from or write to restricted fields results "
"in an access error"
msgstr ""
"cheklangan maydonlardan (aniq) o'qish yoki ularga yozish urinishlari "
"kirish xatosiga olib keladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:188
msgid ""
"field access groups apply to the Superuser in fields_get but not in "
"read/write..."
msgstr ""
"maydon kirish guruhlari fields_get da Superuserga qo'llaniladi, lekin "
"o'qish/yozishda emas..."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:197
msgid "Security Pitfalls"
msgstr "Xavfsizlik tuzoqlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:199
msgid ""
"As a developer, it is important to understand the security mechanisms and"
" avoid common mistakes leading to insecure code."
msgstr ""
"Ishlab chiquvchi sifatida, xavfsizlik mexanizmlarini tushunish va "
"xavfsiz bo'lmagan kodga olib keladigan umumiy xatolardan qochish "
"muhimdir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:203
msgid "Unsafe Public Methods"
msgstr "Xavfsiz bo'lmagan ommaviy metodlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:205
msgid ""
"Any public method can be executed via a :ref:`RPC call "
"<api/external_api/calling_methods>` with the chosen parameters. The "
"methods starting with a ``_`` are not callable from an action button or "
"external API."
msgstr ""
"Har qanday ommaviy metod tanlangan parametrlar bilan :ref:`RPC chaqiruvi "
"<api/external_api/calling_methods>` orqali bajarilishi mumkin. ``_`` bilan "
"boshlanadigan metodlar amal tugmasi yoki tashqi API orqali chaqirib bo'lmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:209
msgid ""
"On public methods, the record on which a method is executed and the "
"parameters can not be trusted, ACL being only verified during CRUD "
"operations."
msgstr ""
"Ommaviy metodlarda metod bajariladigan yozuv va parametrlarga ishonib "
"bo'lmaydi, chunki ACL faqat CRUD operatsiyalari davomida tekshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:223
msgid ""
"Making a method private is obviously not enough and care must be taken to"
" use it properly."
msgstr ""
"Metodini shaxsiy qilish, albatta, yetarli emas va undan to'g'ri foydalanishga "
"e'tibor qaratish kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:227
msgid "Bypassing the ORM"
msgstr "ORM ni chetlab o'tish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:229
msgid ""
"You should never use the database cursor directly when the ORM can do the"
" same thing! By doing so you are bypassing all the ORM features, possibly"
" the automated behaviours like translations, invalidation of fields, "
"``active``, access rights and so on."
msgstr ""
"ORM xuddi shunday ishni qila oladigan bo'lsa, hech qachon ma'lumotlar bazasi "
"kursorini bevosita ishlatmasligingiz kerak! Buni qilish orqali siz barcha ORM "
"xususiyatlarini, ya'ni tarjimalar, maydonlarni bekor qilish, ``active``, "
"kirish huquqlari kabi avtomatlashtirilgan xatti-harakatlarni chetlab o'tasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:234
msgid ""
"And chances are that you are also making the code harder to read and "
"probably less secure."
msgstr ""
"Bundan tashqari, siz kodni o'qishni qiyinlashtirasiz va "
"ehtimol uni kamroq xavfsiz qilasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:259
msgid "SQL injections"
msgstr "SQL in'eksiyalari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:261
msgid ""
"Care must be taken not to introduce SQL injections vulnerabilities when "
"using manual SQL queries. The vulnerability is present when user input is"
" either incorrectly filtered or badly quoted, allowing an attacker to "
"introduce undesirable clauses to a SQL query (such as circumventing "
"filters or executing ``UPDATE`` or ``DELETE`` commands)."
msgstr ""
"Qo'lda SQL so'rovlaridan foydalanishda SQL in'eksiyasi zaifliklarini "
"kiritmaslik uchun ehtiyot bo'lish kerak. Zaiflik foydalanuvchi kiritgan "
"ma'lumot noto'g'ri filtrlanganda yoki yomon qo'shtirnoqlanganda mavjud bo'lib, "
"bu tajovuzkorga SQL so'roviga keraksiz bandlar kiritishga (masalan, filtrlarni "
"chetlab o'tish yoki ``UPDATE`` yoki ``DELETE`` buyruqlarini bajarish) imkon beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:267
msgid ""
"The best way to be safe is to never, NEVER use Python string "
"concatenation (+) or string parameters interpolation (%) to pass "
"variables to a SQL query string."
msgstr ""
"Xavfsiz bo'lishning eng yaxshi usuli — hech qachon, HECH QACHON SQL so'rov "
"satriga o'zgaruvchilarni uzatish uchun Python satrini birlashtirish (+) yoki "
"satr parametrlarini interpolatsiya qilish (%) dan foydalanmaslik."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:270
msgid ""
"The second reason, which is almost as important, is that it is the job of"
" the database abstraction layer (psycopg2) to decide how to format query "
"parameters, not your job! For example psycopg2 knows that when you pass a"
" list of values it needs to format them as a comma-separated list, "
"enclosed in parentheses !"
msgstr ""
"Deyarli shuncha muhim bo'lgan ikkinchi sabab shuki, so'rov parametrlarini "
"qanday formatlash haqida qaror qilish sizning vazifangiz emas, balki ma'lumotlar "
"bazasi abstraktsiya qatlamining (psycopg2) vazifasidir! Masalan, psycopg2 "
"qiymatlar ro'yxatini uzatganingizda, ularni qavslar ichiga olingan vergul "
"bilan ajratilgan ro'yxat sifatida formatlashi kerakligini biladi!"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:275
msgid ""
"Even better, there exists a :class:`~odoo.tools.SQL` wrapper to build "
"queries using templates that handles the formatting of inputs. Check "
":ref:`SQL execution <reference/orm/sql>` for detailed usage."
msgstr ""
"Bundan ham yaxshisi, kiritishlar formatlashini boshqaradigan shablonlar "
"yordamida so'rovlar yaratish uchun :class:`~odoo.tools.SQL` o'rash mavjud. "
"Batafsil foydalanish uchun :ref:`SQL ijrosi <reference/orm/sql>` ga qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:301
msgid ""
"This is very important, so please be careful also when refactoring, and "
"most importantly do not copy these patterns!"
msgstr ""
"Bu juda muhim, shuning uchun refaktoring paytida ham ehtiyot bo'ling va "
"eng muhimi, bu naqshlarni nusxalamang!"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:304
msgid ""
"Here is a memorable example to help you remember what the issue is about "
"(but do not copy the code there). Before continuing, please be sure to "
"read the online documentation of pyscopg2 to learn of to use it properly:"
msgstr ""
"Muammo nima haqida ekanligini eslab qolishga yordam beruvchi yodda qoladigan "
"misol keltirilgan (lekin u yerdan kodni nusxalamang). Davom etishdan oldin, "
"undan to'g'ri foydalanishni o'rganish uchun pyscopg2 onlayn hujjatlarini "
"o'qib chiqing:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:308
msgid ""
"`The problem with query parameters "
"<http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html#the-problem-with-the-query-"
"parameters>`_"
msgstr ""
"`So'rov parametrlari bilan bog'liq muammo "
"<http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html#the-problem-with-the-query-"
"parameters>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:309
msgid ""
"`How to pass parameters with psycopg2 "
"<http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html#passing-parameters-to-sql-"
"queries>`_"
msgstr ""
"`psycopg2 bilan parametrlarni qanday uzatish kerak "
"<http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html#passing-parameters-to-sql-"
"queries>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:310
msgid ""
"`Advanced parameter types <http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html"
"#adaptation-of-python-values-to-sql-types>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Kengaytirilgan parametr turlari <http://initd.org/psycopg/docs/usage.html"
"#adaptation-of-python-values-to-sql-types>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:311
msgid "`Psycopg documentation <https://www.psycopg.org/docs/sql.html>`_"
msgstr "`Psycopg hujjatlari <https://www.psycopg.org/docs/sql.html>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:314
msgid "Building the domains"
msgstr "Domenlarni yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:316
msgid ""
"Domains are represented as lists and are serializable. You would be "
"tented to manipulate these lists directly, however it can introduce "
"subtle issues where the user could inject a domain if the input is not "
"normalized. Use :class:`~odoo.fields.Domain` to handle safely the "
"manipulation of domains."
msgstr ""
"Domenlar ro'yxatlar sifatida ifodalanadi va serializatsiya qilinishi mumkin. "
"Bu ro'yxatlarni bevosita boshqarishga urinishingiz mumkin, ammo bu kiritish "
"normallashtirılmagan bo'lsa, foydalanuvchi domen kiritishi mumkin bo'lgan "
"nozik muammolarga olib kelishi mumkin. Domenlarni xavfsiz boshqarish uchun "
":class:`~odoo.fields.Domain` dan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:338
msgid "Unescaped field content"
msgstr "Ekranlanmagan maydon mazmuni"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:340
msgid ""
"When rendering content using JavaScript and XML, one may be tempted to "
"use a ``t-raw`` to display rich-text content. This should be avoided as a"
" frequent `XSS <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-site_scripting>`_ "
"vector."
msgstr ""
"JavaScript va XML yordamida kontent ko'rsatishda boy matnli kontentni "
"ko'rsatish uchun ``t-raw`` dan foydalanishga urinish bo'lishi mumkin. "
"Bu tez-tez uchraydigan `XSS <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-site_scripting>`_ "
"vektori sifatida qochish kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:344
msgid ""
"It is very hard to control the integrity of the data from the computation"
" until the final integration in the browser DOM. A ``t-raw`` that is "
"correctly escaped at the time of introduction may no longer be safe at "
"the next bugfix or refactoring."
msgstr ""
"Hisoblashdan brauzer DOMga yakuniy integratsiyagacha ma'lumotlar yaxlitligini "
"nazorat qilish juda qiyin. Kiritish vaqtida to'g'ri ekranlangan ``t-raw`` "
"keyingi xatoni tuzatish yoki refaktoring paytida xavfsiz bo'lmasligi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:361
msgid ""
"The above code may feel safe as the message content is controlled but is "
"a bad practice that may lead to unexpected security vulnerabilities once "
"this code evolves in the future."
msgstr ""
"Yuqoridagi kod xabar mazmuni nazorat qilinganligi sababli xavfsiz tuyulishi "
"mumkin, ammo bu yomon amaliyot bo'lib, kelajakda bu kod rivojlanganda "
"kutilmagan xavfsizlik zaifliklariga olib kelishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:373
msgid ""
"While formatting the template differently would prevent such "
"vulnerabilities."
msgstr ""
"Shablonni boshqacha formatlash esa bunday zaifliklarning oldini oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:398
msgid "Creating safe content using :class:`~markupsafe.Markup`"
msgstr ":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` yordamida xavfsiz kontent yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:400
msgid ""
"See the `official documentation "
"<https://markupsafe.palletsprojects.com/>`_ for explanations, but the big"
" advantage of :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` is that it's a very rich type "
"overrinding :class:`str` operations to *automatically escape parameters*."
msgstr ""
"Tushuntirishlar uchun `rasmiy hujjatlar "
"<https://markupsafe.palletsprojects.com/>`_ ga qarang, ammo "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` ning asosiy afzalligi shundaki, u *parametrlarni "
"avtomatik ekranlash* uchun :class:`str` operatsiyalarini bekor qiladigan "
"juda boy turdir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:405
msgid ""
"This means that it's easy to create *safe* html snippets by using "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` on a string literal and \"formatting in\" "
"user-provided (and thus potentially unsafe) content:"
msgstr ""
"Bu shuni anglatadiki, satr literalida :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` dan "
"foydalanib va foydalanuvchi tomonidan taqdim etilgan (va shuning uchun "
"potentsial xavfsiz bo'lmagan) kontentni \"formatlash\" orqali *xavfsiz* "
"html parchalarini yaratish oson:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:416
msgid "though it is a very good thing, note that the effects can be odd at times:"
msgstr "bu juda yaxshi narsa bo'lsa-da, ta'sirlar ba'zida g'alati bo'lishi mumkinligini unutmang:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:429
msgid ""
"Most of the content-safe APIs actually return a "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` with all that implies."
msgstr ""
"Kontent-xavfsiz API larning aksariyati aslida barchasi bilan birga "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:432
msgid ""
"The :class:`~markupsafe.escape` method (and its alias "
":class:`~odoo.tools.misc.html_escape`) turns a `str` into a "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` and escapes its content. It will not escape "
"the content of a :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` object."
msgstr ""
":class:`~markupsafe.escape` metodi (va uning taxallusi "
":class:`~odoo.tools.misc.html_escape`) `str` ni :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` ga "
"aylantiradi va uning mazmunini ekranlaydi. U :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` "
"ob'ektining mazmunini ekranlamaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:451
msgid ""
"When generating HTML code, it is important to separate the structure "
"(tags) from the content (text)."
msgstr ""
"HTML kodi yaratishda strukturani (teglar) mazmundan (matn) ajratish muhimdir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:478
msgid ""
"When working with translations, it is especially important to separate "
"the HTML from the text. The translation methods accepts a "
":class:`~markupsafe.Markup` parameters and will escape the translation if"
" it gets receives at least one."
msgstr ""
"Tarjimalar bilan ishlashda HTMLni matndan ajratish ayniqsa muhimdir. "
"Tarjima metodlari :class:`~markupsafe.Markup` parametrlarini qabul qiladi "
"va kamida bittasini qabul qilsa, tarjimani ekranlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:495
msgid "Escaping vs Sanitizing"
msgstr "Ekranlash va Tozalash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:499
msgid ""
"Escaping is always 100% mandatory when you mix data and code, no matter "
"how safe the data"
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumotlar qanchalik xavfsiz bo'lishidan qat'i nazar, ma'lumotlar va kodni "
"aralashtirganda ekranlash har doim 100% majburiydir"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:502
#, python-format
msgid ""
"**Escaping** converts *TEXT* to *CODE*. It is absolutely mandatory to do "
"it every time you mix *DATA/TEXT* with *CODE* (e.g. generating HTML or "
"python code to be evaluated inside a `safe_eval`), because *CODE* always "
"requires *TEXT* to be encoded. It is critical for security, but it's also"
" a question of correctness. Even when there is no security risk (because "
"the text is 100% guarantee to be safe or trusted), it is still required "
"(e.g. to avoid breaking the layout in generated HTML)."
msgstr ""
"**Ekranlash** *MATN* ni *KOD* ga aylantiradi. Har safar *MA'LUMOT/MATN* ni "
"*KOD* bilan aralashtirganda (masalan, `safe_eval` ichida baholanadigan HTML "
"yoki python kodi yaratish) buni qilish mutlaqo majburiydir, chunki *KOD* "
"har doim *MATN* ni kodlashni talab qiladi. Bu xavfsizlik uchun muhim, "
"ammo bu to'g'rilik masalasi ham. Xavfsizlik xavfi bo'lmasa ham (matn 100% "
"xavfsiz yoki ishonchli deb kafolatlanganida), u baribir talab etiladi "
"(masalan, yaratilgan HTMLda maketni buzmaslik uchun)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:510
msgid ""
"Escaping will never break any feature, as long as the developer "
"identifies which variable contains *TEXT* and which contains *CODE*."
msgstr ""
"Ishlab chiquvchi qaysi o'zgaruvchi *MATN* va qaysi biri *KOD* ni o'z ichiga "
"olganligini aniqlaganda, ekranlash hech qachon biron bir xususiyatni buzmasligini ta'minlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:526
msgid ""
"**Sanitizing** converts *CODE* to *SAFER CODE* (but not necessary *safe* "
"code). It does not work on *TEXT*. Sanitizing is only necessary when "
"*CODE* is untrusted, because it comes in full or in part from some user-"
"provided data. If the user-provided data is in the form of *TEXT* (e.g. "
"the content from a form filled by a user), and if that data was correctly"
" escaped before putting it in *CODE*, then sanitizing is useless (but can"
" still be done). If however, the user-provided data was **not escaped**, "
"then sanitizing will **not** work as expected."
msgstr ""
"**Tozalash** *KOD* ni *XAVFSIZROQ KOD* ga aylantiradi (lekin zarur bo'lgan "
"*xavfsiz* kod emas). U *MATN* da ishlamaydi. Tozalash faqat *KOD* ishonchsiz "
"bo'lganda zarur, chunki u to'liq yoki qisman foydalanuvchi tomonidan taqdim "
"etilgan ma'lumotlardan iborat. Agar foydalanuvchi tomonidan taqdim etilgan "
"ma'lumotlar *MATN* shaklida bo'lsa (masalan, foydalanuvchi to'ldirgan "
"formdagi kontent) va agar bu ma'lumotlar *KOD* ga kiritilishdan oldin "
"to'g'ri ekranlangan bo'lsa, tozalash befoyda (ammo baribir bajarilishi "
"mumkin). Biroq, foydalanuvchi tomonidan taqdim etilgan ma'lumotlar "
"**ekranlanmagan** bo'lsa, tozalash kutilganidek **ishlamaydi**."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:545
msgid ""
"Sanitizing can break features, depending on whether the *CODE* is "
"expected to contain patterns that are not safe. That's why `fields.Html` "
"and `tools.html_sanitize()` have options to fine-tune the level of "
"sanitization for styles, etc. Those options have to be carefully "
"considered depending on where the data comes from, and the desired "
"features. The sanitization safety is balanced against sanitization "
"breakages: the safer the sanitisation the more likely it is to break "
"things."
msgstr ""
"Tozalash xususiyatlarni buzishi mumkin, bu *KOD* xavfsiz bo'lmagan naqshlarni "
"o'z ichiga olishi kutilishiga bog'liq. Shuning uchun `fields.Html` va "
"`tools.html_sanitize()` uslublar va boshqalar uchun tozalash darajasini "
"sozlash imkoniyatlariga ega. Bu imkoniyatlar ma'lumotlar qayerdan kelishiga "
"va kerakli xususiyatlarga qarab diqqat bilan ko'rib chiqilishi kerak. "
"Tozalash xavfsizligi tozalash buzilishlari bilan muvozanatlashtiriladi: "
"tozalash qanchalik xavfsiz bo'lsa, u narsalarni buzish ehtimoli shunchalik yuqori."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:562
msgid "Evaluating content"
msgstr "Kontentni baholash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:564
msgid ""
"Some may want to ``eval`` to parse user provided content. Using ``eval`` "
"should be avoided at all cost. A safer, sandboxed, method "
":class:`~odoo.tools.safe_eval` can be used instead but still gives "
"tremendous capabilities to the user running it and must be reserved for "
"trusted privileged users only as it breaks the barrier between code and "
"data."
msgstr ""
"Ba'zilar foydalanuvchi tomonidan taqdim etilgan kontentni tahlil qilish "
"uchun ``eval`` dan foydalanmoqchi bo'lishlari mumkin. ``eval`` dan "
"foydalanishdan har qanday holatda qochish kerak. Buning o'rniga xavfsizroq, "
"qumli muhitdagi :class:`~odoo.tools.safe_eval` metodidan foydalanish mumkin, "
"ammo u baribir uni ishlatayotgan foydalanuvchiga katta imkoniyatlar beradi va "
"kod va ma'lumotlar o'rtasidagi to'siqni buzganligi sababli faqat ishonchli "
"imtiyozli foydalanuvchilar uchun saqlanib qolishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/security.rst:586
msgid "Parsing content does not need ``eval``"
msgstr "Kontentni tahlil qilish ``eval`` talab qilmaydi"

