#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:301
msgid ""
"Testing Python code and JS code separately is very useful, but it does "
"not prove that the web client and the server work together.  In order to "
"do that, we can write another kind of test: tours.  A tour is a mini "
"scenario of some interesting business flow.  It explains a sequence of "
"steps that should be followed.  The test runner will then create a "
"PhantomJs browser, point it to the proper url and simulate the click and "
"inputs, according to the scenario."
msgstr ""
"Python kodi va JS kodini alohida sinovdan o'tkazish juda foydali, ammo bu "
"veb-mijoz va server birgalikda ishlashini isbotlamaydi. Buning uchun boshqa "
"turdagi sinov yozishimiz mumkin: turlar. Tur qiziqarli biznes oqimining mini "
"ssenariyi. U bajarilishi kerak bo'lgan qadamlar ketma-ketligini tushuntiradi. "
"Sinov ishlovchisi keyin PhantomJs brauzerini yaratadi, uni to'g'ri URL ga "
"yo'naltiradi va sssenariyga muvofiq bosish va kiritishlarni simulatsiya qiladi."

