msgid ""
"To start a tour from a python test, make the class inherit from "
":class:`~odoo.tests.HTTPCase`, and call `start_tour`:"
msgstr ""
"Python sinovi orqali turni boshlash uchun sinfni :class:`~odoo.tests.HTTPCase` "
"dan meros oling va `start_tour` ni chaqiring:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:503
msgid "Writing an onboarding tour"
msgstr "Onboarding turini yozish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:508
msgid ""
"To write an onboarding tour for `your_module`, start with creating the "
"required files:"
msgstr ""
"`your_module` uchun onboarding turini yozish uchun kerakli fayllarni yaratishdan boshlang:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:519
msgid ""
"You can then update :file:`__manifest__.py` to add :file:`your_tour.js` "
"in the assets and :file:`your_tour.xml` in the data."
msgstr ""
"Keyin assetlarga :file:`your_tour.js` va dataga :file:`your_tour.xml` qo'shish "
"uchun :file:`__manifest__.py` ni yangilashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:535
msgid ""
"The javascript part is the same as for :ref: `the test tour "
"<testing/javascript/test>`."
msgstr ""
"Javascript qismi :ref: `sinov turi <testing/javascript/test>` uchun xuddi "
"shunday."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:538
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:148
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/website_theme.rst:16
msgid "XML"
msgstr "XML"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:540
msgid ""
"When you have your tour in the javascript registry, you can create a "
"record `web_tour.tour` in the xml, like that:"
msgstr ""
"Javascript registrida turingiz bo'lganda, xmlda `web_tour.tour` yozuvini "
"quyidagicha yaratishingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:553
msgid ""
"`name`: Required, the name must be the same as the one in the javascript "
"registry."
msgstr ""
"`name`: Majburiy, nom javascript registridagiga o'xshash bo'lishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:555
msgid ""
"`sequence`: Optional; determines the order to execute the onboarding "
"tours. Defaults to 1000."
msgstr ""
"`sequence`: Ixtiyoriy; onboarding turlarini bajarish tartibini belgilaydi. "
"Sukut bo'yicha 1000."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:557
msgid ""
"`url`: Optional; the url where to start the tour. If ``url`` is "
"``False``, take the url from the registry. Defaults to \"/odoo\"."
msgstr ""
"`url`: Ixtiyoriy; turni qayerdan boshlash URL manzili. ``url`` ``False`` "
"bo'lsa, registrdan URL manzilini oling. Sukut bo'yicha \"/odoo\"."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:559
msgid ""
"`rainbow_man_message`: Optional; will show the message in the rainbow man"
" effect at the completion of the tour. If ``rainbow_man_message`` is "
"``False``, there is no rainbow effect. Defaults to ``<b>Good job!</b> You"
" went through all steps of this tour.``"
msgstr ""
"`rainbow_man_message`: Ixtiyoriy; tur tugagandan so'ng rainbow man "
"effektida xabarni ko'rsatadi. ``rainbow_man_message`` ``False`` bo'lsa, "
"kamalak effekti yo'q. Sukut bo'yicha ``<b>Good job!</b> You went through "
"all steps of this tour.``"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:564
msgid "Running onboarding tours"
msgstr "Onboarding turlarini ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:566
msgid ""
"They can all be started in their sequence order by toggling the "
":guilabel:`Onboarding` option in the user menu. You can run specific "
"onboarding tours by going to the :menuselection:`Settings --> Technical "
"--> User Interface --> Tours` and clicking on :guilabel:`Onboarding` or "
":guilabel:`Testing`."
msgstr ""
"Barchasini foydalanuvchi menyusidagi :guilabel:`Onboarding` opsiyasini "
"o'zgartirish orqali ketma-ket tartibda boshlash mumkin. :menuselection:`Sozlamalar "
"--> Texnik --> Foydalanuvchi interfeysi --> Turlar` ga o'tib va "
":guilabel:`Onboarding` yoki :guilabel:`Testing` tugmasini bosish orqali "
"muayyan onboarding turlarini ishga tushirishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:570
msgid ""
"**Onboarding**: will execute the tour in interactive mode. That means the"
" tour will show what to do and wait for interactions from the user."
msgstr ""
"**Onboarding**: turni interaktiv rejimda bajaradi. Bu tur nima qilish "
"kerakligini ko'rsatadi va foydalanuvchidan munosabatlarni kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:572
msgid ""
"**Testing**: will execute the tour automatically. That means the tour "
"will be executing all the step in front of the user."
msgstr ""
"**Testing**: turni avtomatik tarzda bajaradi. Bu tur foydalanuvchi "
"oldida barcha qadamlarni bajaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:576
msgid "Tour recorder"
msgstr "Tur yozuvchisi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:578
msgid ""
"You can also create tours easily with the tour recorder. To do so, click "
"on :guilabel:`Record` on the onboarding tours view. When started, this "
"tool will record all your interactions in Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Siz tur yozuvchisi yordamida turlarni osonlikcha ham yaratishingiz mumkin. "
"Buning uchun onboarding turlari ko'rinishida :guilabel:`Record` tugmasini "
"bosing. Ishga tushirilganda, bu vosita Odooda barcha o'zaro munosabatlaringizni "
"yozib oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:581
msgid ""
"The created tours are flagged in the onboarding tours view as **Custom**."
" These tours can also be exported to a javascript file, ready to be put "
"in your module."
msgstr ""
"Yaratilgan turlar onboarding turlari ko'rinishida **Maxsus** sifatida "
"belgilanadi. Bu turlar ham modulingizga qo'yishga tayyor javascript fayliga "
"eksport qilinishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:585
msgid "Debugging tips"
msgstr "Nosozliklarni tuzatish bo'yicha maslahatlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:588
msgid "Observing test tours in a browser"
msgstr "Brauzerda sinov turlarini kuzatish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:590
msgid "There are three ways with different tradeoffs:"
msgstr "Turli muvozanatlar bilan uchta usul mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:593
msgid "``watch=True``"
msgstr "``watch=True``"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:595
msgid ""
"When running a tour locally via the test suite, the ``watch=True`` "
"parameter can be added to the ``browser_js`` or ``start_tour`` call::"
msgstr ""
"Sinov to'plami orqali mahalliy tarzdagi turni ishga tushirishda "
"``browser_js`` yoki ``start_tour`` chaqiruviga ``watch=True`` parametri "
"qo'shilishi mumkin::"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:601
msgid ""
"This will automatically open a Chrome window with the tour being run "
"inside it."
msgstr "Bu ichida tur ishga tushirilgan Chrome oynasini avtomatik ravishda ochadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:606
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:627
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:648
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:703
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:716
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:725
msgid "**Advantages**"
msgstr "**Afzalliklari**"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:605
msgid ""
"always works if the tour has Python setup / surrounding code, or multiple"
" steps"
msgstr ""
"tur Python sozlamasi / qo'shimcha kodi yoki bir nechta qadamga ega bo'lsa, "
"har doim ishlaydi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:606
msgid "runs entirely automatically (just select the test which launches the tour)"
msgstr "to'liq avtomatik ravishda ishlaydi (faqat turni ishga tushiradigan sinovni tanlang)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:607
msgid "transactional (*should* always be runnable multiple times)"
msgstr "tranzaksiyali (bir necha marta ishga tushirilishi *mumkin* bo'lishi kerak)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:610
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:631
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:652
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:706
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:730
msgid "**Drawbacks**"
msgstr "**Kamchiliklari**"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:609
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:630
msgid "only works locally"
msgstr "faqat mahalliy tarzda ishlaydi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:610
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:631
msgid "only works if the test / tour can run correctly locally"
msgstr "faqat sinov / tur mahalliy tarzda to'g'ri ishlashi mumkin bo'lganda ishlaydi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:613
msgid "``debug=True``"
msgstr "``debug=True``"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:615
msgid ""
"When running a tour locally via the test suite, the ``debug=True`` "
"parameter can be added to the ``browser_js`` or ``start_tour`` call::"
msgstr ""
"Sinov to'plami orqali mahalliy tarzdagi turni ishga tushirishda "
"``browser_js`` yoki ``start_tour`` chaqiruviga ``debug=True`` parametri "
"qo'shilishi mumkin::"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:621
msgid ""
"This will automatically open a fullscreen Chrome window with opened "
"devtools and a debugger breakpoint set at the start of the tour. The tour"
" is ran with the debug=assets query parameter. When an error is thrown, "
"the debugger stops on the exception."
msgstr ""
"Bu ochiq devtools va tur boshida o'rnatilgan nosozlik tuzatish to'xtash "
"nuqtasi bilan to'liq ekranli Chrome oynasini avtomatik ravishda ochadi. "
"Tur debug=assets so'rov parametri bilan ishga tushiriladi. Xato yuzaga "
"kelganda, nosozlik tuzatuvchi istisnoda to'xtaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:627
msgid "Same advantages as mode `watch=True`"
msgstr "`watch=True` rejimi bilan bir xil afzalliklari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:628
msgid "Easier to debug steps"
msgstr "Qadamlarni nosozliklarni tuzatish osonroq"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:634
msgid "Run via browser"
msgstr "Brauzer orqali ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:636
msgid "Test tours can also be launched via the browser UI by calling"
msgstr "Sinov turlarini brauzer UI orqali qo'ng'iroq qilish orqali ham ishga tushirish mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:642
msgid ""
"in the javascript console, or by enabling :ref:`tests mode "
"<frontend/framework/tests_debug_mode>` by setting ``?debug=tests`` in the"
" URL."
msgstr ""
"javascript konsolida yoki URL da ``?debug=tests`` ni o'rnatish orqali "
":ref:`sinovlar rejimini <frontend/framework/tests_debug_mode>` yoqish orqali."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:647
msgid "easier to run"
msgstr "ishga tushirish osonroq"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:648
msgid "can be used on production or test sites, not just local instances"
msgstr "faqat mahalliy nusxalarda emas, balki ishlab chiqarish yoki sinov saytlarida ham ishlatilishi mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:649
msgid "allows running in \"Onboarding\" mode (manual steps)"
msgstr "\"Onboarding\" rejimida (qo'lda qadamlar) ishga tushirishga imkon beradi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:651
msgid "harder to use with test tours involving Python setup"
msgstr "Python sozlamasini o'z ichiga olgan sinov turlari bilan foydalanish qiyinroq"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:652
msgid "may not work multiple times depending on tour side-effects"
msgstr "tur yon ta'sirlariga qarab bir necha marta ishlamasligi mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:656
msgid ""
"It's possible to use this method to observe or interact with tours which "
"require Python setup:"
msgstr ""
"Python sozlamasini talab qiladigan turlarni kuzatish yoki ularda ishtirok "
"etish uchun bu usuldan foydalanish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:659
msgid ""
"add a *python* breakpoint before the relevant tour is started "
"(``start_tour`` or ``browser_js`` call)"
msgstr ""
"tegishli tur boshlanishidan oldin *python* to'xtash nuqtasini qo'shing "
"(``start_tour`` yoki ``browser_js`` chaqiruvi)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:661
msgid "when the breakpoint is hit, open the instance in your browser"
msgstr "to'xtash nuqtasiga yetilganda, brauzeringizda nusxani oching"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:662
msgid "run the tour"
msgstr "turni ishga tushiring"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:664
msgid ""
"At this point the Python setup will be visible to the browser, and the "
"tour will be able to run."
msgstr ""
"Bu nuqtada Python sozlamasi brauzer uchun ko'rinadigan bo'ladi va tur "
"ishga tushirila oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:667
msgid ""
"You may want to comment the ``start_tour`` or ``browser_js`` call if you "
"also want the test to continue afterwards, depending on the tour's side-"
"effects."
msgstr ""
"Tur yon ta'sirlariga qarab, sinovning keyinroq davom etishini ham xohlasangiz, "
"``start_tour`` yoki ``browser_js`` chaqiruvini izohlashni xohlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:672
msgid "Screenshots and screencasts during browser_js tests"
msgstr "browser_js sinovlari davomida skrinshot va screencastlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:674
msgid ""
"When running tests that use ``HttpCase.browser_js`` from the command "
"line, the Chrome browser is used in headless mode. By default, if a test "
"fails, a PNG screenshot is taken at the moment of the failure and written"
" in"
msgstr ""
"Buyruq satri orqali ``HttpCase.browser_js`` dan foydalanadigan sinovlarni "
"ishga tushirishda Chrome brauzeri boshsiz rejimda ishlatiladi. Sukut bo'yicha, "
"sinov muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lsa, muvaffaqiyatsizlik vaqtida PNG skrinshot "
"olinadi va quyidagiga yoziladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:682
msgid ""
"Two new command line arguments were added since Odoo 13.0 to control this"
" behavior: :option:`--screenshots <odoo-bin --screenshots>` and "
":option:`--screencasts <odoo-bin --screencasts>`"
msgstr ""
"Bu xatti-harakatni boshqarish uchun Odoo 13.0 dan boshlab ikkita yangi "
"buyruq satri argumentlari qo'shildi: :option:`--screenshots <odoo-bin --screenshots>` "
"va :option:`--screencasts <odoo-bin --screencasts>`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:686
msgid "Introspecting / debugging steps"
msgstr "Qadamlarni introspektsiya qilish / nosozliklarni tuzatish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:688
msgid ""
"When trying to fix / debug a tour, the screenshots (on failure) are not "
"necessarily sufficient. In that case it can be useful to see what's "
"happening at some or each step."
msgstr ""
"Turni tuzatish / nosozliklarni tuzatishga urinishda, skrinshot (muvaffaqiyatsizlikda) "
"albatta yetarli emas. Bunday holda ba'zi yoki har bir qadamda nima sodir "
"bo'layotganini ko'rish foydali bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:692
msgid ""
"While this is pretty easy when in an \"onboarding\" (as they're mostly "
"driven explicitly by the user) it's more complicated when running "
"\"test\" tours, or when running tours through the test suite. In that "
"case there are two main tricks:"
msgstr ""
"\"Onboarding\" da bu ancha oson bo'lsa-da (chunki ular asosan foydalanuvchi "
"tomonidan aniq boshqariladi), \"sinov\" turlarini ishga tushirishda yoki "
"sinov to'plami orqali turlarni ishga tushirishda bu yanada murakkab. Bunday "
"holda ikkita asosiy hiyla mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:697
msgid "A step property ``break: true,`` in debug mode (debug=True)."
msgstr "Debug rejimida (debug=True) qadam xususiyati ``break: true,``."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:699
msgid ""
"This adds a debugger breakpoint at the start of the step. You can then "
"add your own wherever you need."
msgstr ""
"Bu qadam boshida nosozlik tuzatuvchi to'xtash nuqtasi qo'shadi. Keyin "
"o'zingiznikini kerak joyga qo'shishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:703
msgid "very simple"
msgstr "juda oddiy"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:704
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:726
msgid "the tour continues as soon as you resume execution"
msgstr "ijroni davom ettirganingizda tur davom etadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:706
#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:728
msgid "page interaction is limited as all javascript is blocked"
msgstr "barcha javascript bloklanganligi sababli sahifa bilan aloqa cheklangan"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:708
msgid "A step property ``pause: true,`` in debug mode (debug=True)."
msgstr "Debug rejimida (debug=True) qadam xususiyati ``pause: true,``."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:710
msgid ""
"The tour will stop at the end of the step. This allows inspecting and "
"interacting with the page until the developer is ready to resume by "
"typing **play();** in the browser console."
msgstr ""
"Tur qadam oxirida to'xtaydi. Bu ishlab chiquvchi brauzer konsolida "
"**play();** ni yozish orqali davom ettirishga tayyor bo'lguncha sahifani "
"tekshirish va u bilan munosabatda bo'lishga imkon beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:715
msgid "allows interacting with the page"
msgstr "sahifa bilan munosabatda bo'lishga imkon beradi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:716
msgid "no useless (for this situation) debugger UI"
msgstr "(bu holat uchun) foydasiz nosozlik tuzatuvchi UI yo'q"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:718
#, python-brace-format
msgid "A step with a ``run() { debugger; }`` action."
msgstr "``run() { debugger; }`` amali bilan qadam."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:720
msgid ""
"This can be added to an existing step, or can be a new dedicated step. "
"Once the step's **trigger** is matched, the execution will stop all "
"javascript execution."
msgstr ""
"Bu mavjud qadamga qo'shilishi yoki yangi maxsus qadam bo'lishi mumkin. "
"Qadam **trigger** mos kelgandan so'ng, ijro barcha javascript ijrosini to'xtatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:725
msgid "simple"
msgstr "oddiy"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:729
msgid ""
"the debugger is triggered after trying to find targeted element defined "
"in the step."
msgstr "nosozlik tuzatuvchi qadamda aniqlangan maqsadli elementni topishga urinishdan so'ng ishga tushiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:733
msgid "Performance Testing"
msgstr "Ishlash samaradorligini sinash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:736
msgid "Query counts"
msgstr "So'rovlar soni"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/backend/testing.rst:738
msgid ""
"One of the ways to test performance is to measure database queries. "
"Manually, this can be tested with the `--log-sql` CLI parameter. If you "
"want to establish the maximum number of queries for an operation, you can"
" use the :meth:`~odoo.tests.BaseCase.assertQueryCount` method, integrated"
" in Odoo test classes."
msgstr ""
"Ishlash samaradorligini sinashning bir usuli ma'lumotlar bazasi so'rovlarini "
"o'lchashdir. Qo'lda buni `--log-sql` CLI parametri bilan sinab ko'rish mumkin. "
"Agar amal uchun maksimal so'rovlar sonini belgilashni xohlasangiz, Odoo "
"sinov sinflarida birlashtirilgan "
":meth:`~odoo.tests.BaseCase.assertQueryCount` metodidan foydalanishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:5
msgid "Command-line interface (CLI)"
msgstr "Buyruq satri interfeysi (CLI)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:7
msgid ""
"The CLI :dfn:`command-line interface` offers several functionalities "
"related to Odoo. You can use it to :ref:`run the server "
"<reference/cmdline/server>`, :ref:`launch Odoo as a Python console "
"environment <reference/cmdline/shell>`, :ref:`scaffold an Odoo module "
"<reference/cmdline/scaffold>`, :ref:`populate a database "
"<reference/cmdline/populate>` or :ref:`count the number of lines of code "
"<reference/cmdline/cloc>`."
msgstr ""
"CLI :dfn:`buyruq satri interfeysi` Odoo bilan bog'liq bir nechta "
"funksionalliklarni taklif etadi. Uni :ref:`serverni ishga tushirish "
"<reference/cmdline/server>`, :ref:`Odoo ni Python konsol muhiti sifatida "
"ishga tushirish <reference/cmdline/shell>`, :ref:`Odoo modulini yaratish "
"<reference/cmdline/scaffold>`, :ref:`ma'lumotlar bazasini to'ldirish "
"<reference/cmdline/populate>` yoki :ref:`kod satrlari sonini hisoblash "
"<reference/cmdline/cloc>` uchun ishlatishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:13
msgid ""
"The command to use to call the CLI depends on how you installed Odoo. In "
"the examples below, we assume that you are :doc:`running Odoo from source"
" </administration/on_premise/source>` with the :file:`odoo-bin` file. If "
"you installed Odoo :doc:`from a distribution package "
"</administration/on_premise/packages>` or with `Docker "
"<https://hub.docker.com/_/odoo/>`_, you must adapt the command."
msgstr ""
"CLI ni chaqirish uchun ishlatiladigan buyruq Odooni qanday o'rnatganingizga "
"bog'liq. Quyidagi misollarda siz :file:`odoo-bin` fayli bilan "
":doc:`Odooni manba koddan ishga tushirayapsiz </administration/on_premise/source>` "
"deb taxmin qilamiz. Agar Odooni :doc:`tarqatish paketidan "
"</administration/on_premise/packages>` yoki `Docker "
"<https://hub.docker.com/_/odoo/>`_ bilan o'rnatgan bo'lsangiz, buyruqni "
"moslashtirishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:21
msgid "Run Odoo from source"
msgstr "Odooni manba koddan ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:23
msgid ""
"Navigate to the root of the directory where you downloaded the source "
"files of Odoo Community."
msgstr ""
"Odoo Community manba fayllarini yuklab olgan katalog ildiziga o'ting."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:25
msgid "Run all CLI commands with :command:`./odoo-bin`"
msgstr "Barcha CLI buyruqlarni :command:`./odoo-bin` bilan bajaring"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:27
msgid "Odoo was installed from a distribution package"
msgstr "Odoo tarqatish paketidan o'rnatilgan"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:29
msgid ""
"When Odoo was installed, an executable named `odoo` was added to your "
"user's PATH. Replace all occurrences of :command:`odoo-bin` with "
":command:`odoo` in the examples below."
msgstr ""
"Odoo o'rnatilganda, `odoo` nomli bajariladigan fayl foydalanuvchining "
"PATH ga qo'shildi. Quyidagi misollarda :command:`odoo-bin` ning barcha "
"uchrashuvi o'rniga :command:`odoo` yozing."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:32
msgid "Odoo was installed with Docker"
msgstr "Odoo Docker bilan o'rnatilgan"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/cli.rst:34
msgid ""
"Please refer to the `documentation of the official Docker image of Odoo "
"<https://hub.docker.com/_/odoo/>`_."
msgstr ""
"`Odoo rasmiy Docker tasvirining hujjatlariga <https://hub.docker.com/_/odoo/>`_ "
"murojaat qiling."

