#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:210
msgid "Transaction"
msgstr "Tranzaksiya"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:212
msgid ""
"All calls to the JSON-2 endpoint run in their own SQL transaction. The "
"transaction is committed in case of success and is discarded in case of "
"error. Using the JSON-2 API, it is not possible to chain multiple calls "
"inside a single transaction. It means that one must be cautious when "
"making multiple consecutive calls, as the database might be modified by "
"other concurrent transactions. This is especially dangerous when "
"performing operations related to reservations, payments, and such."
msgstr ""
"JSON-2 endpointiga barcha chaqiruvlar o'zlarining SQL tranzaksiyasida "
"ishlaydi. Tranzaksiya muvaffaqiyat holatida amalga oshiriladi va xato "
"holatida bekor qilinadi. JSON-2 API dan foydalanib, bitta tranzaksiya "
"ichida bir nechta chaqiruvlarni zanjirlash mumkin emas. Bu bir nechta "
"ketma-ket chaqiruvlar amalga oshirilganda ehtiyot bo'lish kerakligini "
"anglatadi, chunki ma'lumotlar bazasi boshqa bir vaqtda amalga oshirilgan "
"tranzaksiyalar tomonidan o'zgartirilgan bo'lishi mumkin. Bu ayniqsa "
"bron, to'lov va shunga o'xshash operatsiyalar bilan ishlashda xavfli."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:218
msgid ""
"The solution is to always call a single method that performs all the "
"related operations in a single transaction. This way, the data is "
"guaranteed to stay consistent: either everything is done (success, "
"commit), or nothing is done (error, rollback)."
msgstr ""
"Yechim har doim barcha tegishli operatsiyalarni bitta tranzaksiyada "
"bajaradigan bitta metodini chaqirish. Shu tarzda, ma'lumotlar izchil "
"bo'lib qolishi kafolatlanadi: ya hamma narsa bajariladi (muvaffaqiyat, "
"commit), yoki hech narsa bajarilmaydi (xato, rollback)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:222
msgid ""
"In the ORM, the ``search_read`` method is an example of a single method "
"that performs multiple operations (``search`` then ``read``) in a single "
"transaction. If a concurrent request removes one of the records "
"``search`` retrieves, then there is a risk that subsequent calls to "
"``read`` fail for a missing record error. Such a problem cannot occur in "
"``search_read``, as the system guarantees proper isolation between "
"transactions."
msgstr ""
"ORM da ``search_read`` metodi bitta tranzaksiyada bir nechta operatsiyalarni "
"(``search`` keyin ``read``) bajaradigan bitta metod misolidir. Agar parallel "
"so'rov ``search`` oladigan yozuvlardan birini o'chirsa, keyingi ``read`` "
"chaqiruvlari yo'qolgan yozuv xatosi bilan muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lish xavfi bor. "
"Bunday muammo ``search_read`` da yuz bera olmaydi, chunki tizim tranzaksiyalar "
"o'rtasida to'g'ri izolyatsiyani kafolatlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:228
msgid ""
"In business models, those methods are often prefixed by ``action_``, such"
" as ``sale.order``'s ``action_confirm`` method, which verifies that a "
"sales order is valid before confirming it."
msgstr ""
"Biznes modellarida bu metodlar ko'pincha ``action_`` prefiksi bilan "
"nomlanadi, masalan ``sale.order`` ning ``action_confirm`` metodi, u "
"tasdiqlashdan oldin sotuv buyurtmasining to'g'ri ekanligini tekshiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:232
msgid ""
"When no method exists for a set of related operations, a new one can be "
"created in a dedicated module."
msgstr ""
"Tegishli operatsiyalar to'plami uchun metod mavjud bo'lmasa, maxsus "
"modulda yangi metod yaratish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:236
msgid ":doc:`Tutorial to create a module <../tutorials/server_framework_101>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Modul yaratish bo'yicha qo'llanma <../tutorials/server_framework_101>`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/external_api.rst:237
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL - Transaction Isolation - `Repeatable Read "
"<https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/transaction-iso.html#XACT-"
"REPEATABLE-READ>`_"
msgstr ""
"PostgreSQL - Tranzaksiya izolyatsiyasi - `Qayta o'qiladigan o'qish "
"<https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/transaction-iso.html#XACT-"
"REPEATABLE-READ>`_"

