#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend.rst:6
msgid "Web framework"
msgstr "Veb freymvork"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:8
msgid ""
"Managing assets in Odoo is not as straightforward as it is in some other "
"apps. One of the reasons is that we have a variety of situations where "
"some, but not all of the assets are required. For example, the needs of "
"the web client, the point of sale app, the website or even the mobile "
"application are different. Also, some assets may be large, but are seldom"
" needed: in that case we may want them to be :ref:`loaded lazily (on "
"demand) <frontend/assets/lazy_loading>`."
msgstr ""
"Odoo da aktivlarni boshqarish ba'zi boshqa ilovalardagidek oddiy emas. "
"Buning bir sababi - aktivlarning bir qismi talab qilinadigan, lekin "
"hammasi emas bo'lgan turli vaziyatlar mavjud. Masalan, veb-mijoz, "
"savdo nuqtasi ilovasi, veb-sayt yoki mobil ilova ehtiyojlari turlicha. "
"Shuningdek, ba'zi aktivlar katta bo'lishi mumkin, lekin kamdan-kam "
"kerak bo'ladi: bu holda ularni :ref:`dangasa ravishda (talabga ko'ra) "
"yuklash <frontend/assets/lazy_loading>` xohlashimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:16
msgid "Asset types"
msgstr "Aktiv turlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:18
msgid ""
"There are three different asset types: code (`js` files), style (`css` or"
" `scss` files) and templates (`xml` files)."
msgstr ""
"Uch xil aktiv turi mavjud: kod (`js` fayllar), uslub (`css` yoki "
"`scss` fayllar) va shablonlar (`xml` fayllar)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:27
msgid "Code"
msgstr "Kod"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:22
msgid ""
"Odoo supports :ref:`three different kinds of javascript "
"files<frontend/js_modules>`. All these files are then processed (native "
"JS modules are transformed into odoo modules), then minified (if not in "
"`debug=assets` :ref:`mode <frontend/framework/assets_debug_mode>`) and "
"concatenated. The result is then saved as a file attachment. These file "
"attachments are usually loaded via a `<script>` tag in the `<head>` part "
"of the page (as a static file)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo :ref:`uch xil javascript fayllarini<frontend/js_modules>` qo'llab-"
"quvvatlaydi. Barcha bu fayllar qayta ishlanadi (mahalliy JS modullari odoo "
"modullariga aylantiriladi), keyin minifikatsiya qilinadi (`debug=assets` "
":ref:`rejimida <frontend/framework/assets_debug_mode>` bo'lmasa) va "
"birlashtriladi. Natija fayl ilovasi sifatida saqlanadi. Bu fayl ilovalar "
"odatda sahifaning `<head>` qismidagi `<script>` tegi orqali yuklanadi "
"(statik fayl sifatida)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:35
msgid "Style"
msgstr "Uslub"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:30
msgid ""
"Styling can be done with either `css` or `scss <https://sass-"
"lang.com/>`_. Like the javascript files, these files are processed "
"(`scss` files are converted into `css`), then minified (again, if not in "
"`debug=assets` :ref:`mode <frontend/framework/assets_debug_mode>`) and "
"concatenated. The result is then saved as a file attachment. They are "
"then usually loaded via a `<link>` tag in the `<head>` part of the page "
"(as a static file)."
msgstr ""
"Uslub `css` yoki `scss <https://sass-lang.com/>`_ bilan bajarilishi "
"mumkin. Javascript fayllari kabi, bu fayllar ham qayta ishlanadi "
"(`scss` fayllar `css` ga aylantiriladi), keyin minifikatsiya qilinadi "
"(yana, `debug=assets` :ref:`rejimida <frontend/framework/assets_debug_mode>` "
"bo'lmasa) va birlashtiriladi. Natija fayl ilovasi sifatida saqlanadi. "
"Ular keyin odatda sahifaning `<head>` qismidagi `<link>` tegi orqali "
"yuklanadi (statik fayl sifatida)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:38
msgid ""
"Templates (static `xml` files) are handled in a different way: they are "
"simply read from the file system whenever they are needed, and "
"concatenated."
msgstr ""
"Shablonlar (statik `xml` fayllar) boshqacha tarzda ishlanadi: ular kerak "
"bo'lganda fayl tizimidan o'qilib, birlashtiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:41
msgid ""
"Whenever the browser loads odoo, it calls the `/web/webclient/qweb/` "
"controller to fetch the :ref:`templates <reference/qweb>`."
msgstr ""
"Brauzer Odoo ni yuklagan har safar :ref:`shablonlarni <reference/qweb>` "
"olish uchun `/web/webclient/qweb/` kontrollerini chaqiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:44
msgid ""
"It is useful to know that in most cases, a browser only performs a "
"request the first time it loads a page. This is because each of these "
"assets are associated with a checksum, which is injected into the page "
"source. The checksum is then added to the url, which means that it is "
"possible to safely set the cache headers to a long period."
msgstr ""
"Ko'p hollarda brauzer faqat birinchi marta sahifani yuklashda so'rov "
"bajarishini bilish foydali. Buning sababi - bu aktivlarning har biri sahifa "
"manbasiga kiritilgan nazorat yig'indisi bilan bog'liq. Nazorat yig'indisi "
"keyin URL ga qo'shiladi, bu kesh sarlavhalarini uzoq muddatga xavfsiz "
"o'rnatish imkonini beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:53
msgid "Bundles"
msgstr "To'plamlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:55
msgid ""
"Odoo assets are grouped by *bundles*. Each bundle (a *list of file paths*"
" of specific types: `xml`, `js`, `css` or `scss`) is listed in the "
":ref:`module manifest <reference/module/manifest>`. Files can be declared"
" using `glob <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glob_(programming)>`_ syntax,"
" meaning that you can declare several asset files using a single line."
msgstr ""
"Odoo aktivlari *to'plamlar* bo'yicha guruhlanadi. Har bir to'plam (muayyan "
"turlarning *fayl yo'llari ro'yxati*: `xml`, `js`, `css` yoki `scss`) "
":ref:`modul manifestida <reference/module/manifest>` ko'rsatilgan. "
"Fayllar `glob <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glob_(programming)>`_ "
"sintaksisidan foydalanib e'lon qilinishi mumkin, ya'ni bitta satr bilan "
"bir nechta aktiv fayllarini e'lon qilish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:61
msgid ""
"The bundles are defined in each module's :file:`__manifest__.py`, with a "
"dedicated `assets` key which contains a dictionary. The dictionary maps "
"bundle names (keys) to the list of files they contain (values). It looks "
"like this:"
msgstr ""
"To'plamlar har bir modulning :file:`__manifest__.py` da lug'at o'z ichiga "
"olgan maxsus `assets` kaliti bilan belgilanadi. Lug'at to'plam nomlari "
"(kalitlar) ni ular o'z ichiga olgan fayllar ro'yxatiga (qiymatlar) "
"moslashtiradi. Bu shunday ko'rinadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:83
msgid ""
"Here is a list of some important bundles that most odoo developers will "
"need to know:"
msgstr ""
"Ko'pchilik Odoo ishlab chiquvchilar bilishi kerak bo'lgan ba'zi muhim "
"to'plamlar ro'yxati:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:86
msgid ""
"`web.assets_common`: this bundle contains most assets which are common to"
" the web client, the website and also the point of sale. This is supposed"
" to contain lower level building blocks for the odoo framework. Note that"
" it contains the :file:`boot.js` file, which defines the odoo module "
"system."
msgstr ""
"`web.assets_common`: bu to'plam veb-mijoz, veb-sayt va savdo nuqtasiga "
"umumiy bo'lgan ko'pchilik aktivlarni o'z ichiga oladi. Bu Odoo freymvorki "
"uchun quyi darajadagi qurilish bloklarini o'z ichiga olishi kerak. "
"E'tibor bering, u Odoo modul tizimini belgilaydigan :file:`boot.js` "
"faylini o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:91
msgid ""
"`web.assets_backend`: this bundle contains the code specific to the web "
"client (notably the web client/action manager/views/static XML templates)"
msgstr ""
"`web.assets_backend`: bu to'plam veb-mijozga xos kodni o'z ichiga oladi "
"(ayniqsa veb-mijoz/harakat menejeri/ko'rinishlar/statik XML shablonlar)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:94
msgid ""
"`web.assets_frontend`: this bundle is about all that is specific to the "
"public website: ecommerce, portal, forum, blog, ..."
msgstr ""
"`web.assets_frontend`: bu to'plam ommaviy veb-saytga xos bo'lgan hamma "
"narsani o'z ichiga oladi: ecommerce, portal, forum, blog, ..."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:97
msgid ""
"`web.assets_unit_tests`: all javascript unit testing code (tests, "
"helpers, mocks)"
msgstr ""
"`web.assets_unit_tests`: barcha javascript birlik sinovi kodi "
"(sinovlar, yordamchilar, macklari)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:102
msgid ""
"Typically, handling assets is simple: you just need to add some new files"
" to a frequently used bundle like `assets_common` or `assets_backend`. "
"But there are other operations available to cover some more specific use "
"cases."
msgstr ""
"Odatda aktivlarni boshqarish oddiy: `assets_common` yoki `assets_backend` "
"kabi tez-tez ishlatiladigan to'plamga yangi fayllar qo'shish kifoya. "
"Lekin ba'zi aniqroq foydalanish holatlari uchun boshqa operatsiyalar ham mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:106
msgid ""
"Note that all directives targeting a certain asset file (i.e. `before`, "
"`after`, `replace` and `remove`) need that file to be declared "
"beforehand, either in manifests higher up in the hierarchy or in "
"``ir.asset`` records with a lower sequence."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, muayyan aktiv faylni nishonga oluvchi barcha direktivalar "
"(ya'ni `before`, `after`, `replace` va `remove`) bu faylning oldindan "
"e'lon qilinishini talab qiladi, ya'ni ierarxiyada yuqoriroqdagi "
"manifestlarda yoki pastroq ketma-ketlikdagi ``ir.asset`` yozuvlarida."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:112
msgid "`append`"
msgstr "`append`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:114
msgid ""
"This operation adds one or multiple file(s). Since it is the most common "
"operation, it can be done by simply using the file name:"
msgstr ""
"Bu operatsiya bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) qo'shadi. Bu eng keng "
"tarqalgan operatsiya bo'lgani uchun, uni shunchaki fayl nomini "
"ishlatib bajarish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:123
msgid ""
"By default, adding a simple string to a bundle will append the files "
"matching the glob pattern at the end of the bundle. Obviously, the "
"pattern may also be directly a single file path."
msgstr ""
"Standart bo'yicha, to'plamga oddiy satr qo'shish glob namunasiga mos "
"fayllarni to'plamning oxiriga qo'shadi. Albatta, naqsh bevosita bitta "
"fayl yo'li ham bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:128
msgid "`prepend`"
msgstr "`prepend`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:130
msgid "Add one or multiple file(s) at the beginning of the bundle."
msgstr "To'plamning boshiga bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) qo'shish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:132
msgid ""
"Useful when you need to put a certain file before the others in a bundle "
"(for example with css files). The `prepend` operation is invoked with the"
" following syntax: `('prepend', <path>)`."
msgstr ""
"To'plamda ma'lum faylni boshqalardan oldin qo'yish kerak bo'lganda foydali "
"(masalan css fayllar bilan). `prepend` operatsiyasi quyidagi sintaksis bilan "
"chaqiriladi: `('prepend', <path>)`."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:143
msgid "`before`"
msgstr "`before`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:145
msgid "Add one or multiple file(s) before a specific file."
msgstr "Muayyan fayldan oldin bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) qo'shish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:147
msgid ""
"Prepending a file at the beginning of a bundle might not be precise "
"enough. The `before` directive can be used to add the given file(s) right"
" *before* the target file. It is declared by replacing the normal path "
"with a 3-element tuple `('before', <target>, <path>)`."
msgstr ""
"Faylni to'plamning boshiga qo'shish yetarli darajada aniq bo'lmasligi "
"mumkin. `before` direktivasi berilgan fayl(lar) ni maqsadli fayldan "
"to'g'ridan-to'g'ri *oldin* qo'shish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin. U normal "
"yo'lni 3 elementli kortej `('before', <target>, <path>)` bilan "
"almashtirish orqali e'lon qilinadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:159
msgid "`after`"
msgstr "`after`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:161
msgid "Add one or multiple file(s) after a specific file."
msgstr "Muayyan fayldan keyin bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) qo'shish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:163
msgid ""
"Same as `before`, with the matching file(s) appended right *after* the "
"target file. It is declared by replacing the normal path with a 3-element"
" tuple `('after', <target>, <path>)`."
msgstr ""
"`before` bilan bir xil, mos fayl(lar) maqsadli fayldan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri "
"*keyin* qo'shiladi. U normal yo'lni 3 elementli kortej "
"`('after', <target>, <path>)` bilan almashtirish orqali e'lon qilinadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:174
msgid "`include`"
msgstr "`include`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:176
msgid "Use nested bundles."
msgstr "Ichma-ich to'plamlardan foydalanish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:178
msgid ""
"The `include` directive is a way to use a bundle in other bundles to "
"minimize the size of your manifest. In Odoo we use sub bundles (prefixed "
"with an underscore by convention) to batch files used in multiple other "
"bundles. You can then specify the sub bundle as a pair `('include', "
"<bundle>)` like this:"
msgstr ""
"`include` direktivasi manifestingiz o'lchamini kamaytirish uchun boshqa "
"to'plamlarda to'plamdan foydalanish usulidir. Odoo da biz bir nechta boshqa "
"to'plamlarda ishlatiladigan fayllarni to'plamlash uchun pastki to'plamlardan "
"(qo'shimcha ravishda pastki chiziq bilan prefikslangan) foydalanamiz. Keyin "
"pastki to'plamni `('include', <bundle>)` juftlik sifatida ko'rsatish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:190
msgid "`remove`"
msgstr "`remove`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:192
msgid "Remove one or multiple file(s)."
msgstr "Bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) ni o'chirish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:194
msgid ""
"In some cases, you may want to remove one or multiple files from a "
"bundle. This can be done using the `remove` directive by specifying a "
"pair `('remove', <target>)`:"
msgstr ""
"Ba'zi hollarda to'plamdan bir yoki bir nechta fayllarni o'chirmoqchi "
"bo'lishingiz mumkin. Bu `('remove', <target>)` juftlikni ko'rsatib "
"`remove` direktivasidan foydalanib bajarilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:205
msgid "`replace`"
msgstr "`replace`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:207
msgid "Replace an asset file with one or multiple file(s)."
msgstr "Aktiv faylni bir yoki bir nechta fayl(lar) bilan almashtirish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:209
msgid ""
"Let us say that an asset needs not only to be removed, but you also want "
"to insert your new version of that asset at the same exact position. This"
" can be done with the `replace` directive, using a 3-element tuple "
"`('replace', <target>, <path>)`:"
msgstr ""
"Faraz qilaylik, aktiv nafaqat o'chirilishi, balki shu aniq pozitsiyaga "
"aktivning yangi versiyasini kiritmoqchi ham bo'lishingiz mumkin. Bu "
"3 elementli kortej `('replace', <target>, <path>)` ishlatib `replace` "
"direktivasi bilan bajarilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:221
msgid "Loading order"
msgstr "Yuklash tartibi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:223
msgid ""
"The order in which assets are loaded is sometimes critical and must be "
"deterministic, mostly for stylesheets priorities and setup scripts. "
"Assets in Odoo are processed as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Aktivlar yuklanadigan tartib ba'zan muhim va deterministik bo'lishi kerak, "
"asosan uslublar jadvallarining ustuvorliklari va sozlash skriptlari uchun. "
"Odoo da aktivlar quyidagicha qayta ishlanadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:227
msgid ""
"When an asset bundle is called (e.g. `t-call-"
"assets=\"web.assets_common\"`), an empty list of assets is generated"
msgstr ""
"Aktiv to'plami chaqirilganda (masalan `t-call-assets=\"web.assets_common\"`), "
"bo'sh aktivlar ro'yxati yaratiladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:230
msgid ""
"All records of type `ir.asset` matching the bundle are fetched and sorted"
" by sequence number. Then all records with a sequence strictly less than "
"16 are processed and applied to the current list of assets."
msgstr ""
"To'plamga mos keladigan `ir.asset` turidagi barcha yozuvlar olinadi va "
"ketma-ketlik raqami bo'yicha saralanadi. Keyin ketma-ketligi 16 dan qat'iy "
"kamroq bo'lgan barcha yozuvlar qayta ishlanadi va aktivlarning joriy "
"ro'yxatiga qo'llaniladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:234
msgid ""
"All modules declaring assets for said bundle in their manifest apply "
"their assets operations to this list. This is done following the order of"
" modules dependencies (e.g. `web` assets is processed before `website`). "
"If a directive tries to add a file already present in the list, nothing "
"is done for that file. In other word, only the first occurrence of a file"
" is kept in the list."
msgstr ""
"Manifestlarida ko'rsatilgan to'plam uchun aktivlarni e'lon qiluvchi barcha "
"modullar o'z aktiv operatsiyalarini bu ro'yxatga qo'llaydi. Bu modul "
"bog'liqliklarining tartibiga ko'ra amalga oshiriladi (masalan `web` aktivlari "
"`website` dan oldin qayta ishlanadi). Agar direktiva ro'yxatda allaqachon "
"mavjud bo'lgan faylni qo'shishga urinsa, bu fayl uchun hech narsa qilinmaydi. "
"Boshqacha qilib aytganda, ro'yxatda faqat faylning birinchi yuz berishi saqlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:240
msgid ""
"The remaining `ir.asset` records (those with a sequence greater than or "
"equal to 16) are then processed and applied as well."
msgstr ""
"Qolgan `ir.asset` yozuvlari (ketma-ketligi 16 dan katta yoki teng bo'lganlar) "
"keyin ham qayta ishlanadi va qo'llaniladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:243
msgid ""
"Assets declared in the manifest may need to be loaded in a particular "
"order, for example :file:`jquery.js` must be loaded before all other "
"jquery scripts when loading the lib folder. One solution would be to "
"create an :ref:`ir.asset <frontend/assets/ir_asset>` record with a lower "
"sequence or a 'prepend' directive, but there is another simpler way to do"
" so."
msgstr ""
"Manifestda e'lon qilingan aktivlar muayyan tartibda yuklanishi kerak bo'lishi "
"mumkin, masalan lib papkasini yuklashda :file:`jquery.js` barcha boshqa "
"jquery skriptlaridan oldin yuklanishi kerak. Bitta yechim - pastroq "
"ketma-ketlik yoki 'prepend' direktivasi bilan "
":ref:`ir.asset <frontend/assets/ir_asset>` yozuvini yaratish, lekin buni "
"amalga oshirishning yana bir oddiyroq usuli mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:249
msgid ""
"Since the unicity of each file path in the list of assets is guaranteed, "
"you can mention any specific file before a glob that includes it. That "
"file will thus appear in the list before all the others included in the "
"glob."
msgstr ""
"Aktivlar ro'yxatidagi har bir fayl yo'lining yagonaligi kafolatlanganligi "
"sababli, uni o'z ichiga olgan glob oldidan istalgan muayyan faylni "
"eslatish mumkin. Bu fayl shunday qilib ro'yxatda glob ichiga kiritilgan "
"barcha boshqalardan oldin paydo bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:262
msgid ""
"A module *b* removing/replacing the assets declared in a module *a* will "
"have to depend on it. Trying to operate on assets that have yet to be "
"declared will result in an error."
msgstr ""
"*a* modulida e'lon qilingan aktivlarni o'chiruvchi/almashtirishchi *b* moduli "
"unga bog'liq bo'lishi kerak. Hali e'lon qilinmagan aktivlarda operatsiya "
"bajarishga urinish xatoga olib keladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:269
msgid "Lazy loading"
msgstr "Dangasa yuklash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:271
msgid ""
"It is sometimes useful to load files and/or asset bundles dynamically, "
"for example to only load a library once it is needed. To do that, the "
"Odoo framework provides a few helper functions, located in "
":file:`@web/core/assets`."
msgstr ""
"Ba'zan fayllarni va/yoki aktiv to'plamlarini dinamik ravishda yuklash foydali, "
"masalan kutubxonani faqat kerak bo'lganda yuklash. Buning uchun Odoo "
"freymvork :file:`@web/core/assets` da joylashgan bir nechta yordamchi "
"funksiyalarni taqdim etadi."

