msgstr "`sequence` (standart= `16`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:363
msgid ""
"Loading order of the asset records (ascending). A sequence lower than 16 "
"means that the asset will be processed *before* the ones declared in the "
"manifest."
msgstr ""
"Aktiv yozuvlarining yuklash tartibi (o'sish tartibida). 16 dan past "
"ketma-ketlik aktivning manifestda e'lon qilinganlarga *qadar* qayta "
"ishlanishini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:368
msgid ""
"Note that the ``ir.asset`` use case is mainly for website-related "
"applications, as it allows for conditional assets (for example, when a "
"style option is enabled)."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, ``ir.asset`` foydalanish holati asosan veb-sayt bilan "
"bog'liq ilovalar uchun, chunki u shartli aktivlarga imkon beradi (masalan, "
"uslub opsiyasi yoqilganda)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:372
msgid ""
"In such cases, the ``<asset id=\"...\">`` syntax should be preferred over"
" the ``<record id=\"...\" model=\"ir.asset\">`` syntax when defining the "
"record in XML."
msgstr ""
"Bunday hollarda, XMLda yozuvni belgilashda ``<record id=\"...\" "
"model=\"ir.asset\">`` sintaksisidan ko'ra ``<asset id=\"...\">`` "
"sintaksisi afzal ko'rilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/assets.rst:376
msgid "See :ref:`reference/data/asset`, especially about the ``active`` value."
msgstr ":ref:`reference/data/asset` ga, ayniqsa ``active`` qiymati haqida qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:3
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr "Xatolarni boshqarish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:5
msgid ""
"In programming, error handling is a complex topic with many pitfalls, and"
" it can be even more daunting when you're writing code within the "
"constraints of a framework, as the way you handle errors needs to mesh "
"with the way the framework dispatches errors and vice versa."
msgstr ""
"Dasturlashda xatolarni boshqarish ko'plab tuzoqlarga ega murakkab mavzu "
"bo'lib, freymvork cheklovlari doirasida kod yozayotganda yanada og'irroq "
"bo'lishi mumkin, chunki xatolarni boshqarish usuli freymvorkning xatolarni "
"yuborish usuli bilan mos kelishi kerak va aksincha."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:10
msgid ""
"This article paints the broad strokes of how errors are handled by the "
"JavaScript framework and Owl, and gives some recommendations on how to "
"interface with these systems in a way that avoids common problems."
msgstr ""
"Bu maqola JavaScript freymvork va Owl tomonidan xatolar qanday boshqarilishi "
"haqida umumiy ko'rinishni taqdim etadi va umumiy muammolardan qochuvchi "
"tarzda bu tizimlar bilan qanday muloqot qilish bo'yicha ba'zi tavsiyalar "
"beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:15
msgid "Errors in JavaScript"
msgstr "JavaScript da xatolar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:17
msgid ""
"Before we dive into how errors are handled in Odoo as well as how and "
"where to customize error handling behavior, it's a good idea to make sure"
" we're on the same page when it comes to what we mean exactly by "
"\"error\", as well as some of the peculiarities of error handling in "
"JavaScript."
msgstr ""
"Odoo da xatolar qanday boshqarilishi hamda xatolarni boshqarish xatti-"
"harakatini qayerda va qanday moslashtirishni muhokama qilishdan oldin, "
"\"xato\" bilan nimani nazarda tutayotganimiz va JavaScript da xatolarni "
"boshqarishning ba'zi xususiyatlari haqida bir fikrda ekanligimizga "
"ishonch hosil qilish yaxshi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:23
msgid "The `Error` class"
msgstr "`Error` sinfi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:25
msgid ""
"The first thing that may come to mind when we talk about error handling "
"is the built-in `Error` class, or classes that extend it. In the rest of "
"this article, when we refer to an object that is an instance of this "
"class, we will use the term *Error object* in italics."
msgstr ""
"Xatolarni boshqarish haqida gapirganda birinchi xayolga keladigan narsa "
"o'rnatilgan `Error` sinfi yoki uni kengaytiradigan sinflaridir. Ushbu "
"maqolaning qolgan qismida bu sinfning nusxasi bo'lgan ob'ektni "
"ko'rsatganda kursiv bilan *Error ob'ekti* atamasini ishlatamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:31
msgid "Anything can be thrown"
msgstr "Har qanday narsa tashlash mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:33
msgid ""
"In JavaScript, you can throw any value. It is customary to throw *Error "
"objects*, but it is possible to throw any other object, and even "
"primitives. While we don't recommend that you ever throw anything that is"
" not an *Error object*, the Odoo JavaScript framework needs to be able to"
" deal with these scenarios, which will help you understand some design "
"decisions that we've had to make."
msgstr ""
"JavaScript da har qanday qiymatni tashlash mumkin. *Error ob'ektlarini* "
"tashlash odatiy holat, lekin boshqa har qanday ob'ektni va hatto primitivlarni "
"tashlash mumkin. *Error ob'ekti* bo'lmagan hech narsani tashlashni "
"tavsiya etmasak ham, Odoo JavaScript freymvorki bu stsenariylarga dosh "
"bera olishi kerak, bu esa qilishga to'g'ri kelgan ba'zi dizayn "
"qarorlarini tushunishga yordam beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:39
msgid ""
"When instanciating an *Error object*, the browser collects information "
"about the current state of the \"call stack\" (either a proper call "
"stack, or a reconstructed call stack for async functions and promise "
"continuations). This information is called a \"stack trace\" and is very "
"useful for debugging. The Odoo framework displays this stack trace in "
"error dialogs when available."
msgstr ""
"*Error ob'ektini* yaratishda brauzer \"chaqiruv to'plami\" ning joriy holati "
"haqida ma'lumot to'playdi (to'g'ri chaqiruv to'plami yoki asinxron "
"funksiyalar va promise davomiyliklarining qayta qurilgan chaqiruv to'plami). "
"Bu ma'lumot \"stek izi\" deb ataladi va nosozliklarni tuzatish uchun "
"juda foydali. Odoo freymvorki bu stek izini mavjud bo'lganda xato "
"dialog oynalarida ko'rsatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:45
msgid ""
"When throwing a value that is not an *Error object*, the browser still "
"collects information about the current call stack, but this information "
"is not available in JavaScript: it is only available in the devtools "
"console if the error is not handled."
msgstr ""
"*Error ob'ekti* bo'lmagan qiymatni tashlaganda, brauzer hali ham joriy "
"chaqiruv to'plami haqida ma'lumot to'playdi, lekin bu ma'lumot JavaScript da "
"mavjud emas: u faqat xato boshqarilmagan bo'lsa devtools konsolida mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:50
msgid ""
"Throwing *Error objects* enables us to show more detailed information, "
"which a user will be able to copy/paste if needed for a bug report, but "
"it also makes error handling more robust as it allows us to filter errors"
" based on their class when handling them. Unfortunately, JavaScript does "
"not have syntactic support for filtering by error class in the catch "
"clause, but you can relatively easily do it yourself:"
msgstr ""
"*Error ob'ektlarini* tashlash bizga ko'proq batafsil ma'lumotni ko'rsatish "
"imkonini beradi, foydalanuvchi xato hisobot uchun kerak bo'lsa nusxalash/"
"joylashtirishi mumkin, lekin bu shuningdek xatolarni boshqarishni yanada "
"mustahkam qiladi, chunki ularni boshqarishda sinfiga qarab filtrlash "
"imkonini beradi. Afsuski, JavaScript catch bandida xato sinfi bo'yicha "
"filtrlashga sintaktik qo'llab-quvvatlash mavjud emas, lekin buni nisbatan "
"oson o'zingiz qilishingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:69
msgid "Promise rejections are errors"
msgstr "Promise rad etishlari xatolar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:71
msgid ""
"During the early days of Promise adoption, Promises were often treated as"
" a way to store a disjoint union of a result and an \"error\", and it was"
" pretty common to use a Promise rejection as a way to signal a soft "
"failure. While it might seem like a good idea at first glance, browsers "
"and JavaScript runtimes have long started to treat rejected Promises the "
"same way as thrown errors in pretty much every way:"
msgstr ""
"Promise qabul qilishning dastlabki kunlarida, Promise lar ko'pincha natija "
"va \"xato\" ning ajratilgan birlashmasini saqlash usuli sifatida ko'rilardi "
"va Promise ni rad etishni yumshoq muvaffaqiyatsizlikni signal berish usuli "
"sifatida ishlatish juda keng tarqalgan edi. Bir qarashdagi yaxshi g'oya "
"kabi ko'rinsa ham, brauzerlar va JavaScript ish vaqtlari rad etilgan "
"Promise larni deyarli hamma jihatdan tashlangan xatolar bilan bir xil "
"tarzda ko'rishni boshlagan:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:78
msgid ""
"throwing in an async function has the same effect as returning a Promise "
"that is rejected with the thrown value as its rejection reason."
msgstr ""
"asinxron funksiyada tashlash tashlangan qiymat rad etish sababi sifatida "
"rad etilgan Promise ni qaytarish bilan bir xil ta'sir qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:80
msgid ""
"catch blocks in async functions catch rejected Promises that were awaited"
" in the corresponding try block."
msgstr ""
"asinxron funksiyalardagi catch bloklari mos try blokida kutilgan rad "
"etilgan Promise larni ushlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:82
msgid "runtimes collect stack information about rejected promises."
msgstr "ish vaqtlari rad etilgan promise lar haqida stek ma'lumot to'playdi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:83
msgid ""
"a rejected Promise that is not caught synchronously dispatches an event "
"on the global/window object, and if `preventDefault` is not called on the"
" event, browsers log an error, and standalone runtimes like node kill the"
" process."
msgstr ""
"sinxron ushlalmaydigan rad etilgan Promise global/window ob'ektida hodisa "
"yuboradi va hodisada `preventDefault` chaqirilmasa, brauzerlar xato "
"jurnali yozadi va node kabi mustaqil ish vaqtlari jarayonni o'ldiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:86
msgid ""
"the debugger feature \"pause on exceptions\" pauses when Promises are "
"rejected"
msgstr "\"pause on exceptions\" nosozlik tuzatuvchi xususiyati Promise lar rad etilganda to'xtatadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:88
msgid ""
"For these reasons, the Odoo framework treats rejected Promises in the "
"exact same way as thrown errors. Do not create rejected promises in "
"places where you would not throw an error, and always reject Promises "
"with *Error objects* as their rejection reason."
msgstr ""
"Bu sabablar uchun, Odoo freymvorki rad etilgan Promise larni tashlangan "
"xatolar bilan tamoman bir xil tarzda ko'radi. Xato tashlamaydigan joylarda "
"rad etilgan promise lar yaratmang va har doim Promise larni *Error ob'ektlari* "
"bilan rad etish sababi sifatida rad eting."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:94
msgid "`error` events are not errors"
msgstr "`error` hodisalari xatolar emas"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:96
msgid ""
"With the exception of `error` events on the window, `error` events on "
"other objects such as `<media>`, `<audio>` `<img>`, `<script>` and "
"`<link>` elements, or XMLHttpRequest objects are not errors. For the "
"purpose of this article, \"error\" specifically refers only to thrown "
"values and rejected promises. If you need to handle errors on these "
"elements or want them to be treated as errors, you need to explicitly add"
" an event listener for said event:"
msgstr ""
"window dagi `error` hodisalaridan tashqari, `<media>`, `<audio>` `<img>`, "
"`<script>` va `<link>` elementlari yoki XMLHttpRequest ob'ektlari kabi "
"boshqa ob'ektlardagi `error` hodisalari xatolar emas. Ushbu maqolaning "
"maqsadida, \"error\" faqat tashlangan qiymatlar va rad etilgan promise "
"larni anglatadi. Agar bu elementlardagi xatolarni boshqarish yoki ularni "
"xatolar sifatida ko'rishni istasangiz, ushbu hodisa uchun hodisa "
"tinglovchisini aniq qo'shishingiz kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:114
msgid "Lifecycle of errors within the Odoo JS framework"
msgstr "Odoo JS freymvorki ichida xatolar hayot sikli"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:116
msgid ""
"Thrown errors unwind their call stack to find a catch clause that can "
"handle them. The way an error is handled depends on what code is "
"encountered while unwinding the call stack. While there are a virtually "
"infinite number of places errors could be thrown from, there are only a "
"few possible paths into the JS framework's error handling code."
msgstr ""
"Tashlangan xatolar ularni boshqara oladigan catch bandini topish uchun "
"chaqiruv to'plamini ochadi. Xato qanday boshqarilishi chaqiruv to'plamini "
"ochishda qanday kod uchraganiga bog'liq. Xatolar tashlanishi mumkin bo'lgan "
"deyarli cheksiz miqdordagi joylar bo'lsa-da, JS freymvorkining xatolarni "
"boshqarish kodiga faqat bir nechta mumkin bo'lgan yo'llar mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:123
msgid "Throwing an error at the top-level of a module"
msgstr "Modulning yuqori darajasida xato tashlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:125
msgid ""
"When a JS module is loaded, the code at the top level of that module is "
"executed and may throw. While the framework might report these errors "
"with a dialog, module loading is a critical moment for the JavaScript "
"framework and some modules throwing errors might prevent the framework "
"code from booting entirely, so any error reporting at this stage is "
"\"best effort\". Errors thrown during module loading should however "
"always at the very least log an error message in the browser console. "
"Because this type of error is critical, there is no way for the "
"application to recover and you should write your code in such a way that "
"it's impossible for the module to throw during definition. Any error "
"handling and reporting that does happen at this stage is purely with the "
"objective of helping you, the developer, fix the code that threw the "
"error, and we provide no mechanism to customize how these errors are "
"handled."
msgstr ""
"JS moduli yuklanganida, bu modulning yuqori darajasidagi kod bajariladi "
"va tashlanishi mumkin. Freymvork bu xatolarni dialog bilan xabar qilishi "
"mumkin bo'lsa ham, modul yuklash JavaScript freymvorki uchun muhim moment "
"bo'lib, ba'zi modullar xato tashlashi freymvork kodini butunlay ishga "
"tushirishdan to'xtatishi mumkin, shuning uchun bu bosqichdagi har qanday "
"xato xabari \"maksimal harakat\" dir. Modul yuklash vaqtida tashlangan "
"xatolar har holda kamida brauzer konsolida xato xabari jurnali yozishi "
"kerak. Bu turdagi xato muhim bo'lgani uchun, ilova tiklanish imkoni yo'q "
"va kodingizni shunday yozishingiz kerakki, modulgay tarif paytida tashlash "
"mumkin bo'lmasin. Bu bosqichda sodir bo'ladigan har qanday xatolarni "
"boshqarish va xabar qilish faqat siz, ishlab chiquvchiga, xato tashlagan "
"kodni tuzatishga yordam berish maqsadida va biz bu xatolar qanday "
"boshqarilishini moslashtirishga hech qanday mexanizm bermaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:138
msgid "The error service"
msgstr "Xato xizmati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:140
msgid ""
"When an error is thrown but never caught, the runtime dispatches an event"
" on the global object (`window`). The type of the event depends on "
"whether the error was thrown synchronously or asynchronously: "
"synchronously thrown errors dispatch an `error` event, and errors thrown "
"from within an asynchronous context as well as rejected Promises dispatch"
" an `unhandledrejection` event."
msgstr ""
"Xato tashlansa lekin hech qachon ushlunmasa, ish vaqti global ob'ektda "
"(`window`) hodisa yuboradi. Hodisa turi xatoning sinxron yoki asinxron "
"tashlanganligi ga bog'liq: sinxron tashlangan xatolar `error` hodisasini "
"yuboradi va asinxron kontekst ichidan tashlangan xatolar hamda rad etilgan "
"Promise lar `unhandledrejection` hodisasini yuboradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:146
msgid ""
"The JS framework contains a service that is dedicated to handling these "
"events: the error service. When receiving one of these events, the error "
"service starts by creating a new *Error object* that is used to wrap the "
"error that was thrown; this is because any value can be thrown, and "
"Promises can be rejected with any value, including `undefined` or `null`,"
" meaning that it's not guaranteed that it contains any information, or "
"that we can store any information on that value. The wrapping *Error "
"object* is used to collect some information about the thrown value so "
"that it can be used uniformly in the framework code that needs to display"
" information about errors of any type."
msgstr ""
"JS freymvork bu hodisalarni boshqarish uchun maxsus xizmatni o'z ichiga "
"oladi: xato xizmati. Bu hodisalardan birini olganda, xato xizmati tashlangan "
"xatoni o'rash uchun ishlatiladigan yangi *Error ob'ektini* yaratishdan "
"boshlanadi; buning sababi har qanday qiymat tashlanishi mumkin va Promise lar "
"`undefined` yoki `null` kabi har qanday qiymat bilan rad etilishi mumkin, "
"ya'ni u biron bir ma'lumot o'z ichiga olishi yoki bu qiymatda biron ma'lumot "
"saqlashimiz kafolatlanmaydi. O'rash *Error ob'ekti* tashlangan qiymat haqida "
"ba'zi ma'lumotlarni to'plash uchun ishlatiladi, shunda u har qanday turdagi "
"xatolar haqida ma'lumot ko'rsatishi kerak bo'lgan freymvork kodida bir "
"xil tarzda ishlatilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:155
msgid ""
"The error service stores a complete stack trace of the thrown error on "
"this wrapper *Error object* and, when the debug mode is `assets`, uses "
"the source maps to add information in this stack trace about the source "
"file that contains the function of each stack frame. The position of the "
"function in the bundled assets is kept, as it can be useful is some "
"scenarios. When errors have a `cause`, this process also unwinds the "
"`cause` chain to build a complete composite stack trace. While the "
"`cause` field on *Error objects* is standard, some major browsers still "
"do not display the full stack trace of error chains. Because of this, we "
"add this information manually. This is particularly useful when errors "
"are thrown within Owl hooks, more on that later."
msgstr ""
"Xato xizmati bu o'rash *Error ob'ektida* tashlangan xatoning to'liq stek "
"izini saqlaydi va debug rejimi `assets` bo'lganda, har bir stek ramkasi "
"funksiyasini o'z ichiga olgan manba fayl haqida bu stek iziga ma'lumot "
"qo'shish uchun manba xaritalaridan foydalanadi. To'plangan aktivlardagi "
"funksiyaning pozitsiyasi saqlanadi, chunki ba'zi stsenariylarda foydali "
"bo'lishi mumkin. Xatolarda `cause` bo'lganda, bu jarayon to'liq kompozit "
"stek izini yaratish uchun `cause` zanjirini ham ochadi. *Error ob'ektlardagi* "
"`cause` maydoni standart bo'lsa-da, ba'zi asosiy brauzerlar hali ham "
"xato zanjirlari ning to'liq stek izini ko'rsatmaydi. Shu sababli biz bu "
"ma'lumotni qo'lda qo'shamiz. Bu ayniqsa Owl hooklari ichida xatolar "
"tashlanganda foydali, bu haqida keyinroq."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:165
msgid ""
"Once the wrapper error contains all the required information, we start "
"the process of actually handling the error. To do this, the error service"
" successively calls all functions registered in the `error_handlers` "
"registry, until one of these functions returns a truthy value, which "
"signals that the error has been handled. After this, if `preventDefault` "
"was not called on the error event, and if the error service was able to "
"add a stack trace on the wrapper error object, the error service calls "
"`preventDefault` on the error event, and logs the stack trace in the "
"console. This is because, as previously mentioned, some browsers do not "
"display error chains correctly, and the default behaviour of the event is"
" the browser logging the error, so we simply override that behaviour to "
"log a more complete stack trace. If the error service was not able to "
"collect stack trace information about the thrown error, we do not call "
"`preventDefault`. This can happen when throwing non-error values: "
"strings, undefined or other random objects. In those cases, the browser "
"logs the stack trace itself, as it has that information but does not "
"expose it to the JS code."
msgstr ""
"O'rash xatosi barcha kerakli ma'lumotlarni o'z ichiga olgandan so'ng, "
"xatoni haqiqatda boshqarish jarayonini boshlaymiz. Buning uchun xato "
"xizmati `error_handlers` registrida ro'yxatdan o'tgan barcha funksiyalarni "
"ketma-ket chaqiradi, bu funksiyalardan biri haqiqiy qiymat qaytarmaguncha, "
"bu xato boshqarilganligidan dalolat beradi. Shundan so'ng, `preventDefault` "
"xato hodisasida chaqirilmagan bo'lsa va xato xizmati o'rash xato ob'ektiga "
"stek izini qo'sha olgan bo'lsa, xato xizmati xato hodisasida `preventDefault` "
"ni chaqiradi va konsolda stek izini jurnalga yozadi. Avval aytib o'tilganidek, "
"ba'zi brauzerlar xato zanjirlarini to'g'ri ko'rsatmaydi va hodisaning "
"standart xulq-atvori brauzerning xatoni jurnalga yozishi bo'lgani uchun, "
"biz bu xulq-atvorni to'liqroq stek izini jurnalga yozish uchun almashtirish "
"ni amalga oshiramiz. Agar xato xizmati tashlangan xato haqida stek iz "
"ma'lumotlarini to'play olmagan bo'lsa, `preventDefault` ni chaqirmaymiz. "
"Bu xato bo'lmagan qiymatlar tashlanganda sodir bo'lishi mumkin: satrlar, "
"undefined yoki boshqa tasodifiy ob'ektlar. Bunday holatlarda brauzer stek "
"izini o'zi jurnalga yozadi, chunki bu ma'lumot uning o'zida bor, lekin u "
"JS kodiga ochiq emas."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:181
msgid "The `error_handlers` registry"
msgstr "`error_handlers` registri"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:183
msgid ""
"The `error_handlers` registry is the main way to extend the way that the "
"JS framework handles \"generic\" errors. Generic errors, in this context,"
" means errors that can happen in many places, but that should be handled "
"uniformly. Some examples:"
msgstr ""
"`error_handlers` registri JS freymvorki \"umumiy\" xatolarni boshqarish "
"usulini kengaytirish uchun asosiy yo'ldir. Bu kontekstda umumiy xatolar "
"ko'p joylarda sodir bo'lishi mumkin, lekin bir xil tarzda boshqarilishi "
"kerak bo'lgan xatolarni anglatadi. Ba'zi misollar:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:187
msgid ""
"UserError: when the user attempts to perform an operation that the python"
" code deems invalid for business reasons, the python code raises a "
"UserError, and the rpc function throws a corresponding error in "
"JavaScript. This has the potential to happen on any rpc anywhere, and we "
"do not want developers to have to handle this kind of error explicitly in"
" all those places, and we want the same behavior to happen everywhere: "
"stop the currently executing code (which is achieved by the throw), and "
"display a dialog that explains to the user what went wrong."
msgstr ""
"UserError: foydalanuvchi biznes sabablari bilan yaroqsiz deb hisoblangan "
"amalni bajarishga harakat qilganda, python kodi UserError ni ko'taradi va "
"rpc funksiyasi JavaScript da tegishli xato tashlaydi. Bu har qanday joyda "
"har qanday rpc da sodir bo'lishi mumkin va biz ishlab chiquvchilardan bu "
"turdagi xatoni barcha joylarda aniq boshqarishni talab qilishni "
"xohlamaymiz, hamda hamma joyda bir xil xulq-atvor bo'lishini xohlaymiz: "
"hozirda bajarilayotgan kodni to'xtatish (bu tashlash bilan amalga oshiriladi) "
"va foydalanuvchiga nima noto'g'ri ketganini tushuntiruvchi dialog ko'rsatish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:194
msgid ""
"AccessError: same reasoning as for user errors: it can happen at any "
"point and should be displayed the same way regardless of where it happens"
msgstr ""
"AccessError: foydalanuvchi xatolaridagi kabi: u har qanday nuqtada sodir "
"bo'lishi mumkin va qayerda sodir bo'lishidan qat'i nazar bir xil tarzda "
"ko'rsatilishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:196
msgid "LostConnection: same reasoning again."
msgstr "LostConnection: yana bir xil mantiq."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:199
msgid "Throwing an error in an Owl component"
msgstr "Owl komponentida xato tashlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:201
msgid ""
"Registering or modifying Owl components is the main way in which you can "
"extend the functionality of the web client. As such, most errors that are"
" thrown are in one way or another thrown from an Owl component. There are"
" a few possible scenarios:"
msgstr ""
"Owl komponentlarini ro'yxatdan o'tkazish yoki o'zgartirish veb-mijoz "
"funksionalligini kengaytirish uchun asosiy usuldir. Shu sababli, "
"tashlanadigan xatolarning aksariyati bir yoki boshqa tarzda Owl "
"komponentidan tashlanadi. Bir nechta mumkin bo'lgan stsenariylar mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:205
msgid "Throwing in the component's setup or during rendering"
msgstr "Komponentning sozlash jarayonida yoki renderda tashlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:206
msgid "Throwing from within a lifecycle hook"
msgstr "Hayot sikli hook ichidan tashlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:207
msgid "Throwing from an event handler"
msgstr "Hodisa ishlov beruvchisidan tashlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:209
msgid ""
"Throwing an error from an event handler or a function or method called "
"directly or indirectly from an event handler means that neither Owl's "
"code nor the JS framework's code is in the call stack. If you don't catch"
" the error, it lands directly in the error service."
msgstr ""
"Hodisa ishlov beruvchisidan yoki hodisa ishlov beruvchisidan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri "
"yoki bilvosita chaqirilgan funksiya yoki metoddan xato tashlash Owl kodi "
"ham, JS freymvorki kodi ham chaqiruv to'plamida emasligini anglatadi. "
"Agar xatoni ushlasangiz, u to'g'ridan-to'g'ri xato xizmatiga tushadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:214
msgid ""
"When throwing an error in a component's setup or during rendering, Owl "
"catches the error and goes up the component hierarchy, allowing "
"components that have registered error handlers with the `onError` hook to"
" attempt to handle the error. If the error is not handled by any of them,"
" Owl destroys the application as it is likely in a corrupted state."
msgstr ""
"Komponentning sozlash jarayonida yoki renderda xato tashlaganda, Owl "
"xatoni ushlaydi va komponent ierarxiyasi bo'ylab yuqoriga ko'tariladi, "
"`onError` hook orqali xato ishlov beruvchilarini ro'yxatdan o'tkazgan "
"komponentlarga xatoni boshqarishga harakat qilishga imkon beradi. Agar "
"xato ularning hech biri tomonidan boshqarilmasa, Owl ilovani yo'q qiladi, "
"chunki u ehtimol buzilgan holatda."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:221
msgid ""
"`Error handling in the Owl documentation "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/error_handling.md>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Owl hujjatlaridagi xatolarni boshqarish "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/error_handling.md>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:223
msgid ""
"Inside Odoo, there are some places where we do not want the entire "
"application to crash in case of error, and so the framework has a few "
"places where it uses the `onError` hook. The action service wraps actions"
" and views in a component that handles errors. If a client action or view"
" throws an error during rendering, it attempts to go back to the previous"
" action. The error is dispatched to the error service so that an error "
"dialog can be shown regardless. A similar strategy is used in most places"
" where the framework calls into \"user\" code: we generally stop "
"displaying the faulty component an show an error dialog."
msgstr ""
"Odoo ichida xato bo'lganda butun ilovaning ishdan chiqishini xohlamagan "
"ba'zi joylar mavjud, shuning uchun freymvork `onError` hookidan foydalanadigan "
"bir nechta joyga ega. Amal xizmati amallar va ko'rinishlarni xatolarni "
"boshqaradigan komponentga o'raydi. Agar mijoz amali yoki ko'rinish render "
"paytida xato tashlasa, u oldingi amalga qaytishga harakat qiladi. Xato "
"xato xizmatiga yuboriladi, shunda xato dialogi ko'rsatilishi mumkin. "
"Freymvork \"foydalanuvchi\" kodini chaqiradigan ko'pgina joylarda shunga "
"o'xshash strategiya qo'llaniladi: odatda nosoz komponentni ko'rsatishni "
"to'xtatamiz va xato dialogini ko'rsatamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:232
msgid ""
"When throwing an error inside of a hook's callback function, Owl creates "
"a new *Error object* that contains stack information about where the hook"
" was registered, and sets its cause as the originally thrown value. This "
"is because the stack trace of the original error contains no information "
"about which component registered this hook and where, it only contains "
"information about what called the hook. Because hooks are called by Owl "
"code, most of this information is *generally* not very useful for "
"developers, but knowing where the hook was registered and by which "
"component is very useful."
msgstr ""
"Hook ning qayta chaqiruv funksiyasi ichida xato tashlaganda, Owl hook "
"qayerda ro'yxatdan o'tkazilganligi haqida stek ma'lumotlarini o'z ichiga "
"olgan yangi *Error ob'ektini* yaratadi va uning sababini dastlab tashlangan "
"qiymat sifatida belgilaydi. Buning sababi shundaki, asl xatoning stek izi "
"bu hookni qaysi komponent qayerda ro'yxatdan o'tkazganligi haqida hech "
"qanday ma'lumot o'z ichiga olmaydi, u faqat hookni nima chaqirganligi "
"haqidagi ma'lumotni o'z ichiga oladi. Hooklar Owl kodi tomonidan "
"chaqirilganligi sababli, bu ma'lumotlarning aksariyati ishlab chiquvchilar "
"uchun *odatda* juda foydali emas, lekin hookni qayerda va qaysi komponent "
"tomonidan ro'yxatdan o'tkazilganligi bilish juda foydali."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:241
msgid ""
"When reading errors that mention \"OwlError: the following error occurred"
" in <hookName>\", make sure to read both parts of the composite stack "
"trace:"
msgstr ""
"\"OwlError: the following error occurred in <hookName>\" deb eslatib "
"o'tadigan xatolarni o'qiyotganda, kompozit stek izining ikkala qismini "
"ham o'qishga ishonch hosil qiling:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:263
msgid ""
"The first highlighted line tells you which component registered the "
"`onMounted` hook, while the second highlighted line tells you which "
"function threw the error. In this case, a child component is calling a "
"function it received as prop from its parent, and that function is a "
"method of the parent component. Both pieces of information can be useful,"
" as the method could have been called by mistake by the child (or at a "
"point in the lifecycle where it shouldn't), but it could also be that the"
" parent's method contains a bug."
msgstr ""
"Birinchi ta'kidlangan satr qaysi komponent `onMounted` hookini "
"ro'yxatdan o'tkazganini aytadi, ikkinchi ta'kidlangan satr esa qaysi "
"funksiya xato tashlaganini aytadi. Bu holda, bola komponent ota-onasidan "
"prop sifatida olgan funksiyani chaqirmoqda va bu funksiya ota-ona "
"komponentining metodidir. Ikkala ma'lumot ham foydali bo'lishi mumkin, "
"chunki metod bola tomonidan xato chaqirilgan bo'lishi mumkin (yoki hayot "
"siklining u bo'lmasligi kerak bo'lgan nuqtasida), lekin ota-onaning "
"metodida ham xato bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:272
msgid "Marking errors as handled"
msgstr "Xatolarni boshqarilgan deb belgilash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:274
msgid ""
"In the previous sections, we talked about two ways to register error "
"handlers: one is adding them to the `error_handlers` registry, the other "
"is using the `onError` hook in owl. In both cases, the handler has to "
"decide whether to mark the error as handled."
msgstr ""
"Oldingi bo'limlarda biz xato ishlov beruvchilarini ro'yxatdan o'tkazishning "
"ikki usulini muhokama qildik: biri ularni `error_handlers` registriga "
"qo'shish, ikkinchisi owl da `onError` hookidan foydalanish. Ikkala holda "
"ham ishlov beruvchi xatoni boshqarilgan deb belgilash yoki belgilmaslikni "
"hal qilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:280
msgid "`onError`"
msgstr "`onError`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:282
msgid ""
"In the case of a handler registered in Owl with `onError`, the error is "
"considered by Owl as handled unless you rethrow it. Whatever you do in "
"`onError`, the user interface is likely not synchronized with the state "
"of the application, as the error prevented owl from completing some work."
" If you are unable to handle the error, you should rethrow it, and let "
"the rest of the code handle it."
msgstr ""
"`onError` bilan Owl da ro'yxatdan o'tkazilgan ishlov beruvchi holatida, "
"xato uni qayta tashlamasangiz Owl tomonidan boshqarilgan deb hisoblanadi. "
"`onError` da qilganingizdan qat'i nazar, foydalanuvchi interfeysi ilovaning "
"holati bilan sinxronlashtirilmagan bo'lishi ehtimoli bor, chunki xato "
"owl ning ba'zi ishlarni bajarishiga to'sqinlik qildi. Agar xatoni "
"boshqara olmasangiz, uni qayta tashlashingiz va qolgan kodga boshqarishga "
"ruxsat berishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:288
msgid ""
"If you don't rethrow the error, you need to change some state so that the"
" application can render again in a non-erroring way. At this point, if "
"you don't rethrow the error it will not be reported. In some cases this "
"is desirable, but in most cases, what you should do instead is dispatch "
"this error in a separate call stack outside of Owl. The easiest way to do"
" this is to simply create a rejected Promise with the error as its "
"rejection reason:"
msgstr ""
"Agar xatoni qayta tashlamasangiz, ilova xatosiz tarzda qayta render qila "
"olishi uchun ba'zi holatni o'zgartirishingiz kerak. Bu nuqtada, agar "
"xatoni qayta tashlamasangiz u xabar qilinmaydi. Ba'zi holatlarda bu "
"maqsadga muvofiq, lekin aksariyat holatlarda o'rniga bu xatoni Owl "
"tashqarisidagi alohida chaqiruv to'plamida yuborishingiz kerak. Buning "
"eng oson yo'li rad etish sababi sifatida xato bilan rad etilgan Promise "
"yaratishdir:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:308
msgid ""
"This causes the browser to dispatch an `unhandledrejection` event on the "
"window, which causes the JS framework's error handling to kick in and "
"deal with the error, in most cases by opening a dialog with information "
"about the error. This is the strategy that is used internally by the "
"action service and dialog service to stop rendering broken actions or "
"dialogs while still reporting the error."
msgstr ""
"Bu brauzerga window da `unhandledrejection` hodisasini yuborishga sabab "
"bo'ladi, bu esa JS freymvorkining xatolarni boshqarishini ishga tushiradi "
"va xato bilan shug'ullanadi, aksariyat holatlarda xato haqida ma'lumot "
"bilan dialog ochish orqali. Bu amal xizmati va dialog xizmati tomonidan "
"xatoni xabar qilish davom etayotganda nosoz amallar yoki dialoglarni "
"renderdan to'xtatish uchun ichki tomondan qo'llaniladigan strategiyadir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:315
msgid "Handler in the `error_handlers` registry"
msgstr "`error_handlers` registridagi ishlov beruvchi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:317
msgid ""
"Handlers that are added to the `error_handlers` registry can mark an "
"error as being handled in two ways, with different meanings."
msgstr ""
"`error_handlers` registriga qo'shilgan ishlov beruvchilar xatoni turli "
"ma'nolarda boshqarilgan deb ikkita usulda belgilashi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:320
msgid ""
"The first way is that the handler can return a truthy value, this means "
"that the handler has processed the error and made something happen "
"because the error it received matched the type of error it is able to "
"handle. This generally means it has opened a dialog or notification to "
"warn the user about the error. This prevents the error service from "
"calling the following handlers with higher sequence number."
msgstr ""
"Birinchi usul shundaki, ishlov beruvchi haqiqiy qiymat qaytarishi mumkin, "
"bu ishlov beruvchi xatoni qayta ishladi va u qabul qilgan xato boshqara "
"oladigan xato turi bilan mos kelganligi sababli biror narsa sodir etdi "
"degani. Bu odatda foydalanuvchini xato haqida ogohlantirish uchun dialog "
"yoki bildirishnoma ochganligini anglatadi. Bu xato xizmatining yuqori "
"ketma-ket raqamli keyingi ishlov beruvchilarni chaqirishiga to'sqinlik "
"qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:326
msgid ""
"The other way is to call `preventDefault` on the error event: this has a "
"different meaning. After deciding that it is able to handle the error, "
"the handler needs to decide if the error it received is something that is"
" allowed to happen during normal operation and if it is, it should call "
"`preventDefault`. This is generally applicable to business errors such as"
" an access errors or validation errors: users can share links with other "
"users to ressources to which they do not have acces, and users can "
"attempt to save a record that's in an invalid state."
msgstr ""
"Ikkinchi usul xato hodisasida `preventDefault` ni chaqirish: bu boshqa "
"ma'noga ega. Xatoni boshqara olishini hal qilgandan so'ng, ishlov beruvchi "
"qabul qilgan xatoning odatiy ishlash paytida sodir bo'lishiga ruxsat "
"beriladigan narsa ekanligini va u shunday bo'lsa, `preventDefault` ni "
"chaqirishi kerakligini hal qilishi kerak. Bu odatda kirish xatolari yoki "
"validatsiya xatolari kabi biznes xatolariga qo'llaniladi: foydalanuvchilar "
"kirish imkoni bo'lmagan resurslarga havolalarni boshqa foydalanuvchilar "
"bilan ulashishi mumkin va foydalanuvchilar yaroqsiz holatdagi yozuvni "
"saqlashga harakat qilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:334
msgid ""
"When not calling `preventDefault`, the error is treated as unexpected, "
"any such occurrence during a test causes the test to fail, as it's "
"generally indicative of defective code."
msgstr ""
"`preventDefault` ni chaqirmaslik holatida xato kutilmagan deb qabul "
"qilinadi, test paytida bunday holat testning muvaffaqiyatsizligiga "
"olib keladi, chunki bu odatda nuqsonli kodning belgisidir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:340
msgid "Avoid throwing errors as much as possible"
msgstr "Imkon qadar xato tashlashdan saqlaning"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:342
msgid ""
"Errors introduce complexity in many ways, here are some reasons why you "
"should avoid throwing them."
msgstr ""
"Xatolar ko'p jihatdan murakkablikni oshiradi, siz ularni tashlashdan "
"saqlanish uchun quyidagi sabablarga e'tibor bering."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:346
msgid "Errors are expensive"
msgstr "Xatolar qimmatga tushadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:348
msgid ""
"Because errors need to unwind the callstack and collect information as "
"they do so, throwing errors is slow. Additionally, JavaScript runtimes "
"are generally optimized with the assumption that exceptions are rare, and"
" as such generally compiles the code with the assumption that it doesn't "
"throw, and fall back to a slower code path if it ever does."
msgstr ""
"Xatolar chaqiruv to'plamini ochishi va shu jarayonda ma'lumot to'plashi "
"kerakligi sababli, xato tashlash sekin. Bundan tashqari, JavaScript ish "
"vaqtlari odatda istisnolar kamdan-kam deb taxmin qilib optimallashtirilgan "
"va shu sabab odatda tashlamas deb taxmin qilib kodni kompilyatsiya qiladi "
"va qachondir tashlasa sekinroq kod yo'liga o'tadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:355
msgid "Throwing errors makes debugging harder"
msgstr "Xato tashlash disk raskadrovkani qiyinlashtiradi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:357
msgid ""
"JavaScript debuggers, like the one included in the Chrome and Firefox "
"devtools for example, have a feature that allows you to pause the "
"execution when an exception is thrown. You can also choose whether to "
"pause only on caught exceptions, or on both caught and uncaught "
"exceptions."
msgstr ""
"JavaScript disk raskadrovkalari, masalan Chrome va Firefox devtools da "
"mavjud, istisno tashlaganda ijroni to'xtatish imkonini beruvchi "
"xususiyatga ega. Shuningdek, faqat ushlangan istisnolarda yoki ham "
"ushlangan, ham ushlunmagan istisnolarda to'xtatishni tanlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:362
msgid ""
"When you throw an error inside of code that is called by Owl or by the "
"JavaScript framework (e.g. in a field, view, action, component, ...), "
"because they manage resources, they need to catch errors and inspect them"
" to decide whether the error is critical and the application should "
"crash, or if the error is expected and should be handled in a particular "
"manner."
msgstr ""
"Owl yoki JavaScript freymvork tomonidan chaqirilgan kodda (masalan, "
"maydon, ko'rinish, amal, komponent, ...) xato tashlaganda, ular resurslarni "
"boshqarganligi sababli, xatolarni ushlashlari va xato muhim ekanligini "
"va ilova ishdan chiqishi kerakligini yoki xato kutilgan ekanligini va "
"muayyan tarzda boshqarilishi kerakligini hal qilish uchun ularni tekshirishlari "
"kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:368
msgid ""
"Because of this, almost all errors that are thrown within JavaScript code"
" are caught at some point, and although they may be rethrown if they "
"cannot be handled, this means that using the \"pause on uncaught "
"exceptions\" feature is effectively useless while working within Odoo, as"
" it always pauses within the JavaScript framework code, instead of near "
"the code that threw the error originally."
msgstr ""
"Shu sababli, JavaScript kodi ichida tashlangan deyarli barcha xatolar "
"biron nuqtada ushlangan va agar boshqarilmasa qayta tashlanishi mumkin "
"bo'lsa ham, bu Odoo ichida ishlashda \"ushlunmagan istisnolarda to'xtatish\" "
"xususiyatidan foydalanish amalda foydasiz ekanligini anglatadi, chunki "
"u har doim dastlab xato tashlagan kodga yaqin o'rnida JavaScript freymvorki "
"kodi ichida to'xtatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:374
msgid ""
"However, the \"pause on caught exceptions\" feature is still very useful,"
" as it pauses execution on every throw statement and rejected promise. "
"This allows the developer to stop and inspect the execution context "
"whenever an exceptional situation occurs."
msgstr ""
"Biroq, \"ushlangan istisnolarda to'xtatish\" xususiyati hali ham juda "
"foydali, chunki u har bir tashlash operatori va rad etilgan promiseda "
"ijroni to'xtatadi. Bu ishlab chiquvchiga istisno holat yuzaga kelganda "
"ijroni to'xtatib va kontekstni tekshirish imkonini beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:379
msgid ""
"However, this is only true assuming that exceptions are rarely thrown. If"
" exceptions are thrown routinely, any action within the page can cause "
"the debugger to stop the execution, and the developer might need to step "
"through many \"routine\" exceptions before they can get to the actual "
"exceptional scenario they are interested in. In some situations, because "
"clicking the play button in the debugger removes focus from the page, it "
"may even make the interesting throw scenario inaccessible without using "
"the keyboard shortcut for resuming execution which results in poor "
"developer experience."
msgstr ""
"Biroq, bu faqat istisnolar kamdan-kam tashlanadi deb taxmin qilinganda "
"to'g'ri. Agar istisnolar muntazam ravishda tashlanadigan bo'lsa, sahifa "
"ichidagi har qanday amal disk raskadrovkaning ijroni to'xtatishiga sabab "
"bo'lishi mumkin va ishlab chiquvchi qiziqtiruvchi istisno stsenariysiga "
"yetishidan oldin ko'plab \"odatiy\" istisnolardan o'tishi kerak bo'lishi "
"mumkin. Ba'zi holatlarda, disk raskadrovkadagi o'ynash tugmasini bosish "
"sahifadan fokusni olib tashlaydi, bu esa ijroni davom ettirish uchun "
"klaviatura yorlig'idan foydalanmasdan qiziqarli tashlash stsenariysiga "
"kirish imkonsiz bo'lishiga ham olib kelishi mumkin, bu esa yomon ishlab "
"chiquvchi tajribasiga olib keladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:389
msgid "Throwing breaks the normal flow of the code"
msgstr "Tashlash kodning odatiy oqimini buzadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:391
msgid ""
"When throwing an error, code that looks like it should always execute may"
" be skipped, this can cause many subtle bugs and memory leaks. Here is a "
"simple example:"
msgstr ""
"Xato tashlaganda, har doim bajarilishi kerak ko'rinadigan kod o'tkazib "
"yuborilishi mumkin, bu ko'plab nozik xatolar va xotira sizishlariga "
"olib kelishi mumkin. Mana oddiy misol:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:400
msgid ""
"In this block of code, we add an event listener to an event target, then "
"call a function which may dispatch events on that target. After the "
"function call, we remove the event listener."
msgstr ""
"Bu kod blokida, hodisa nishoniga hodisa tinglovchi qo'shamiz, so'ngra "
"o'sha nishonda hodisalarni yuborishi mumkin bo'lgan funksiyani chaqiramiz. "
"Funksiya chaqiruvidan so'ng, hodisa tinglovchini olib tashlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:404
msgid ""
"If `someFunction` throws, the event listener will never be removed. This "
"means that the memory associated with this event listener is effectively "
"leaked and will never be freed unless the eventTarget itself gets "
"deallocated."
msgstr ""
"Agar `someFunction` tashlasa, hodisa tinglovchi hech qachon olib "
"tashlanmaydi. Bu hodisa tinglovchi bilan bog'liq xotira amalda sizib "
"chiqadi va eventTarget o'zi xotira ajratmagunicha hech qachon bo'shatilmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:408
msgid ""
"On top of the memory being leaked, the handler still being attached means"
" that it may be called for events being dispatched for reasons other than"
" the call to `someFunction`. This is a bug."
msgstr ""
"Xotiraning sizishi bilan birga, ishlov beruvchining hali ham biriktirilgan "
"holda qolishi `someFunction` chaqiruvidan boshqa sabablarda yuborilayotgan "
"hodisalar uchun ham chaqirilishi mumkinligini anglatadi. Bu xato."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:412
msgid ""
"To account for this, one would need to wrap the call in a `try` block, "
"and the cleanup in a `finally` block:"
msgstr ""
"Buning uchun chaqiruvni `try` blokiga va tozalashni `finally` blokiga "
"o'rash kerak bo'ladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:424
msgid ""
"While this now avoids the problems mentioned above, not only does this "
"require more code, it also requires knowledge that the function may "
"throw. It would be unmanageable to wrap all code that may throw in a "
"`try/finally` block."
msgstr ""
"Bu endi yuqorida aytib o'tilgan muammolardan qochsa-da, bu nafaqat ko'proq "
"kod talab qiladi, balki funksiya tashlashi mumkinligi haqida bilimni ham "
"talab qiladi. Tashlashi mumkin bo'lgan barcha kodlarni `try/finally` blokiga "
"o'rash boshqarib bo'lmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:429
msgid "Catching errors"
msgstr "Xatolarni ushlash"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:431
msgid ""
"Sometimes, you need to call into code that is known to throw errors and "
"you want to handle some of these errors. There are two important things "
"to keep in mind:"
msgstr ""
"Ba'zida xato tashlashi ma'lum bo'lgan kodga chaqiruv qilishingiz va bu "
"xatolardan ba'zilarini boshqarishni xohlashingiz kerak. Esda tutish "
"kerak bo'lgan ikki muhim narsa bor:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:434
msgid ""
"Rethrow errors that are not the type of error you expect. This should "
"generally be done with and `instanceof` check"
msgstr ""
"Kutayotgan xato turi bo'lmagan xatolarni qayta tashlang. Bu odatda "
"`instanceof` tekshiruvi bilan amalga oshirilishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:436
msgid ""
"Keep the try block as small as possible. This avoid catching errors that "
"are not the one you're trying to catch. Generally, the try block should "
"contain exactly *one* statement."
msgstr ""
"try blokini imkon qadar kichik saqlang. Bu ushlashga harakat qilgan "
"xato bo'lmagan xatolarni ushlashdan qochadi. Odatda, try bloki aynan "
"*bitta* operatorni o'z ichiga olishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:454
msgid ""
"While this is straightforward with try/catch, it's much easier to "
"accidentally wrap a much larger portion of code in a catch clause when "
"working with `Promise.catch`:"
msgstr ""
"Bu try/catch bilan sodda bo'lsa-da, `Promise.catch` bilan ishlashda "
"catch bandiga kodning ancha katta qismini tasodifan o'rash ancha oson:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:468
msgid ""
"In this example, the catch block is actually catching errors in the "
"entire then block, which is not what we want. In this particular example,"
" because we properly filter based on the error type, we're not swallowing"
" the error, but you can see that it may be much easier to do so if we're "
"expecting a single error type and decide not to have the instanceof "
"check. Notice however that unlike the previous example, the null isn't "
"going through the codepath that uses `someVal`. To avoid this, catch "
"clauses should generally be as close as possible to the promise that may "
"throw, and should always filter on the error type."
msgstr ""
"Bu misolda, catch bloki aslida butun then blokidagi xatolarni ushlaydi, "
"bu biz xohlagan narsa emas. Ushbu alohida misolda, xato turi bo'yicha "
"to'g'ri filtrlaganligi sababli, xatoni yutib yubormaymiz, lekin instanceof "
"tekshiruvini o'tkazib yuborgan holda bir xil xato turini kutayotgan bo'lsak "
"buni qilish ancha oson bo'lishini ko'rishingiz mumkin. Biroq, oldingi "
"misoldan farqli ravishda, null `someVal` ni ishlatadigan kod yo'lidan "
"o'tmayaotganini e'tibor bering. Buning oldini olish uchun catch bandlari "
"odatda tashlashi mumkin bo'lgan promisega imkon qadar yaqin bo'lishi va "
"har doim xato turi bo'yicha filtrlashi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:478
msgid "Error free control flow"
msgstr "Xatosiz boshqaruv oqimi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:480
msgid ""
"For the reasons outlined above, you should avoid throwing errors for "
"doing routine things, and in particular, for control flow. If a function "
"is expected to be unable to complete its work on a regular basis, it "
"should communicate that failure without throwing an exception. Consider "
"the example code:"
msgstr ""
"Yuqorida bayon qilingan sabablarga ko'ra, odatiy ishlar uchun va xususan, "
"boshqaruv oqimi uchun xato tashlashdan qochishingiz kerak. Agar funksiya "
"muntazam ravishda o'z ishini bajara olmaydi deb kutilsa, istisno tashlamasdan "
"bu muvaffaqiyatsizlikni yetkazishi kerak. Namuna kodni ko'rib chiqing:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:497
msgid ""
"There are many things that are problematic with this code. First, because"
" we want the variable `someVal` to be accessible after the `try/catch` "
"block, it needs to be declared before that block, and it cannot be "
"`const` since it needs to be assigned after initialization. This hurts "
"readability further down the road as you now have to look out for this "
"variable potentially being reassigned later in the code."
msgstr ""
"Bu kodda muammoli narsalar ko'p. Birinchidan, `someVal` o'zgaruvchisi "
"`try/catch` blokidan so'ng ham kirish mumkin bo'lishini xohlasak, u bu "
"blokdan oldin e'lon qilinishi kerak va initsializatsiyadan so'ng "
"tayinlanishi kerakligi sababli `const` bo'lishi mumkin emas. Bu keyinroq "
"o'qilishni qiyinlashtiradi, chunki endi kodda keyinroq bu o'zgaruvchi "
"qayta tayinlanishi mumkinligini kuzatib borishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:503
msgid ""
"Second, when we catch the error, we have to check that the error is "
"actually the type of error we were expecting to catch, and if not, "
"rethrow the error. If we don't do this, we might end up swallowing errors"
" that were *actually* unexpected instead of reporting them correctly, "
"e.g. we could be catching and swallowing a TypeError if the underlying "
"code tries to access a property on `null` or `undefined`."
msgstr ""
"Ikkinchidan, xatoni ushlashda, xatoning haqiqatan ham ushlashni kutgan "
"xato turi ekanligini tekshirishimiz va agar bo'lmasa, xatoni qayta "
"tashlashimiz kerak. Buni qilmasak, kutilmagan bo'lgan xatolarni to'g'ri "
"xabar qilish o'rniga yutib yuborishimiz mumkin, masalan, asosiy kod "
"`null` yoki `undefined` da xususiyatga kirishga harakat qilsa TypeError ni "
"ushlash va yutib yuborishimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:509
msgid ""
"Lastly, not only is this very verbose, but it's easy to do this "
"incorrectly: if you forget to add the `try/catch`, you are likely to end "
"up with a traceback. If you add the `try/catch` block but forget to "
"rethrow unexpected errors, you are swallowing unrelated errors. And if "
"you want to avoid having to reassign the variable you may move the entire"
" block that uses the variable inside the `try` block. The more code you "
"have inside your `try` block, the more likely you are to catch unrelated "
"errors, and swallow them if you forgot to filter by error type. It also "
"adds an indentation level to the entire block, and you may even end up "
"with nested `try/catch` blocks. Lastly, it makes it harder to identify "
"which line is actually expected to throw the error."
msgstr ""
"Nihoyat, bu nafaqat juda batafsil, balki noto'g'ri bajarishni ham oson: "
"agar `try/catch` qo'shishni unutsangiz, ehtimol traceback bilan tugaysiz. "
"Agar `try/catch` blokini qo'shsangiz, lekin kutilmagan xatolarni qayta "
"tashlashni unutsangiz, bog'liq bo'lmagan xatolarni yutib yuborasiz. "
"O'zgaruvchini qayta tayinlashdan qochish uchun o'zgaruvchini ishlatadigan "
"butun blokni `try` bloki ichiga ko'chirishingiz mumkin. `try` bloki ichida "
"qancha ko'p kod bo'lsa, bog'liq bo'lmagan xatolarni ushlash ehtimoli "
"shuncha yuqori va agar xato turi bo'yicha filtrlashni unutsangiz ularni "
"yutib yuborasiz. Bu butun blokga ham chaqiruv darajasini qo'shadi va "
"hatto ichma-ich `try/catch` bloklari bilan tugashingiz ham mumkin. Nihoyat, "
"bu qaysi satr haqiqatan ham xato tashlashi kutilganini aniqlashni qiyinlashtiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:520
msgid ""
"The following sections outline some alternative approaches you can use "
"instead of using errors."
msgstr ""
"Quyidagi bo'limlar xatolardan foydalanish o'rniga ishlatishingiz mumkin "
"bo'lgan muqobil yondashuvlarni belgilaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:524
msgid "Return `null` or `undefined`"
msgstr "`null` yoki `undefined` qaytarish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:526
msgid ""
"If the function returns a primitive or an object, you can generally use "
"`null` or `undefined` to signal that it was unable to do its intended "
"job. This suffices in most cases. The code ends up looking something like"
" this:"
msgstr ""
"Agar funksiya primitiv yoki ob'ekt qaytarsa, odatda `null` yoki `undefined` "
"ni mo'ljallangan ishini bajara olmaganligini bildirish uchun ishlatishingiz "
"mumkin. Bu aksariyat hollarda yetarli. Kod quyidagicha ko'rinish oladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:536
msgid "As you can see, this is much simpler."
msgstr "Ko'ringanidek, bu ancha soddaroq."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:539
msgid "Return an object or array"
msgstr "Ob'ekt yoki massiv qaytarish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:541
msgid ""
"In some cases, a value of `null` or `undefined` is part of the expected "
"return values. In those cases, you can instead return a wrapper object or"
" a two-element array that contains either the return value or the error:"
msgstr ""
"Ba'zi holatlarda, `null` yoki `undefined` qiymati kutilgan qaytarish "
"qiymatlarining bir qismidir. Bunday holatlarda o'rniga qaytarish qiymatini "
"yoki xatoni o'z ichiga olgan o'rash ob'ekti yoki ikki elementli massiv "
"qaytarishingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:553
msgid "Or with an array:"
msgstr "Yoki massiv bilan:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:565
msgid ""
"When using a two-element array, it is advisable to have the error be the "
"first element, so that it is harder to ignore by mistake when "
"destructuring. One would need to explicitly add a placeholder or comma to"
" skip the error, whereas if the error is the second element, it is easy "
"to simply destructure only the first element and mistakenly forget to "
"handle the error."
msgstr ""
"Ikki elementli massiv ishlatishda, destrukturizatsiya paytida xatoni "
"xato bilan e'tiborsiz qoldirish qiyinroq bo'lishi uchun xatoni birinchi "
"element qilish tavsiya etiladi. Xatoni o'tkazib yuborish uchun aniq "
"to'ldiruvchi yoki vergul qo'shish kerak bo'ladi, holbuki agar xato "
"ikkinchi element bo'lsa, faqat birinchi elementni destrukturizatsiya "
"qilib, xatoni boshqarishni unutish osondir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:572
msgid "When to throw errors"
msgstr "Qachon xato tashlash kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:574
msgid ""
"The previous sections give many good reasons to avoid throwing errors, so"
" what are some examples of cases where throwing an error is the best "
"course of action?"
msgstr ""
"Oldingi bo'limlar xato tashlashdan qochish uchun ko'plab yaxshi sabablarga "
"ega, shunday ekan, xato tashlash eng yaxshi harakat bo'lgan holatlarga "
"qanday misollar bor?"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:577
msgid ""
"Generic errors that can happen in many places but should be treated the "
"same everywhere; e.g., access errors can happen on basically any RPC, and"
" we always want to display information about why the user doesn't have "
"access."
msgstr ""
"Ko'p joylarda sodir bo'lishi mumkin bo'lgan, lekin hamma joyda bir xil "
"ko'rib chiqilishi kerak bo'lgan umumiy xatolar; masalan, kirish xatolari "
"asosan har qanday RPC da sodir bo'lishi mumkin va biz har doim "
"foydalanuvchining nima uchun kirishga ega emasligi haqida ma'lumot "
"ko'rsatishni xohlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:580
msgid ""
"Some precondition that should always be fulfilled for some operation is "
"not fulfilled; e.g., a view couldn't be rendered because the domain is "
"invalid. These types of error are generally not intended to be caught "
"anywhere and signal that code is incorrect or data is corrupted. Throwing"
" forces the framework to bail out and prevents operating in a broken "
"state."
msgstr ""
"Ba'zi amal uchun har doim bajarilishi kerak bo'lgan ba'zi oldingi shart "
"bajarilmaydi; masalan, domen yaroqsiz bo'lgani uchun ko'rinish render "
"qilinmadi. Bu turdagi xatolar odatda hech qaerda ushlash maqsadida "
"bo'lmaydi va kod noto'g'ri yoki ma'lumotlar buzilganligidan dalolat beradi. "
"Tashlash freymvorkni chiqib ketishga majbur qiladi va buzilgan holatda "
"ishlashning oldini oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/error_handling.rst:585
msgid ""
"When traversing some deep data structure recursively, throwing an error "
"can be more ergonomic and less error prone than having to manually test "
"for errors and forward them through many levels of calls. This should be "
"very rare in practice, and needs to be weighed against all the "
"disadvantages mentioned in this article."
msgstr ""
"Ba'zi chuqur ma'lumotlar tuzilmasini rekursiv ravishda o'tayotganda, "
"xato tashlash xatolarni qo'lda tekshirish va ularni ko'p darajali "
"chaqiruvlar orqali yo'naltirish kerak bo'lgandan ko'ra ergonomikroq va "
"xatoga kamroq moyil bo'lishi mumkin. Bu amalda juda kamdan-kam bo'lishi "
"va ushbu maqolada aytib o'tilgan barcha kamchiliklarga nisbatan "
"baholanishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:3
msgid "Framework Overview"
msgstr "Freymvork umumiy ko'rinishi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:6
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/mobile.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Kirish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:8
msgid ""
"The Odoo Javascript framework is a set of features/building blocks "
"provided by the ``web/`` addon to help build odoo applications running in"
" the browser. At the same time, the Odoo Javascript framework is a single"
" page application, usually known as the *web client* (available at the "
"url ``/web``)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo Javascript freymvorki brauzerda ishlaydigan odoo ilovalarini yaratishga "
"yordam berish uchun ``web/`` plagin tomonidan taqdim etiladigan "
"xususiyatlar/qurilish bloklari to'plamidir. Ayni paytda, Odoo Javascript "
"freymvorki odatda *web client* deb nomlanuvchi (``/web`` url manzilida "
"mavjud) bitta sahifali ilovadir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:13
msgid ""
"The web client started as an application made with a custom class and "
"widget system, but it is now transitioning to using native javascript "
"classes instead, and Owl as a component system. This explains why both "
"systems are currently in use in the codebase."
msgstr ""
"Veb-mijoz maxsus sinf va vidjet tizimi bilan yaratilgan ilova sifatida "
"boshlandi, lekin hozir u o'rniga mahalliy javascript sinflari va komponent "
"tizimi sifatida Owl ga o'tmoqda. Bu kod bazasida hozirda ikkala tizim ham "
"ishlatilayotganini tushuntiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:18
msgid ""
"From a high-level perspective, the web client is a single-page "
"application: it does not need to request a full page from the server each"
" time the user performs an action. Instead, it only requests what it "
"needs and then replaces/updates the current screen accordingly. Also, it "
"manages the url to keep it in sync with the current state."
msgstr ""
"Yuqori darajadagi nuqtai nazardan, veb-mijoz bitta sahifali ilova: "
"foydalanuvchi amal bajarganida serverdan har safar to'liq sahifa so'rash "
"shart emas. O'rniga, u faqat kerakli narsani so'raydi va joriy ekranni "
"mos ravishda almashtiradi/yangilaydi. Shuningdek, joriy holat bilan "
"sinxronlashtirib turish uchun url ni boshqaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:24
msgid ""
"The javascript framework (all or some parts) is also used in other "
"situations, such as the Odoo website or the point of sale. This reference"
" is mostly focused on the web client."
msgstr ""
"Javascript freymvorki (barchasi yoki ba'zi qismlari) Odoo veb-sayti yoki "
"sotish nuqtasi kabi boshqa holatlarda ham ishlatiladi. Ushbu ma'lumotnoma "
"asosan veb-mijozga qaratilgan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:30
msgid ""
"It is common in the Odoo ecosystem to see the words *frontend* and "
"*backend* as synonyms for the odoo website (public) and the web client, "
"respectively. This terminology is not to be confused with the more common"
" use of browser-code (frontend) and server (backend)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo ekotizimida *frontend* va *backend* so'zlarini mos ravishda odoo "
"veb-sayti (ommaviy) va veb-mijoz uchun sinonimlar sifatida ko'rish "
"odatiy holdir. Bu atamalar brauzer kodi (frontend) va server (backend) "
"ning ko'proq tarqalgan ishlatilishi bilan adashtirmaslik kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:37
msgid ""
"In this documentation, the word *component* always refers to new Owl "
"components, and *widget* refers to old Odoo widgets."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu hujjatda *komponent* so'zi har doim yangi Owl komponentlariga, "
"*vidjet* esa eski Odoo vidjetlariga ishora qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:42
msgid "All new development should be done in Owl, if possible!"
msgstr "Iloji bo'lsa, barcha yangi ishlanmalar Owl da amalga oshirilishi kerak!"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:45
msgid "Code structure"
msgstr "Kod tuzilmasi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:47
msgid ""
"The ``web/static/src`` folder contains all the ``web/`` javascript (and "
"css and templates) codebase. Here is a list of the most important "
"folders:"
msgstr ""
"``web/static/src`` papkasi barcha ``web/`` javascript (va css va shablonlar) "
"kod bazasini o'z ichiga oladi. Eng muhim papkalar ro'yxati:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:50
msgid "``core/`` most of the low level features"
msgstr "``core/`` past darajadagi xususiyatlarning aksariyati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:51
msgid "``fields/`` all field components"
msgstr "``fields/`` barcha maydon komponentlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:52
msgid "``views/`` all javascript views components (``form``, ``list``, ...)"
msgstr "``views/`` barcha javascript ko'rinish komponentlari (``form``, ``list``, ...)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:53
msgid "``search/`` control panel, search bar, search panel, ..."
msgstr "``search/`` boshqaruv paneli, qidiruv paneli, qidiruv bo'limi, ..."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:54
msgid ""
"``webclient/`` the web client specific code: navbar, user menu, action "
"service, ..."
msgstr ""
"``webclient/`` veb-mijozga xos kod: navbar, foydalanuvchi menyusi, amal "
"xizmati, ..."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:56
msgid ""
"The ``web/static/src`` is the root folder. Everything inside can simply "
"be imported by using the ``@web`` prefix. For example, here is how one "
"can import the ``memoize`` function located in "
"``web/static/src/core/utils/functions``:"
msgstr ""
"``web/static/src`` asosiy papkadir. Ichidagi hamma narsa ``@web`` prefiksi "
"yordamida import qilinishi mumkin. Masalan, ``web/static/src/core/utils/functions`` "
"da joylashgan ``memoize`` funksiyasini qanday import qilish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:65
msgid "WebClient Architecture"
msgstr "WebClient arxitekturasi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:67
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, the web client is an owl application. Here is a "
"slightly simplified version of its template:"
msgstr ""
"Yuqorida aytib o'tilganidek, veb-mijoz owl ilovasidir. Mana uning shablonining "
"biroz soddalashtirilgan versiyasi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:80
msgid ""
"As we can see, it basically is a wrapper for a navbar, the current action"
" and some additional components. The ``ActionContainer`` is a higher "
"order component that will display the current action controller (so, a "
"client action, or a specific view in the case of actions of type "
"``act_window``). Managing actions is a huge part of its work: the action "
"service keeps in memory a stack of all active actions (represented in the"
" breadcrumbs), and coordinates each change."
msgstr ""
"Ko'ringanidek, bu asosan navbar, joriy amal va ba'zi qo'shimcha "
"komponentlar uchun o'rash. ``ActionContainer`` joriy amal boshqaruvchisini "
"ko'rsatadigan yuqori tartibli komponentdir (ya'ni, ``act_window`` turi "
"amallar holatida mijoz amali yoki muayyan ko'rinish). Amallarni boshqarish "
"uning ishining katta qismini tashkil etadi: amal xizmati xotirada barcha "
"faol amallar to'plamini (breadcrumbs da ifodalangan) saqlaydi va har bir "
"o'zgarishni muvofiqlashtiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:88
msgid ""
"Another interesting thing to note is the ``MainComponentsContainer``: it "
"is simply a component that displays all components registered in the "
"``main_components`` registry. This is how other parts of the system can "
"extend the web client."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor qaratishga loyiq yana bir qiziqarli narsa ``MainComponentsContainer``: "
"bu shunchaki ``main_components`` registrida ro'yxatdan o'tgan barcha "
"komponentlarni ko'rsatadigan komponentdir. Bu tizimning boshqa qismlari "
"veb-mijozni qanday kengaytira olishidir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:98
msgid ""
"As an Owl application, the Odoo web client defines its own environment "
"(components can access it using ``this.env``). Here is a description of "
"what Odoo adds to the shared ``env`` object:"
msgstr ""
"Owl ilovasi sifatida, Odoo veb-mijozi o'z muhitini belgilaydi (komponentlar "
"unga ``this.env`` yordamida kirishlari mumkin). Mana Odoo umumiy ``env`` "
"ob'ektiga nimalarni qo'shishini tavsifi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:107
msgid "Value"
msgstr "Qiymat"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:109
msgid "required by Owl (contains all templates)"
msgstr "Owl tomonidan talab qilinadi (barcha shablonlarni o'z ichiga oladi)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:110
msgid "`bus`"
msgstr "`bus`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:111
msgid ""
":ref:`main bus <frontend/framework/bus>`, used to coordinate some generic"
" events"
msgstr ""
":ref:`asosiy avtobus <frontend/framework/bus>`, ba'zi umumiy hodisalarni "
"muvofiqlashtirish uchun ishlatiladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:112
msgid "`services`"
msgstr "`services`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:113
msgid ""
"all deployed :ref:`services <frontend/services>` (should usually be "
"accessed with the `useService` hook)"
msgstr ""
"barcha joylashtirilgan :ref:`xizmatlar <frontend/services>` (odatda "
"`useService` hook orqali kirilishi kerak)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:115
msgid "`debug`"
msgstr "`debug`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:116
msgid ""
"string. If non empty, the web client is in :ref:`debug mode "
"<frontend/framework/debug_mode>`"
msgstr ""
"satr. Agar bo'sh bo'lmasa, veb-mijoz :ref:`debug rejimida "
"<frontend/framework/debug_mode>`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:117
msgid "`_t`"
msgstr "`_t`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:118
msgid "translation function"
msgstr "tarjima funksiyasi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:119
msgid "`isSmall`"
msgstr "`isSmall`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:120
msgid ""
"boolean. If true, the web client is currently in mobile mode (screen "
"width <= 767px)"
msgstr ""
"mantiqiy. Agar to'g'ri bo'lsa, veb-mijoz hozirda mobil rejimda "
"(ekran kengligi <= 767px)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:122
msgid ""
"So, for example, to translate a string in a component (note: templates "
"are automatically translated, so no specific action is required in that "
"case), one can do this:"
msgstr ""
"Shunday qilib, masalan, komponentdagi satrni tarjima qilish uchun "
"(eslatma: shablonlar avtomatik tarjima qilinadi, shuning uchun bunday "
"holatda maxsus amal talab qilinmaydi), buni qilish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:133
msgid ""
"Having a reference to the environment is quite powerful, because it "
"provides access to all services. This is useful in many cases: for "
"example, user menu items are mostly defined as a string, and a function "
"taking the `env` as unique argument. This is enough to express all user "
"menu needs."
msgstr ""
"Muhitga havola qilish juda kuchli, chunki u barcha xizmatlarga kirish "
"imkonini beradi. Bu ko'p holatlarda foydali: masalan, foydalanuvchi menyu "
"elementlari asosan satr va `env` ni yagona argument sifatida qabul qiluvchi "
"funksiya sifatida aniqlanadi. Bu barcha foydalanuvchi menyu ehtiyojlarini "
"ifodalash uchun yetarli."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:139
msgid "Building Blocks"
msgstr "Qurilish bloklari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:141
msgid ""
"Most of the web client is built with a few types of abstractions: "
"registries, services, components and hooks."
msgstr ""
"Veb-mijozning aksariyati bir nechta abstraktsiya turlari bilan qurilgan: "
"registrlar, xizmatlar, komponentlar va hooklar."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:145
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/javascript_reference.rst:177
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/registries.rst:5
msgid "Registries"
msgstr "Registrlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:147
msgid ""
":ref:`Registries <frontend/registries>` are basically a simple key/value "
"mapping that stores some specific kind of objects. They are an important "
"part of the extensibility of the UI: once some object is registered, the "
"rest of the web client can use it. For example, the field registry "
"contains all field components (or widgets) that can be used in views."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Registrlar <frontend/registries>` asosan ma'lum turdagi ob'ektlarni "
"saqlaydigan oddiy kalit/qiymat xaritalashidir. Ular UI ning kengaytirilishi "
"muhim qismidir: bir marta ob'ekt ro'yxatdan o'tkazilgach, veb-mijozning "
"qolgan qismi undan foydalana oladi. Masalan, maydon registri ko'rinishlarda "
"ishlatilishi mumkin bo'lgan barcha maydon komponentlarini (yoki vidjetlarni) "
"o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:164
msgid ""
"Note that we import the main registry from ``@web/core/registry`` then "
"open the sub registry ``fields``."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, biz asosiy registrni ``@web/core/registry`` dan import "
"qilamiz, so'ngra ``fields`` alt registrini ochamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:168
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/javascript_reference.rst:217
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/services.rst:6
msgid "Services"
msgstr "Xizmatlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:170
msgid ""
":ref:`Services <frontend/services>` are long lived pieces of code that "
"provide a feature. They may be imported by components (with "
"``useService``) or by other services. Also, they can declare a set of "
"dependencies. In that sense, services are basically a DI (dependency "
"injection) system. For example, the ``notification`` service provides a "
"way to display a notification, or the ``rpc`` service is the proper way "
"to perform a request to the Odoo server."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Xizmatlar <frontend/services>` xususiyat taqdim etadigan uzoq muddatli "
"kod qismlaridir. Ular komponentlar tomonidan (``useService`` bilan) yoki "
"boshqa xizmatlar tomonidan import qilinishi mumkin. Shuningdek, ular "
"bog'liqliklar to'plamini e'lon qilishi mumkin. Shu ma'noda, xizmatlar "
"asosan DI (bog'liqlikni in'eksiya qilish) tizimidir. Masalan, ``notification`` "
"xizmati bildirishnoma ko'rsatish usulini taqdim etadi yoki ``rpc`` xizmati "
"Odoo serveriga so'rov qilishning to'g'ri usulidir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:177
msgid ""
"The following example registers a simple service that displays a "
"notification every 5 second:"
msgstr ""
"Quyidagi misol har 5 soniyada bildirishnoma ko'rsatadigan oddiy xizmatni "
"ro'yxatdan o'tkazadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:199
msgid "Components and Hooks"
msgstr "Komponentlar va Hooklar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:201
msgid ""
":ref:`Components <frontend/components>` and :ref:`hooks <frontend/hooks>`"
" are ideas coming from the `Owl component system "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/readme.md>`_. Odoo "
"components are simply owl components that are part of the web client."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Komponentlar <frontend/components>` va :ref:`hooklar <frontend/hooks>` "
"`Owl komponent tizimi <https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/readme.md>`_ "
"dan kelgan g'oyalardir. Odoo komponentlari shunchaki veb-mijozning bir "
"qismi bo'lgan owl komponentlaridir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:205
msgid ""
"`Hooks <https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_"
" are a way to factorize code, even if it depends on lifecycle. This is a "
"composable/functional way to inject a feature in a component. They can be"
" seen as a kind of mixin."
msgstr ""
"`Hooklar <https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_ "
"hayot sikliga bog'liq bo'lsa ham kodni faktorizatsiya qilish usulidir. "
"Bu komponentga xususiyat in'eksiya qilishning kompozitsiyalanuvchi/funksional "
"usulidir. Ularni bir turdagi mixin deb ko'rish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:224
msgid ""
"An important concept in the Odoo javascript is the *context*: it provides"
" a way for code to give more context to a function call or a rpc, so "
"other parts of the system can properly react to that information. In some"
" way, it is like a bag of information that is propagated everywhere. It "
"is useful in some situations, such as letting the Odoo server know that a"
" model rpc comes from a specific form view, or activating/disabling some "
"features in a component."
msgstr ""
"Odoo javascript da muhim tushuncha *kontekst*: u kodga funksiya chaqiruvi "
"yoki rpc ga ko'proq kontekst berish usulini taqdim etadi, shunda tizimning "
"boshqa qismlari bu ma'lumotga to'g'ri munosabat bildirishi mumkin. Bir "
"jihatdan, bu hamma joyga tarqaladigan ma'lumotlar sumkasiga o'xshaydi. "
"Bu ba'zi holatlarda foydali, masalan, Odoo serveriga model rpc ning muayyan "
"shakl ko'rinishidan kelayotganligini bildirishda yoki komponentdagi ba'zi "
"xususiyatlarni yoqish/o'chirish da."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:231
msgid ""
"There are two different contexts in the Odoo web client: the *user "
"context* and the *action context* (so, we should be careful when using "
"the word *context*: it could mean a different thing depending on the "
"situation)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo veb-mijozida ikki xil kontekst mavjud: *foydalanuvchi konteksti* va "
"*amal konteksti* (shuning uchun *kontekst* so'zini ishlatishda ehtiyot "
"bo'lish kerak: u vaziyatga qarab boshqa narsa anglatishi mumkin)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/framework_overview.rst:236
msgid ""
"The `context` object may be useful in many cases, but one should be "
"careful not to overuse it! Many problems can be solved in a standard way "
"without modifying the context."
msgstr ""
"`context` ob'ekti ko'p holatlarda foydali bo'lishi mumkin, lekin undan "
"haddan tashqari ko'p foydalanmaslik kerak! Ko'plab muammolarni kontekstni "
"o'zgartirmasdan standart tarzda hal qilish mumkin."

