#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:6
msgid "JavaScript Unit Testing"
msgstr "JavaScript birlik testlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:8
msgid ""
"Writing unit tests is as important as writing the code itself: it helps "
"to ensure that the code is written according to a given specification and"
" that it remains correct as it evolves."
msgstr ""
"Birlik testlarini yozish kodning o'zini yozish kabi muhim: u kodning "
"berilgan spetsifikatsiyaga muvofiq yozilganligini va u rivojlanar ekan "
"to'g'ri bo'lib qolishini ta'minlashga yordam beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:13
msgid "Testing Framework"
msgstr "Sinov framework i"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:15
msgid ""
"Testing the code starts with a testing framework. The framework provides "
"a level of abstraction that makes it possible to write tests in an easy "
"and efficient way. It also provides a set of tools to run the tests, make"
" assertions and report the results."
msgstr ""
"Kodni sinovdan o'tkazish sinov framework i bilan boshlanadi. Framework "
"testlarni oson va samarali yozishni mumkin qiluvchi abstraksiya darajasini "
"taqdim etadi. U shuningdek testlarni ishga tushirish, ta'kidlar yaratish "
"va natijalarni hisobot qilish uchun vositalar to'plamini ham taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:20
msgid ""
"Odoo developers use a home-grown testing framework called :abbr:`HOOT "
"(Hierarchically Organized Odoo Tests)`. The main reason for using a "
"custom framework is that it allows us to extend it based on our needs "
"(tags system, mocking of global objects, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo dasturchilari :abbr:`HOOT (Hierarchically Organized Odoo Tests)` "
"deb nomlangan o'z yaratgan sinov framework i dan foydalanadi. Maxsus "
"framework dan foydalanishning asosiy sababi shundaki, u bizga o'z "
"ehtiyojlarimizga qarab uni kengaytirishga imkon beradi (teglar tizimi, "
"global ob'ektlarni taqlid qilish va boshqalar)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:24
msgid ""
"On top of that framework we have built a set of tools to help us write "
"tests for the web client (`web_test_helpers`), and a mock server to "
"simulate the server side (`mock_server`)."
msgstr ""
"Shu framework ustiga biz veb-mijoz uchun testlar yozishga yordam beruvchi "
"vositalar to'plamini (`web_test_helpers`) va server tomonini simulyatsiya "
"qiluvchi taqlid serverini (`mock_server`) yaratdik."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:27
msgid ""
"You can find links to the reference of each of these parts below, as well"
" as a section filled with examples and best practices for writing tests."
msgstr ""
"Quyida ushbu qismlarning har birining havolalarini, shuningdek testlar "
"yozish uchun misollar va eng yaxshi amaliyotlar bilan to'ldirilgan "
"bo'limni ham topishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:33
msgid ""
"Before learning how to write tests, it is good to start with the basics. "
"The following steps will ensure that your test files are properly picked "
"up by the test runner."
msgstr ""
"Testlarni qanday yozishni o'rganishdan oldin asoslardan boshlash yaxshi. "
"Quyidagi qadamlar test fayllaringiz test ishga tushiruvchisi tomonidan "
"to'g'ri tanlanishini ta'minlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:36
msgid ""
"Note that in existing addons, most of these steps can be skipped since "
"the proper folder structure and asset bundles are probably set up."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, mavjud qo'shimchalarda to'g'ri papka tuzilmasi va asset "
"to'plamlari allaqachon o'rnatilgan bo'lgani sababli bu qadamlarning "
"aksariyatini o'tkazib yuborish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:39
msgid "Writing files in the right **place**:"
msgstr "Fayllarni to'g'ri **joyga** yozish:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:41
msgid ""
"All JavaScript test files should be put under the `/static/tests` folder "
"of the related addon (e.g. :file:`/web/static/tests/env.test.js`)."
msgstr ""
"Barcha JavaScript test fayllari tegishli qo'shimchaning `/static/tests` "
"papkasiga joylashtirilishi kerak (masalan, :file:`/web/static/tests/env.test.js`)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:44
msgid "Using the right **name**:"
msgstr "To'g'ri **nom** ishlatish:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:46
msgid ""
"Test files must end with :file:`.test.js`. This is not only a convention,"
" but a requirement for test files to be picked up by the runner. All "
"other JavaScript files will be interpreted either as production code "
"(i.e. the code to be tested), or as test helper files (such as "
"`web_test_helpers "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/tests/web_test_helpers.js>`_)."
msgstr ""
"Test fayllari :file:`.test.js` bilan tugashi kerak. Bu nafaqat odatiy "
"qoida, balki test fayllarining ishga tushiruvchi tomonidan olinishi "
"uchun talab. Boshqa barcha JavaScript fayllari ishlab chiqarish kodi "
"(ya'ni sinov qilinishi kerak bo'lgan kod) yoki test yordamchi fayllari "
"sifatida talqin qilinadi (masalan, `web_test_helpers "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/tests/web_test_helpers.js>`_)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:52
msgid ""
"It is to be noted that there is an exception for :file:`.hoot.js` files, "
"which are not considered as test files, but as global modules for the "
"whole test run, while other JavaScript modules are re-created for each "
"test suite. Since the same instance of these modules will be running for "
"the whole test run, they follow strict constraints, such as restricted "
"imports, or advanced memory management techniques to ensure no side-"
"effects are affecting tests."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, :file:`.hoot.js` fayllari uchun istisno mavjud, ular "
"test fayllari sifatida emas, balki butun test ishga tushirish uchun "
"global modullar sifatida ko'riladi, boshqa JavaScript modullari esa "
"har bir test to'plami uchun qayta yaratiladi. Bu modullarning bir xil "
"nusxasi butun test ishga tushirish uchun ishlashi sababli, ular cheklangan "
"importlar yoki testlarga yon ta'sirlar ta'sir qilmasligi uchun kengaytirilgan "
"xotira boshqaruvi usullari kabi qat'iy cheklishlarga amal qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:59
msgid "Calling the files in the right **bundle**:"
msgstr "Fayllarni to'g'ri **to'plam** da chaqirish:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:61
msgid ""
"Test files, added in the right folder, must be included in the "
"`web.assets_unit_tests` bundle. For ease of use, this can be done with "
"glob syntax to import all test and test helper files:"
msgstr ""
"To'g'ri papkaga qo'shilgan test fayllari `web.assets_unit_tests` "
"to'plamiga kiritilishi kerak. Qulay ishlatish uchun bu barcha test va "
"test yordamchi fayllarini import qilish uchun glob sintaksisi bilan "
"amalga oshirilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:72
msgid "Heading to the right **URL**:"
msgstr "To'g'ri **URL** ga o'tish:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:74
msgid "To run tests, you can then go to the `/web/tests` URL."
msgstr "Testlarni ishga tushirish uchun `/web/tests` URL ga o'tishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:77
msgid ""
"This page can be accessed through :icon:`fa-bug` :menuselection:`Debug "
"menu --> Run Unit Tests`."
msgstr ""
"Bu sahifaga :icon:`fa-bug` :menuselection:`Nosozliklarni tuzatish menyusi "
"--> Birlik testlarini ishga tushirish` orqali kirish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:80
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:143
msgid "Writing tests"
msgstr "Testlar yozish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing.rst:82
msgid ""
"After creating and including test files, it is time to write tests. You "
"may refer to the following documentation sections to learn about the "
"testing framework."
msgstr ""
"Test fayllarini yaratib va kiritgandan so'ng, testlar yozish vaqti keldi. "
"Sinov framework i haqida bilish uchun quyidagi hujjat bo'limlariga "
"murojaat qilishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:3
msgid "HOOT"
msgstr "HOOT"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:8
msgid ""
":abbr:`HOOT (Hierarchically Organized Odoo Tests)` is a testing framework"
" written with Owl whose key features are:"
msgstr ""
":abbr:`HOOT (Hierarchically Organized Odoo Tests)` — Owl bilan yozilgan "
"sinov framework bo'lib, asosiy xususiyatlari quyidagilardir:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:11
msgid "to register and run tests and test suites;"
msgstr "testlar va test to'plamlarini ro'yxatdan o'tkazish va ishga tushirish;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:12
msgid "to display an intuitive interface to view and filter test results;"
msgstr "test natijalarini ko'rish va filtrlash uchun intuitiv interfeys ko'rsatish;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:13
msgid "to provide ways to interact with the DOM to simulate user actions;"
msgstr "foydalanuvchi harakatlarini simulyatsiya qilish uchun DOM bilan ishlash usullarini taqdim etish;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:14
msgid "to provide low-level helpers allowing to mock various global objects."
msgstr "turli global ob'ektlarni taqlid qilish uchun past darajali yordamchilarni taqdim etish."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:16
msgid ""
"As such, it has been integrated as a :file:`lib/` in the Odoo codebase "
"and exports 2 main modules:"
msgstr ""
"Shuning uchun u Odoo kod bazasida :file:`lib/` sifatida integratsiya "
"qilingan va 2 ta asosiy modulni eksport qiladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:18
msgid ":file:`@odoo/hoot-dom`: (can be used in tours) helpers to:"
msgstr ":file:`@odoo/hoot-dom`: (tourlarda ishlatilishi mumkin) quyidagi yordamchilar:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:20
msgid "**interact** with the DOM, such as :js:meth:`click` and :js:meth:`press`;"
msgstr "DOM bilan **ishlash**, masalan :js:meth:`click` va :js:meth:`press`;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:21
msgid ""
"**query** elements from the DOM, such as :js:meth:`queryAll` and "
":js:meth:`waitFor`;"
msgstr ""
"DOM dan elementlarni **so'rash**, masalan :js:meth:`queryAll` va "
":js:meth:`waitFor`;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:23
msgid ""
":file:`@odoo/hoot`: (only to be used in unit tests) all the test "
"framework features:"
msgstr ""
":file:`@odoo/hoot`: (faqat birlik testlarida ishlatilishi kerak) barcha sinov "
"framework xususiyatlari:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:25
msgid "`test`, `describe` and `expect`"
msgstr "`test`, `describe` va `expect`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:26
msgid "test hooks like `after` and `afterEach`"
msgstr "`after` va `afterEach` kabi test hooklari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:27
msgid "fixture handling with `getFixture`"
msgstr "`getFixture` bilan fixture boshqaruvi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:28
msgid "date and time handling like `mockDate` or `advanceTime`"
msgstr "`mockDate` yoki `advanceTime` kabi sana va vaqtni boshqarish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:29
msgid ""
"mocking network responses through :js:meth:`mockFetch` or "
":js:meth:`mockWebSocket`"
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`mockFetch` yoki :js:meth:`mockWebSocket` orqali tarmoq javoblarini taqlid qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:30
msgid "every helper exported by :file:`@odoo/hoot-dom`"
msgstr ":file:`@odoo/hoot-dom` tomonidan eksport qilingan barcha yordamchilar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:33
msgid ""
"This section of the documentation is not meant to list *all* helpers "
"available in Hoot (the full list can be found in the `@odoo/hoot "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/lib/hoot/hoot.js>`_"
" module itself). The goal here is to showcase the most used helpers and "
"to justify some of the decisions that have led to the current shape of "
"the testing framework."
msgstr ""
"Hujjatning ushbu bo'limi Hoot da mavjud bo'lgan *barcha* yordamchilarni "
"sanab o'tish maqsadida emas (to'liq ro'yxatni `@odoo/hoot "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/lib/hoot/hoot.js>`_"
" modulining o'zida topish mumkin). Bu yerda maqsad eng ko'p ishlatiladigan "
"yordamchilarni namoyish etish va sinov framework ining hozirgi ko'rinishiga "
"olib kelgan ba'zi qarorlarni asoslashdir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:41
msgid ""
"In Odoo, frontend unit tests can be run by going to the `/web/tests` URL."
" Most of the setup for calling the test runner is already in place:"
msgstr ""
"Odoo da frontend birlik testlarini `/web/tests` URL ga o'tib ishga tushirish "
"mumkin. Test ishlovchisini chaqirish uchun sozlamalarning ko'p qismi allaqachon mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:44
msgid ""
"the `web.assets_unit_tests` bundle is already defined, and picks up all "
"tests defined in most addons;"
msgstr ""
"`web.assets_unit_tests` to'plami allaqachon aniqlangan va aksariyat addonlarda "
"belgilangan barcha testlarni oladi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:47
msgid ""
"a :file:`start.hoot.js` file takes care of calling the test runner with "
"its exported `start` entry point function."
msgstr ""
":file:`start.hoot.js` fayli eksport qilingan `start` kirish nuqtasi funksiyasi "
"bilan test ishlovchisini chaqirishni ta'minlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:50
msgid ""
"When going to the test page, tests will be run sequentially and the "
"results will be displayed in the console and in the GUI (if not running "
"in `headless` mode)."
msgstr ""
"Test sahifasiga o'tilganda, testlar ketma-ket ishga tushiriladi va natijalar "
"konsolda va grafik interfeysda ko'rsatiladi (`headless` rejimida ishlamasa)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:54
msgid "Runner options"
msgstr "Ishlovchi parametrlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:56
msgid "The runner can be configured either:"
msgstr "Ishlovchini quyidagi usullarda sozlash mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:58
msgid ""
"through the interface (with the configuration dropdown and the search "
"bar);"
msgstr "interfeys orqali (konfiguratsiya ochiladigan ro'yxati va qidiruv paneli bilan);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:59
msgid ""
"or through the URL query parameters (e.g. `?headless` to run in headless "
"mode)."
msgstr "yoki URL so'rov parametrlari orqali (masalan, `?headless` headless rejimida ishga tushirish uchun)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:61
msgid "Here is the list of available options for the runner:"
msgstr "Ishlovchi uchun mavjud parametrlar ro'yxati:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:65
msgid "`bail`"
msgstr "`bail`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:64
msgid ""
"Amount of failed tests after which the test runner will be stopped. A "
"falsy value (including 0) means that the runner should never be aborted. "
"(default: `0`)"
msgstr ""
"Test ishlovchisi to'xtatilishidan oldin muvaffaqiyatsiz testlar soni. Noto'g'ri "
"qiymat (0 ni o'z ichiga olgan holda) ishlovchi hech qachon to'xtatilmasligini bildiradi. "
"(standart: `0`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:69
msgid "`debugTest`"
msgstr "`debugTest`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:68
msgid ""
"Same as the `FILTER_SCHEMA.test` filter, while also putting the test "
"runner in \"debug\" mode. See `TestRunner.debug` for more info. (default:"
" `false`)"
msgstr ""
"`FILTER_SCHEMA.test` filteri bilan bir xil, lekin test ishlovchisini ham "
"\"debug\" rejimiga o'tkazadi. Ko'proq ma'lumot uchun `TestRunner.debug` ga qarang. "
"(standart: `false`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:73
msgid "`fps`"
msgstr "`fps`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:72
msgid ""
"Sets the value of frames per seconds (this will be transformed to "
"milliseconds and used in `advanceFrame`)"
msgstr ""
"Soniyada kadrlar qiymatini belgilaydi (bu millisekundlarga o'zgartiriladi "
"va `advanceFrame` da ishlatiladi)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:77
msgid "`filter`"
msgstr "`filter`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:76
msgid ""
"Search string that will filter matching tests/suites, based on their full"
" name (including their parent suite(s)) and their tags. (default: `\"\"`)"
msgstr ""
"Mos testlar/to'plamlarni filtrlash uchun qidiruv satri, ularning to'liq nomi "
"(ota-to'plam(lar)ni o'z ichiga olgan holda) va teglari asosida. (standart: `\"\"`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:81
msgid "`frameRate`"
msgstr "`frameRate`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:80
msgid ""
"*Estimated* amount of frames rendered per second, used when mocking "
"animation frames. (default: `60` fps)"
msgstr ""
"Animatsiya kadrlarini taqlid qilishda ishlatiladigan, soniyada ko'rsatiladigan "
"kadrlarning *taxminiy* soni. (standart: `60` fps)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:84
msgid "`fun`"
msgstr "`fun`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:84
msgid "Lightens the mood. (default: `false`)"
msgstr "Kayfiyatni ko'taradi. (standart: `false`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:87
msgid "`headless`"
msgstr "`headless`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:87
msgid "Whether to render the test runner user interface. (default: `false`)"
msgstr "Test yuklovchi foydalanuvchi interfeysini ko'rsatish kerakmi. (standart: `false`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:90
msgid ""
"IDs of the suites OR tests to run exclusively. The ID of a job is "
"generated deterministically based on its full name."
msgstr ""
"Faqat ishlatilishi kerak bo'lgan to'plam yoki testlarning IDlari. Ish IDsi "
"to'liq nomiga asoslanib deterministik tarzda yaratiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:99
msgid "`loglevel`"
msgstr "`loglevel`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:94
msgid ""
"Log level used by the test runner. The higher the level, the more logs "
"will be displayed:"
msgstr ""
"Test yuklovchi tomonidan ishlatiladigan jurnal darajasi. Daraja qancha yuqori "
"bo'lsa, shuncha ko'p jurnallar ko'rsatiladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:96
msgid "`0`: only runner logs are displayed (default)"
msgstr "`0`: faqat yuklovchi jurnallari ko'rsatiladi (standart)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:97
msgid "`1`: all suite results are also logged"
msgstr "`1`: barcha to'plam natijalari ham jurnalga yoziladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:98
msgid "`2`: all test results are also logged"
msgstr "`2`: barcha test natijalari ham jurnalga yoziladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:99
msgid "`3`: debug information for each test is also logged"
msgstr "`3`: har bir test uchun debug ma'lumotlari ham jurnalga yoziladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:102
msgid ""
"Whether the test runner must be manually started after page load "
"(defaults to starting automatically). (default: `false`)"
msgstr ""
"Sahifa yuklanganidan keyin test yuklovchi qo'lda ishga tushirilishi kerakmi "
"(standart: avtomatik ishga tushadi). (standart: `false`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:107
msgid "`notrycatch`"
msgstr "`notrycatch`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:106
msgid ""
"Removes the safety of `try .. catch` statements around each test's run "
"function to let errors bubble to the browser. (default: `false`)"
msgstr ""
"Xatolarning brauzerga ko'tarilishiga imkon berish uchun har bir test ishlatish "
"funksiyasi atrofidagi `try .. catch` operatorlarining xavfsizligini olib tashlaydi. "
"(standart: `false`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:114
msgid "`order`"
msgstr "`order`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:110
msgid "Determines the order of test execution:"
msgstr "Test bajarilish tartibini belgilaydi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:112
msgid "`\"fifo\"`: tests will be run sequentially as declared in the file system;"
msgstr "`\"fifo\"`: testlar fayl tizimida e'lon qilingan tartibda ketma-ket ishlatiladi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:113
msgid "`\"lifo\"`: tests will be run sequentially in the reverse order;"
msgstr "`\"lifo\"`: testlar teskari tartibda ketma-ket ishlatiladi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:114
msgid "`\"random\"`: shuffles tests and suites within their parent suite."
msgstr "`\"random\"`: ota to'plam ichidagi testlar va to'plamlarni tasodifiy tartibda aralashtiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:122
msgid "`preset`"
msgstr "`preset`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:117
msgid ""
"Environment in which the test runner is running. This parameter is used "
"to determine the default value of other features, namely:"
msgstr ""
"Test yuklovchi ishlayotgan muhit. Bu parametr boshqa xususiyatlarning "
"standart qiymatini aniqlash uchun ishlatiladi, jumladan:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:120
msgid "the user agent;"
msgstr "foydalanuvchi agenti;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:121
msgid "touch support;"
msgstr "sezgir ekran qo'llab-quvvatlashi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:122
msgid "expected size of the viewport."
msgstr "ko'rinish oynasining kutilayotgan o'lchami."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:125
msgid "`showdetail`"
msgstr "`showdetail`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:125
msgid ""
"Determines how the failed tests must be unfolded in the UI. (default: "
"`\"first-fail\"`)"
msgstr ""
"Muvaffaqiyatsiz testlarning interfeysda qanday ko'rsatilishini belgilaydi. "
"(standart: `\"first-fail\"`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:128
msgid "`tag`"
msgstr "`tag`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:128
msgid ""
"Tag names of tests and suites to run exclusively (case insensitive). "
"(default: empty)"
msgstr ""
"Faqat ishlatilishi kerak bo'lgan test va to'plamlarning teg nomlari "
"(katta-kichik harf farqsiz). (standart: bo'sh)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:132
msgid "`timeout`"
msgstr "`timeout`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:131
msgid ""
"Duration (in milliseconds) at the end of which a test will automatically "
"fail. (default: `5` seconds)"
msgstr ""
"Test avtomatik ravishda muvaffaqiyatsiz tugaydigan davomiylik "
"(millisekundlarda). (standart: `5` soniya)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:135
msgid ""
"When selecting tests and suites to run, an implicit `OR` is applied "
"between the *including* filters. This means that adding more inclusive "
"filters will result in more tests being run. This applies to the "
"`filter`, `id` and `tag` filters (*excluding* filters however will remove"
" matching tests from the list of tests to run)."
msgstr ""
"Ishlatilacak testlar va to'plamlarni tanlashda, *qo'shuvchi* filtrlar "
"orasiga yashirin `OR` qo'llaniladi. Bu shuni anglatadiki, qo'shimcha "
"qo'shuvchi filtrlar qo'shish ko'proq testlarning ishlashiga olib keladi. "
"Bu `filter`, `id` va `tag` filtrlariga tegishli (*istisno qiluvchi* "
"filtrlar esa mos kelgan testlarni ishlatilacak testlar ro'yxatidan olib tashlaydi)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:146
msgid "Test"
msgstr "Test"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:148
msgid ""
"Writing a test can be very straightforward, as it is just a matter of "
"calling the `test` function with a name and a function that will contain "
"the test logic."
msgstr ""
"Test yozish juda oddiy bo'lishi mumkin, chunki bu shunchaki `test` funksiyasini "
"nom va test mantig'ini o'z ichiga oladigan funksiya bilan chaqirishdan iborat."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:151
msgid "Here is a simple example:"
msgstr "Mana oddiy misol:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:163
msgid "Describe"
msgstr "Describe"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:165
msgid ""
"Most of the time, tests are not that simple. They often require some "
"setup and teardown, and sometimes they need to be grouped together in a "
"suite. This is where the `describe` function comes into play."
msgstr ""
"Ko'pincha, testlar shunchalik oddiy bo'lmaydi. Ular ko'p hollarda "
"sozlash va tozalashni talab qiladi, ba'zan esa to'plamda birlashtirilishi "
"kerak bo'ladi. Ana shu yerda `describe` funksiyasi ishga tushadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:169
msgid "Here is how you would declare a suite and a test within it:"
msgstr "Mana to'plam va uning ichidagi testni qanday e'lon qilish mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:182
msgid ""
"In Odoo, all test files are run in an isolated environment and are "
"wrapped within a global `describe` block (with the name of the suite "
"being the *path* of the test file)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo'da barcha test fayllari izolyatsiya qilingan muhitda ishlatiladi va "
"global `describe` bloki ichiga o'raladi (to'plam nomi test faylining "
"*yo'li* bo'ladi)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:185
msgid ""
"With that in mind you should not need to declare a suite in your test "
"files, although you can still declare sub-suites in the same file if you "
"still want to split the file's suite, for organization or tagging "
"purposes."
msgstr ""
"Buni hisobga olib, test fayllaringizda to'plam e'lon qilishingiz shart "
"emas, biroq tashkiliy maqsadlar yoki teg qo'shish uchun faylning to'plamini "
"bo'lishni xohlasangiz, bir xil faylda ichki to'plamlarni e'lon qilishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:192
msgid "Expect"
msgstr "Expect"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:194
msgid ""
"The `expect` function is the main assertion function of the framework. It"
" is used to assert that a value or an object is what it is expected to be"
" or in the state it is supposed to be. To do so, it provides a few "
"modifiers and a wide range of matchers."
msgstr ""
"`expect` funksiyasi freymvorkning asosiy tasdiqlash funksiyasidir. U "
"qiymat yoki ob'ektning kutilganidek yoki bo'lishi kerak bo'lgan holatda "
"ekanligini tasdiqlash uchun ishlatiladi. Buning uchun u bir necha "
"modifikator va keng matchers to'plamini taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:201
msgid "Modifiers"
msgstr "Modifikatorlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:203
msgid ""
"An `expect` modifier is a getter that returns another set of *altered* "
"matchers that will behave in a specific way."
msgstr ""
"`expect` modifikatori ma'lum bir tarzda ishlaydigan boshqa *o'zgartirilgan* "
"matcherlar to'plamini qaytaruvchi getterdir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:211
msgid "`not`"
msgstr "`not`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:207
msgid ""
"Inverts the result of the following matcher: it will succeed if the "
"matcher fails."
msgstr ""
"Keyingi matcherning natijasini teskari aylantiradi: agar matcher "
"muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lsa, u muvaffaqiyatli bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:219
msgid "`resolves`"
msgstr "`resolves`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:214
msgid ""
"Waits for the value (`Promise`) to be *\"resolved\"* before running the "
"following matcher with the resolved value."
msgstr ""
"Hal qilingan qiymat bilan keyingi matcherni ishlatishdan oldin qiymatning "
"(`Promise`) *\"resolved\"* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:227
msgid "`rejects`"
msgstr "`rejects`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:222
msgid ""
"Waits for the value (`Promise`) to be *\"rejected\"* before running the "
"following matcher with the rejected reason."
msgstr ""
"Rad etilgan sabab bilan keyingi matcherni ishlatishdan oldin qiymatning "
"(`Promise`) *\"rejected\"* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:230
msgid ""
"The `resolves` and `rejects` modifiers are only available when the value "
"is a promise, and will return a promise that will resolve once the "
"assertion is done."
msgstr ""
"`resolves` va `rejects` modifikatorlari faqat qiymat promise bo'lganda "
"mavjud bo'ladi va tasdiqlash tugagandan so'ng hal bo'ladigan promise "
"qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:236
msgid "Regular matchers"
msgstr "Oddiy matcherlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:238
msgid ""
"The matchers dictate what to do on the value being tested. Some will take"
" that value as-is, while others will *transform* that value before "
"performing the assertion on it (i.e. DOM matchers)."
msgstr ""
"Matcherlar sinab ko'rilayotgan qiymat bilan nima qilishni belgilaydi. "
"Ba'zilari qiymatni o'ziga xos holda qabul qiladi, boshqalari esa "
"tasdiqlashdan oldin qiymatni *o'zgartiradi* (masalan, DOM matcherlari)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:242
msgid ""
"Note that the last argument parameter of all matchers is an optional "
"dictionary with additional options, in which a custom assertion `message`"
" can be given for added context/specificity."
msgstr ""
"Barcha matcherlarning oxirgi argument parametri qo'shimcha ixtiyoriy "
"lug'at ekanligini e'tiborda tuting, unda qo'shimcha kontekst/aniqlik "
"uchun maxsus tasdiqlash `message` berilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:245
msgid ""
"The first list of matchers are primitive or object based and are the most"
" common ones:"
msgstr ""
"Matcherlarning birinchi ro'yxati primitiv yoki ob'ektga asoslangan va "
"eng keng tarqalgan matcherlardir:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:249
msgid "Expects the received value to be *strictly equal* to the `expected` value."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat `expected` qiymatiga *qat'iy teng* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:253
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:270
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:389
msgid "`expected`: `any`"
msgstr "`expected`: `any`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:254
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:291
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:308
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:324
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:340
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:356
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:373
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:390
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:407
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:431
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:449
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:465
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:507
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:523
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:538
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:550
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:568
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:584
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:602
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:660
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:700
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:743
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`options`: `{ message?: string }`"
msgstr "`options`: `{ message?: string }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:265
msgid ""
"Expects the received value to be *close to* the `expected` value up to a "
"given amount of digits (default is 2)."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan raqamlar sonigacha (standart 2) `expected` "
"qiymatiga *yaqin* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:271
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`options`: `{ message?: string, digits?: number }`"
msgstr "`options`: `{ message?: string, digits?: number }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:282
msgid "Expects the received value to be empty:"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat bo'sh bo'lishini kutadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:284
msgid "`iterable`: no items"
msgstr "`iterable`: elementlar yo'q"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:285
msgid "`object`: no keys"
msgstr "`object`: kalitlar yo'q"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:286
msgid "`node`: no content (i.e. no value or text)"
msgstr "`node`: kontent yo'q (ya'ni qiymat yoki matn yo'q)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:287
msgid "anything else: falsy value (`false`, `0`, `\"\"`, `null`, `undefined`)"
msgstr "boshqa narsalar: soxta qiymat (`false`, `0`, `\"\"`, `null`, `undefined`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:303
msgid "Expects the received value to be *strictly greater* than `min`."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat `min` dan *qat'iy katta* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:307
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:371
msgid "`min`: `number`"
msgstr "`min`: `number`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:319
msgid "Expects the received value to be an instance of the given `cls`."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan `cls` sinifining namunasi bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:323
msgid "`cls`: `Function`"
msgstr "`cls`: `Function`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:335
msgid "Expects the received value to be *strictly less* than `max`."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat `max` dan *qat'iy kichik* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:339
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:372
msgid "`max`: `number`"
msgstr "`max`: `number`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:351
msgid "Expects the received value to be of the given `type`."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan `type` turiga tegishli bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:355
msgid "`type`: `string`"
msgstr "`type`: `string`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:367
msgid ""
"Expects the received value to be *between* `min` and `max` (both "
"inclusive)."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan qiymat `min` va `max` *orasida* bo'lishini kutadi "
"(ikkalasi ham kiritilgan holda)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:385
msgid "Expects the received value to be *deeply equal* to the `expected` value."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat `expected` qiymatiga *chuqur teng* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:401
msgid ""
"Expects the received value to have a length of the given `length`. "
"Received value can be any `Iterable` or `Object`."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan `length` uzunligiga ega bo'lishini kutadi. "
"Qabul qilingan qiymat istalgan `Iterable` yoki `Object` bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:406
msgid "`length`: `number`"
msgstr "`length`: `number`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:420
msgid "Expects the received value to include an `item` of a given shape."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan shakldagi `item` ni o'z ichiga olishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:422
msgid ""
"Received value can be an iterable or an object (in case it is an object, "
"the `item` should be a key or a tuple representing an entry in that "
"object)."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan qiymat takrorlanadigan yoki ob'ekt bo'lishi mumkin (ob'ekt "
"bo'lgan taqdirda, `item` ushbu ob'ektdagi yozuvni ifodalovchi kalit yoki "
"kortej bo'lishi kerak)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:425
msgid ""
"Note that it is NOT a strict comparison: the item will be matched for "
"deep equality against each item of the iterable."
msgstr ""
"Bu QATIY taqqoslash emasligini e'tiborda tuting: element takrorlanadigan "
"to'plamdagi har bir element bilan chuqur tenglik uchun solishtiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:430
msgid "`item`: `any`"
msgstr "`item`: `any`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:444
msgid "Expects the received value to match the given `matcher`."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan qiymat berilgan `matcher` ga mos kelishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:448
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:464
msgid "`matcher`: `string | number | RegExp`"
msgstr "`matcher`: `string | number | RegExp`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:460
msgid "Expects the received `Function` to throw an error after being called."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Function` chaqirilgandan keyin xato chiqarishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:476
msgid "DOM matchers"
msgstr "DOM matcherlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:478
msgid ""
"This next list of matchers are node-based and are used to assert the "
"state of a node or a list of nodes. They generally take a :ref:`custom "
"selector <hoot/custom-dom-selectors>` as the argument of the `expect` "
"function (although a `Node` or an iterable of `Node` is also accepted)."
msgstr ""
"Keyingi matcherlar ro'yxati tugunga asoslangan va tugun yoki tugunlar "
"ro'yxatining holatini tasdiqlash uchun ishlatiladi. Ular odatda `expect` "
"funksiyasining argumenti sifatida :ref:`maxsus selektor <hoot/custom-dom-"
"selectors>` ni qabul qiladi (garchi `Node` yoki `Node` takrorlanuvchisi "
"ham qabul qilinsa ham)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:485
msgid ""
"Expects the received `Target` to be `\"checked\"`, or to be "
"`\"indeterminate\"` if the homonymous option is set to `true`."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` `\"checked\"` bo'lishini, yoki nomdosh variant "
"`true` ga o'rnatilgan bo'lsa `\"indeterminate\"` bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:490
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`options`: `{ message?: string, indeterminate?: boolean }`"
msgstr "`options`: `{ message?: string, indeterminate?: boolean }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:500
msgid "Expects the received `Target` to be *\"displayed\"*, meaning that:"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` *\"ko'rsatilgan\"* bo'lishini kutadi, ya'ni:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:502
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:544
msgid "it has a bounding box;"
msgstr "uning chegara qutisi mavjud;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:503
msgid "it is contained in the root document."
msgstr "u ildiz hujjatida joylashgan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:518
msgid ""
"Expects the received `Target` to be *\"enabled\"*, meaning that it "
"matches the `:enabled` pseudo-selector."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` *\"yoqilgan\"* bo'lishini kutadi, ya'ni u "
"`:enabled` pseudo-selektoriga mos keladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:534
msgid "Expects the received `Target` to be *\"focused\"* in its owner document."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` egasi hujjatida *\"fokusda\"* bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:542
msgid "Expects the received `Target` to be *\"visible\"*, meaning that:"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` *\"ko'rinadigan\"* bo'lishini kutadi, ya'ni:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:545
msgid "it is contained in the root document;"
msgstr "u ildiz hujjatida joylashgan;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:546
msgid "it is not hidden by CSS properties."
msgstr "u CSS xossalari tomonidan yashirilmagan."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:561
msgid ""
"Expects the received `Target` to have the given attribute set, and for "
"that attribute value to match the given `value` if any."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` berilgan atribut o'rnatilganiga ega bo'lishini va "
"agar berilgan bo'lsa, ushbu atribut qiymatining berilgan `value` ga mos "
"kelishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:566
msgid "`attribute`: `string`"
msgstr "`attribute`: `string`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:567
msgid "`value`: `string | number | RegExp`"
msgstr "`value`: `string | number | RegExp`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:579
msgid "Expects the received `Target` to have the given class name(s)."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` berilgan sinf nomi(larini) ga ega bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:583
msgid "`className`: `string | string[]`"
msgstr "`className`: `string | string[]`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:595
msgid ""
"Expects the received `Target` to contain exactly `amount` element(s). "
"Note that the `amount` parameter can be omitted, in which case the "
"function will expect *at least* one element."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` aynan `amount` ta element(lar) ni o'z ichiga "
"olishini kutadi. `amount` parametrini tushirib qoldirish mumkinligini "
"e'tiborda tuting, bunday holda funksiya *kamida* bitta elementni kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:601
msgid "`amount`: `number`"
msgstr "`amount`: `number`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:614
msgid ""
"Expects the `innerHTML` of the received `Target` to match the `expected` "
"value (upon formatting)."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` ning `innerHTML` i `expected` qiymatiga "
"(formatlangandan so'ng) mos kelishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:619
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:637
msgid "`expected`: `string | RegExp`"
msgstr "`expected`: `string | RegExp`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:620
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:638
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"`options`: `{ message?: string, type?: \"html\" | \"xml\", tabSize?: "
"number, keepInlineTextNodes?: boolean }`"
msgstr ""
"`options`: `{ message?: string, type?: \"html\" | \"xml\", tabSize?: "
"number, keepInlineTextNodes?: boolean }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:632
msgid ""
"Expects the `outerHTML` of the received `Target` to match the `expected` "
"value (upon formatting)."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` ning `outerHTML` i `expected` qiymatiga "
"(formatlangandan so'ng) mos kelishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:652
msgid ""
"Expects the received `Target` to have its given property value match the "
"given `value`. If no value is given: the matcher will instead check that "
"the given property exists on the target."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` ning berilgan xossa qiymati berilgan `value` ga "
"mos kelishini kutadi. Agar qiymat berilmasa: matcher o'rniga berilgan "
"xossaning maqsadda mavjudligini tekshiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:658
msgid "`property`: `string`"
msgstr "`property`: `string`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:659
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:742
msgid "`value`: `any`"
msgstr "`value`: `any`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:672
msgid ""
"Expects the `DOMRect` of the received `Target` to match the given `rect` "
"object. The `rect` object can either be:"
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan `Target` ning `DOMRect` i berilgan `rect` ob'ektiga mos "
"kelishini kutadi. `rect` ob'ekti quyidagilardan biri bo'lishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:675
msgid "a `DOMRect` object;"
msgstr "`DOMRect` ob'ekti;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:676
msgid "a CSS selector string (to get the rect of the *only* matching element);"
msgstr "CSS selektor qatori (faqat mos keluvchi elementning to'rtburchagini olish uchun);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:677
msgid "a node."
msgstr "tugun."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:679
msgid ""
"If the resulting `rect` value is a node, then both nodes' rects will be "
"compared."
msgstr ""
"Agar natijadagi `rect` qiymati tugun bo'lsa, ikkala tugunning "
"to'rtburchaklari taqqoslanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:683
msgid "`rect`: `Partial<DOMRect> | Target`"
msgstr "`rect`: `Partial<DOMRect> | Target`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:684
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`options`: `{ message?: string, trimPadding?: boolean }`"
msgstr "`options`: `{ message?: string, trimPadding?: boolean }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:695
msgid "Expects the received `Target` to match the given style properties."
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` berilgan stil xossalariga mos kelishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:699
msgid "`style`: `string | Record<string, string | RegExp>`"
msgstr "`style`: `string | Record<string, string | RegExp>`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:711
msgid "Expects the `text` content of the received `Target` to either:"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` ning `text` kontenti quyidagilardan biri bo'lishini kutadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:713
msgid "be strictly equal to a given string;"
msgstr "berilgan qatorga qat'iy teng bo'lishi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:714
msgid "match a given regular expression."
msgstr "berilgan muntazam ifodaga mos kelishi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:716
msgid ""
"Note: `innerHTML` is used to retrieve the text content to take CSS "
"visibility into account. This also means that text values from child "
"elements will be joined using a line-break as separator."
msgstr ""
"Eslatma: CSS ko'rinishini hisobga olish uchun matn kontentini olishda "
"`innerHTML` ishlatiladi. Bu shuningdek bolalar elementlardan matn "
"qiymatlari satr uzilishi ajratuvchi sifatida birlashtirilishini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:722
msgid "`text`: `string | RegExp`"
msgstr "`text`: `string | RegExp`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:723
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`options`: `{ message?: string, raw?: boolean }`"
msgstr "`options`: `{ message?: string, raw?: boolean }`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:734
msgid "Expects the value of the received `Target` to either:"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan `Target` ning qiymati quyidagilardan biri bo'lishini kutadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:736
msgid "be strictly equal to a given string or number;"
msgstr "berilgan qator yoki raqamga qat'iy teng bo'lishi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:737
msgid "match a given regular expression;"
msgstr "berilgan muntazam ifodaga mos kelishi;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:738
msgid "contain file objects matching the given `files` list."
msgstr "berilgan `files` ro'yxatiga mos keladigan fayl ob'ektlarini o'z ichiga olishi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:754
msgid "Static methods"
msgstr "Statik metodlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:756
msgid ""
"The `expect` helper function also contains static methods that can be "
"used to run through a detached testing flow that isn't bound to one "
"specific value at a certain moment."
msgstr ""
"`expect` yordamchi funksiyasi ma'lum bir vaqtda bitta aniq qiymatga "
"bog'liq bo'lmagan ajratilgan test oqimini bajarish uchun ishlatiladigan "
"statik metodlarni ham o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:760
msgid ""
"These methods are mainly used to register steps or errors in the scope of"
" the current test, and to evaluate them later on."
msgstr ""
"Bu metodlar asosan joriy test doirasida qadamlarni yoki xatolarni "
"ro'yxatdan o'tkazish va ularni keyinroq baholash uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:767
msgid ""
"Expects the current test to have the `expected` amount of assertions. "
"This number cannot be less than 1."
msgstr ""
"Joriy testda `expected` miqdordagi tasdiqlashlar bo'lishini kutadi. "
"Bu son 1 dan kam bo'lishi mumkin emas."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:771
msgid ""
"It is generally preferred to use :js:meth:`expect.step` and "
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps` instead as it is more reliable and allows "
"to test more extensively."
msgstr ""
"Umuman olganda, ishonchli bo'lgani va ko'proq keng qamrovli testlashga "
"imkon bergani uchun uning o'rniga :js:meth:`expect.step` va "
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps` dan foydalanish afzal."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:778
msgid "Expects the current test to have the `expected` amount of errors."
msgstr "Joriy testda `expected` miqdordagi xatolar bo'lishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:780
msgid ""
"This also means that from the moment this function is called, the test "
"will accept that amount of errors before being considered as failed."
msgstr ""
"Bu shuningdek, ushbu funksiya chaqirilgan paytdan boshlab, test "
"muvaffaqiyatsiz hisoblanmasdan oldin shu miqdordagi xatolarni qabul "
"qilishini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:787
msgid ""
"Registers a step for the current test, that can be consumed by "
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps`. Unconsumed steps will fail the test."
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps` tomonidan ishlatilishi mumkin bo'lgan "
"joriy test uchun qadam ro'yxatdan o'tkazadi. Ishlatilmagan qadamlar "
"testni muvaffaqiyatsiz qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:796
msgid ""
"Expects the received matchers to match the errors thrown since the start "
"of the test or the last call to :js:meth:`expect.verifyErrors`. Calling "
"this matcher will reset the list of current errors."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan matcherlar test boshlanganidan yoki "
":js:meth:`expect.verifyErrors` ga oxirgi chaqiruvdan beri chiqarilgan "
"xatolarga mos kelishini kutadi. Bu matcherni chaqirish joriy xatolar "
"ro'yxatini tiklaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:810
msgid ""
"Expects the received steps to be equal to the steps emitted since the "
"start of the test or the last call to :js:meth:`expect.verifySteps`. "
"Calling this matcher will reset the list of current steps."
msgstr ""
"Qabul qilingan qadamlar test boshlanganidan yoki "
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps` ga oxirgi chaqiruvdan beri chiqarilgan "
"qadamlarga teng bo'lishini kutadi. Bu matcherni chaqirish joriy qadamlar "
"ro'yxatini tiklaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:824
#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:842
msgid "`Promise<boolean>`"
msgstr "`Promise<boolean>`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:826
msgid ""
"Same as :js:meth:`expect.verifyErrors`, but will not immediatly fail if "
"errors are not caught yet, and will instead wait for a certain timeout "
"(default: 2000ms) to allow errors to be caught later."
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`expect.verifyErrors` bilan bir xil, lekin xatolar hali "
"ushlangmagan bo'lsa darhol muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lmaydi va xatolarning "
"keyinroq ushlanishiga imkon berish uchun ma'lum bir kutish vaqtini "
"(standart: 2000ms) kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:830
msgid ""
"Checks are performed initially, at the end of the timeout, and each time "
"an error is detected."
msgstr ""
"Tekshiruvlar dastlab, kutish vaqti oxirida va har safar xato "
"aniqlanganida amalga oshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:844
msgid ""
"Same as :js:meth:`expect.verifySteps`, but will not immediatly fail if "
"steps have not been registered yet, and will instead wait for a certain "
"timeout (default: 2000ms) to allow steps to be registered later."
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`expect.verifySteps` bilan bir xil, lekin qadamlar hali "
"ro'yxatdan o'tkazilmagan bo'lsa darhol muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lmaydi va "
"qadamlarning keyinroq ro'yxatdan o'tkazilishiga imkon berish uchun "
"ma'lum bir kutish vaqtini (standart: 2000ms) kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:848
msgid ""
"Checks are performed initially, at the end of the timeout, and each time "
"a step is registered."
msgstr ""
"Tekshiruvlar dastlab, kutish vaqti oxirida va har safar qadam "
"ro'yxatdan o'tkazilganida amalga oshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:858
msgid "DOM: queries"
msgstr "DOM: so'rovlar"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:863
msgid "Custom DOM selectors"
msgstr "Maxsus DOM selektorlari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:865
msgid ""
"Here's a brief section on DOM selectors in Hoot, as they support "
"additional pseudo-classes that can be used to target elements based on "
"non-standard features, such as their text content or their global "
"position in the document."
msgstr ""
"Mana Hoot'dagi DOM selektorlari haqida qisqacha bo'lim, chunki ular "
"matn kontenti yoki hujjatdagi global joylashuvi kabi nostandart "
"xususiyatlarga asoslanib elementlarni nishonga olish uchun ishlatiladigan "
"qo'shimcha pseudo-klasslarni qo'llab-quvvatlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:873
msgid "`:contains(text)`"
msgstr "`:contains(text)`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:870
msgid "matches nodes whose text content matches the given `text`"
msgstr "matn kontenti berilgan `text` ga mos keladigan tugunlarga mos keladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:872
msgid ""
"given *text* supports regular expression syntax (e.g. "
"`:contains(/^foo.+/)`) and is case-insensitive (unless using the `i` flag"
" at the end of the regex)"
msgstr ""
"berilgan *text* muntazam ifoda sintaksisini qo'llab-quvvatlaydi (masalan, "
"`:contains(/^foo.+/)`) va katta-kichik harf farqsiz (muntazam ifoda "
"oxirida `i` bayrog'i ishlatilmasa)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:876
msgid "`:displayed`"
msgstr "`:displayed`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:876
msgid "matches nodes that are *\"displayed\"* (see `isDisplayed`)"
msgstr "*\"ko'rsatilgan\"* tugunlarga mos keladi (qarang: `isDisplayed`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:879
msgid "`:empty`"
msgstr "`:empty`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:879
msgid "matches nodes that have an empty content (value or text content)"
msgstr "bo'sh kontentga (qiymat yoki matn kontenti) ega tugunlarga mos keladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:882
msgid "`:eq(n)`"
msgstr "`:eq(n)`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:882
msgid "returns the *nth* node based on its global position (0-based index);"
msgstr "global joylashuviga asoslanib *n-chi* tugunni qaytaradi (0 dan boshlanadigan indeks);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:885
msgid "`:first`"
msgstr "`:first`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:885
msgid "returns the first node matching the selector (in the whole document)"
msgstr "selektorga mos keladigan birinchi tugunni qaytaradi (butun hujjatda)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:888
msgid "`:focusable`"
msgstr "`:focusable`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:888
msgid "matches nodes that can be *\"focused\"* (see `isFocusable`)"
msgstr "*\"fokuslanishi\"* mumkin bo'lgan tugunlarga mos keladi (qarang: `isFocusable`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:891
msgid "`:hidden`"
msgstr "`:hidden`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:891
msgid "matches nodes that are *not* *\"visible\"* (see `isVisible`)"
msgstr "*\"ko'rinadigan\"* *bo'lmagan* tugunlarga mos keladi (qarang: `isVisible`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:894
msgid "`:iframe`"
msgstr "`:iframe`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:894
msgid ""
"matches nodes that are `<iframe>` elements, and returns their `body` if "
"it is ready"
msgstr "`<iframe>` elementlari bo'lgan tugunlarga mos keladi va tayyor bo'lsa ularning `body` sini qaytaradi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:897
msgid "`:last`"
msgstr "`:last`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:897
msgid "returns the last node matching the selector (in the whole document)"
msgstr "selektorga mos keladigan oxirgi tugunni qaytaradi (butun hujjatda)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:900
msgid "`:selected`"
msgstr "`:selected`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:900
msgid "matches nodes that are selected (e.g. `<option>` elements)"
msgstr "tanlangan tugunlarga mos keladi (masalan, `<option>` elementlari)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:903
msgid "`:shadow`"
msgstr "`:shadow`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:903
msgid "matches nodes that have shadow roots, and returns their shadow root"
msgstr "soya ildizlarga ega tugunlarga mos keladi va ularning soya ildizini qaytaradi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:906
msgid "`:scrollable`"
msgstr "`:scrollable`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:906
msgid "matches nodes that are scrollable (see `isScrollable`)"
msgstr "aylantirilishi mumkin bo'lgan tugunlarga mos keladi (qarang: `isScrollable`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:912
msgid "`:value(text)`"
msgstr "`:value(text)`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:909
msgid "matches nodes whose value matches the given `text`"
msgstr "qiymati berilgan `text` ga mos keladigan tugunlarga mos keladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:911
msgid ""
"given *text* supports regular expression syntax (e.g. `:value(/^foo.+/)`)"
" and is case-insensitive (unless using the `i` flag at the end of the "
"regex)"
msgstr ""
"berilgan *text* muntazam ifoda sintaksisini qo'llab-quvvatlaydi (masalan, "
"`:value(/^foo.+/)`) va katta-kichik harf farqsiz (muntazam ifoda oxirida "
"`i` bayrog'i ishlatilmasa)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:915
msgid "`:visible`"
msgstr "`:visible`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:915
msgid "matches nodes that are *\"visible\"* (see `isVisible`)"
msgstr "*\"ko'rinadigan\"* tugunlarga mos keladi (qarang: `isVisible`)"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:918
msgid "Query & node properties helpers"
msgstr "So'rov va tugun xossalari yordamchilari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:920
msgid ""
"Hoot provides helpers to query nodes and some of their properties in a "
"streamlined and elegant way. This can mainly be done through the use of "
"`queryX` helpers:"
msgstr ""
"Hoot tugunlarni va ularning ba'zi xossalarini sodda va nafis tarzda "
"so'rash uchun yordamchilarni taqdim etadi. Bu asosan `queryX` "
"yordamchilaridan foydalanish orqali amalga oshirilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:925
msgid ""
"Returns a list of nodes matching the given `Target`. This function can "
"either be used as a `template literal tag <https://developer.mozilla.org"
"/en-"
"US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Template_literals#tagged_templates>`_ "
"(only supports string selector without options) or invoked the usual way."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `Target` ga mos keladigan tugunlar ro'yxatini qaytaradi. Bu "
"funksiya `template literal tag <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/"
"Web/JavaScript/Reference/Template_literals#tagged_templates>`_ sifatida "
"(faqat variantsiz qator selektori qo'llab-quvvatlanadi) yoki odatiy tarzda "
"chaqirilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:929
msgid "The target can be:"
msgstr "Maqsad quyidagilardan biri bo'lishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:931
msgid "a `Node` (or an iterable of nodes), or `Window` object;"
msgstr "`Node` (yoki tugunlar takrorlanuvchisi), yoki `Window` ob'ekti;"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:932
msgid "a `Document` object (which will be converted to its body);"
msgstr "`Document` ob'ekti (u o'z body ga aylantiriladi);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:933
msgid ""
"a string representing a :ref:`custom selector <hoot/custom-dom-"
"selectors>` (which will be queried from the `root` option)."
msgstr ""
":ref:`maxsus selektor <hoot/custom-dom-selectors>` ni ifodalovchi qator "
"(`root` variantidan so'raladi)."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:936
msgid "An `options` object can be specified to filter [#]_ the results:"
msgstr "Natijalarni filtrlash uchun `options` ob'ekti ko'rsatilishi mumkin [#]_:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:938
msgid ""
"`count`: the exact number of nodes to match (throws an error if the "
"number of nodes doesn't match);"
msgstr ""
"`count`: mos kelishi kerak bo'lgan tugunlarning aniq soni (tugunlar soni "
"mos kelmasa xato chiqaradi);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:940
msgid "`displayed`: whether the nodes must be \"displayed\" (see `isDisplayed`);"
msgstr "`displayed`: tugunlar \"ko'rsatilgan\" bo'lishi kerakmi (qarang: `isDisplayed`);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:941
msgid "`focusable`: whether the nodes must be \"focusable\" (see `isFocusable`);"
msgstr "`focusable`: tugunlar \"fokuslanishi\" mumkin bo'lishi kerakmi (qarang: `isFocusable`);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:942
msgid ""
"`root`: the root node to query the selector in (defaults to the current "
"fixture);"
msgstr ""
"`root`: selektori so'ralanadigan ildiz tugun (standart: joriy fixture);"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:943
msgid ""
"`visible`: whether the nodes must be \"visible\" (see `isVisible`). * "
"This option implies `displayed`"
msgstr ""
"`visible`: tugunlar \"ko'rinadigan\" bo'lishi kerakmi (qarang: `isVisible`). * "
"Bu variant `displayed` ni ham anglatadi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:946
msgid ""
"these filters (except for `count` and `root`) achieve the same result as "
"using their homonym pseudo-classes on the final group of the given "
"selector string, e.g.:"
msgstr ""
"bu filtrlar (`count` va `root` dan tashqari) berilgan selektor qatorining "
"oxirgi guruhida ularning nomdosh pseudo-klasslarini ishlatish bilan bir xil "
"natijaga erishadi, masalan:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:955
msgid "`Node[]`"
msgstr "`Node[]`"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:959
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` on the given `target` and returns a list "
"of attribute values."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `target` da :js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi va atribut "
"qiymatlari ro'yxatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:962
msgid "`string[]` list of attribute values"
msgstr "`string[]` atribut qiymatlari ro'yxati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:966
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` on the given `target` and returns a list "
"of property values."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `target` da :js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi va xossa "
"qiymatlari ro'yxatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:969
msgid "`unknown[]` list of property values"
msgstr "`unknown[]` xossa qiymatlari ro'yxati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:973
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` on the given `target` and returns a list "
"of text contents."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `target` da :js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi va matn "
"kontentlari ro'yxatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:976
msgid "`string[]` list of text contents"
msgstr "`string[]` matn kontentlari ro'yxati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:980
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` on the given `target` and returns a list "
"of values."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `target` da :js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi va qiymatlar "
"ro'yxatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:983
msgid "`string[]` a list of values"
msgstr "`string[]` qiymatlar ro'yxati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:987
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryOne` with the given arguments and returns the "
"value of the given `attribute` of the matching node."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan argumentlar bilan :js:meth:`queryOne` ni bajaradi va mos "
"keladigan tugunning berilgan `attribute` qiymatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:990
msgid "`string` the attribute value"
msgstr "`string` atribut qiymati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:994
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` with the given arguments and returns the "
"first result or `null`."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan argumentlar bilan :js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi va birinchi "
"natijani yoki `null` ni qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:997
msgid "`Node` | `null` the first matching node"
msgstr "`Node` | `null` birinchi mos keladigan tugun"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1001
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryAll` with the given arguments, along with a "
"forced `count: 1` option to ensure only one node matches the given "
"`Target`."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan `Target` ga faqat bitta tugun mos kelishini ta'minlash uchun "
"majburiy `count: 1` variantini qo'shib, berilgan argumentlar bilan "
":js:meth:`queryAll` ni bajaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1004
msgid "The returned value is a single node instead of a list of nodes."
msgstr "Qaytarilgan qiymat tugunlar ro'yxati o'rniga bitta tugundir."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1006
msgid "`Node` a single node"
msgstr "`Node` bitta tugun"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1010
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryOne` with the given arguments and returns the "
"*text* of the matching node."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan argumentlar bilan :js:meth:`queryOne` ni bajaradi va mos "
"keladigan tugunning *matnini* qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1013
msgid "`string` text of the matching node"
msgstr "`string` mos keladigan tugunning matni"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1017
msgid ""
"Performs a :js:meth:`queryOne` with the given arguments and returns the "
"*value* of the matching node."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan argumentlar bilan :js:meth:`queryOne` ni bajaradi va mos "
"keladigan tugunning *qiymatini* qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1020
msgid "`string` value of the matching node"
msgstr "`string` mos keladigan tugunning qiymati"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1022
msgid ""
"All of the above helpers are synchronous, meaning that they will attempt "
"to query nodes instantly. Although some use cases require the element to "
"be awaited for an arbitrary amount of time, unknown in advance due to UI "
"fetching and rendering complexity."
msgstr ""
"Yuqoridagi barcha yordamchilar sinxron, ya'ni ular tugunlarni darhol "
"so'rashga harakat qiladi. Biroq, ba'zi foydalanish holatlari elementni "
"UI olish va ko'rsatish murakkabligi tufayli oldindan noma'lum bo'lgan "
"o'zboshimcha vaqt davomida kutishni talab qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1026
msgid ""
"Hoot provides 2 methods to wait for an element to appear / disappear "
"within a certain time frame (by default: `200` milliseconds) for such "
"cases:"
msgstr ""
"Bunday holatlarda Hoot elementning ma'lum vaqt oralig'ida (standart: "
"`200` millisekund) paydo bo'lishi / yo'qolishini kutish uchun 2 ta metod "
"taqdim etadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1031
msgid ""
"Combination of :js:meth:`queryAll` and :js:meth:`waitUntil`: waits for a "
"given target to match elements in the DOM and returns the first matching "
"node when it appears (or immediately if it is already present)."
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`queryAll` va :js:meth:`waitUntil` kombinatsiyasi: berilgan "
"maqsadning DOM dagi elementlarga mos kelishini kutadi va u paydo "
"bo'lganda (yoki allaqachon mavjud bo'lsa darhol) birinchi mos keladigan "
"tugunni qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1035
msgid "`Promise<Node>` containing the first matching node"
msgstr "`Promise<Node>` birinchi mos keladigan tugunni o'z ichiga oladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1039
msgid ""
"Opposite of :js:meth:`waitFor` waits for a given target to disappear from"
" the DOM."
msgstr ""
":js:meth:`waitFor` ning teskarisi: berilgan maqsadning DOM dan "
"yo'qolishini kutadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1041
msgid "`Promise<number>` containing the number of matching nodes"
msgstr "`Promise<number>` mos keladigan tugunlar sonini o'z ichiga oladi"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1045
msgid "DOM: interaction helpers"
msgstr "DOM: o'zaro ta'sir yordamchilari"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1047
msgid ""
"Along with querying elements, it is often required to interact with them."
" As such, Hoot provides helpers to simulate various user interactions on "
"elements."
msgstr ""
"Elementlarni so'rashdan tashqari, ular bilan o'zaro ta'sir o'rnatish ham "
"ko'pincha talab qilinadi. Shuning uchun Hoot elementlarda turli "
"foydalanuvchi o'zaro ta'sirlarini simulyatsiya qilish uchun yordamchilarni "
"taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1050
msgid ""
"These can be split into 2 types based on their parameters: **pointer-"
"based** interaction helpers, and the **other** ones."
msgstr ""
"Ular parametrlariga asoslanib 2 turga bo'linishi mumkin: **ko'rsatgichga "
"asoslangan** o'zaro ta'sir yordamchilari va **boshqa** turlar."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1054
msgid "Pointer interaction helpers:"
msgstr "Ko'rsatgich o'zaro ta'sir yordamchilari:"

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1056
msgid ""
"Pointer interaction helpers (such as :js:meth:`click` or :js:meth:`drag`)"
" will simulate actual pointer movements and events on the given target, "
"and on any previous element the pointer was *supposed* to have been."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rsatgich o'zaro ta'sir yordamchilari (masalan, :js:meth:`click` yoki "
":js:meth:`drag`) berilgan maqsadda va ko'rsatgich *bo'lishi kerak* "
"bo'lgan oldingi elementlarda haqiqiy ko'rsatgich harakatlarini va "
"hodisalarini simulyatsiya qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1062
msgid "Ensures that the given `Target` is checked."
msgstr "Berilgan `Target` belgilangan ekanligini ta'minlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/reference/frontend/unit_testing/hoot.rst:1064
msgid ""
"If it is not checked, a :js:meth:`click` is simulated on the input. If "
"the input is still not checked after the click, an error is thrown."
msgstr ""
"Agar belgilanmagan bo'lsa, kiritishda :js:meth:`click` simulyatsiya "
"qilinadi. Agar kiritish bosilgandan keyin ham belgilanmagan bo'lsa, xato "
"chiqariladi."

