#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:329
msgid "Accessing the data"
msgstr "Ma'lumotlarga kirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:331
msgid ""
"You should never access demo data outside of the demo data declaration, "
"not even in tests."
msgstr ""
"Demo ma'lumotlarga demo ma'lumot e'lonidan tashqarida hech qachon kirmasligingiz "
"kerak, hatto testlarda ham."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:334
msgid "There are multiple ways to access the master/demo data."
msgstr "Asosiy/demo ma'lumotlarga kirish uchun bir necha yo'l mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:336
msgid ""
"In python code, you can use the ``env.ref(self, xml_id, "
"raise_if_not_found=True)`` method. It returns the recordset linked to the"
" ``xml_id`` you specify."
msgstr ""
"Python kodida ``env.ref(self, xml_id, raise_if_not_found=True)`` metodidan "
"foydalanishingiz mumkin. U ko'rsatgan ``xml_id`` ga bog'liq yozuvlar "
"to'plamini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:339
msgid "In XML, you can use the `ref` key like this"
msgstr "XML da `ref` kalitini quyidagi tarzda ishlatishingiz mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:349
msgid ""
"It will call the ref method, and store the id of the record returned on "
"the field ``related_id`` of the record of type ``tutorial.example`` with "
"id ``id1``."
msgstr ""
"U ref metodini chaqiradi va qaytarilgan yozuvning id sini id ``id1`` bo'lgan "
"``tutorial.example`` turidagi yozuvning ``related_id`` maydonida saqlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:352
msgid "In CSV, the title of the column must be suffixed with ``:id`` or ``/id``."
msgstr "CSV da ustun sarlavhasi ``:id`` yoki ``/id`` bilan tugashi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:361
msgid ""
"In SQL, it is more complicated, see :ref:`the advanced section "
"<tutorials/define_module_data/xml_id>`."
msgstr ""
"SQL da bu murakkabroq, qarang: :ref:`kengaytirilgan bo'lim "
"<tutorials/define_module_data/xml_id>`."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:364
msgid ""
"Data can always be deleted by the user. Always code defensively, taking "
"this into account."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumotlar har doim foydalanuvchi tomonidan o'chirilishi mumkin. Buni "
"hisobga olib, har doim himoya ko'rinishida kod yozing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:371
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr "Kengaytirilgan"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:376
msgid "What is the XML id?"
msgstr "XML id nima?"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:378
msgid ""
"Because we don't want a column ``xml_id`` in every single SQL table of "
"the database, we need a mechanism to store it. This is done with the "
"``ir.model.data`` model."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumotlar bazasining har bir SQL jadvalida ``xml_id`` ustunini "
"xohlamaganimiz sababli, uni saqlash mexanizmiga ehtiyoj bor. Bu "
"``ir.model.data`` modeli bilan amalga oshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:381
msgid ""
"It contains the name of the record (the ``xml_id``) along with the module"
" in which it is defined, the model defining it, and the id of it."
msgstr ""
"U yozuv nomini (``xml_id``) u aniqlangan modul, uni aniqlovchi model "
"va uning id si bilan birga o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:385
msgid "No update"
msgstr "Yangilanmaydigan"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:387
msgid ""
"The records created with the ``noupdate`` flag won't be updated when "
"upgrading the module that created them, but it will be created if it "
"didn't exist yet."
msgstr ""
"``noupdate`` bayrog'i bilan yaratilgan yozuvlar ularni yaratgan modulni "
"yangilashda yangilanmaydi, lekin hali mavjud bo'lmasa yaratiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:390
msgid ""
"``odoo-bin -i module`` will bypass this setting and always load the data."
" But normally one shouldn't do this on a production database."
msgstr ""
"``odoo-bin -i module`` bu sozlamani chetlab o'tadi va ma'lumotlarni "
"har doim yuklaydi. Lekin odatda ishlab chiqarish ma'lumotlar bazasida "
"buni qilmaslik kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:403
msgid "Import as SQL"
msgstr "SQL sifatida import qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:405
msgid ""
"In some cases, it makes sense to do the import directly in SQL. This is "
"however discouraged as it bypasses all the features of the ORM, computed "
"fields (including metadata) and python constraints."
msgstr ""
"Ba'zi hollarda, importni to'g'ridan-to'g'ri SQL da qilish mantiqli. Biroq "
"bu ORM, hisoblangan maydonlar (metadata ni o'z ichiga olgan) va python "
"cheklovlarining barcha xususiyatlarini chetlab o'tgani uchun tavsiya "
"etilmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:408
msgid ""
"Generally using raw SQL also bypasses ACLs and increases the risks of "
"injections."
msgstr ""
"Umuman olganda xom SQL dan foydalanish ACL larni ham chetlab o'tadi va "
"in'eksiya xavflarini oshiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:410
msgid "**Reference**: :ref:`Security in Odoo<reference/security>`"
msgstr "**Ma'lumot**: :ref:`Odoo da xavfsizlik<reference/security>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:412
msgid ""
"It can help to speed the import time by a lot `with huge files "
"<https://github.com/odoo/enterprise/blob/d46cceef8c594b9056d0115edb7169e207a5986f/product_unspsc/hooks.py#L19>`__."
msgstr ""
"Bu `ulkan fayllar bilan <https://github.com/odoo/enterprise/blob/d46cceef8c594b9056d0115edb7169e207a5986f/product_unspsc/hooks.py#L19>`__ "
"import vaqtini ancha tezlashtirishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:414
msgid ""
"For more complex imports like for the `translations "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e1f8d549895cd9c459e6350430f30d541d02838a/odoo/addons/base/models/ir_translation.py#L24>`__."
msgstr ""
"`tarjimalar <https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e1f8d549895cd9c459e6350430f30d541d02838a/odoo/addons/base/models/ir_translation.py#L24>`__ "
"uchun bo'lgani kabi murakkabroq importlar uchun."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/define_module_data.rst:416
msgid ""
"It can be necessary to `initialize the database "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e1f8d549895cd9c459e6350430f30d541d02838a/odoo/addons/base/data/base_data.sql>`__."
msgstr ""
"`Ma'lumotlar bazasini ishga tushirish <https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e1f8d549895cd9c459e6350430f30d541d02838a/odoo/addons/base/data/base_data.sql>`__ "
"zarur bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework.rst:13
msgid ""
"This two parts tutorial is designed to introduce you to the basics of the"
" web framework. Whether you are new to the framework or have some prior "
"experience, this tutorial will provide you with a solid foundation for "
"using the web framework in your projects."
msgstr ""
"Bu ikki qismli qo'llanma sizni veb framework ning asoslari bilan "
"tanishtirish uchun mo'ljallangan. Framework ga yangi bo'lsangiz yoki oldingi "
"tajribangiz bo'lsa, bu qo'llanma sizga loyihalaringizda veb framework "
"dan foydalanish uchun mustahkam asos beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework.rst:17
msgid ""
"The first part covers the basics of Owl components, which are a key part "
"of the web framework. Owl components are reusable UI components that can "
"be used to build complex web interfaces quickly and efficiently. We will "
"explore how to create and use Owl components in Odoo. Then, in the second"
" part of this tutorial, we focus on creating a dashboard using various "
"features of Odoo. Dashboards are an essential part of any web "
"application, and provide a nice starting point to use and interact with "
"the Odoo codebase."
msgstr ""
"Birinchi qism veb framework ning asosiy qismi bo'lgan Owl komponentlarining "
"asoslarini qamrab oladi. Owl komponentlari murakkab veb interfeyslarini "
"tezda va samarali qurish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin bo'lgan qayta "
"ishlatiladigan UI komponentlaridir. Biz Odoo da Owl komponentlarini qanday "
"yaratish va ishlatishni o'rganamiz. Keyin, ushbu qo'llanmaning ikkinchi "
"qismida biz Odoo ning turli xususiyatlaridan foydalanib boshqaruv paneli "
"yaratishga e'tibor qaratamiz. Boshqaruv panellari har qanday veb "
"ilovaning muhim qismi bo'lib, Odoo kod bazasidan foydalanish va u bilan "
"ishlash uchun yaxshi boshlang'ich nuqta taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework.rst:24
msgid ""
"This tutorial assumes that you have some basic knowledge of development "
"with Odoo in general (models, controllers, QWeb, ...). If you are new to "
"Odoo, we recommend that you start with the "
":doc:`/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101` tutorial before "
"proceeding with this one."
msgstr ""
"Bu qo'llanma sizda umuman Odoo bilan ishlab chiqish bo'yicha ba'zi asosiy "
"bilimlar (modellar, kontrollerlar, QWeb, ...) borligini taxmin qiladi. "
"Agar Odoo ga yangi bo'lsangiz, ushbu qo'llanmani boshlashdan oldin "
":doc:`/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101` qo'llanmasidan "
"boshlashingizni tavsiya qilamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework.rst:30
msgid ""
"Each chapter of this tutorial is an independant project.  If you feel "
"comfortable with Owl, you can start directly with chapter 2."
msgstr ""
"Bu qo'llanmaning har bir bobi mustaqil loyiha. Agar Owl bilan qulay "
"his qilsangiz, to'g'ridan-to'g'ri 2-bobdan boshlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework.rst:38
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:52
msgid ""
