#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:327
msgid "Theory: Component lifecycle and hooks"
msgstr "Nazariya: Komponent hayot tsikli va hooklar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:329
msgid ""
"So far, we have seen one example of a hook function: `useState`. A `hook "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_ is a "
"special function that *hook into* the internals of the component. In the "
"case of `useState`, it generates a proxy object linked to the current "
"component. This is why hook functions have to be called in the `setup` "
"method, and no later!"
msgstr ""
"Hozirgacha biz hook funksiyasining bir misolini ko'rdik: `useState`. "
"`hook <https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_ "
"komponentning ichkiligiga *hook into* qiladigan maxsus funksiya. "
"`useState` holatida, u joriy komponentga bog'liq proksi ob'ekt yaratadi. "
"Shuning uchun hook funksiyalari `setup` metodida va undan oldin "
"chaqirilishi kerak!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:379
msgid ""
"An Owl component goes through a lot of phases: it can be instantiated, "
"rendered, mounted, updated, detached, destroyed... This is the `component"
" lifecycle "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/component.md#lifecycle>`_."
" The figure above show the most important events in the life of a "
"component (hooks are shown in purple). Roughly speaking, a component is "
"created, then updated (potentially many times), then is destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Owl komponenti ko'plab bosqichlardan o'tadi: ishga tushirilishi, "
"ko'rsatilishi, o'rnatilishi, yangilanishi, ajratilishi, yo'q qilinishi... "
"Bu `komponent hayot tsikli "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/component.md#lifecycle>`_ "
"dir. Yuqoridagi rasm komponentning hayotidagi eng muhim hodisalarni "
"ko'rsatadi (hooklar binafsha rangda ko'rsatilgan). Taxminan aytganda, "
"komponent yaratiladi, keyin yangilanadi (ko'p marta), keyin yo'q qilinadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:384
msgid ""
"Owl provides a variety of built-in `hooks functions "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_. All "
"of them have to be called in the `setup` function. For example, if you "
"want to execute some code when your component is mounted, you can use the"
" `onMounted` hook:"
msgstr ""
"Owl turli o'rnatilgan `hook funksiyalarini "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_ taqdim "
"etadi. Ularning barchasi `setup` funksiyasida chaqirilishi kerak. Masalan, "
"komponentingiz o'rnatilganda ba'zi kod bajarish uchun `onMounted` hook dan "
"foydalanishingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:398
msgid ""
"All hook functions start with `use` or `on`. For example: `useState` or "
"`onMounted`."
msgstr ""
"Barcha hook funksiyalari `use` yoki `on` bilan boshlanadi. Masalan: "
"`useState` yoki `onMounted`."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:402
msgid "10. Focusing the input"
msgstr "10. Inputga fokuslanish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:404
msgid ""
"Let's see how we can access the DOM with `t-ref "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/refs.md>`_ and "
"`useRef "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useref>`_."
" The main idea is that you need to mark the target element in the "
"component template with a `t-ref`:"
msgstr ""
"`t-ref <https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/refs.md>`_ "
"va `useRef "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useref>`_"
" bilan DOM ga qanday kirish mumkinligini ko'raylik. Asosiy g'oya shuki, "
"komponent shablonidagi maqsad elementini `t-ref` bilan belgilashingiz kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:412
msgid ""
"Then you can access it in the JS with the `useRef hook "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useref>`_."
" However, there is a problem if you think about it: the actual html "
"element for a component does not exist when the component is created. It "
"only exists when the component is mounted. But hooks have to be called in"
" the `setup` method. So, `useRef` return an object that contains a `el` "
"(for element) key that is only defined when the component is mounted."
msgstr ""
"Keyin uni JS da `useRef hook "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useref>`_"
" bilan kirishingiz mumkin. Biroq, o'ylasangiz muammo bor: komponent "
"uchun haqiqiy html element komponent yaratilganda mavjud emas. U faqat "
"komponent o'rnatilganda mavjud. Lekin hooklar `setup` metodida chaqirilishi "
"kerak. Shuning uchun, `useRef` komponent o'rnatilganda faqat aniqlanadigan "
"`el` (element uchun) kalitini o'z ichiga olgan ob'ekt qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/01_owl_components.rst:429
msgid ""
"Focus the `input` from the previous exercise. This this should be done "
