#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:6
msgid ""
"This tutorial assumes familiarity with the :doc:`server_framework_101` "
"tutorial and the :doc:`define_module_data` tutorial."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu qo'llanma :doc:`server_framework_101` qo'llanmasi va "
":doc:`define_module_data` qo'llanmasi bilan tanishishni talab qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:9
msgid ""
"Although, as developers, we prefer to have the full power of Python to "
"write our modules, it is sometimes not possible to do so; typically on "
"managed hosting solutions which do not allow the deployment of custom "
"Python code like the `Odoo.com <https://www.odoo.com/start>`_ platform."
msgstr ""
"Garchi dasturchilar sifatida modullarimizni yozish uchun Python ning to'liq "
"imkoniyatlariga ega bo'lishni afzal ko'rsak-da, buni bajarish har doim ham "
"mumkin emas; odatda maxsus Python kodini joylashtirishga ruxsat bermaydigan "
"boshqariladigan hosting yechimlarida, masalan `Odoo.com <https://www.odoo.com/start>`_ "
"platformasida."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:14
msgid ""
"However, the flexible nature of Odoo is meant to allow customizations out"
" of the box. Whilst a lot is possible with :doc:`Studio "
"</applications/studio>`, it is also possible to define models, fields and"
" logic in :doc:`XML Data Files <define_module_data>`. This makes it "
"easier to develop, maintain and deploy these customizations."
msgstr ""
"Biroq, Odoo ning moslashuvchan tabiati kutilgan holda sozlashlarni amalga "
"oshirishga mo'ljallangan. :doc:`Studio </applications/studio>` bilan ko'p "
"narsalar mumkin bo'lsa-da, :doc:`XML Ma'lumot Fayllarida <define_module_data>` "
"modellar, maydonlar va mantiqni aniqlash ham mumkin. Bu sozlashlarni "
"ishlab chiqish, saqlash va joylashtirishni osonlashtiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:19
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, we will learn how to define models, fields and logic in"
" XML data files and bundle them into a module. These are sometimes called"
" *importable modules*, or *data modules*. We will also see the "
"limitations of this approach to module development."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu qo'llanmada modellar, maydonlar va mantiqni XML ma'lumot fayllarida "
"qanday aniqlash va ularni modulga to'plashni o'rganamiz. Ular ba'zan "
"*import qilinadigan modullar* yoki *ma'lumot modullari* deb ataladi. Shuningdek, "
"modul ishlab chiqishning ushbu yondashuvining cheklovlarini ko'ramiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:24
msgid "Problem statement"
msgstr "Muammo bayoni"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:26
msgid ""
"Like in the :doc:`server_framework_101` tutorial, we will be working on "
"Real Estate concepts."
msgstr ""
":doc:`server_framework_101` qo'llanmasidagi kabi, Ko'chmas mulk kontseptsiyalari "
"ustida ishlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:28
msgid ""
"Our goal is to create a new application to manage Real Estate properties "
"in a similar (albeit simpler) way to the :doc:`server_framework_101` "
"tutorial. We will define the models, fields and logic in XML data files "
"instead of Python files."
msgstr ""
"Bizning maqsadimiz :doc:`server_framework_101` qo'llanmasiga o'xshash "
"(garchi oddiyroq bo'lsa-da) usulda Ko'chmas mulk ob'ektlarini boshqarish "
"uchun yangi ilova yaratishdir. Modellar, maydonlar va mantiqni Python fayllari "
"o'rniga XML ma'lumot fayllarida aniqlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:32
msgid ""
"At the end of this tutorial, we will be able to achieve the following in "
"our app:"
msgstr "Ushbu qo'llanma oxirida ilovamizda quyidagilarni amalga oshira olamiz:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:34
msgid "Manage Real Estate properties that are for sale"
msgstr "Sotuvdagi Ko'chmas mulk ob'ektlarini boshqarish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:35
msgid "Publish these properties on a website"
msgstr "Bu ob'ektlarni veb-saytda nashr qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:36
msgid "Accept offers online from the website"
msgstr "Veb-saytdan onlayn takliflarni qabul qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:37
msgid "Invoice the buyer when the property is sold"
msgstr "Mulk sotilganda xaridorga hisob-faktura yuborish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:42
msgid ""
"Like in any development project, a clear structure makes it easier to "
"manage and maintain the code."
msgstr ""
"Har qanday ishlab chiqish loyihasidagi kabi, aniq tuzilma kodni boshqarish "
"va saqlashni osonlashtiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:44
msgid ""
"Unlike standard Odoo modules that use both Python and XML files, data "
"modules use only XML files. Therefore, it is expected that your work tree"
" will look something like this:"
msgstr ""
"Python va XML fayllaridan foydalanadigan standart Odoo modullaridan farqli "
"o'laroq, ma'lumot modullari faqat XML fayllardan foydalanadi. Shuning uchun, "
"ish daraxti quyidagicha ko'rinishi kutiladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:62
msgid ""
"The only Python files you will have are the :file:`__init__.py` and "
":file:`__manifest__.py` files. The :file:`__manifest__.py` file will be "
"the same as for any Odoo module, but will also import its models in the "
"`data` list."
msgstr ""
"Sizda bo'ladigan yagona Python fayllari :file:`__init__.py` va "
":file:`__manifest__.py` fayllaridir. :file:`__manifest__.py` fayli har "
"qanday Odoo moduli uchun xuddi shunday bo'ladi, lekin `data` ro'yxatida "
"o'z modellarini ham import qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:66
msgid ""
"Remember to list files in the `data` section of :file:`__manifest__.py` "
"in order of dependency, typically starting with model files."
msgstr ""
":file:`__manifest__.py` ning `data` bo'limida fayllarni bog'liqlik tartibida, "
"odatda model fayllaridan boshlab ro'yxatga olishni unutmang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:69
msgid ""
"The :file:`__init__.py` file is empty, but is required for Odoo to "
"recognize the module if you ever want to deploy your module in the "
"classic way (by adding it in an addons path). It is not strictly "
"necessary for modules that will be *imported*, but it is a good practice "
"to keep it."
msgstr ""
":file:`__init__.py` fayli bo'sh, lekin modulni klassik usulda (addons yo'lida "
"qo'shish orqali) joylashtirishni xohlaganingizda Odoo modulni tan olishi uchun "
"kerak. Bu *import qilinadigan* modullar uchun qat'iy zarur emas, lekin uni "
"saqlash yaxshi amaliyotdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:74
msgid "Deploying the module"
msgstr "Modulni joylashtirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:76
msgid ""
"To deploy the module, you will need to create a zip file of the module "
"and upload it to your Odoo instance. Make sure that the module "
"`base_import_module` is installed on your instance, then go to the "
":menuselection:`Apps --> Import Module` and upload the zip file. You must"
" be in :ref:`developer mode <developer-mode>` to see the `Import Module` "
"menu item."
msgstr ""
"Modulni joylashtirish uchun modul zip faylini yaratish va uni Odoo "
"instansingizga yuklash kerak. `base_import_module` moduli instansingizda "
"o'rnatilganiga ishonch hosil qiling, keyin :menuselection:`Apps --> Import Module` "
"ga o'ting va zip faylni yuklang. `Import Module` menyu bandini ko'rish uchun "
":ref:`dasturchi rejimida <developer-mode>` bo'lishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:81
msgid ""
"If you modify the module, you will need to create a new zip file and "
"upload it again, which will reload all the data in the module. Note "
"however that some operations are not possible, like changing the type of "
"a field you created previously. Data created by previous versions of the "
"module (like removed fields) will not be automatically deleted. In "
"general, the simplest way to handle this is to start with a fresh "
"database or to uninstall the module prior to uploading the new version."
msgstr ""
"Modulni o'zgartirsangiz, yangi zip fayl yaratib qayta yuklashingiz kerak, "
"bu moduldagi barcha ma'lumotlarni qayta yuklaydi. Biroq, ba'zi amallarni "
"bajarish mumkin emas, masalan, ilgari yaratgan maydon turini o'zgartirish. "
"Modulning oldingi versiyalari tomonidan yaratilgan ma'lumotlar (o'chirilgan "
"maydonlar kabi) avtomatik o'chirilmaydi. Umuman olganda, buni hal qilishning "
"eng oddiy usuli yangi ma'lumotlar bazasidan boshlash yoki yangi versiyani "
"yuklashdan oldin modulni o'chirib tashlashdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:88
msgid "When uploading a module, the wizard will accept two options:"
msgstr "Modul yuklanayotganda sehrgar ikkita variantni qabul qiladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:90
msgid ""
"`Force init`: if your module is already installed and you upload it "
"again; checking this option will force the update of all data marked as "
"`noupdate=\"1\"` in the XML files."
msgstr ""
"`Force init`: agar modulingiz allaqachon o'rnatilgan bo'lsa va siz uni qayta "
"yuklasangiz; bu variantni belgilash XML fayllardagi `noupdate=\"1\"` deb "
"belgilangan barcha ma'lumotlarni majburiy yangilaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:92
msgid "`Import demo data`: self explanatory"
msgstr "`Import demo data`: o'z-o'zidan tushuntirib beradi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:94
msgid ""
"It is also possible to deploy the module using the :doc:`odoo-bin "
"<../reference/cli>` command line tool with the `deploy` command:"
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, modulni `deploy` buyrug'i bilan :doc:`odoo-bin "
"<../reference/cli>` buyruq qatori vositasidan foydalanib joylashtirish ham mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:101
msgid ""
"This command also accepts the `--force` option, which is equivalent to "
"the :guilabel:`Force init` option in the wizard."
msgstr ""
"Bu buyruq shuningdek sehrgardagi :guilabel:`Force init` variantiga ekvivalent "
"bo'lgan `--force` variantini ham qabul qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:104
msgid ""
"Note that the user you use to deploy the module must have "
"`Administration/Settings` access rights."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, modulni joylashtirish uchun ishlatiladigan foydalanuvchi "
"`Administration/Settings` kirish huquqlariga ega bo'lishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:108
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/02_newapp.rst:76
msgid "Create the following folders and files:"
msgstr "Quyidagi papkalar va fayllarni yarating:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:110
msgid ":file:`/home/$USER/src/tutorials/estate/__init__.py`"
msgstr ":file:`/home/$USER/src/tutorials/estate/__init__.py`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:111
msgid ":file:`/home/$USER/src/tutorials/estate/__manifest__.py`"
msgstr ":file:`/home/$USER/src/tutorials/estate/__manifest__.py`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:113
msgid ""
"The :file:`__manifest__.py` file should only define the name and the "
"dependencies of our modules. The only necessary framework module for now "
"is ``base`` (and ``base_import_module`` - although your module does not "
"*depend* on it strictly speaking, you need it to be able to import your "
"module)."
msgstr ""
":file:`__manifest__.py` fayli faqat modullarimizning nomini va bog'liqliklarini "
"aniqlashi kerak. Hozircha zarur bo'lgan yagona framework moduli ``base`` dir "
"(va ``base_import_module`` - garchi modulingiz qat'iy ma'noda unga "
"*bog'liq* bo'lmasa-da, modulingizni import qila olish uchun unga muhtojsiz)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:118
msgid "Create a zip file of your module and upload it to your Odoo instance."
msgstr "Modulingiz zip faylini yarating va Odoo instansingizga yuklang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:121
msgid "Models and basic fields"
msgstr "Modellar va asosiy maydonlar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:123
msgid ""
"As you can imagine, defining models and fields in XML files is not as "
"straightforward as in Python."
msgstr ""
"Tasavvur qilganingizdek, XML fayllarda modellar va maydonlarni aniqlash "
"Pythondagi kabi oddiy emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:125
msgid ""
"Since data files are read sequentially, you must define the elements in "
"the right order. For example, you must define a model before you can "
"define a field on that model, and you must define fields before adding "
"them to a view."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumot fayllari ketma-ket o'qilganligi sababli, elementlarni to'g'ri "
"tartibda aniqlashingiz kerak. Masalan, model ustida maydon aniqlanishidan "
"oldin modelni aniqlashingiz kerak va ularni ko'rinishga qo'shishdan oldin "
"maydonlarni aniqlashingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:129
msgid "In addition, XML is simply much more verbose than Python."
msgstr "Bundan tashqari, XML shunchaki Pythondan ancha batafsil."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:131
msgid ""
"Let's start by defining a simple model to represent a Real Estate "
"property in the `models` directory of our module."
msgstr ""
"Keling, modulimizning `models` papkasida Ko'chmas mulk ob'ektini ifodalash "
"uchun oddiy model aniqlashdan boshlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:134
msgid ""
"Odoo models are stored in database as `ir.model` records. Like any other "
"record, they can be defined in XML files:"
msgstr ""
"Odoo modellari ma'lumotlar bazasida `ir.model` yozuvlari sifatida saqlanadi. "
"Boshqa har qanday yozuv kabi, ularni XML fayllarda aniqlash mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:147
msgid ""
"Note that all models and fields defined in data files must be prefixed "
"with `x_`; this is mandatory and is used to differentiate them from "
"models and fields defined in Python files."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, ma'lumot fayllarida aniqlangan barcha modellar va maydonlar "
"`x_` bilan boshlanishi kerak; bu majburiy va ularni Python fayllarida "
"aniqlangan modellar va maydonlardan farqlash uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:150
msgid ""
"Like for classic models defined in Python, Odoo will automatically add "
"several fields to the model:"
msgstr ""
"Pythonda aniqlangan klassik modellardagi kabi, Odoo modelga bir nechta "
"maydonlarni avtomatik qo'shadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:152
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.id` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Id`) The unique "
"identifier for a record of the model."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.id` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Id`) Model yozuvining "
"noyob identifikatori."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:154
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.create_date` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Datetime`) "
"Creation date of the record."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.create_date` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Datetime`) "
"Yozuv yaratilgan sana."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:156
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.create_uid` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Many2one`) "
"User who created the record."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.create_uid` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Many2one`) "
"Yozuvni yaratgan foydalanuvchi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:158
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.write_date` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Datetime`) "
"Last modification date of the record."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.write_date` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Datetime`) "
"Yozuvning oxirgi o'zgartirilgan sanasi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:160
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.write_uid` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Many2one`) "
"User who last modified the record."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Model.write_uid` (:class:`~odoo.fields.Many2one`) "
"Yozuvni oxirgi marta o'zgartirgan foydalanuvchi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:163
msgid ""
"We can also add several fields to our new model. Let's add some simple "
"fields, like a name (string), selling price (float), a description (as "
"html), and a postcode (as a char)."
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, yangi modelimizga bir nechta maydonlar qo'shishimiz mumkin. "
"Nom (string), sotish narxi (float), tavsif (html sifatida) va pochta indeksi "
"(char sifatida) kabi oddiy maydonlar qo'shamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:166
msgid ""
"Like for models, fields are simply records of the `ir.model.fields` model"
" and can be defined as such in data files:"
msgstr ""
"Modellar kabi, maydonlar ham shunchaki `ir.model.fields` modelining yozuvlari "
"va ma'lumot fayllarida shu tarzda aniqlanishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:205
msgid ""
"You can set various attributes for your new field. For basic fields, "
"these include:"
msgstr ""
"Yangi maydoningiz uchun turli atributlarni o'rnatishingiz mumkin. Asosiy "
"maydonlar uchun bular:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:207
msgid "`name`: the technical name of the field (must begin with `x_`)"
msgstr "`name`: maydonning texnik nomi (`x_` bilan boshlanishi kerak)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:208
msgid "`field_description`: the label of the field"
msgstr "`field_description`: maydon yorlig'i"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:209
msgid "`help`: a help text for the field, displayed in the interface"
msgstr "`help`: interfeysdagi maydon uchun yordam matni"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:210
msgid ""
"`ttype`: the type of the field (e.g. `char`, `integer`, `float`, `html`, "
"etc.)"
msgstr "`ttype`: maydon turi (masalan, `char`, `integer`, `float`, `html` va h.k.)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:211
msgid "`required`: whether the field is required or not (default: `False`)"
msgstr "`required`: maydon majburiy yoki yo'qligi (standart: `False`)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:212
msgid "`readonly`: whether the field is read-only or not (default: `False`)"
msgstr "`readonly`: maydon faqat o'qish uchun yoki yo'qligi (standart: `False`)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:213
msgid "`index`: whether the field is indexed or not (default: `False`)"
msgstr "`index`: maydon indekslangan yoki yo'qligi (standart: `False`)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:214
msgid ""
"`copied`: whether the field is copied when duplicating a record or not "
"(default: `True` for non-relational non-computed fields, `False` for "
"relational and computed fields)"
msgstr ""
"`copied`: yozuvni nusxalashda maydon nusxalanishi yoki nusxalanmasligi "
"(standart: relatsion bo'lmagan va hisoblanbagan maydonlar uchun `True`, "
"relatsion va hisoblangan maydonlar uchun `False`)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:216
msgid "`translate`: whether the field is translatable or not (default: `False`)"
msgstr "`translate`: maydon tarjima qilinishi yoki yo'qligi (standart: `False`)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:218
msgid ""
"Attributes are also available to control HTML sanitization as well as "
"other, more advanced features; for a complete list, refer to the "
"`ir.model.fields` model in the database available in the "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Database Structure --> Fields`"
" menu or see the `ir.model.fields` model definition in the `base` module."
msgstr ""
"HTML sanitizatsiyasini nazorat qilish va boshqa, yanada rivojlangan "
"xususiyatlar uchun atributlar ham mavjud; to'liq ro'yxat uchun "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Database Structure --> Fields` "
"menyusida mavjud bo'lgan ma'lumotlar bazasidagi `ir.model.fields` modeliga "
"yoki `base` modulidagi `ir.model.fields` model ta'rifiga qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:225
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/03_basicmodel.rst:182
msgid "Add the following basic fields to the table:"
msgstr "Jadvalga quyidagi asosiy maydonlarni qo'shing:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:228
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:360
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:372
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:407
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:446
msgid "Required"
msgstr "Majburiy"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:230
msgid "x_date_availability"
msgstr "x_date_availability"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:231
msgid "x_expected_price"
msgstr "x_expected_price"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:231
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:448
