":ref:`reference/fields/compute`."
msgstr ""
"**Havola**: ushbu mavzu bilan bog'liq hujjatlar :ref:`reference/fields/compute` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:474
msgid ""
"Data modules can define computed fields of any type, but are quite "
"limited compared to Python modules. Indeed, since data modules are meant "
"to be deployed on systems that do not allow arbitrary code to run, the "
"Python code that is allowed is very limited."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumot modullari har qanday turdagi hisoblangan maydonlarni aniqlay oladi, "
"lekin Python modullariga nisbatan ancha cheklangan. Haqiqatan ham, ma'lumot "
"modullari ixtiyoriy kodni ishga tushirishga ruxsat bermaydigan tizimlarda "
"joylashtirilishi mo'ljallanganligi sababli, ruxsat etilgan Python kodi juda "
"cheklangan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:479
msgid ""
"All Python code written for data modules is executed in a sandboxed "
"environment that limits the operations that can be performed. For "
"example, you cannot import libraries, you cannot access any OS files, and"
" you cannot even print to the console. Some utilities are provided, but "
"this varies with the type of sandboxed environment that is used."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumot modullari uchun yozilgan barcha Python kodi bajarilishi mumkin bo'lgan "
"amallarni cheklaydigan sandbox muhitida bajariladi. Masalan, kutubxonalarni "
"import qila olmaysiz, OS fayllariga kira olmaysiz va hatto konsolga chiqara "
"olmaysiz. Ba'zi yordamchi vositalar taqdim etiladi, lekin bu foydalaniladigan "
"sandbox muhiti turiga qarab farq qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:484
msgid ""
"In the case of compute methods, the sandbox is very limited and only "
"provides the bare minimum of utilities to allow the execution of the "
"code. In addition to the Python builtins, you also have access to the "
"`datetime`, `dateutil` and `time` modules (e.g., to help with date "
"calculations)."
msgstr ""
"Hisoblash metodlari holatida, sandbox juda cheklangan va faqat kodni "
"bajarishga imkon beradigan minimal yordamchi vositalarni taqdim etadi. "
"Python builtins dan tashqari, `datetime`, `dateutil` va `time` modullariga "
"ham kirish imkoniyatingiz bor (masalan, sana hisob-kitoblarga yordam berish uchun)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:489
msgid ""
"Note also that \"dot assignation\" is disabled in the sandbox, so you "
"cannot write ``property.x_total_area = 1`` in the compute method. You "
"have to use dictionary access: ``property['x_total_area'] = 1``. Dot "
"notation for field *access* works normally: ``property.x_garden_area`` "
"will return the value of the ``x_garden_area`` field."
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, \"nuqta bilan belgilash\" sandboxda o'chirilganligini unutmang, "
"shuning uchun hisoblash metodida ``property.x_total_area = 1`` yoza olmaysiz. "
"Lug'at kirishidan foydalanishingiz kerak: ``property['x_total_area'] = 1``. "
"Maydonga *kirish* uchun nuqta notatsiyasi odatdagidek ishlaydi: "
"``property.x_garden_area`` ``x_garden_area`` maydon qiymatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:495
msgid ""
"We previously defined two \"area\" fields on our ``x_estate.property`` "
"model: ``living_area`` and ``garden_area``. To define a computed field on"
" the model that returns the sum of the two areas, we can add the "
"following code to our data module:"
msgstr ""
"Ilgari ``x_estate.property`` modelimizda ikkita \"maydon\" maydonini aniqladik: "
"``living_area`` va ``garden_area``. Ikki maydoning yig'indisini qaytaradigan "
"hisoblangan maydonni modelda aniqlash uchun ma'lumot modulimizga quyidagi "
"kodni qo'shishimiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:518
msgid ""
"Whilst in server actions, you iterate on a `records` variable, in the "
"case of a computed field, you iterate on a `self` variable that contains "
"the recordset on which the field is computed."
msgstr ""
"Server amallarda `records` o'zgaruvchisi bo'yicha takrorlashsangiz, hisoblangan "
"maydon holatida maydon hisoblanadigan yozuvlar to'plamini o'z ichiga olgan "
"`self` o'zgaruvchisi bo'yicha takrorlaysiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:521
msgid ""
"The ``depends`` attribute is used to define the fields that the computed "
"field depends on and the ``compute`` attribute is used to define the code"
" that is executed to compute the field (using Python code)."
msgstr ""
"``depends`` atributi hisoblangan maydon bog'liq bo'lgan maydonlarni aniqlash "
"uchun ishlatiladi va ``compute`` atributi maydonni hisoblash uchun bajariladigan "
"kodni (Python kodi yordamida) aniqlash uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:525
msgid ""
"Unlike in Python modules, computed fields are stored by default. If you "
"wish for a computed field to not be stored (e.g., for performance reasons"
" or to avoid database bloat), you can set the ``store`` attribute to "
"``False``. The same applies to ``readonly``: if you want your computed "
"field to not be editable, you need to set the ``readonly`` attribute to "
"``True``."
msgstr ""
"Python modullaridan farqli o'laroq, hisoblangan maydonlar standart bo'yicha "
"saqlanadi. Agar hisoblangan maydon saqlanmaslini xohlasangiz (masalan, "
"ishlash sabablari yoki ma'lumotlar bazasining ortib ketishidan qochish uchun), "
"``store`` atributini ``False`` ga o'rnatishingiz mumkin. Xuddi shu ``readonly`` ga "
"ham tegishli: agar hisoblangan maydoningiz tahrirlana olmasligini xohlasangiz, "
"``readonly`` atributini ``True`` ga o'rnatishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:530
msgid ""
"The `CDATA` section is used to specify to XML parsers that the content is"
" a string and not XML; this prevents the parser from trying to interpret "
"the Python code as XML, or the addition of extra space, etc. when the "
"code gets inserted into the database at module install time."
msgstr ""
"`CDATA` bo'limi XML parserlariga kontent XML emas, balki satr ekanligini "
"ko'rsatish uchun ishlatiladi; bu parserni modul o'rnatish vaqtida kod "
"ma'lumotlar bazasiga kiritilganda Python kodini XML sifatida talqin "
"qilishga yoki qo'shimcha bo'sh joy qo'shishga urinishdan to'xtatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:536
msgid ""
"Add a computed field to the ``x_estate.property`` model that returns the "
"sum of the ``x_living_area`` and ``x_garden_area`` fields, as shown "
"above."
msgstr ""
"``x_estate.property`` modeliga yuqorida ko'rsatilganidek ``x_living_area`` "
"va ``x_garden_area`` maydonlari yig'indisini qaytaradigan hisoblangan "
"maydon qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:538
msgid "Include the field in the form view of the ``x_estate.property`` model."
msgstr "Maydonni ``x_estate.property`` modelining forma ko'rinishiga qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:541
msgid ""
"Unlike in Python modules, it is not possible to define an inverse or "
"search method for computed fields."
msgstr ""
"Python modullaridan farqli o'laroq, hisoblangan maydonlar uchun teskari yoki "
"qidiruv metodini aniqlash mumkin emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:547
msgid ""
"Related fields are a simplified form of computed fields that mirror the "
"value of another field through a many2one relationship."
msgstr ""
"Bog'liq maydonlar many2one munosabati orqali boshqa maydon qiymatini aks "
"ettiradigan hisoblangan maydonlarning soddalashtirilgan shaklidir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:550
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
":ref:`reference/fields/related`."
msgstr ""
"**Havola**: ushbu mavzu bilan bog'liq hujjatlar :ref:`reference/fields/related` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:553
msgid ""
"Related fields can be of any type (the type of the field at the other end"
" of the relation traversal). They are defined as if one were adding the "
"field directly to the model with the addition of a ``related`` attribute "
"that specifies the target field on the related model that contains the "
"value to be mirrored."
msgstr ""
"Bog'liq maydonlar har qanday turdagi bo'lishi mumkin (munosabat traversali "
"boshqa uchidagi maydon turi). Ular aks ettirilishi kerak bo'lgan qiymatni "
"o'z ichiga olgan bog'liq modeldagi maqsadli maydonni ko'rsatadigan "
"``related`` atributini qo'shish bilan maydonni to'g'ridan-to'g'ri modelga "
"qo'shayotgandek aniqlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:558
msgid ""
"For example, if we want to access the country of the buyer directly from "
"the ``x_estate.property`` model, we can add the following code to our "
"data module:"
msgstr ""
"Masalan, agar ``x_estate.property`` modelidan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri xaridorning "
"mamlakatiga kirmoqchi bo'lsak, ma'lumot modulimizga quyidagi kodni qo'shishimiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:575
msgid ""
"The ``related`` attribute is used to specify the target field on the "
"related model that contains the value to be mirrored. This must be a dot-"
"separated list of field names."
msgstr ""
"``related`` atributi aks ettirilishi kerak bo'lgan qiymatni o'z ichiga olgan "
"bog'liq modeldagi maqsadli maydonni ko'rsatish uchun ishlatiladi. Bu nuqta "
"bilan ajratilgan maydonlar nomlari ro'yxati bo'lishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:579
msgid "Code and business logic"
msgstr "Kod va biznes mantiq"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:582
msgid "Server actions"
msgstr "Server amallari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:584
msgid ""
"In a Python module, you are free to define any method on your model. One "
"common usage pattern is to add so-called \"actions\" methods to your "
"model then bind these methods to buttons in the UI (e.g to confirm a "
"quote, post an invoice, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Python modulida modelingizda har qanday metodni aniqlashingiz mumkin. "
"Keng tarqalgan foydalanish naqshi modelingizga \"amallar\" metodlarini qo'shish, "
"so'ngra bu metodlarni UI dagi tugmalar bilan bog'lashdir (masalan, tijorat "
"taklifini tasdiqlash, hisob-faktura yuborish va h.k.)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:588
msgid ""
"In a data module, you can achieve the same effect by defining "
":ref:`Server Actions <reference/actions/server>` bound to your model. "
"Server actions represent pieces of logic that are run dynamically on the "
"server. These actions can be configured manually in the database directly"
" via the :menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Actions --> Server "
"Actions` menu and can be of different types; in our case, we will use the"
" ``code`` type which allows us to run any Python code in a sandboxed "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumot modulida, modelingizga bog'langan :ref:`Server Amallari "
"<reference/actions/server>` aniqlab xuddi shunday ta'sirga erishishingiz mumkin. "
"Server amallari serverda dinamik ravishda bajariladigan mantiq bo'laklarini "
"ifodalaydi. Bu amallar :menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Actions --> "
"Server Actions` menyusi orqali bevosita ma'lumotlar bazasida qo'lda sozlanishi "
"va turli turlarda bo'lishi mumkin; bizning holatimizda, sandboxlangan muhitda "
"har qanday Python kodini ishga tushirishga imkon beruvchi ``code`` turini ishlatamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:596
msgid ""
"This environment contains several utilities to help you interact with the"
" Odoo database:"
msgstr "Bu muhit Odoo ma'lumotlar bazasi bilan o'zaro ta'sir qilishga yordam beradigan bir nechta yordamchi vositalarni o'z ichiga oladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:598
msgid "``env``: the environment of the record"
msgstr "``env``: yozuv muhiti"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:599
msgid "``model``: the model of the record"
msgstr "``model``: yozuv modeli"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:600
msgid "``user`` and ``uid``: the current user and their id"
msgstr "``user`` va ``uid``: joriy foydalanuvchi va uning identifikatori"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:601
msgid ""
"``datetime``, ``dateutil``, ``timezone`` and ``time``: libraries to help "
"with date/time calculations"
msgstr ""
"``datetime``, ``dateutil``, ``timezone`` va ``time``: sana/vaqt hisob-kitoblariga yordam beradigan kutubxonalar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:603
msgid ""
"``float_compare``: a utility function to compare two float values with a "
"given precision"
msgstr "``float_compare``: berilgan aniqlik bilan ikkita float qiymatini solishtiruvchi yordamchi funksiya"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:604
msgid ""
"``b64encode`` and ``b64decode``: utility functions to encode and decode "
"values in base64"
msgstr "``b64encode`` va ``b64decode``: qiymatlarni base64 da kodlash va dekodlash uchun yordamchi funksiyalar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:605
msgid ""
"``Command``: a utility class to help build complex expressions and "
"commands (see the `Command` class in the :ref:`ORM reference "
"<reference/fields/relational>`)"
msgstr ""
"``Command``: murakkab ifodalar va buyruqlar tuzishga yordam beruvchi yordamchi "
"sinf (:ref:`ORM havolasi <reference/fields/relational>` dagi `Command` sinfiga qarang)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:608
msgid ""
"In addition, you have access to the recordset on which the action is "
"executed (typically a single record when the action is executed from a "
"form view, and multiple records when the action is executed from a list "
"view) via the ``record`` and ``records`` variables."
msgstr ""
"Bundan tashqari, ``record`` va ``records`` o'zgaruvchilari orqali amal "
"bajariladigan yozuvlar to'plamiga kirish imkoniyatiga egasiz (odatda forma "
"ko'rinishidan bajarilganda bitta yozuv, ro'yxat ko'rinishidan bajarilganda "
"bir nechta yozuv)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:613
msgid ""
"If your action needs to return an action to the client (for example to "
"redirect the user to another view), you can assign it to a an ``action`` "
"variable inside your server action's code. The code sandbox will inspect "
"the variables defined in your code after its execution and will "
"automatically return it if it detects the presence of an ``action`` "
"variable."
msgstr ""
"Agar amalingiz mijozga amal qaytarishi kerak bo'lsa (masalan, foydalanuvchini "
"boshqa ko'rinishga yo'naltirish uchun), server amali kodingiz ichidagi "
"``action`` o'zgaruvchisiga uni tayinlashingiz mumkin. Kod sandboxi bajarilgandan "
"keyin kodingizda aniqlangan o'zgaruvchilarni tekshiradi va ``action`` "
"o'zgaruvchisining mavjudligini aniqlasa uni avtomatik qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:618
msgid ""
"If the `website` module is installed, the `request` object will be "
"available in the code sandbox and you can assign a `response` object to "
"the `response` variable to return a response to the client in a similar "
"way. This is explored in more details in the "
":ref:`tutorials/importable_modules/website_controllers` section."
msgstr ""
"Agar `website` moduli o'rnatilgan bo'lsa, `request` obyekti kod sandboxida "
"mavjud bo'ladi va o'xshash usulda mijozga javob qaytarish uchun `response` "
"o'zgaruvchisiga `response` obyektini tayinlashingiz mumkin. Bu "
":ref:`tutorials/importable_modules/website_controllers` bo'limida batafsil "
"o'rganiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:623
msgid ""
"For example, we could define an action on the ``x_estate.property`` model"
" that sets the ``x_status`` field of all its offers to ``Refused``:"
msgstr ""
"Masalan, barcha takliflarning ``x_status`` maydonini ``Refused`` ga o'rnatadigam "
"``x_estate.property`` modelida amal aniqlashimiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:638
msgid ""
"To include this action as a button in the form view of the "
"``x_estate.property`` model, we can add the following :ref:`button "
"<reference/view_architectures/form/button>` node in the header of our "
"form view:"
msgstr ""
"Bu amalni ``x_estate.property`` modelining forma ko'rinishida tugma sifatida "
"qo'shish uchun, forma ko'rinishimizning sarlavhasiga quyidagi :ref:`button "
"<reference/view_architectures/form/button>` tugunini qo'shishimiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:649
msgid ""
"It is also possible to add an entry in the gear icon (:icon:`fa-gear`) to"
" run this action (e.g. to avoid adding buttons to views that are already "
"crowded). To do so, you can *bind* your server action to the model and to"
" specific types of views:"
msgstr ""
"Bu amalni ishga tushirish uchun tishli g'ildirak belgisiga (:icon:`fa-gear`) "
"yozuv qo'shish ham mumkin (masalan, allaqachon band bo'lgan ko'rinishlarga "
"tugmalar qo'shishdan qochish uchun). Buning uchun server amallangizni modelga "
"va ko'rinishlarning muayyan turlariga *bog'lashingiz* mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:667
msgid ""
"This will make the action available in the gear icon (:icon:`fa-gear`) of"
" the ``x_estate.property`` model, in the list (when one or more records "
"are selected via the checkbox) and form views."
msgstr ""
"Bu amalning ``x_estate.property`` modelining tishli g'ildirak belgisida "
"(:icon:`fa-gear`), ro'yxatda (belgilash katakchasi orqali bir yoki bir nechta "
"yozuv tanlanganda) va forma ko'rinishlarida mavjud bo'lishini ta'minlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:672
msgid ""
"Add a server action to the ``x_estate.property.offer`` model that sets "
"the ``x_status`` field of an offer to ``Accepted`` and updates the "
"selling price and buyer of the property to which the offer is attached "
"accordingly. This action should also mark all the other offers on the "
"same property as ``Refused``."
msgstr ""
"``x_estate.property.offer`` modeliga taklif ``x_status`` maydonini "
"``Accepted`` ga o'rnatadigam va taklifga biriktirilgan mulkning sotish "
"narxini va xaridorini tegishli ravishda yangilaydigam server amali qo'shing. "
"Bu amal shuningdek bir xil mulkdagi barcha boshqa takliflarni ``Refused`` "
"deb belgilashi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:676
msgid ""
"Include a button in the embedded list view of offers that allows to "
"execute this action"
msgstr "Ushbu amalni bajarishga imkon beruvchi takliflarning ichki ro'yxat ko'rinishiga tugma qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:682
msgid "Overriding Python models"
msgstr "Python modellarini bekor qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:685
msgid "Via UI elements"
msgstr "UI elementlari orqali"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:687
msgid ""
"Unlike in Python modules, it is not possible to override a Python model's"
" method cleanly."
msgstr "Python modullaridan farqli o'laroq, Python modelining metodini tozalab bekor qilish mumkin emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:689
msgid ""
"However, it is possible (in some cases) to replace the elements of the UI"
" that call these methods and to intercept the calls to these methods in a"
" server action."
msgstr ""
"Biroq, (ba'zi holatlarda) bu metodlarni chaqiradigan UI elementlarini almashtirish "
"va bu metodlarga chaqiruvlarni server amalida ushlab qolish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:692
msgid ""
"A typical example would be an integration with the ``Sales`` app of Odoo."
" Let's imagine that your Real Estate module integrates with the Sales "
"application so that when a specific product is sold (e.g., a quote for "
"managing the sale of a property), you want to automatically create a new "
"property record in your module."
msgstr ""
"Odatdagi misol Odoo ning ``Sales`` ilovasi bilan integratsiya bo'ladi. "
"Ko'chmas mulk modulingiz Savdo ilovasi bilan integratsiyalashganligini "
"tasavvur qiling, shunda muayyan mahsulot sotilganda (masalan, mulk sotishni "
"boshqarish uchun taklif), modulingizda avtomatik ravishda yangi mulk yozuvini "
"yaratishni xohlaysiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:697
msgid "To achieve this, you will need to:"
msgstr "Bunga erishish uchun siz:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:699
msgid ""
"create a server action that calls the original method of the button and "
"add custom logic before or after that method call"
msgstr "tugmaning asl metodini chaqiradigan server amal yarating va bu metod chaqiruvidan oldin yoki keyin maxsus mantiq qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:701
msgid ""
"replace the button in the view with a custom button that calls the server"
" action"
msgstr "ko'rinishdagi tugmani server amalini chaqiradigan maxsus tugma bilan almashtiring"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:741
msgid "Via automation rules"
msgstr "Avtomatlashtirish qoidalari orqali"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:743
msgid ""
"Automations rules are a way to automatically execute actions on records "
"in the database based on specific triggers, like state changes, addition "
"of a tag, etc. They can be useful to tie behaviour to life-cycle events "
"of records, for example by sending an email when an offer is accepted."
msgstr ""
"Avtomatlashtirish qoidalari holat o'zgarishlari, teg qo'shish va h.k. kabi "
"muayyan triggerlar asosida ma'lumotlar bazasidagi yozuvlarda amallarni "
"avtomatik bajarish usulidir. Ular yozuvlarning hayot tsikli hodisalariga "
"xatti-harakatlarni bog'lash uchun foydali bo'lishi mumkin, masalan, taklif "
"qabul qilinganda elektron pochta yuborish."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:747
msgid ""
"Using automation rules for extending a standard behaviour can be more "
"robust than the UI-based approach since it will also run if the life-"
"cycle event is triggered in another way than via a button (e.g., via a "
"webhook or a direct call to the method; for example when a quote is "
"confirmed via the portal or the e-commerce). They are however a bit more "
"finicky to set up properly, as one needs to ensure that the automation "
"will only run at the proper moment by setting up specific fields to "
"watch, etc."
msgstr ""
"Standart xatti-harakatni kengaytirish uchun avtomatlashtirish qoidalaridan "
"foydalanish UI ga asoslangan yondashuvdan ko'ra ishonchliroq bo'lishi mumkin, "
"chunki hayot tsikli hodisasi tugma orqali emas, boshqa usulda (masalan, webhook "
"yoki metodga to'g'ridan-to'g'ri chaqiruv; masalan, taklif portal yoki e-tijorat "
"orqali tasdiqlanganda) ishga tushirilganda ham ishlaydi. Biroq, ular to'g'ri "
"sozlash uchun biroz murakkablik, chunki kuzatish uchun muayyan maydonlarni "
"o'rnatib, avtomatlashtirish faqat to'g'ri vaqtda ishga tushishini ta'minlash kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:754
msgid ""
"**Documentation**: a more complete documentation related to this topic "
"can be found in :doc:`/applications/studio/automated_actions`."
msgstr ""
"**Hujjat**: ushbu mavzu bilan bog'liq to'liqroq hujjatlar "
":doc:`/applications/studio/automated_actions` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:758
msgid ""
"Automation Rules are not part of the ``base`` module; they come with the "
"``base_automation`` module; so if you define automation rules in your "
"data module, you need to make sure that ``base_automation`` is part of "
"your module's dependencies."
msgstr ""
"Avtomatlashtirish Qoidalari ``base`` modulining bir qismi emas; ular "
"``base_automation`` moduli bilan keladi; shuning uchun agar ma'lumot "
"modulingizda avtomatlashtirish qoidalarini aniqlasangiz, ``base_automation`` "
"modulingizning bog'liqliklarining bir qismi ekanligiga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:762
msgid ""
"Once installed, Automation Rules are managed via the "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Automations --> Automation "
"Rules` menu."
msgstr ""
"O'rnatilgandan so'ng, Avtomatlashtirish Qoidalari "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Technical --> Automations --> Automation Rules` "
"menyusi orqali boshqariladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:765
msgid ""
"Automation Rules are particularly useful to tie a data module to an "
"existing standard Odoo module. Since data modules cannot override "
"methods, tying automation to life-cycle changes of standard models is a "
"common way to extend standard modules."
msgstr ""
"Avtomatlashtirish Qoidalari ma'lumot modulini mavjud standart Odoo moduliga "
"bog'lash uchun ayniqsa foydali. Ma'lumot modullari metodlarni bekor qila "
"olmaydi, shuning uchun standart modellarning hayot tsikli o'zgarishlariga "
"avtomatlashtirishni bog'lash standart modullarni kengaytirishning keng "
"tarqalgan usulidir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:769
msgid ""
"If we were to rewrite our example from the previous section using "
"automation rules, a few changes would be needed:"
msgstr ""
"Agar oldingi bo'limdagi misolimizni avtomatlashtirish qoidalaridan foydalanib "
"qayta yozsak, bir nechta o'zgartirishlar kerak bo'lardi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:772
msgid ""
"the server action should no longer call the original method of the button"
" (instead, the original method will trigger the change that will fire the"
" automation rule)"
msgstr ""
"server amal endi tugmaning asl metodini chaqirmasligi kerak (buning o'rniga, "
"asl metod avtomatlashtirish qoidasini ishga tushiradigan o'zgarishni ishga tushiradi)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:774
msgid "the view extension is not needed"
msgstr "ko'rinish kengaytmasi kerak emas"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:775
msgid ""
"we need to define an Automation Rule to trigger the server action on the "
"appropriate event"
msgstr "tegishli hodisada server amalni ishga tushirish uchun Avtomatlashtirish Qoidasini aniqlashimiz kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:805
msgid ""
"Note that the :ref:`XML IDs <tutorials/define_module_data/xml_id>` to "
"standard Odoo models, fields, selection values, etc. can be found in the "
"Odoo instance itself by navigating to the appropriate record in the "
"technical menus and using the ``View Metadata`` menu entry of the debug "
"menu. XML IDs for models are simply the model name with dots replaced by "
"underscores and prefixed by ``model_`` (e.g., ``sale.model_sale_order`` "
"is ``sale.order`` as defined in the `sale` module); XML IDs for fields "
"are the model name with dots replaced by underscores and prefixed by "
"``field_``, the model's name and the field name (e.g., "
"``sale.field_sale_order__name`` is the XML ID for the ``name`` field of "
"the ``sale.order`` model which is defined in the `sale` module)."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, standart Odoo modellari, maydonlari, tanlov qiymatlari va "
"h.k. ga :ref:`XML IDlar <tutorials/define_module_data/xml_id>` Odoo instansning "
"o'zida texnik menyular orqali tegishli yozuvga o'tib va debug menyusining "
"``View Metadata`` menyu bandidan foydalanib topish mumkin. Modellar uchun "
"XML IDlar shunchaki nuqtalar pastki chiziq bilan almashtirilgan va ``model_`` "
"bilan prefiks qo'yilgan model nomi (masalan, ``sale.model_sale_order`` "
"`sale` modulida aniqlangan ``sale.order`` dir); maydonlar uchun XML IDlar "
"nuqtalar pastki chiziq bilan almashtirilgan va ``field_``, modelning nomi va "
"maydon nomi bilan prefiks qo'yilgan model nomi (masalan, "
"``sale.field_sale_order__name`` `sale` modulida aniqlangan ``sale.order`` "
"modelining ``name`` maydoni uchun XML ID dir)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:817
msgid "Website controllers"
msgstr "Veb-sayt controllerlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:819
msgid ""
"HTTP Controllers in Odoo are usually defined in the :file:`controllers` "
"directory of a module. In data modules, it is possible to define server "
"actions that behave as controllers if the website module is installed."
msgstr ""
"Odoo dagi HTTP Controllerlari odatda modul :file:`controllers` papkasida "
"aniqlanadi. Ma'lumot modullarida, agar website moduli o'rnatilgan bo'lsa, "
"controllerlar kabi ishlaydigan server amallarini aniqlash mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:823
msgid ""
"When the website module is installed, server actions can be marked as "
"`Available on the website` and given a path (the full path is always "
"prefixed with `/website/action` to avoid URL collisions); the global "
"`request` object is made available in the local scope of the code server "
"action."
msgstr ""
"Website moduli o'rnatilganda, server amallar `Available on the website` "
"deb belgilanishi va yo'l berilishi mumkin (URL to'qnashuvlaridan qochish "
"uchun to'liq yo'l har doim `/website/action` bilan boshlanadi); global "
"`request` obyekti kod server amalining mahalliy ko'lamida mavjud bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:827
msgid ""
"The `request` object provides several methods to access the body of the "
"request:"
msgstr "`request` obyekti so'rov tanasiga kirish uchun bir nechta metodlarni taqdim etadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:829
msgid ""
"`request.get_http_params()`: extract key-value pairs from the query "
"string and the forms present in the body (both `application/x-www-form-"
"urlencoded` and `multipart/form-data`)."
msgstr ""
"`request.get_http_params()`: so'rov satridan va tanada mavjud formalardan "
"kalit-qiymat juftlarini ajratib oladi (ham `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` "
"ham `multipart/form-data`)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:831
msgid ""
"`request.get_json_data()`: extract the JSON data from the body of the "
"request."
msgstr "`request.get_json_data()`: so'rov tanasidan JSON ma'lumotlarini ajratib oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:833
msgid ""
"Since it is not possible to return a value from within a server action, "
"to define the response to return, one can assign a response-like object "
"to the `response` variable, which will be returned to the website "
"automatically."
msgstr ""
"Server amalidan qiymat qaytarish mumkin emasligi sababli, qaytariladigan javobni "
"aniqlash uchun `response` o'zgaruvchisiga javobga o'xshash obyektni tayinlash "
"mumkin, u veb-saytga avtomatik ravishda qaytariladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:837
msgid ""
"Here is an example of a simple website controller that will return a list"
" of properties when the URL `/website/action/estate` is called:"
msgstr ""
"`/website/action/estate` URL si chaqirilganda mulklar ro'yxatini qaytaradigan "
"oddiy veb-sayt controllerining namunasi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:857
msgid ""
"Several useful methods are available in the `request` object to "
"facilitate the generation of the response object:"
msgstr ""
"Javob obyektini yaratishni osonlashtirish uchun `request` obyektida bir nechta "
"foydali metodlar mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:860
msgid ""
"`request.render(template, qcontext=None, lazy=True, **kw)` to render a "
"QWeb template using its xmlid; the extra keyword arguments are forwarded "
"to the `werkzeug.Response` object (e.g. to set cookies, headers, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"`request.render(template, qcontext=None, lazy=True, **kw)` xmlid yordamida "
"QWeb shablonini render qilish uchun; qo'shimcha kalit so'z argumentlari "
"`werkzeug.Response` obyektiga yo'naltiriladi (masalan, cookie lar, sarlavhalar va h.k. o'rnatish uchun)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:863
msgid ""
"`request.redirect(location, code=303, local=True)` to redirect to a "
"different URL; the `local` argument is used to specify whether the "
"redirection should be relative to the website or not (default: `True`)."
msgstr ""
"`request.redirect(location, code=303, local=True)` boshqa URL ga yo'naltirish uchun; "
"`local` argumenti yo'naltirishning veb-saytga nisbatan bo'lishi yoki bo'lmasligini "
"ko'rsatish uchun ishlatiladi (standart: `True`)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:866
msgid ""
"`request.not_found()` to return a `werkzeug.HTTPException` exception to "
"signal a 404 error to the website."
msgstr ""
"`request.not_found()` veb-saytga 404 xatosini bildirish uchun "
"`werkzeug.HTTPException` istisnosi qaytarish uchun."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:868
msgid ""
"`request.make_response(data, headers=None, cookies=None, status=200)` to "
"manually create a `werkzeug.Response` object; the `status` argument is "
"the HTTP status code to return (default: 200)."
msgstr ""
"`request.make_response(data, headers=None, cookies=None, status=200)` "
"qo'lda `werkzeug.Response` obyekti yaratish uchun; `status` argumenti "
"qaytariladigan HTTP holat kodi (standart: 200)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:871
msgid ""
"`request.make_json_response(data, headers=None, cookies=None, "
"status=200)` to manually create a JSON response; the data will be json-"
"serialized using `json.dumps` utility; this can be useful to set up "
"server-to-server communications via API calls."
msgstr ""
"`request.make_json_response(data, headers=None, cookies=None, status=200)` "
"qo'lda JSON javob yaratish uchun; ma'lumotlar `json.dumps` yordamchi vositasi "
"yordamida json-serializatsiya qilinadi; bu API chaqiruvlari orqali server-server "
"aloqalarini sozlash uchun foydali bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:875
msgid ""
"For implementation details or other (less common) methods, refer to the "
"`Request` object's implementation in the `odoo.http` module."
msgstr ""
"Amalga oshirish tafsilotlari yoki boshqa (kamroq tarqalgan) metodlar uchun "
"`odoo.http` modulidagi `Request` obyektini amalga oshirishga qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:878
msgid ""
"Note that security concerns are left to the developer (typically through "
"security rules or by using `sudo` to access records)."
msgstr ""
"Xavfsizlik muammolari dasturchiga qoldirilganligini unutmang (odatda xavfsizlik "
"qoidalari orqali yoki yozuvlarga kirish uchun `sudo` dan foydalanib)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:882
msgid ""
"The model used in the `model_id` field of the server action must be "
"accessible to the public user for the write operation for this server "
"action to run; otherwise the server action will return a 403 error. A way"
" to avoid giving access is to link your server action to a model that is "
"already accessible to the public user, a typical (if weird) example is to"
" link the server action to the `ir.filters` model."
msgstr ""
"Server amalning `model_id` maydonida ishlatiladigan model bu server amal "
"ishga tushishi uchun yozish operatsiyasi uchun ommaviy foydalanuvchiga "
"ochiq bo'lishi kerak; aks holda server amal 403 xatosini qaytaradi. Kirish "
"bermaslikdan qochishning bir usuli - server amalini ommaviy foydalanuvchiga "
"allaqachon ochiq bo'lgan modelga bog'lashdir, odatdagi (agar g'alati bo'lsa) "
"misol server amalni `ir.filters` modeliga bog'lashdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:890
msgid ""
"Add a JSON API to your module so that external services can retrieve a "
"list of properties for sale."
msgstr ""
"Tashqi xizmatlar sotuvdagi mulklar ro'yxatini olish imkoniyatiga ega bo'lishi "
"uchun modulingizga JSON API qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:893
msgid ""
"add a new `x_api_published` field to the model to control whether the "
"properties are published on the API or not"
msgstr "mulklar API da nashr etilgan yoki yo'qligini nazorat qilish uchun modelga yangi `x_api_published` maydoni qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:895
msgid ""
"add an access right record to allow public users to read and write the "
"model"
msgstr "ommaviy foydalanuvchilarga modelni o'qish va yozish imkonini beruvchi kirish huquqi yozuvini qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:896
msgid ""
"prevent any write from the public user by adding a record rule for the "
"write operation with an impossible domain (e.g. `[('id', '=', False)]`)"
msgstr ""
"mumkin bo'lmagan domen (masalan, `[('id', '=', False)]`) bilan yozish operatsiyasi "
"uchun yozuv qoidasi qo'shib ommaviy foydalanuvchidan har qanday yozishning oldini oling"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:898
msgid ""
"add a record rule so that properties marked as `x_api_published` can be "
"read by the public user"
msgstr "`x_api_published` deb belgilangan mulklar ommaviy foydalanuvchi tomonidan o'qilishi uchun yozuv qoidasini qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:900
msgid ""
"add a server action to return a list of properties in JSON format when "
"the URL `/website/action/estate` is called"
msgstr "`/website/action/estate` URL si chaqirilganda JSON formatida mulklar ro'yxatini qaytaruvchi server amali qo'shing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:904
msgid "A sprinkle of JavaScript"
msgstr "Bir mikdor JavaScript"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:906
msgid ""
"Whilst importable modules cannot include Python files, no such "
"restriction exists for JavaScript files. Adding JavaScript files to your "
"importable module is exactly the same as adding them to a standard Odoo "
"module."
msgstr ""
"Import qilinadigan modullar Python fayllarini o'z ichiga ola olmasa-da, "
"JavaScript fayllari uchun bunday cheklov mavjud emas. Import qilinadigan "
"modulingizga JavaScript fayllarini qo'shish standart Odoo moduliga ularni "
"qo'shish bilan aynan bir xil."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:910
msgid ""
"This means that an importable module can include new field components or "
"even entirely new views."
msgstr ""
"Bu import qilinadigan modul yangi maydon komponentlarini yoki hatto butunlay "
"yangi ko'rinishlarni o'z ichiga olishi mumkinligini bildiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:912
msgid ""
"As an example, let's add a simple 'tour' to the Estate module. Tours are "
"a standard mechanism in Odoo used to onboard users by guiding them "
"through your application."
msgstr ""
"Misol sifatida, Estate moduliga oddiy 'tour' qo'shamiz. Tourlar foydalanuvchilarni "
"ilova orqali yo'naltirish orqali ularga ko'nikma hosil qildirish uchun "
"Odoo da ishlatiladigan standart mexanizmdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:915
msgid ""
"A very minimal tour with a single step can be added by adding this file "
"in `static/src/js/tour.js`:"
msgstr ""
"Bitta qadamli juda minimal tour `static/src/js/tour.js` da ushbu faylni qo'shish orqali qo'shilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:930
msgid ""
"You then need to include the file in the appropriate bundle in the "
"manifest file:"
msgstr "Keyin faylni manifest faylida tegishli bundlega qo'shishingiz kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:944
msgid ""
"You also need to add an xml record in a new estate_tour.xml file in the "
"data folder so that your tour is displayed:"
msgstr ""
"Touringiz ko'rsatilishi uchun data papkasidagi yangi estate_tour.xml faylida "
"xml yozuvi qo'shishingiz ham kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/importable_modules.rst:956
msgid ""
"Unlike normal Python modules, glob expansion is not supported in "
"importable modules; so you need to list each file you want to include in "
"the module specifically."
msgstr ""
"Oddiy Python modullaridan farqli o'laroq, glob kengaytmasi import qilinadigan "
"modullarda qo'llab-quvvatlanmaydi; shuning uchun modulga qo'shmoqchi bo'lgan "
"har bir faylni maxsus ro'yxatga olishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:6
msgid "Master the web framework"
msgstr "Veb frameworkni o'zlashtirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:9
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:8
msgid "This tutorial is outdated."
msgstr "Bu qo'llanma eskirgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:17
msgid ""
"This tutorial is designed for those who have completed the "
":doc:`discover_js_framework` tutorial and are looking to deepen their "
"knowledge of the web framework. It is organized in four independent "
"projects, each focusing on different features of Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Bu qo'llanma :doc:`discover_js_framework` qo'llanmasini tugatgan va veb "
"framework haqidagi bilimlarini chuqurlashtirmoqchi bo'lganlar uchun mo'ljallangan. "
"U to'rtta mustaqil loyihada tashkil etilgan, har biri Odoo ning turli "
"xususiyatlariga qaratilgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:23
msgid ""
"Each of these chapters can be done independantly, in any order. Also, be "
"aware that some of them cover a lot of material, so they may be quite "
"long."
msgstr ""
"Bu boblarning har biri mustaqil ravishda, har qanday tartibda bajarilishi "
"mumkin. Shuningdek, ulardan ba'zilari ko'p material qamrab olganligi sababli "
"ancha uzun bo'lishi mumkinligini unutmang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:26
msgid ""
"The first project is about building a `clicker game "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incremental_game>`_. While working on it, "
"you will learn various aspects of the web framework: systray, command "
"palette, dialogs, notifications, customizing existing components and much"
" more."
msgstr ""
"Birinchi loyiha `clicker o'yini <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incremental_game>`_ "
"yaratish haqida. U ustida ishlayotganda, veb frameworkning turli jihatlari: "
"systray, buyruqlar palitrasi, muloqot oynalari, bildirishnomalar, mavjud "
"komponentlarni sozlash va boshqa ko'p narsalarni o'rganasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:30
msgid ""
"The second project is focused on an important category of components: "
"fields. Field components represent the value of a field for a record, "
"they appear in many places in the web client: in form views, obviously, "
"but also in kanban and list views, and may even be used alone, without a "
"view. Due to their importance, it makes sense to learn how to create and "
"manipulate such components."
msgstr ""
"Ikkinchi loyiha muhim komponentlar toifasiga qaratilgan: maydonlar. Maydon "
"komponentlari yozuv maydon qiymatini ifodalaydi, ular veb mijozda ko'p "
"joylarda ko'rinadi: forma ko'rinishlarida, albatta, lekin kanban va ro'yxat "
"ko'rinishlarida ham, va hatto ko'rinishsiz, mustaqil ishlatilishi mumkin. "
"Ularning ahamiyatliligi sababli, bunday komponentlarni qanday yaratish va "
"boshqarishni o'rganish mantiqan to'g'ri."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:35
msgid ""
"In the context of the web framework, views usually refers to the "
"javascript implementation of a component that represents one or many "
"records, depending on a description (`ir.ui.view`). Such components are "
"actually quite complicated and usually requires various sub systems (a "
"renderer, a model, a controller, a arch parser, ...). In chapter 3, we "
"create a new view from scratch to represent a list of images."
msgstr ""
"Veb framework kontekstida ko'rinishlar odatda tavsifga (`ir.ui.view`) "
"qarab bir yoki bir nechta yozuvni ifodalovchi komponentning javascript "
"amalga oshirilishiga ishora qiladi. Bunday komponentlar aslida juda murakkab "
"va odatda turli quyi tizimlarni talab qiladi (renderer, model, controller, "
"arch parser, ...). 3-bobda tasvirlar ro'yxatini ifodalash uchun yangi ko'rinish "
"noldan yaratamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:41
msgid ""
"Finally, the last project in chapter 4 is about customizing an existing "
"view (a kanban view) by adding a search panel on its left. It is "
"interesting to see how one can take existing code, and modify it to suit "
"our needs. Also, it is a realistic project, that will feature many common"
" issues that arises while working on Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Nihoyat, 4-bobdagi so'nggi loyiha mavjud ko'rinishni (kanban ko'rinishini) "
"chapiga qidiruv paneli qo'shib sozlash haqida. Mavjud kodni qanday olish va "
"ehtiyojlarimizga muvofiq o'zgartirish mumkinligini ko'rish qiziqarli. Shuningdek, "
"bu Odoo ustida ishlashda paydo bo'ladigan ko'plab keng tarqalgan muammolarni "
"o'z ichiga olgan realistik loyihadir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:55
msgid ""
"Start a new Odoo database and install the modules for each chapter that "
"you want to work on: `awesome_clicker` (for chapter 1), `awesome_fields` "
"(for chapter 2), `awesome_gallery` (for chapter 3) or `awesome_kanban` "
"(for chapter 4)."
msgstr ""
"Yangi Odoo ma'lumotlar bazasini boshlang va ishlashni xohlagan har bir bob "
"uchun modullarni o'rnating: `awesome_clicker` (1-bob uchun), `awesome_fields` "
"(2-bob uchun), `awesome_gallery` (3-bob uchun) yoki `awesome_kanban` (4-bob uchun)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:61
msgid ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game`"
msgstr ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:62
msgid ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view`"
msgstr ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework.rst:63
msgid ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/03_customize_kanban_view`"
msgstr ":doc:`master_odoo_web_framework/03_customize_kanban_view`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 1: Build a Clicker game"
msgstr "1-bob: Clicker o'yinini yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:5
msgid ""
"For this project, we will build together a `clicker game "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incremental_game>`_, completely integrated"
" with Odoo. In this game, the goal is to accumulate a large number of "
"clicks, and to automate the system. The interesting part is that we will "
"use the Odoo user interface as our playground. For example, we will hide "
"bonuses in some random parts of the web client."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu loyiha uchun Odoo bilan to'liq integratsiyalashgan `clicker o'yini "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incremental_game>`_ ni birga yaratamiz. "
"Bu o'yinda maqsad ko'p miqdordagi kliklarsni to'plash va tizimni avtomatlashtirishdir. "
"Qiziqarli qismi shundaki, Odoo foydalanuvchi interfeysidan o'yin maydoni "
"sifatida foydalanamiz. Masalan, veb mijozning ba'zi tasodifiy qismlarida "
"bonuslarni yashiramiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:10
msgid ""
"To get started, you need a running Odoo server and a development "
"environment. Before getting into the exercises, make sure you have "
"followed all the steps described in this :ref:`tutorial introduction "
"<tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/setup>`."
msgstr ""
"Boshlash uchun ishlaydigan Odoo server va ishlab chiqish muhiti kerak. "
"Mashqlarga kirishdan oldin, ushbu :ref:`qo'llanma kirish "
"<tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/setup>` da tasvirlangan barcha qadamlarni "
"bajarganingizga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:21
msgid ""
"The solutions for each exercise of the chapter are hosted on the "
"`official Odoo tutorials repository "
"<https://github.com/odoo/tutorials/commits/19.0-master-odoo-web-"
"framework-solutions/awesome_clicker>`_."
msgstr ""
"Bobning har bir mashqi uchun yechimlar `Odoo ning rasmiy qo'llanmalar "
"repositorysi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/tutorials/commits/19.0-master-odoo-web-"
"framework-solutions/awesome_clicker>`_ da joylashgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:27
msgid "1. Create a systray item"
msgstr "1. Systray elementi yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:29
msgid "To get started, we want to display a counter in the systray."
msgstr "Boshlash uchun systray da hisoblagichni ko'rsatmoqchimiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:31
msgid ""
"Create a `clicker_systray_item.js` (and `xml`) file with a hello world "
"Owl component."
msgstr "Hello world Owl komponenti bilan `clicker_systray_item.js` (va `xml`) faylini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:32
msgid "Register it to the systray registry, and make sure it is visible."
msgstr "Uni systray registryiga ro'yxatdan o'tkazing va ko'rinishligiga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:33
msgid ""
"Update the content of the item so that it displays the following string: "
"`Clicks: 0`, and add a button on the right to increment the value."
msgstr ""
"Elementning tarkibini quyidagi satrni ko'rsatadigan qilib yangilang: "
"`Clicks: 0`, va qiymatni oshirish uchun o'ngga tugma qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:39
msgid "And voila, we have a completely working clicker game!"
msgstr "Va mana, bizda to'liq ishlaydigan clicker o'yini bor!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:43
msgid ":ref:`Documentation on the systray registry <frontend/registries/systray>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Systray registry bo'yicha hujjat <frontend/registries/systray>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:44
msgid ""
"`Example: adding a systray item to the registry "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c4fb9c92d7826ddbc183d38b867ca4446b2fb709/addons/web/static/src/webclient/user_menu/user_menu.js#L41-L42>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Misol: registryga systray elementi qo'shish "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c4fb9c92d7826ddbc183d38b867ca4446b2fb709/addons/web/static/src/webclient/user_menu/user_menu.js#L41-L42>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:48
msgid "2. Count external clicks"
msgstr "2. Tashqi kliklrni hisoblash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:50
msgid ""
"Well, to be honest, it is not much fun yet. So let us add a new feature: "
"we want all clicks in the user interface to count, so the user is "
"incentivized to use Odoo as much as possible! But obviously, the "
"intentional clicks on the main counter should still count more."
msgstr ""
"Xo'sh, rostini aytganda, hali unchalik qiziqarli emas. Keling, yangi "
"xususiyat qo'shamiz: foydalanuvchi interfeysidagi barcha klikllar hisoblanishini "
"xohlaymiz, shuning uchun foydalanuvchi Odoo dan imkon qadar ko'proq "
"foydalanishga undaydi! Ammo, asosiy hisoblagichdagi ataylab qilingan "
"klikllar hali ham ko'proq hisoblanishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:54
msgid "Use `useExternalListener` to listen on all clicks on `document.body`."
msgstr "`document.body` dagi barcha klikllarni tinglash uchun `useExternalListener` dan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:55
msgid "Each of these clicks should increase the counter value by 1."
msgstr "Bu klikllarning har biri hisoblagich qiymatini 1 ga oshirishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:56
msgid ""
"Modify the code so that each click on the counter increased the value by "
"10"
msgstr "Kodni hisoblagichdagi har bir klik qiymatni 10 ga oshiradigan qilib o'zgartiring"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:57
msgid "Make sure that a click on the counter does not increase the value by 11!"
msgstr "Hisoblagichdagi klik qiymatni 11 ga oshirmasligiga ishonch hosil qiling!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:58
msgid ""
"Also additional challenge: make sure the external listener capture the "
"events, so we don't miss any clicks."
msgstr ""
"Qo'shimcha vazifa: tashqi tinglovchi hodisalarni ushlab qolishiga ishonch "
"hosil qiling, shuning uchun hech qanday klikllarni o'tkazib yubormaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:63
msgid ""
"`Owl documentation on useExternalListener "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useexternallistener>`_"
msgstr ""
"`useExternalListener bo'yicha Owl hujjati "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md#useexternallistener>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:64
msgid ""
"`MDN page on event capture <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-"
"US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Building_blocks/Events#event_capture>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Hodisa yozib olish bo'yicha MDN sahifasi <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-"
"US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Building_blocks/Events#event_capture>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:68
msgid "3. Create a client action"
msgstr "3. Mijoz amali yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:70
msgid ""
"Currently, the current user interface is quite small: it is just a "
"systray item. We certainly need more room to display more of our game. To"
" do that, let us create a client action. A client action is a main "
"action, managed by the web client, that displays a component."
msgstr ""
"Hozirda joriy foydalanuvchi interfeysi juda kichik: bu shunchaki systray "
"elementi. Albatta o'yinimizning ko'proqini ko'rsatish uchun ko'proq joy kerak. "
"Buning uchun mijoz amali yarataylik. Mijoz amali veb mijoz tomonidan "
"boshqariladigan komponentni ko'rsatadigan asosiy amaldir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:74
msgid ""
"Create a `client_action.js` (and `xml`) file, with a hello world "
"component."
msgstr "Hello world komponenti bilan `client_action.js` (va `xml`) faylini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:75
msgid ""
"Register that client action in the action registry under the name "
"`awesome_clicker.client_action`"
msgstr ""
"Bu mijoz amalini amallar registryida `awesome_clicker.client_action` nomi "
"ostida ro'yxatdan o'tkazing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:76
msgid ""
"Add a button on the systray item with the text `Open`. Clicking on it "
"should open the client action `awesome_clicker.client_action` (use the "
"action service to do that)."
msgstr ""
"`Open` matni bilan systray elementiga tugma qo'shing. Uni bosish "
"`awesome_clicker.client_action` mijoz amalini ochishi kerak (buning uchun "
"amal xizmatidan foydalaning)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:78
msgid ""
"To avoid disrupting employees' workflow, we prefer the client action to "
"open within a popover rather than in fullscreen mode. Modify the "
"`doAction` call to open it in a popover."
msgstr ""
"Xodimlarning ish oqimini buzmaslik uchun, mijoz amalining to'liq ekran "
"rejimida emas, balki popover ichida ochilishini afzal ko'ramiz. `doAction` "
"chaqiruvini uni popover da ochish uchun o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:83
msgid ""
"You can use `target: \"new\"` in the `doAction` to open the action in a "
"popover:"
msgstr ""
"Amalni popover da ochish uchun `doAction` da `target: \"new\"` dan "
"foydalanishingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:99
msgid ":ref:`How to create a client action <howtos/javascript_client_action>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Mijoz amalini qanday yaratish <howtos/javascript_client_action>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:102
msgid "4. Move the state to a service"
msgstr "4. Holatni xizmatga ko'chirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:104
msgid ""
"For now, our client action is just a hello world component. We want it to"
" display our game state, but that state is currently only available in "
"the systray item. So it means that we need to change the location of our "
"state to make it available for all our components. This is a perfect use "
"case for services."
msgstr ""
"Hozircha, bizning mijoz amalimiz shunchaki hello world komponenti. U "
"o'yin holatimizni ko'rsatishini xohlaymiz, lekin bu holat hozirda faqat "
"systray elementida mavjud. Demak, barcha komponentlarimiz uchun mavjud "
"bo'lishi uchun holatimiz joylashuvini o'zgartirishimiz kerak. Bu xizmatlar "
"uchun mukammal foydalanish holatidir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:108
msgid "Create a `clicker_service.js` file with the corresponding service."
msgstr "Tegishli xizmat bilan `clicker_service.js` faylini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:109
msgid ""
"This service should export a reactive value (the number of clicks) and a "
"few functions to update it:"
msgstr ""
"Bu xizmat reaktiv qiymatni (klikllar soni) va uni yangilash uchun bir nechta "
"funksiyalarni eksport qilishi kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:122
msgid ""
"Access the state in both the systray item and the client action (don't "
"forget to `useState` it). Modify the systray item to remove its own local"
" state and use it. Also, you can remove the `+10 clicks` button."
msgstr ""
"Ham systray elementida, ham mijoz amalida holatga kiring (`useState` ni "
"unutmang). Systray elementini o'zining mahalliy holatini olib tashlash va "
"undan foydalanish uchun o'zgartiring. Shuningdek, `+10 clicks` tugmasini "
"olib tashlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:124
msgid ""
"Display the state in the client action, and add a `+10` clicks button in "
"it."
msgstr "Holatni mijoz amalida ko'rsating va unda `+10` klikllar tugmasi qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:131
msgid ""
":ref:`Short explanation on services "
"<tutorials/discover_js_framework/services>`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`Xizmatlar bo'yicha qisqacha tushuntirish "
"<tutorials/discover_js_framework/services>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:134
msgid "5. Use a custom hook"
msgstr "5. Maxsus hook dan foydalanish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:136
msgid ""
"Right now, every part of the code that will need to use our clicker "
"service will have to import `useService` and `useState`. Since it is "
"quite common, let us use a custom hook. It is also useful to put more "
"emphasis on the `clicker` part, and less emphasis on the `service` part."
msgstr ""
"Hozirda clicker xizmatimizdan foydalanishi kerak bo'lgan kodning har qanday "
"qismi `useService` va `useState` ni import qilishi kerak bo'ladi. Bu juda "
"keng tarqalgan bo'lganligi sababli, maxsus hook dan foydalanamiz. Shuningdek, "
"`clicker` qismiga ko'proq, `service` qismiga kamroq urg'u berish uchun foydali."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:140
msgid "Export a `useClicker` hook."
msgstr "`useClicker` hookini eksport qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:141
msgid "Update all current uses of the clicker service to the new hook:"
msgstr "Clicker xizmatining barcha joriy foydalanishlarini yangi hookka yangilang:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:149
msgid ""
"`Documentation on hooks: "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Hooklar bo'yicha hujjat: "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/hooks.md>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:152
msgid "6. Humanize the displayed value"
msgstr "6. Ko'rsatiladigan qiymatni inson ko'zi uchun moslash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:154
msgid ""
"We will in the future display large numbers, so let us get ready for "
"that. There is a `humanNumber` function that format numbers in a easier "
"to comprehend way: for example, `1234` could be formatted as `1.2k`"
msgstr ""
"Kelajakda katta raqamlarni ko'rsatamiz, shuning uchun bunga tayyorlanamiz. "
"Raqamlarni tushunish osonroq formatda formatlash uchun `humanNumber` "
"funksiyasi mavjud: masalan, `1234` ni `1.2k` sifatida formatlash mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:157
msgid ""
"Use it to display our counters (both in the systray item and the client "
"action)."
msgstr "Hisoblagichlarimizni (ham systray elementida, ham mijoz amalida) ko'rsatish uchun undan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:158
msgid "Create a `ClickValue` component that display the value."
msgstr "Qiymatni ko'rsatuvchi `ClickValue` komponenti yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:162
msgid "Owl allows component that contains just text nodes!"
msgstr "Owl shunchaki matn tugunlarini o'z ichiga olgan komponentga ruxsat beradi!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:169
msgid ""
"`definition of humanNumber function "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/utils/numbers.js#L119>`_"
msgstr ""
"`humanNumber funksiyasi ta'rifi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/utils/numbers.js#L119>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:172
msgid "7. Add a tooltip in `ClickValue` component"
msgstr "7. `ClickValue` komponentiga tooltip qo'shish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:174
msgid ""
"With the `humanNumber` function, we actually lost some precision on our "
"interface. Let us display the real number as a tooltip."
msgstr ""
"`humanNumber` funksiyasi bilan interfeysimizda bir oz aniqlikni yo'qotdik. "
"Keling, haqiqiy raqamni tooltip sifatida ko'rsataylik."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:177
msgid ""
"Tooltip needs an html element. Change the `ClickValue` to wrap the value "
"in a `<span/>` element"
msgstr ""
"Tooltip html elementiga muhtoj. `ClickValue` ni qiymatni `<span/>` elementiga "
"o'rash uchun o'zgartiring"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:178
msgid "Add a dynamic `data-tooltip` attribute to display the exact value."
msgstr "Aniq qiymatni ko'rsatish uchun dinamik `data-tooltip` atributini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:185
msgid ""
"`Documentation in the tooltip service "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/tooltip/tooltip_service.js#L17>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Tooltip xizmatidagi hujjat "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/tooltip/tooltip_service.js#L17>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:188
msgid "8. Buy ClickBots"
msgstr "8. ClickBot satib olish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:190
msgid ""
"Let us make our game even more interesting: once a player get to 1000 "
"clicks for the first time, the game should unlock a new feature: the "
"player can buy robots for 1000 clicks. These robots will generate 10 "
"clicks every 10 seconds."
msgstr ""
"O'yinimizni yanada qiziqarliroq qilaylik: o'yinchi birinchi marta 1000 "
"kliklga yetganda, o'yin yangi xususiyatni ochishi kerak: o'yinchi 1000 "
"kliklga robotlar sotib olishi mumkin. Bu robotlar har 10 soniyada 10 ta "
"klikk yaratadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:194
msgid ""
"Add a `level` number to our state. This is a number that will be "
"incremented at some milestones, and open new features"
msgstr ""
"Holatimizdga `level` raqamini qo'shing. Bu ba'zi erishuvlarda "
"oshiriladigan va yangi xususiyatlarni ochadigan raqam"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:196
msgid ""
"Add a `clickBots` number to our state. It represents the number of robots"
" that have been purchased."
msgstr ""
"Holatimizdga `clickBots` raqamini qo'shing. U sotib olingan robotlar "
"sonini ifodalaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:197
msgid ""
"Modify the client action to display the number of click bots (only if "
"`level >= 1`), with a `Buy` button that is enabled if `clicks >= 1000`. "
"The `Buy` button should increment the number of clickbots by 1."
msgstr ""
"Mijoz amalini click botlar sonini ko'rsatish uchun o'zgartiring (faqat "
"`level >= 1` bo'lsa), `clicks >= 1000` bo'lsa yoqiladigan `Buy` tugmasi "
"bilan. `Buy` tugmasi clickbotlar sonini 1 ga oshirishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:199
msgid ""
"Set a 10s interval in the service that will increment the number of "
"clicks by `10*clickBots`."
msgstr ""
"Xizmatda kliklar sonini `10*clickBots` ga oshiradigan 10 soniyalik "
"interval o'rnating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:200
msgid ""
"Make sure the Buy button is disabled if the player does not have enough "
"clicks."
msgstr "O'yinchida yetarli klik bo'lmasa, Buy tugmasi o'chirilganligiga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:206
msgid "9. Refactor to a class model"
msgstr "9. Sinf modeliga qayta ishlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:208
msgid ""
"The current code is written in a somewhat functional style. But to do so,"
" we have to export the state and all its update functions in our clicker "
"object.  As this project grows, this may become more and more complex. To"
" make it simpler, let us split our business logic out of our service and "
"into a class."
msgstr ""
"Joriy kod funktsional uslubda yozilgan. Ammo buning uchun clicker "
"ob'ektimizda holatni va barcha yangilash funksiyalarini eksport qilishimiz "
"kerak. Loyiha o'sishi bilan bu tobora murakkablashishi mumkin. Uni "
"soddalashtirish uchun biznes mantiqimizni xizmatdan ajratib, sinfga "
"ko'chiramiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:212
msgid ""
"Create a `clicker_model` file that exports a reactive class. Move all the"
" state and update functions from the service into the model."
msgstr ""
"Reaktiv sinfni eksport qiladigan `clicker_model` faylini yarating. "
"Barcha holat va yangilash funksiyalarini xizmatdan modelga ko'chiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:217
msgid ""
"You can extends the ClickerModel with the `Reactive` class from "
":file:`@web/core/utils/reactive`. The `Reactive` class wrap the model "
"into a reactive proxy."
msgstr ""
"ClickerModel ni :file:`@web/core/utils/reactive` dan `Reactive` sinfi "
"bilan kengaytirishingiz mumkin. `Reactive` sinfi modelni reaktiv proksi "
"sifatida o'raydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:220
msgid ""
"Rewrite the clicker service to instantiate and export the clicker model "
"class."
msgstr "Clicker xizmatini clicker model sinfini yaratish va eksport qilish uchun qayta yozing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:224
msgid ""
"`Example of subclassing Reactive "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/model/relational_model/datapoint.js#L32>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Reactive ni quyi sinfga olish namunasi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/model/relational_model/datapoint.js#L32>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:227
msgid "10. Notify when a milestone is reached"
msgstr "10. Erishuvga yetilganda xabardor qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:229
msgid ""
"There is not much feedback that something changed when we reached 1k "
"clicks. Let us use the `effect` service to communicate that information "
"clearly. The problem is that our click model does not have access to "
"services. Also, we want to keep as much as possible the UI concern out of"
" the model. So, we can explore a new strategy for communication: event "
"buses."
msgstr ""
"1k kliklga yetganimizda biror narsa o'zgarganligidan ko'p fikr-mulohaza "
"yo'q. Keling, bu ma'lumotni aniq etkazish uchun `effect` xizmatidan "
"foydalanamiz. Muammo shundaki, bizning klik modelimiz xizmatlarga kirish "
"imkoniga ega emas. Shuningdek, UI tashvishlini imkon qadar modeldan "
"tashqarida saqlashni xohlaymiz. Shunday qilib, muloqot uchun yangi "
"strategiyani o'rganishimiz mumkin: voqea shinalar."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:234
msgid ""
"Update the clicker model to instantiate a bus, and to trigger a "
"`MILESTONE_1k` event when we reach 1000 clicks for the first time."
msgstr ""
"Clicker modelini shinani yaratish va birinchi marta 1000 kliklga "
"yetganimizda `MILESTONE_1k` voqeasini ishga tushirish uchun yangilang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:236
msgid "Change the clicker service to listen to the same event on the model bus."
msgstr "Clicker xizmatini model shinasida bir xil voqeani tinglash uchun o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:237
msgid "When that happens, use the `effect` service to display a rainbow man."
msgstr "Bu sodir bo'lganda, kamalak odamni ko'rsatish uchun `effect` xizmatidan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:238
msgid "Add some text to explain that the user can now buy clickbots."
msgstr "Foydalanuvchi endi clickbotlar sotib olishi mumkinligini tushuntirish uchun matn qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:245
msgid ""
"`Owl documentation on event bus "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/utils.md#eventbus>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Owl hujjatlari voqea shinasi haqida "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/utils.md#eventbus>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:246
msgid ":ref:`Documentation on effect service <frontend/services/effect>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Effect xizmati hujjati <frontend/services/effect>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:249
msgid "11. Add BigBots"
msgstr "11. BigBot qo'shish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:251
msgid ""
"Clearly, we need a way to provide the player with more choices. Let us "
"add a new type of clickbot: `BigBots`, which are just more powerful: they"
" provide with 100 clicks each 10s, but they cost 5000 clicks"
msgstr ""
"Shubhasiz, o'yinchiga ko'proq tanlov taqdim etish usuli kerak. Keling, "
"yangi turdagi clickbot qo'shamiz: `BigBots`, ular shunchaki kuchliroq: "
"har 10 soniyada 100 ta klik taqdim etadi, lekin ular 5000 kliklga tushadi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:254
msgid "increment `level` when it gets to 5k (so it should be 2)"
msgstr "`level` ni 5k ga yetganda oshiring (demak, u 2 bo'lishi kerak)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:255
msgid "Update the state to keep track of bigbots"
msgstr "Bigbotlarni kuzatib borish uchun holatni yangilang"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:256
msgid "bigbots should be available at `level >=2`"
msgstr "bigbotlar `level >=2` da mavjud bo'lishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:257
msgid "Display the corresponding information in the client action"
msgstr "Tegishli ma'lumotni mijoz amalida ko'rsating"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:261
msgid ""
"If you need to use `<` or `>` in a template as a javascript expression, "
"be careful since it might class with the xml parser. To solve that, you "
"can use one of the special aliases: `gt, gte, lt` or `lte`. See the `Owl "
"documentation page on template expressions "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/templates.md"
"#expression-evaluation>`_."
msgstr ""
"Agar shablonda `<` yoki `>` ni javascript ifodasi sifatida ishlatishingiz "
"kerak bo'lsa, ehtiyot bo'ling, chunki bu xml parser bilan to'qnashishi "
"mumkin. Buni hal qilish uchun maxsus taxalluslardan birini ishlatishingiz "
"mumkin: `gt, gte, lt` yoki `lte`. `Owl hujjatlari sahifasiga shablon "
"ifodalari bo'yicha "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/templates.md"
"#expression-evaluation>`_ qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:269
msgid "12. Add a new type of resource: power"
msgstr "12. Yangi turdagi resurs qo'shish: kuch"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:271
msgid ""
"Now, to add another scaling point, let us add a new type of resource: a "
"power multiplier. This is a number that can be increased at `level >= 3`,"
" and multiplies the action of the bots (so, instead of providing one "
"click, clickbots now provide us with `multiplier` clicks)."
msgstr ""
"Endi yana bir o'lchov nuqtasini qo'shish uchun yangi turdagi resurs "
"qo'shamiz: kuch ko'paytiruvchi. Bu `level >= 3` da oshirilishi mumkin "
"bo'lgan raqam bo'lib, botlar harakatini ko'paytiradi (shunday qilib, "
"bitta klik taqdim etish o'rniga, clickbotlar endi bizga `multiplier` ta "
"klik taqdim etadi)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:275
msgid "increment `level` when it gets to 100k (so it should be 3)."
msgstr "`level` ni 100k ga yetganda oshiring (demak, u 3 bo'lishi kerak)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:276
msgid "update the state to keep track of the power (initial value is 1)."
msgstr "kuchni kuzatib borish uchun holatni yangilang (boshlang'ich qiymat 1)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:277
msgid "change bots to use that number as a multiplier."
msgstr "botlarni bu raqamni ko'paytiruvchi sifatida ishlatish uchun o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:278
msgid ""
"Update the user interface to display and let the user purchase a new "
"power level (costs: 50k)."
msgstr ""
"Foydalanuvchi interfeysini yangi kuch darajasini ko'rsatish va sotib "
"olish imkonini berish uchun yangilang (narxi: 50k)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:284
msgid "13. Define some random rewards"
msgstr "13. Ba'zi tasodifiy mukofotlarni aniqlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:286
msgid "We want the user to obtain sometimes bonuses, to reward using Odoo."
msgstr "Foydalanuvchi ba'zan Ododan foydalanishni mukofotlash uchun bonuslar olishini xohlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:288
msgid ""
"Define a list of rewards in `click_rewards.js`. A reward is an object "
"with: - a `description` string. - a `apply` function that take the game "
"state in argument and can modify it. - a `minLevel` number (optional) "
"that describes at which unlock level the bonus is available. - a "
"`maxLevel` number (optional) that describes at which unlock level a bonus"
" is no longer available."
msgstr ""
"`click_rewards.js` da mukofotlar ro'yxatini aniqlang. Mukofot quyidagilardan "
"iborat ob'ekt: - `description` satri. - o'yin holatini argument sifatida "
"qabul qilib, uni o'zgartira oladigan `apply` funksiyasi. - bonusning qaysi "
"ochish darajasida mavjudligini ko'rsatuvchi `minLevel` raqami (ixtiyoriy). "
"- bonusning qaysi ochish darajasida endi mavjud emasligini ko'rsatuvchi "
"`maxLevel` raqami (ixtiyoriy)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:323
msgid "You can add whatever you want to that list!"
msgstr "Siz bu ro'yxatga xohlagan narsangizni qo'shishingiz mumkin!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:325
msgid ""
"Define a function `getReward` that will select a random reward from the "
"list of rewards that matches the current unlock level."
msgstr ""
"Joriy ochish darajasiga mos keladigan mukofotlar ro'yxatidan tasodifiy "
"mukofot tanlaydigan `getReward` funksiyasini aniqlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:327
msgid ""
"Extract the code that choose randomly in an array in a function `choose` "
"that you can move to another `utils.js` file."
msgstr ""
"Massivda tasodifiy tanlash kodini boshqa `utils.js` fayliga ko'chirishingiz "
"mumkin bo'lgan `choose` funksiyasiga ajrating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:330
msgid "14. Provide a reward when opening a form view"
msgstr "14. Forma ko'rinishini ochishda mukofot taqdim etish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:332
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Patch the form controller. Each time a form controller is created, it "
"should randomly decides (1% chance) if a reward should be given."
msgstr ""
"Forma controllerni yamang. Har safar forma controller yaratilganda, u "
"mukofot berilishi kerakligini tasodifiy (1% ehtimol) hal qilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:334
msgid "If the answer is yes, call a method `getReward` on the model."
msgstr "Agar javob ha bo'lsa, modelda `getReward` metodini chaqiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:335
msgid ""
"That method should choose a reward, send a sticky notification, with a "
"button `Collect` that will then apply the reward, and finally, it should "
"open the `clicker` client action."
msgstr ""
"Bu metod mukofot tanlashi, keyin mukofotni qo'llaydigan `Collect` tugmasi "
"bilan yopishqoq bildirishnoma yuborishi va nihoyat `clicker` mijoz "
"amalini ochishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:343
msgid ":ref:`Documentation on patching a class <frontend/patching_class>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Sinfni yamoqlash hujjati <frontend/patching_class>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:344
msgid ""
"`Definition of patch function "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/utils/patch.js#L71>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Patch funksiyasining ta'rifi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/utils/patch.js#L71>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:345
msgid ""
"`Example of patching a class "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/pos_mercury/static/src/app/screens/receipt_screen/receipt_screen.js#L6>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Sinfni yamoqlash namunasi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/pos_mercury/static/src/app/screens/receipt_screen/receipt_screen.js#L6>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:348
msgid "15. Add commands in command palette"
msgstr "15. Buyruqlar palitrasi qo'shish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:350
msgid "Add a command `Open Clicker Game` to the command palette."
msgstr "Buyruqlar palitrasiga `Open Clicker Game` buyrug'ini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:351
msgid "Add another command: `Buy 1 click bot`."
msgstr "Yana bir buyruq qo'shing: `Buy 1 click bot`."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:358
msgid ""
"`Example of use of command provider registry "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/debug/debug_providers.js#L10>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Buyruq provayder registridan foydalanish namunasi "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/src/core/debug/debug_providers.js#L10>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:361
msgid "16. Add yet another resource: trees"
msgstr "16. Yana bir resurs qo'shish: daraxtlar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:363
msgid ""
"It is now time to introduce a completely new type of resources. Here is "
"one that should not be too controversial: trees. We will now allow the "
"user to plant (collect?) fruit trees. A tree costs 1 million clicks, but "
"it will provide us with fruits (either pears or cherries)."
msgstr ""
"Endi butunlay yangi turdagi resursni tanishtirishga vaqt keldi. Mana bu "
"juda munozarali bo'lmasligi kerak bo'lgan biri: daraxtlar. Endi "
"foydalanuvchiga mevali daraxtlarni ekish (yig'ish?) imkonini beramiz. "
"Daraxt 1 million kliklga tushadi, lekin u bizga meva (nok yoki gilos) "
"taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:367
msgid ""
"Update the state to keep track of various types of trees: pear/cherries, "
"and their fruits."
msgstr ""
"Turli xil daraxt turlarini: nok/gilos va ularning mevalarini kuzatib "
"borish uchun holatni yangilang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:368
msgid "Add a function that computes the total number of trees and fruits."
msgstr "Daraxtlar va mevalarning umumiy sonini hisoblaydigan funksiya qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:369
msgid "Define a new unlock level at `clicks >= 1 000 000`."
msgstr "`clicks >= 1 000 000` da yangi ochish darajasini aniqlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:370
msgid ""
"Update the client user interface to display the number of trees and "
"fruits, and also, to buy trees."
msgstr ""
"Daraxtlar va mevalar sonini ko'rsatish va shuningdek, daraxtlar sotib "
"olish uchun mijoz foydalanuvchi interfeysini yangilang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:371
msgid "Increment the fruit number by 1 for each tree every 30s."
msgstr "Har 30 soniyada har bir daraxt uchun meva sonini 1 ga oshiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:377
msgid "17. Use a dropdown menu for the systray item"
msgstr "17. Systray elementi uchun ochiladigan menyu ishlatish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:379
msgid ""
"Our game starts to become interesting. But for now, the systray only "
"displays the total number of clicks. We want to see more information: the"
" total number of trees and fruits. Also, it would be useful to have a "
"quick access to some commands and some more information. Let us use a "
"dropdown menu!"
msgstr ""
"O'yinimiz qiziqarliroq bo'la boshlaydi. Ammo hozircha systray faqat "
"kliklar umumiy sonini ko'rsatadi. Biz ko'proq ma'lumot ko'rishni "
"xohlaymiz: daraxtlar va mevalarning umumiy soni. Shuningdek, ba'zi "
"buyruqlar va ko'proq ma'lumotlarga tezkor kirish foydali bo'lar edi. "
"Keling, ochiladigan menyudan foydalanamiz!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:383
msgid "Replace the systray item by a dropdown menu."
msgstr "Systray elementini ochiladigan menyu bilan almashtiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:384
msgid ""
"It should display the numbers of clicks, trees, and fruits, each with a "
"nice icon."
msgstr "U kliklar, daraxtlar va mevalar sonini, har birini chiroyli belgi bilan ko'rsatishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:385
msgid ""
"Clicking on it should open a dropdown menu that displays more detailed "
"information: each types of trees and fruits."
msgstr ""
"Ustiga bosish ko'proq batafsil ma'lumot ko'rsatadigan ochiladigan menyuni "
"ochishi kerak: daraxt va mevalarning har bir turi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:387
msgid ""
"Also, a few dropdown items with some commands: open the clicker game, buy"
" a clickbot, ..."
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, ba'zi buyruqlar bilan bir nechta ochiladigan elementlar: "
"clicker o'yinini ochish, clickbot sotib olish, ..."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:393
msgid "18. Use a Notebook component"
msgstr "18. Notebook komponentidan foydalanish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:395
msgid ""
"We now keep track of a lot more information. Let us improve our client "
"interface by organizing the information and features in various tabs, "
"with the `Notebook` component:"
msgstr ""
"Endi biz ancha ko'proq ma'lumotni kuzatib boramiz. Keling, `Notebook` "
"komponenti yordamida ma'lumot va xususiyatlarni turli yorliqlarda "
"tashkil etish orqali mijoz interfeysimizni takomillashtiramiz:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:398
msgid "Use the `Notebook` component."
msgstr "`Notebook` komponentidan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:399
msgid "All `click` content should be displayed in one tab."
msgstr "Barcha `click` kontenti bitta yorliqda ko'rsatilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:400
msgid "All `tree/fruits` content should be displayed in another tab."
msgstr "Barcha `tree/fruits` kontenti boshqa yorliqda ko'rsatilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:407
msgid ":ref:`Odoo: Documentation on Notebook component <frontend/owl/notebook>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Odoo: Notebook komponenti hujjati <frontend/owl/notebook>`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:408
msgid ""
"`Owl: Documentation on slots "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/slots.md>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Owl: Slotlar hujjati "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/slots.md>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:409
msgid ""
"`Tests of Notebook component "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/tests/core/notebook_tests.js#L27>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Notebook komponenti testlari "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/c638913df191dfcc5547f90b8b899e7738c386f1/addons/web/static/tests/core/notebook_tests.js#L27>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:412
msgid "19.  Persist the game state"
msgstr "19. O'yin holatini saqlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:414
msgid ""
"You certainly noticed a big flaw in our game: it is transient. The game "
"state is lost each time the user closes the browser tab. Let us fix that."
" We will use the local storage to persist the state."
msgstr ""
"Siz albatta o'yinimizdagi katta kamchilikni payqagansiz: u vaqtinchalik. "
"Foydalanuvchi brauzer yorlig'ini yopganda o'yin holati yo'qoladi. Keling, "
"buni tuzatamiz. Holatni saqlash uchun local storagedan foydalanamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:417
msgid ""
"Import `browser` from :file:`@web/core/browser/browser` to access the "
"localstorage."
msgstr ""
"Localstoragega kirish uchun :file:`@web/core/browser/browser` dan "
"`browser` ni import qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:418
msgid ""
"Serialize the state every 10s (in the same interval code) and store it on"
" the local storage."
msgstr ""
"Holatni har 10 soniyada serializatsiya qiling (bir xil interval kodida) "
"va uni local storagega saqlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:419
msgid ""
"When the `clicker` service is started, it should load the state from the "
"local storage (if any), or initialize itself otherwise."
msgstr ""
"`clicker` xizmati ishga tushirilganda, u holatni local storagedan (agar "
"mavjud bo'lsa) yuklashi yoki aks holda o'zini ishga tushirishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:423
msgid "20. Introduce state migration system"
msgstr "20. Holat migratsiya tizimini kiritish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:425
msgid ""
"Once you persist state somewhere, a new problem arises: what happens when"
" you update your code, so the shape of the state changes, and the user "
"opens its browser with a state that was created with an old version? "
"Welcome to the world of migration issues!"
msgstr ""
"Holatni biror joyga saqlasangiz, yangi muammo paydo bo'ladi: kod "
"yangilanganda nima bo'ladi, shunda holat shakli o'zgaradi va foydalanuvchi "
"brauzerini eski versiyada yaratilgan holat bilan ochadi? Migratsiya "
"muammolari dunyosiga xush kelibsiz!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:429
msgid ""
"It is probably wise to tackle the problem early. What we will do here is "
"add a version number to the state, and introduce a system to "
"automatically update the states if it is not up to date."
msgstr ""
"Muammoni erta hal qilish ehtimol aqlli. Bu yerda biz holatga versiya "
"raqamini qo'shamiz va holat yangilangan bo'lmasa avtomatik yangilash "
"tizimini kiritamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:432
msgid "Add a version number to the state."
msgstr "Holatga versiya raqamini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:433
msgid ""
"Define an (empty) list of migrations. A migration is an object with a "
"`fromVersion` number, a `toVersion` number, and a `apply` function."
msgstr ""
"(Bo'sh) migratsiyalar ro'yxatini aniqlang. Migratsiya `fromVersion` "
"raqami, `toVersion` raqami va `apply` funksiyasi bilan ob'ekt."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:434
msgid ""
"Whenever the code loads the state from the local storage, it should check"
" the version number. If the state is not uptodate, it should apply all "
"necessary migrations."
msgstr ""
"Kod holatni local storagedan yuklaganida, u versiya raqamini tekshirishi "
"kerak. Agar holat yangilanmagan bo'lsa, u barcha zarur migratsiyalarni "
"qo'llashi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:438
msgid "21. Add another type of trees"
msgstr "21. Yana bir turdagi daraxt qo'shish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:440
msgid "To test our migration system, let us add a new type of trees: peaches."
msgstr "Migratsiya tizimimizni sinash uchun yangi turdagi daraxt qo'shamiz: shaftoli."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:442
msgid "Add `peach` trees."
msgstr "`peach` daraxtlarini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:443
msgid "Increment the state version number."
msgstr "Holat versiya raqamini oshiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/01_build_clicker_game.rst:444
msgid "Define a migration."
msgstr "Migratsiyani aniqlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 2: Create a Gallery View"
msgstr "2-bob: Galereya ko'rinishini yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:5
msgid ""
"Let us see how one can create a new view, completely from scratch. In a "
"way, it is not very difficult to do, but there are no really good "
"resources on how to do it. Note that most situations should be solved by "
"either customizing an existing view, or with a client action."
msgstr ""
"Keling, qanday qilib yangi ko'rinishni butunlay noldan yaratish mumkinligini "
"ko'ramiz. Bir jihatdan, buni qilish juda qiyin emas, lekin buni qanday "
"qilish bo'yicha haqiqatan yaxshi manbalar yo'q. E'tibor bering, ko'p "
"vaziyatlar mavjud ko'rinishni sozlash yoki mijoz amali bilan hal "
"qilinishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:9
msgid ""
"For this exercise, let's assume that we want to create a `gallery` view, "
"which is a view that lets us represent a set of records with an image "
"field."
msgstr ""
"Bu mashq uchun, biz `gallery` ko'rinishini yaratmoqchi deb faraz qilaylik, "
"bu rasm maydoni bilan yozuvlar to'plamini ifodalashga imkon beradigan "
"ko'rinish."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:12
msgid ""
"The problem could certainly be solved with a kanban view, but this means "
"that it is not possible to have our normal kanban view and the gallery "
"view in the same action."
msgstr ""
"Muammo albatta kanban ko'rinishi bilan hal qilinishi mumkin, lekin bu "
"bir xil amalda odatiy kanban ko'rinishi va galereya ko'rinishiga ega "
"bo'lish mumkin emasligini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:15
msgid ""
"Let us make a gallery view. Each gallery view will be defined by an "
"`image_field` attribute in its arch:"
msgstr ""
"Keling, galereya ko'rinishini yaratamiz. Har bir galereya ko'rinishi "
"o'z archida `image_field` atributi bilan aniqlanadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:22
msgid ""
"To complete the tasks in this chapter, you will need to install the "
"awesome_gallery addon. This addon includes the necessary server files to "
"add a new view."
msgstr ""
"Bu bobdagi vazifalarni bajarish uchun awesome_gallery qo'shimchasini "
"o'rnatishingiz kerak bo'ladi. Bu qo'shimcha yangi ko'rinish qo'shish "
"uchun zarur server fayllarini o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:32
msgid ""
"The solutions for each exercise of the chapter are hosted on the "
"`official Odoo tutorials repository "
"<https://github.com/odoo/tutorials/commits/19.0-master-odoo-web-"
"framework-solutions/awesome_gallery>`_."
msgstr ""
"Bob mashqlarining har biri uchun yechimlar "
"`rasmiy Odoo qo'llanmalar omborida "
"<https://github.com/odoo/tutorials/commits/19.0-master-odoo-web-"
"framework-solutions/awesome_gallery>`_ joylashtirilgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:37
msgid "1. Make a hello world view"
msgstr "1. Hello world ko'rinishini yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:39
msgid ""
"First step is to create a JavaScript implementation with a simple "
"component."
msgstr "Birinchi qadam oddiy komponent bilan JavaScript implementatsiyasini yaratish."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:41
msgid ""
"Create the `gallery_view.js` , `gallery_controller.js` and "
"`gallery_controller.xml` files in `static/src`."
msgstr ""
"`static/src` da `gallery_view.js`, `gallery_controller.js` va "
"`gallery_controller.xml` fayllarini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:43
msgid "Implement a simple hello world component in `gallery_controller.js`."
msgstr "`gallery_controller.js` da oddiy hello world komponentini amalga oshiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:44
msgid ""
"In `gallery_view.js`, import the controller, create a view object, and "
"register it in the view registry under the name `gallery`."
msgstr ""
"`gallery_view.js` da controllerni import qiling, ko'rinish ob'ektini "
"yarating va uni `gallery` nomi bilan ko'rinish registrida ro'yxatdan o'tkazing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:48
msgid "Here is an example on how to define a view object:"
msgstr "Ko'rinish ob'ektini qanday aniqlash bo'yicha misol:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:65
msgid ""
"Add `gallery` as one of the view type in the `contacts.action_contacts` "
"action."
msgstr "`contacts.action_contacts` amalida `gallery` ni ko'rinish turlaridan biri sifatida qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:66
msgid ""
"Make sure that you can see your hello world component when switching to "
"the gallery view."
msgstr "Galereya ko'rinishiga o'tganda hello world komponentingizni ko'rishingiz mumkinligiga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:75
msgid "2. Use the Layout component"
msgstr "2. Layout komponentidan foydalanish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:77
msgid ""
"So far, our gallery view does not look like a standard view. Let's use "
"the `Layout` component to have the standard features like other views."
msgstr ""
"Hozircha bizning galereya ko'rinishimiz standart ko'rinishga o'xshamaydi. "
"Boshqa ko'rinishlar kabi standart xususiyatlarga ega bo'lish uchun "
"`Layout` komponentidan foydalanamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:80
msgid ""
"Import the `Layout` component and add it to the `components` of "
"`GalleryController`."
msgstr "`Layout` komponentini import qiling va `GalleryController` ning `components` ga qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:81
msgid ""
"Update the template to use `Layout`. It needs a `display` prop, which can"
" be found in `props.display`."
msgstr ""
"Shablonni `Layout` ishlatish uchun yangilang. U `props.display` da "
"topilishi mumkin bo'lgan `display` prop ga muhtoj."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:88
msgid "3. Parse the arch"
msgstr "3. Archni tahlil qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:90
msgid ""
"For now, our gallery view does not do much. Let's start by reading the "
"information contained in the arch of the view."
msgstr ""
"Hozircha galereya ko'rinishimiz ko'p narsa qilmaydi. Keling, ko'rinish "
"archida joylashgan ma'lumotlarni o'qishdan boshlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:93
msgid ""
"The process of parsing an arch is usually done with a `ArchParser`, "
"specific to each view. It inherits from a generic `XMLParser` class."
msgstr ""
"Archni tahlil qilish jarayoni odatda har bir ko'rinishga xos `ArchParser` "
"bilan amalga oshiriladi. U umumiy `XMLParser` sinfidan meros oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:98
msgid "Here is an example of what an ArchParser might look like:"
msgstr "ArchParser qanday ko'rinishi mumkinligining namunasi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:111
msgid "Create the `ArchParser` class in its own file."
msgstr "`ArchParser` sinfini o'z faylida yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:112
msgid "Use it to read the `image_field` information."
msgstr "`image_field` ma'lumotlarini o'qish uchun undan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:113
msgid ""
"Update the `gallery` view code to add it to the props received by the "
"controller."
msgstr ""
"`gallery` ko'rinish kodini controller tomonidan qabul qilingan propslarga "
"qo'shish uchun yangilang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:116
msgid ""
"It is probably a little overkill to do it like that, since we basically "
"only need to read one attribute from the arch, but it is a design that is"
" used by every other odoo views, since it lets us extract some upfront "
"processing out of the controller."
msgstr ""
"Buni shunday qilish biroz ortiqcha bo'lishi mumkin, chunki biz aslida "
"archdan faqat bitta atributni o'qishimiz kerak, lekin bu barcha boshqa "
"odoo ko'rinishlari tomonidan qo'llaniladigan dizayn, chunki u bizga "
"ba'zi oldindan ishlashni kontrollerdan ajratib olish imkonini beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:121
msgid ""
"`Example: The graph arch parser "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/src/views/graph/graph_arch_parser.js>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Namuna: Grafik arch parser "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/web/static/src/views/graph/graph_arch_parser.js>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:125
msgid "4. Load some data"
msgstr "4. Ba'zi ma'lumotlarni yuklash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:127
msgid ""
"Let us now get some real data from the server. For that we must use "
"`webSearchRead` from the orm service."
msgstr ""
"Keling, serverdan haqiqiy ma'lumotlar olamiz. Buning uchun orm "
"xizmatidan `webSearchRead` dan foydalanishimiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:132
msgid "Here is an example of a `webSearchRead` to get the records from a model:"
msgstr "Modeldan yozuvlarni olish uchun `webSearchRead` namunasi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:146
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Add a :code:`loadImages(domain) {...}` method to the `GalleryController`."
" It should perform a `webSearchRead` call from the orm service to fetch "
"records corresponding to the domain, and use `imageField` received in "
"props."
msgstr ""
"`GalleryController` ga :code:`loadImages(domain) {...}` metodini qo'shing. "
"U domenga mos yozuvlarni olish uchun orm xizmatidan `webSearchRead` "
"chaqiruvini amalga oshirishi va propsda qabul qilingan `imageField` dan "
"foydalanishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:149
msgid ""
"If you didn't include `bin_size` in the context of the call, you will "
"receive the image field encoded in base64. Make sure to put `bin_size` in"
" the context to receive the size of the image field. We will display the "
"image later."
msgstr ""
"Agar chaqiruv kontekstiga `bin_size` ni qo'shmasangiz, rasm maydoni "
"base64 da kodlangan holda qabul qilinadi. Rasm maydoni hajmini olish "
"uchun kontekstga `bin_size` ni qo'yishingizga ishonch hosil qiling. "
"Rasmni keyinroq ko'rsatamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:152
msgid ""
"Modify the `setup` code to call that method in the `onWillStart` and "
"`onWillUpdateProps` hooks."
msgstr ""
"`onWillStart` va `onWillUpdateProps` hooklarida bu metodini chaqirish "
"uchun `setup` kodini o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:154
msgid ""
"Modify the template to display the id and the size of each image inside "
"the default slot of the `Layout` component."
msgstr ""
"Shablonni `Layout` komponentining standart slotida har bir rasmning "
"id si va hajmini ko'rsatish uchun o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:158
msgid ""
"The loading data code will be moved into a proper model in a next "
"exercise."
msgstr "Ma'lumot yuklash kodi keyingi mashqda to'g'ri modelga ko'chiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:164
msgid "5. Solve the concurrency problem"
msgstr "5. Parallellik muammosini hal qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:166
msgid ""
"For now, our code is not concurrency proof. If one changes the domain "
"twice, it will trigger the `loadImages(domain)` twice. We have thus two "
"requests that can arrive at different time depending on different "
"factors. Receiving the response for the first request after receiving the"
" response for the second request will lead to an inconsistent state."
msgstr ""
"Hozircha kodimiz parallellikka chidamli emas. Agar domenni ikki marta "
"o'zgartirsa, `loadImages(domain)` ni ikki marta ishga tushiradi. Shu "
"tariqa turli omillarga qarab har xil vaqtda kelishi mumkin bo'lgan ikki "
"so'rovimiz bor. Birinchi so'rov uchun javobni ikkinchi so'rov javobidan "
"keyin qabul qilish mos kelmaydigan holatga olib keladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:171
msgid ""
"The `KeepLast` primitive from Odoo solves this problem, it manages a list"
" of tasks, and only keeps the last task active."
msgstr ""
"Odoo dan `KeepLast` primitivasi bu muammoni hal qiladi, u vazifalar "
"ro'yxatini boshqaradi va faqat oxirgi vazifani faol saqlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:174
msgid "Import `KeepLast` from :file:`@web/core/utils/concurrency`."
msgstr ":file:`@web/core/utils/concurrency` dan `KeepLast` ni import qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:175
msgid "Instanciate a `KeepLast` object in the model."
msgstr "Modelda `KeepLast` ob'ektini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:176
msgid ""
"Add the `webSearchRead` call in the `KeepLast` so that only the last call"
" is resolved."
msgstr ""
"Faqat oxirgi chaqiruv hal qilinishi uchun `webSearchRead` chaqiruvini "
"`KeepLast` ga qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:179
msgid ""
"`Example: usage of KeepLast "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/ebf646b44f747567ff8788c884f7f18dffd453e0/addons/web/static/src/core/model_field_selector/model_field_selector_popover.js#L164>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Namuna: KeepLast dan foydalanish "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/ebf646b44f747567ff8788c884f7f18dffd453e0/addons/web/static/src/core/model_field_selector/model_field_selector_popover.js#L164>`_"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:182
msgid "6. Reorganize code"
msgstr "6. Kodni qayta tashkil qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:184
msgid ""
"Real views are a little bit more organized. This may be overkill in this "
"example, but it is intended to learn how to structure code in Odoo. Also,"
" this will scale better with changing requirements."
msgstr ""
"Haqiqiy ko'rinishlar biroz tartibli. Bu misolda bu ortiqcha bo'lishi "
"mumkin, lekin Odoo da kodni qanday tuzilmalash bo'yicha o'rganish "
"uchun mo'ljallangan. Shuningdek, bu o'zgaruvchan talablar bilan "
"yaxshiroq masshtablanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:187
msgid "Move all the model code in its own `GalleryModel` class."
msgstr "Barcha model kodini o'z `GalleryModel` sinfiga ko'chiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:188
msgid "Move all the rendering code in a `GalleryRenderer` component."
msgstr "Barcha rendering kodini `GalleryRenderer` komponentiga ko'chiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:189
msgid ""
"Import `GalleryModel` and `GalleryRenderer` in `GalleryController` to "
"make it work."
msgstr ""
"Ishlashi uchun `GalleryController` da `GalleryModel` va `GalleryRenderer` "
"ni import qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:192
msgid "7. Make the view extensible"
msgstr "7. Ko'rinishni kengaytiriladigan qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:194
msgid ""
"To extends the view, one could import the gallery view object to modify "
"it to their taste. The problem is that for the moment, it is not possible"
" to define a custom model or renderer because it is hardcoded in the "
"controller."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishni kengaytirish uchun galereya ko'rinish ob'ektini o'z didiga "
"ko'ra o'zgartirish uchun import qilish mumkin. Muammo shundaki, hozirda "
"maxsus model yoki renderer aniqlash mumkin emas, chunki u "
"kontrollerda qattiq kodlangan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:198
msgid "Import `GalleryModel` and `GalleryRenderer` in the gallery view file."
msgstr "Galereya ko'rinish faylida `GalleryModel` va `GalleryRenderer` ni import qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:199
msgid ""
"Add a `Model` and `Renderer` key to the gallery view object and assign "
"them to `GalleryModel` and `GalleryRenderer`. Pass `Model` and `Renderer`"
" as props to the controller."
msgstr ""
"Galereya ko'rinish ob'ektiga `Model` va `Renderer` kalitlarini qo'shing "
"va ularni `GalleryModel` va `GalleryRenderer` ga belgilang. `Model` va "
"`Renderer` ni proplar sifatida controllerga uzating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:201
msgid "Remove the hardcoded import in the controller and get them from the props."
msgstr "Kontrolldagi qattiq kodlangan importni olib tashlang va ularni propsdan oling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/master_odoo_web_framework/02_create_gallery_view.rst:202
msgid ""
"Use `t-component "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/component.md"
"#dynamic-sub-components>`_ to have dynamic sub component."
msgstr ""
"`t-component "
"<https://github.com/odoo/owl/blob/master/doc/reference/component.md"
"#dynamic-sub-components>`_ dan dinamik quyi komponentga ega bo'lish uchun foydalaning."

