#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 4: Security - A Brief Introduction"
msgstr "4-bob: Xavfsizlik - Qisqacha kirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:5
msgid ""
"In the :doc:`previous chapter <03_basicmodel>`, we created our first "
"table intended to store business data. In a business application such as "
"Odoo, one of the first questions to consider is who\\ [#who]_ can access "
"the data. Odoo provides a security mechanism to allow access to the data "
"for specific groups of users."
msgstr ""
":doc:`Avvalgi bobda <03_basicmodel>`, biz biznes ma'lumotlarini saqlash "
"uchun mo'ljallangan birinchi jadvalimizni yaratdik. Odoo kabi biznes "
"ilovasida ko'rib chiqiladigan birinchi savollardan biri kim\\ [#who]_ "
"ma'lumotlarga kira olishi. Odoo foydalanuvchilarning muayyan guruhlari "
"uchun ma'lumotlarga kirish imkonini beradigan xavfsizlik mexanizmini "
"taqdim etadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:10
msgid ""
"The topic of security is covered in more detail in "
":doc:`../restrict_data_access`. This chapter aims to cover the minimum "
"required for our new module."
msgstr ""
"Xavfsizlik mavzusi :doc:`../restrict_data_access` da batafsilroq "
"yoritilgan. Ushbu bob yangi modulimiz uchun zarur bo'lgan minimalni "
"qamrab olishni maqsad qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:14
msgid "Data Files (CSV)"
msgstr "Ma'lumot fayllari (CSV)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:16
msgid ""
"Odoo is a highly data driven system. Although behavior is customized "
"using Python code, part of a module's value is in the data it sets up "
"when loaded. One way to load data is through a CSV file. One example is "
"the `list of country states "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/odoo/addons/base/data/res.country.state.csv>`_"
" which is loaded at installation of the `base` module."
msgstr ""
"Odoo - bu yuqori darajada ma'lumotlarga asoslangan tizim. Xatti-harakat "
"Python kodi yordamida sozlangan bo'lsa ham, modulning qiymatining bir "
"qismi u yuklanganda o'rnatadigan ma'lumotlardadir. Ma'lumotlarni yuklashning "
"bir usuli - CSV faylidan foydalanish. Bir misol - bu `base` moduli "
"o'rnatilganda yuklanadigan `viloyatlar ro'yxati "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/odoo/addons/base/data/res.country.state.csv>`_."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:31
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/05_firstui.rst:81
msgid ""
"``id`` is an :term:`external identifier`. It can be used to refer to the "
"record (without knowing its in-database identifier)."
msgstr ""
"``id`` - bu :term:`tashqi identifikator`. U ma'lumotlar bazasidagi "
"identifikatorni bilmasdan yozuvga murojaat qilish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:33
msgid ""
"``country_id:id`` refers to the country by using its :term:`external "
"identifier`."
msgstr ""
"``country_id:id`` mamlakatga uning :term:`tashqi identifikatori` "
"yordamida murojaat qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:34
msgid "``name`` is the name of the state."
msgstr "``name`` viloyat nomi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:35
msgid "``code`` is the code of the state."
msgstr "``code`` viloyat kodi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:37
msgid ""
"These three fields are `defined "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/2ad2f3d6567b6266fc42c6d2999d11f3066b282c/odoo/addons/base/models/res_country.py#L108-L111>`__"
" in the ``res.country.state`` model."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu uch maydon ``res.country.state`` modelida `aniqlangan "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/2ad2f3d6567b6266fc42c6d2999d11f3066b282c/odoo/addons/base/models/res_country.py#L108-L111>`__."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:41
msgid ""
"By convention, a file importing data is located in the ``data`` folder of"
" a module. When the data is related to security, it is located in the "
"``security`` folder. When the data is related to views and actions (we "
"will cover this later), it is located in the ``views`` folder. "
"Additionally, all of these files must be declared in the ``data`` list "
"within the ``__manifest__.py`` file. Our example file is defined `in the "
"manifest of the base module "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L29>`__."
msgstr ""
"An'anaga ko'ra, ma'lumotlarni import qiluvchi fayl modulning ``data`` "
"papkasida joylashgan. Ma'lumotlar xavfsizlikka tegishli bo'lsa, u "
"``security`` papkasida joylashadi. Ma'lumotlar ko'rinishlar va amallarga "
"tegishli bo'lsa (buni keyinroq qamrab olamiz), u ``views`` papkasida "
"joylashadi. Bundan tashqari, ushbu fayllarning barchasi ``__manifest__.py`` "
"faylidagi ``data`` ro'yxatida e'lon qilinishi kerak. Bizning misol faylimiz "
"`base moduli manifestida aniqlangan "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L29>`__."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:48
msgid ""
"Also note that the content of the data files is only loaded when a module"
" is installed or updated."
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, ma'lumot fayllarining tarkibi faqat modul o'rnatilganda yoki "
"yangilanganida yuklanishini unutmang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:53
msgid ""
"The data files are sequentially loaded following their order in the "
"``__manifest__.py`` file. This means that if data ``A`` refers to data "
"``B``, you must make sure that ``B`` is loaded before ``A``."
msgstr ""
"Ma'lumot fayllari ``__manifest__.py`` faylidagi tartibiga ko'ra ketma-ket "
"yuklanadi. Bu ``A`` ma'lumoti ``B`` ma'lumotiga murojaat qilsa, "
"``B`` ning ``A`` dan oldin yuklanishini ta'minlashingiz kerakligini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:57
msgid ""
"In the case of the country states, you will note that the `list of "
"countries "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L22>`__"
" is loaded **before** the `list of country states "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L29>`__."
" This is because the states refer to the countries."
msgstr ""
"Viloyatlar holatida `mamlakatlar ro'yxati "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L22>`__"
" `viloyatlar ro'yxatidan "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/e8697f609372cd61b045c4ee2c7f0fcfb496f58a/odoo/addons/base/__manifest__.py#L29>`__ "
"**oldin** yuklanishini sezasiz. Buning sababi viloyatlar mamlakatlarga "
"murojaat qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:63
msgid ""
"Why is all this important for security? Because all the security "
"configuration of a model is loaded through data files, as we'll see in "
"the next section."
msgstr ""
"Nima uchun bularning barchasi xavfsizlik uchun muhim? Chunki keyingi "
"bo'limda ko'rib chiqamizki, modelning barcha xavfsizlik konfiguratsiyasi "
"ma'lumot fayllari orqali yuklanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:69
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
":ref:`reference/security/acl`."
msgstr ""
"**Manba**: ushbu mavzuga oid hujjatlar :ref:`reference/security/acl` da "
"mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:74
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section, the following warning should not "
"appear anymore:"
msgstr ""
"**Maqsad**: ushbu bo'lim oxirida quyidagi ogohlantirish endi ko'rinmasligi kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:80
msgid ""
"When no access rights are defined on a model, Odoo determines that no "
"users can access the data. It is even notified in the log:"
msgstr ""
"Modelda kirish huquqlari aniqlanmagan bo'lsa, Odoo hech qanday "
"foydalanuvchi ma'lumotlarga kira olmasligini aniqlaydi. Bu hatto "
"jurnalda ham xabar qilinadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:88
msgid ""
"Access rights are defined as records of the model ``ir.model.access``. "
"Each access right is associated with a model, a group (or no group for "
"global access) and a set of permissions: create, read, write and unlink\\"
" [#unlink]_. Such access rights are usually defined in a CSV file named "
"``ir.model.access.csv``."
msgstr ""
"Kirish huquqlari ``ir.model.access`` modelining yozuvlari sifatida "
"aniqlanadi. Har bir kirish huquqi model, guruh (yoki global kirish uchun "
"guruhsiz) va ruxsatlar to'plami bilan bog'liq: yaratish, o'qish, yozish "
"va o'chirish\\ [#unlink]_. Bunday kirish huquqlari odatda "
"``ir.model.access.csv`` nomli CSV faylda aniqlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:94
msgid "Here is an example for our previous `test_model`:"
msgstr "Mana oldingi `test_model` uchun misol:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:101
msgid "``id`` is an :term:`external identifier`."
msgstr "``id`` - bu :term:`tashqi identifikator`."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:102
msgid "``name`` is the name of the ``ir.model.access``."
msgstr "``name`` - bu ``ir.model.access`` nomi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:103
msgid ""
"``model_id/id`` refers to the model which the access right applies to. "
"The standard way to refer to the model is ``model_<model_name>``, where "
"``<model_name>`` is the ``_name`` of the model with the ``.`` replaced by"
" ``_``. Seems cumbersome? Indeed it is..."
msgstr ""
"``model_id/id`` kirish huquqi qo'llaniladigan modelga murojaat qiladi. "
"Modelga murojaat qilishning standart usuli ``model_<model_name>`` bo'lib, "
"bu yerda ``<model_name>`` modelning ``.`` belgisi ``_`` bilan almashtirilgan "
"``_name`` si. Noqulay ko'rinadi? Haqiqatan ham shunday..."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:106
msgid "``group_id/id`` refers to the group which the access right applies to."
msgstr "``group_id/id`` kirish huquqi qo'llaniladigan guruhga murojaat qiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:107
msgid ""
"``perm_read,perm_write,perm_create,perm_unlink``: read, write, create and"
" unlink permissions"
msgstr ""
"``perm_read,perm_write,perm_create,perm_unlink``: o'qish, yozish, yaratish "
"va o'chirish ruxsatlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:109
msgid "Add access rights."
msgstr "Kirish huquqlarini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:111
msgid ""
"Create the ``ir.model.access.csv`` file in the appropriate folder and "
"define it in the ``__manifest__.py`` file."
msgstr ""
"Tegishli papkada ``ir.model.access.csv`` faylini yarating va "
"``__manifest__.py`` faylida aniqlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:116
msgid "Tip: the warning message in the log gives you most of the solution ;-)"
msgstr "Maslahat: jurnaldagi ogohlantirish xabari yechimning ko'p qismini beradi ;-)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/04_securityintro.rst:118
