"Create a list view and a form view with the ``price``, ``partner_id`` and"
" ``status`` fields. No need to create an action or a menu."
msgstr ""
"``price``, ``partner_id`` va ``status`` maydonlari bilan ro'yxat ko'rinishi "
"va forma ko'rinishini yarating. Amal yoki menyu yaratish shart emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/07_relations.rst:249
msgid ""
"Add the field ``offer_ids`` to your ``estate.property`` model and in its "
"form view as depicted in this section's **Goal**."
msgstr ""
"``offer_ids`` maydonini ``estate.property`` modelingizga va ushbu "
"bo'limning **Maqsad** ida ko'rsatilganidek uning forma ko'rinishiga qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/07_relations.rst:252
msgid ""
"There are several important things to notice here. First, we don't need "
"an action or a menu for all models. Some models are intended to be "
"accessed only through another model. This is the case in our exercise: an"
" offer is always accessed through a property."
msgstr ""
"Bu yerda bir nechta muhim narsalarga e'tibor berish kerak. Birinchidan, "
"biz barcha modellar uchun amal yoki menyu kerak emas. Ba'zi modellar "
"faqat boshqa model orqali kirish uchun mo'ljallangan. Bu bizning "
"mashqimizdagi holat: taklifga har doim mulk orqali kiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/07_relations.rst:256
msgid ""
"Second, despite the fact that the ``property_id`` field is required, we "
"did not include it in the views. How does Odoo know which property our "
"offer is linked to? Well that's part of the magic of using the Odoo "
"framework: sometimes things are defined implicitly. When we create a "
"record through a one2many field, the corresponding many2one is populated "
"automatically for convenience."
msgstr ""
"Ikkinchidan, ``property_id`` maydoni majburiy bo'lishiga qaramay, biz "
"uni ko'rinishlarga kiritmadik. Odoo bizning taklifimiz qaysi mulkka "
"bog'liqligini qanday biladi? Bu Odoo framework dan foydalanishning "
"sehriga kiradi: ba'zida narsalar yashirin tarzda aniqlanadi. one2many "
"maydoni orqali yozuv yaratganimizda, tegishli many2one qulay bo'lishi "
"uchun avtomatik ravishda to'ldiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/07_relations.rst:262
msgid ""
"Still alive? This chapter is definitely not the easiest one. It "
"introduced a couple of new concepts while relying on everything that was "
"introduced before. The :doc:`next chapter <08_compute_onchange>` will be "
"lighter, don't worry ;-)"
msgstr ""
"Hali tirikmi? Bu bob, shubhasiz, eng osonlari emas. U avval kiritilgan "
"hamma narsaga tayanib bir nechta yangi tushunchalarni kiritdi. "
":doc:`Keyingi bob <08_compute_onchange>` engil bo'ladi, tashvishlanmang ;-)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 8: Computed Fields And Onchanges"
msgstr "8-bob: Hisoblangan maydonlar va onchange lar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:5
msgid ""
"The :doc:`relations between models <07_relations>` are a key component of"
" any Odoo module. They are necessary for the modelization of any business"
" case. However, we may want links between the fields within a given "
"model. Sometimes the value of one field is determined from the values of "
"other fields and other times we want to help the user with data entry."
msgstr ""
":doc:`Modellar o'rtasidagi munosabatlar <07_relations>` har qanday "
"Odoo modulining asosiy komponenti. Ular har qanday biznes holatini "
"modellashtirish uchun zarur. Biroq, biz berilgan model doirasidagi "
"maydonlar o'rtasidagi havolalarni xohlashimiz mumkin. Ba'zida bitta "
"maydon qiymati boshqa maydonlar qiymatlaridan aniqlanadi va ba'zida "
"foydalanuvchiga ma'lumot kiritishda yordam berishni xohlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:10
msgid ""
"These cases are supported by the concepts of computed fields and "
"onchanges. Although this chapter is not technically complex, the "
"semantics of both concepts is very important. This is also the first time"
" we will write Python logic. Until now we haven't written anything other "
"than class definitions and field declarations."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu holatlar hisoblangan maydonlar va onchange lar tushunchalari "
"bilan qo'llab-quvvatlanadi. Garchi bu bob texnik jihatdan murakkab "
"bo'lmasa-da, ikkala tushunchaning semantikasi juda muhim. Bu, shuningdek, "
"biz birinchi marta Python mantig'ini yozadigan vaqtimiz. Hozirgacha "
"biz klass ta'riflari va maydon e'lonlaridan boshqa hech narsa yozmadik."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:25
msgid ""
"In the property model, the total area and the best offer should be "
"computed:"
msgstr "Mulk modelida umumiy maydon va eng yaxshi taklif hisoblanishi kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst
msgid "Compute fields"
msgstr "Maydonlarni hisoblash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:31
msgid ""
"In the property offer model, the validity date should be computed and can"
" be updated:"
msgstr ""
"Mulk taklifi modelida yaroqlilik sanasi hisoblanishi va yangilanishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst
msgid "Compute field with inverse"
msgstr "Teskari bilan maydonni hisoblash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:37
msgid ""
"In our real estate module, we have defined the living area as well as the"
" garden area. It is then natural to define the total area as the sum of "
"both fields. We will use the concept of a computed field for this, i.e. "
"the value of a given field will be computed from the value of other "
"fields."
msgstr ""
"Ko'chmas mulk modulimizda biz yashash maydonini hamda bog' maydonini "
"aniqladik. Keyin umumiy maydonni ikkala maydon yig'indisi sifatida "
"aniqlash tabiiy. Buning uchun biz hisoblangan maydon tushunchasidan "
"foydalanamiz, ya'ni berilgan maydon qiymati boshqa maydonlar qiymatidan "
"hisoblanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:41
msgid ""
"So far fields have been stored directly in and retrieved directly from "
"the database. Fields can also be *computed*. In this case, the field's "
"value is not retrieved from the database but computed on-the-fly by "
"calling a method of the model."
msgstr ""
"Hozirgacha maydonlar to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ma'lumotlar bazasida saqlangan "
"va undan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri olingan. Maydonlar *hisoblangan* ham bo'lishi "
"mumkin. Bu holda maydon qiymati ma'lumotlar bazasidan olinmaydi, balki "
"model metodini chaqirib, tezda hisoblanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:46
msgid ""
"To create a computed field, create a field and set its attribute "
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Field.compute` to the name of a method. The "
"computation method should set the value of the computed field for every "
"record in ``self``."
msgstr ""
"Hisoblangan maydon yaratish uchun maydon yarating va uning "
":attr:`~odoo.fields.Field.compute` atributini metod nomiga o'rnating. "
"Hisoblash metodi ``self`` dagi har bir yozuv uchun hisoblangan maydon "
"qiymatini o'rnatishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:51
msgid ""
"By convention, :attr:`~odoo.fields.Field.compute` methods are private, "
"meaning that they cannot be called from the presentation tier, only from "
"the business tier (see "
":ref:`tutorials/server_framework_101/01_architecture`). Private methods "
"have a name starting with an underscore ``_``."
msgstr ""
"An'anaga ko'ra, :attr:`~odoo.fields.Field.compute` metodlari shaxsiy, "
"ya'ni ularni taqdimot qatlamidan emas, faqat biznes qatlamidan chaqirish "
"mumkin (qarang: :ref:`tutorials/server_framework_101/01_architecture`). "
"Shaxsiy metodlar nomi pastki chiziq ``_`` dan boshlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:59
msgid ""
"The value of a computed field usually depends on the values of other "
"fields in the computed record. The ORM expects the developer to specify "
"those dependencies on the compute method with the decorator "
":func:`~odoo.api.depends`. The given dependencies are used by the ORM to "
"trigger the recomputation of the field whenever some of its dependencies "
"have been modified::"
msgstr ""
"Hisoblangan maydon qiymati odatda hisoblangan yozuvdagi boshqa "
"maydonlar qiymatlariga bog'liq. ORM ishlab chiquvchidan hisoblash "
"metodidagi ushbu bog'liqliklarni :func:`~odoo.api.depends` dekoratori "
"bilan ko'rsatishni kutadi. Berilgan bog'liqliklar ORM tomonidan "
"bog'liqliklardan ba'zilari o'zgartirilganda maydonni qayta hisoblashni "
"boshlash uchun ishlatiladi::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:78
msgid "``self`` is a collection."
msgstr "``self`` - bu to'plam."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:81
msgid ""
"The object ``self`` is a *recordset*, i.e. an ordered collection of "
"records. It supports the standard Python operations on collections, e.g. "
"``len(self)`` and ``iter(self)``, plus extra set operations such as "
"``recs1 | recs2``."
msgstr ""
"``self`` ob'ekti - bu *recordset*, ya'ni tartiblangan yozuvlar to'plami. "
"U to'plamlardagi standart Python operatsiyalarini, masalan ``len(self)`` "
"va ``iter(self)`` ni, hamda ``recs1 | recs2`` kabi qo'shimcha to'plam "
"operatsiyalarini qo'llab-quvvatlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:86
msgid ""
"Iterating over ``self`` gives the records one by one, where each record "
"is itself a collection of size 1. You can access/assign fields on single "
"records by using the dot notation, e.g. ``record.name``."
msgstr ""
"``self`` bo'ylab takrorlash yozuvlarni birma-bir beradi, bu yerda har "
"bir yozuv o'zi 1 o'lchamli to'plam. Bitta yozuvlardagi maydonlarga "
"nuqta yozuvidan foydalanib kirish/belgilash mumkin, masalan ``record.name``."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:90
msgid ""
"Many examples of computed fields can be found in Odoo. `Here "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/713dd3777ca0ce9d121d5162a3d63de3237509f4/addons/account/models/account_move.py#L3420-L3423>`__"
" is a simple one."
msgstr ""
"Odoo da hisoblangan maydonlarning ko'plab misollari topish mumkin. "
"`Bu yerda <https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/713dd3777ca0ce9d121d5162a3d63de3237509f4/addons/account/models/account_move.py#L3420-L3423>`__ "
"oddiy bir misol."

