#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:228
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section, enabling the garden will set a "
"default area of 10 and an orientation to North."
msgstr ""
"**Maqsad**: ushbu bo'lim oxirida bog'ni yoqish maydon uchun 10 standart "
"qiymatini va shimoliy yo'nalishni o'rnatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:235
msgid ""
"In our real estate module, we also want to help the user with data entry."
" When the 'garden' field is set, we want to give a default value for the "
"garden area as well as the orientation. Additionally, when the 'garden' "
"field is unset we want the garden area to reset to zero and the "
"orientation to be removed. In this case, the value of a given field "
"modifies the value of other fields."
msgstr ""
"Ko'chmas mulk modulimizda biz foydalanuvchiga ma'lumot kiritishda ham "
"yordam berishni xohlaymiz. 'garden' maydoni o'rnatilganda biz bog' "
"maydoni hamda yo'nalish uchun standart qiymat berishni xohlaymiz. "
"Bundan tashqari, 'garden' maydoni o'chirilganda biz bog' maydonini "
"nolga qayta o'rnatish va yo'nalishni olib tashlashni xohlaymiz. "
"Bu holda berilgan maydon qiymati boshqa maydonlar qiymatini o'zgartiradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:241
msgid ""
"The 'onchange' mechanism provides a way for the client interface to "
"update a form without saving anything to the database whenever the user "
"has filled in a field value. To achieve this, we define a method where "
"``self`` represents the record in the form view and decorate it with "
":func:`~odoo.api.onchange` to specify which field it is triggered by. Any"
" change you make on ``self`` will be reflected on the form::"
msgstr ""
"'onchange' mexanizmi foydalanuvchi maydon qiymatini to'ldirganda "
"ma'lumotlar bazasiga hech narsa saqlamasdan formani yangilash uchun "
"mijoz interfeysi uchun yo'l taqdim etadi. Bunga erishish uchun biz "
"``self`` ning forma ko'rinishidagi yozuvni ifodalovchi metodini aniqlaymiz "
"va uni :func:`~odoo.api.onchange` bilan bezatib, qaysi maydon tomonidan "
"ishga tushirilishini ko'rsatamiz. ``self`` da kiritgan har qanday "
"o'zgarish formada aks etadi::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:262
msgid ""
"In this example, changing the partner will also change the name and the "
"description values. It is up to the user whether or not to change the "
"name and description values afterwards. Also note that we do not loop on "
"``self``, this is because the method is only triggered in a form view, "
"where ``self`` is always a single record."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu misolda hamkorni o'zgartirish nom va tavsif qiymatlarini ham "
"o'zgartiradi. Keyinroq nom va tavsif qiymatlarini o'zgartirish yoki "
"yo'q foydalanuvchiga bog'liq. Shuningdek, biz ``self`` bo'ylab tsikl "
"o'tkazmasligimizni ham eslatib o'tamiz, chunki metod faqat forma "
"ko'rinishida ishga tushiriladi, u yerda ``self`` har doim bitta yozuv."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:267
msgid "Set values for garden area and orientation."
msgstr "Bog' maydoni va yo'nalish uchun qiymatlarni o'rnating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:269
msgid ""
"Create an ``onchange`` in the ``estate.property`` model in order to set "
"values for the garden area (10) and orientation (North) when garden is "
"set to True. When unset, clear the fields."
msgstr ""
"Bog' True ga o'rnatilganda bog' maydoni (10) va yo'nalish (Shimol) "
"uchun qiymatlarni o'rnatish uchun ``estate.property`` modelida "
"``onchange`` yarating. O'chirilganda maydonlarni tozalang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:275
msgid ""
"Onchanges methods can also return a non-blocking warning message "
"(`example "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/cd9af815ba591935cda367d33a1d090f248dd18d/addons/payment_authorize/models/payment.py#L34-L36>`__)."
msgstr ""
"Onchange metodlari to'siqsiz ogohlantirish xabarini ham qaytarishi "
"mumkin (`misol "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/cd9af815ba591935cda367d33a1d090f248dd18d/addons/payment_authorize/models/payment.py#L34-L36>`__)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:279
msgid "How to use them?"
msgstr "Ulardan qanday foydalanish kerak?"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:281
msgid "There is no strict rule for the use of computed fields and onchanges."
msgstr "Hisoblangan maydonlar va onchange lardan foydalanish uchun qat'iy qoida yo'q."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:283
msgid ""
"In many cases, both computed fields and onchanges may be used to achieve "
"the same result. Always prefer computed fields since they are also "
"triggered outside of the context of a form view. Never ever use an "
"onchange to add business logic to your model. This is a **very bad** idea"
" since onchanges are not automatically triggered when creating a record "
"programmatically; they are only triggered in the form view."
msgstr ""
"Ko'p hollarda bir xil natijaga erishish uchun hisoblangan maydonlar ham, "
"onchange lar ham ishlatilishi mumkin. Hisoblangan maydonlarni har doim "
"afzal ko'ring, chunki ular forma ko'rinishi kontekstidan tashqarida ham "
"ishga tushiriladi. Modelingizga biznes mantiqini qo'shish uchun hech "
"qachon onchange dan foydalanmang. Bu **juda yomon** fikr, chunki "
"onchange lar yozuv dasturiy ravishda yaratilganda avtomatik ravishda "
"ishga tushirilmaydi; ular faqat forma ko'rinishida ishga tushiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:289
msgid ""
"The usual pitfall of computed fields and onchanges is trying to be 'too "
"smart' by adding too much logic. This can have the opposite result of "
"what was expected: the end user is confused from all the automation."
msgstr ""
"Hisoblangan maydonlar va onchange larning odatiy tuzoq - juda ko'p "
"mantiq qo'shib 'juda aqlli' bo'lishga urinish. Bu kutilganidan teskari "
"natijaga olib kelishi mumkin: oxirgi foydalanuvchi barcha avtomatizatsiyadan "
"chalkashib qoladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:293
msgid ""
"Computed fields tend to be easier to debug: such a field is set by a "
"given method, so it's easy to track when the value is set. Onchanges, on "
"the other hand, may be confusing: it is very difficult to know the extent"
" of an onchange. Since several onchange methods may set the same fields, "
"it easily becomes difficult to track where a value is coming from."
msgstr ""
"Hisoblangan maydonlarni disk raskadrovka qilish osonroq bo'ladi: bunday "
"maydon berilgan metod tomonidan o'rnatiladi, shuning uchun qiymat "
"o'rnatilganda kuzatish oson. Onchange lar, boshqa tomondan, chalkashtirib "
"yuborishi mumkin: onchange ning darajasini bilish juda qiyin. Bir nechta "
"onchange metodlari bir xil maydonlarni o'rnatishi mumkinligi sababli, "
"qiymat qayerdan kelayotganini kuzatish qiyinlashib ketadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:298
msgid ""
"When using stored computed fields, pay close attention to the "
"dependencies. When computed fields depend on other computed fields, "
"changing a value can trigger a large number of recomputations. This leads"
" to poor performance."
msgstr ""
"Saqlangan hisoblangan maydonlardan foydalanganda bog'liqliklarga "
"e'tibor bering. Hisoblangan maydonlar boshqa hisoblangan maydonlarga "
"bog'liq bo'lsa, qiymatni o'zgartirish ko'p sonli qayta hisoblashlarni "
"boshlashi mumkin. Bu ishlash samaradorligining pastligiga olib keladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/08_compute_onchange.rst:302
msgid ""
"In the :doc:`next chapter <09_actions>`, we'll see how we can trigger "
"some business logic when buttons are clicked."
msgstr ""
":doc:`Keyingi bobda <09_actions>`, tugmalar bosilganda ba'zi biznes "
"mantiqini qanday ishga tushirishimiz mumkinligini ko'ramiz."

