#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:190
msgid "View"
msgstr "Ko'rinish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:192
msgid ""
"Ordering is possible at the model level. This has the advantage of a "
"consistent order everywhere a list of records is retrieved. However, it "
"is also possible to define a specific order directly in a view thanks to "
"the ``default_order`` attribute (`example "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/report/crm_activity_report_views.xml#L30>`__)."
msgstr ""
"Model darajasida tartiblash mumkin. Bu yozuvlar ro'yxati olingan har bir "
"joyda izchil tartibning afzalligiga ega. Biroq ``default_order`` atributi "
"yordamida to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ko'rinishda ham maxsus tartib aniqlash mumkin "
"(`misol "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/report/crm_activity_report_views.xml#L30>`__)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:198
msgid "Manual"
msgstr "Qo'lda"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:200
msgid ""
"Both model and view ordering allow flexibility when sorting records, but "
"there is still one case we need to cover: the manual ordering. A user may"
" want to sort records depending on the business logic. For example, in "
"our real estate module we would like to sort the property types manually."
" It is indeed useful to have the most used types appear at the top of the"
" list. If our real estate agency mainly sells houses, it is more "
"convenient to have 'House' appear before 'Apartment'."
msgstr ""
"Model va ko'rinish tartiblari yozuvlarni saralashda moslashuvchanlikka "
"imkon beradi, lekin hali ham biz ko'rib chiqishimiz kerak bo'lgan bitta "
"holat bor: qo'lda tartiblash. Foydalanuvchi biznes mantiqiga qarab "
"yozuvlarni tartiblashni xohlashi mumkin. Masalan, ko'chmas mulk modulimizda "
"mulk turlarini qo'lda tartiblashni xohlaymiz. Eng ko'p ishlatiladigan "
"turlar ro'yxatning yuqori qismida paydo bo'lishi foydalidir. Agar ko'chmas "
"mulk agentligimiz asosan uylar sotsa, 'Uy' 'Kvartira' dan oldin paydo "
"bo'lishi qulayroqdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:206
msgid ""
"To do so, a ``sequence`` field is used in combination with the ``handle``"
" widget. Obviously the ``sequence`` field must be the first field in the "
"``_order`` attribute."
msgstr ""
"Buning uchun ``sequence`` maydoni ``handle`` vidjet bilan birgalikda "
"ishlatiladi. Shubhasiz, ``sequence`` maydoni ``_order`` atributidagi "
"birinchi maydon bo'lishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:209
msgid "Add manual ordering."
msgstr "Qo'lda tartiblashni qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:211
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:258
msgid "Add the following field:"
msgstr "Quyidagi maydonni qo'shing:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:216
msgid "Sequence"
msgstr "Ketma-ketlik"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:219
msgid ""
"Add the sequence to the ``estate.property.type`` list view with the "
"correct widget."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.type`` ro'yxat ko'rinishiga to'g'ri vidjet bilan "
"ketma-ketlikni qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:221
msgid ""
"Tip: you can find an example here: `model "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/models/crm_stage.py#L36>`__"
" and `view "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/views/crm_stage_views.xml#L23>`__."
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: bu yerda misol topishingiz mumkin: `model "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/models/crm_stage.py#L36>`__"
" va `ko'rinish "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/892dd6860733c46caf379fd36f57219082331b66/addons/crm/views/crm_stage_views.xml#L23>`__."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:227
msgid "Attributes and options"
msgstr "Atributlar va opsiyalar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:229
msgid ""
"It would be prohibitive to detail all the available features which allow "
"fine tuning of the look of a view. Therefore, we'll stick to the most "
"common ones."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishning ko'rinishini sozlash imkonini beruvchi barcha mavjud "
"xususiyatlarni batafsil ko'rib chiqish juda katta kuch talab etadi. "
"Shuning uchun eng keng tarqalganlariga yopishib olamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:237
msgid "**Goal**: at the end of this section, the property form view will have:"
msgstr "**Maqsad**: bu bo'lim oxirida mulk forma ko'rinishida quyidagilar bo'ladi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:239
msgid "Conditional display of buttons and fields"
msgstr "Tugmalar va maydonlarning shartli ko'rinishi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:240
msgid "Tag colors"
msgstr "Teg ranglari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst
msgid "Form view with sprinkles"
msgstr "Bezakli forma ko'rinishi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:247
msgid ""
"In our real estate module, we want to modify the behavior of some fields."
" For example, we don't want to be able to create or edit a property type "
"from the form view. Instead we expect the types to be handled in their "
"appropriate menu. We also want to give tags a color. In order to add "
"these behavior customizations, we can add the ``options`` attribute to "
"several field widgets."
msgstr ""
"Ko'chmas mulk modulimizda ba'zi maydonlarning xatti-harakatini o'zgartirmoqchimiz. "
"Masalan, forma ko'rinishidan mulk turini yaratish yoki tahrirlash imkoniyatiga "
"ega bo'lishni istamaymiz. Buning o'rniga turlar ularning tegishli menyusida "
"boshqarilishini kutamiz. Shuningdek, teglarga rang berishni xohlaymiz. "
"Bu xatti-harakat sozlamalarini qo'shish uchun bir nechta maydon vidjetlariga "
"``options`` atributini qo'shishimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:252
msgid "Add widget options."
msgstr "Vidjet opsiyalarini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:254
msgid ""
"Add the appropriate option to the ``property_type_id`` field to prevent "
"the creation and the editing of a property type from the property form "
"view. Have a look at the :ref:`Many2one widget documentation "
"<reference/js/widgets>` for more info."
msgstr ""
"Mulk forma ko'rinishidan mulk turini yaratish va tahrirlashshiga to'sqinlik "
"qilish uchun ``property_type_id`` maydoniga tegishli opsiyani qo'shing. "
"Ko'proq ma'lumot uchun :ref:`Many2one vidjet hujjatlariga "
"<reference/js/widgets>` qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:266
msgid ""
"Then add the appropriate option to the ``tag_ids`` field to add a color "
"picker on the tags. Have a look at the :ref:`FieldMany2ManyTags widget "
"documentation <reference/js/widgets>` for more info."
msgstr ""
"Keyin teglarda rang tanlash imkoniyatini qo'shish uchun ``tag_ids`` maydoniga "
"tegishli opsiyani qo'shing. Ko'proq ma'lumot uchun :ref:`FieldMany2ManyTags "
"vidjet hujjatlariga <reference/js/widgets>` qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:270
msgid ""
"In :doc:`05_firstui`, we saw that reserved fields were used for specific "
"behaviors. For example, the ``active`` field is used to automatically "
"filter out inactive records. We added the ``state`` as a reserved field "
"as well. It's now time to use it! A ``state`` field can be used in "
"combination with an ``invisible`` attribute in the view to display "
"buttons conditionally."
msgstr ""
":doc:`05_firstui` da zaxira maydonlar maxsus xatti-harakatlar uchun "
"ishlatilishini ko'rdik. Masalan, ``active`` maydoni faol bo'lmagan "
"yozuvlarni avtomatik ravishda filtrlash uchun ishlatiladi. Biz ``state`` ni "
"ham zaxira maydon sifatida qo'shdik. Endi uni ishlatish vaqti keldi! "
"``state`` maydoni ko'rinishda tugmalarni shartli ravishda ko'rsatish uchun "
"``invisible`` atributi bilan birgalikda ishlatilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:276
msgid "Add conditional display of buttons."
msgstr "Tugmalarning shartli ko'rinishini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:278
msgid ""
"Use the ``invisible`` attribute to display the header buttons "
"conditionally as depicted in this section's **Goal** (notice how the "
"'Sold' and 'Cancel' buttons change when the state is modified)."
msgstr ""
"Bu bo'limning **Maqsadi** da ko'rsatilganidek sarlavha tugmalarini shartli "
"ravishda ko'rsatish uchun ``invisible`` atributidan foydalaning (holat "
"o'zgartirilganda 'Sotilgan' va 'Bekor qilish' tugmalari qanday o'zgarishiga e'tibor bering)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:281
msgid ""
"Tip: do not hesitate to search for ``invisible=`` in the Odoo XML files "
"for some examples."
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: ba'zi misollar uchun Odoo XML fayllarida ``invisible=`` ni "
"qidirishdan tortinmang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:283
msgid ""
"More generally, it is possible to make a field ``invisible``, "
"``readonly`` or ``required`` based on the value of other fields. Note "
"that ``invisible`` can also be applied to other elements of the view such"
" as ``button`` or ``group``."
msgstr ""
"Umuman olganda, boshqa maydonlarning qiymatiga asoslanib maydonni "
"``invisible``, ``readonly`` yoki ``required`` qilish mumkin. ``invisible`` "
"``button`` yoki ``group`` kabi ko'rinishning boshqa elementlariga ham "
"qo'llanilishi mumkinligini e'tibor bering."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:287
msgid ""
"`invisible`, `readonly` and `required` can have any Python expression as "
"value. The expression gives the condition in which the property applies. "
"For example:"
msgstr ""
"`invisible`, `readonly` va `required` qiymat sifatida har qanday Python "
"ifodaga ega bo'lishi mumkin. Ifoda xususiyat qo'llaniladigan shartni beradi. Masalan:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:296
msgid ""
"This means that the ``description`` field is invisible when "
"``is_partner`` is ``False``. It is important to note that a field used in"
" ``invisible`` **must** be present in the view. If it should not be "
"displayed to the user, we can use the ``invisible`` attribute to hide it."
msgstr ""
"Bu ``is_partner`` ``False`` bo'lganda ``description`` maydoni ko'rinmasligini "
"anglatadi. ``invisible`` da ishlatiladigan maydon ko'rinishda **albatta** "
"mavjud bo'lishi kerakligini e'tibor bering. Agar u foydalanuvchiga "
"ko'rsatilmasligi kerak bo'lsa, uni yashirish uchun ``invisible`` atributidan "
"foydalanishimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:300
msgid "Use ``invisible``."
msgstr "``invisible`` dan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:302
msgid ""
"Make the garden area and orientation invisible in the ``estate.property``"
" form view when there is no garden."
msgstr ""
"Bog' bo'lmaganda ``estate.property`` forma ko'rinishida bog' maydoni va "
"yo'nalishini ko'rinmas qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:304
msgid ""
"Make the 'Accept' and 'Refuse' buttons invisible once the offer state is "
"set."
msgstr "Taklif holati o'rnatilgandan so'ng 'Qabul qilish' va 'Rad etish' tugmalarini ko'rinmas qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:305
msgid ""
"Do not allow adding an offer when the property state is 'Offer Accepted',"
" 'Sold' or 'Cancelled'. To do this use the ``readonly`` attribute."
msgstr ""
"Mulk holati 'Taklif qabul qilindi', 'Sotilgan' yoki 'Bekor qilingan' "
"bo'lganda taklif qo'shishga ruxsat bermang. Buning uchun ``readonly`` "
"atributidan foydalaning."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:310
msgid ""
"Using a (conditional) ``readonly`` attribute in the view can be useful to"
" prevent data entry errors, but keep in mind that it doesn't provide any "
"level of security! There is no check done server-side, therefore it's "
"always possible to write on the field through a RPC call."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishda (shartli) ``readonly`` atributidan foydalanish ma'lumotlarni "
"kiritish xatolarini oldini olishda foydali bo'lishi mumkin, lekin u hech "
"qanday xavfsizlik darajasini ta'minlamasligini yodda tuting! Server "
"tomonida hech qanday tekshiruv amalga oshirilmaydi, shuning uchun RPC "
"chaqiruv orqali maydonga har doim yozish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:319
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section, the property and offer list views "
"should have color decorations. Additionally, offers and tags will be "
"editable directly in the list, and the availability date will be hidden "
"by default."
msgstr ""
"**Maqsad**: bu bo'lim oxirida mulk va taklif ro'yxat ko'rinishlari rang "
"bezaklariga ega bo'lishi kerak. Bundan tashqari, takliflar va teglar "
"to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ro'yxatda tahrirlanadi va mavjudlik sanasi standart "
"bo'yicha yashiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst
msgid "List view with decorations and optional field"
msgstr "Bezaklar va ixtiyoriy maydon bilan ro'yxat ko'rinishi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst
msgid "Editable list"
msgstr "Tahrirlash mumkin bo'lgan ro'yxat"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:331
msgid ""
"When the model only has a few fields, it can be useful to edit records "
"directly through the list view and not have to open the form view. In the"
" real estate example, there is no need to open a form view to add an "
"offer or create a new tag. This can be achieved thanks to the "
"``editable`` attribute."
msgstr ""
"Model faqat bir nechta maydonga ega bo'lganda, yozuvlarni forma ko'rinishini "
"ochmasdan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ro'yxat ko'rinishi orqali tahrirlash foydali "
"bo'lishi mumkin. Ko'chmas mulk misolida taklif qo'shish yoki yangi teg "
"yaratish uchun forma ko'rinishini ochish shart emas. Bu ``editable`` "
"atributi yordamida amalga oshirilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:335
msgid "Make list views editable."
msgstr "Ro'yxat ko'rinishlarini tahrirlash mumkin qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:337
msgid ""
"Make the ``estate.property.offer`` and ``estate.property.tag`` list views"
" editable."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.offer`` va ``estate.property.tag`` ro'yxat ko'rinishlarini "
"tahrirlash mumkin qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:339
msgid ""
"On the other hand, when a model has a lot of fields it can be tempting to"
" add too many fields in the list view and make it unclear. An alternative"
" method is to add the fields, but make them optionally hidden. This can "
"be achieved thanks to the ``optional`` attribute."
msgstr ""
"Boshqa tomondan, model ko'p maydonlarga ega bo'lganda, ro'yxat ko'rinishiga "
"juda ko'p maydonlar qo'shish va uni noaniq qilish vasvasasi paydo bo'lishi "
"mumkin. Muqobil usul - maydonlarni qo'shish, lekin ularni ixtiyoriy yashirish. "
"Bu ``optional`` atributi yordamida amalga oshirilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:343
msgid "Make a field optional."
msgstr "Maydonni ixtiyoriy qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:345
msgid ""
"Make the field ``date_availability`` on the ``estate.property`` list view"
" optional and hidden by default."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property`` ro'yxat ko'rinishidagi ``date_availability`` maydonini "
"ixtiyoriy va standart bo'yicha yashirilgan qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:348
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Finally, color codes are useful to visually emphasize records. For "
"example, in the real estate module we would like to display refused "
"offers in red and accepted offers in green. This can be achieved thanks "
"to the ``decoration-{$name}`` attribute (see :ref:`reference/js/widgets` "
"for a complete list):"
msgstr ""
"Nihoyat, rang kodlari yozuvlarni vizual ravishda ta'kidlash uchun foydali. "
"Masalan, ko'chmas mulk modulida rad etilgan takliflarni qizil rangda va "
"qabul qilingan takliflarni yashil rangda ko'rsatishni xohlaymiz. Bu "
"``decoration-{$name}`` atributi yordamida amalga oshirilishi mumkin "
"(to'liq ro'yxat uchun :ref:`reference/js/widgets` ga qarang):"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:359
msgid "The records where ``is_partner`` is ``True`` will be displayed in green."
msgstr "``is_partner`` ``True`` bo'lgan yozuvlar yashil rangda ko'rsatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:361
msgid "Add some decorations."
msgstr "Ba'zi bezaklar qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:363
msgid "On the ``estate.property`` list view:"
msgstr "``estate.property`` ro'yxat ko'rinishida:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:365
msgid "Properties with an offer received are green"
msgstr "Taklif qabul qilingan mulklar yashil"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:366
msgid "Properties with an offer accepted are green and bold"
msgstr "Taklif tasdiqlangan mulklar yashil va qalin"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:367
msgid "Properties sold are muted"
msgstr "Sotilgan mulklar o'chiq"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:369
msgid "On the ``estate.property.offer`` list view:"
msgstr "``estate.property.offer`` ro'yxat ko'rinishida:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:371
msgid "Refused offers are red"
msgstr "Rad etilgan takliflar qizil"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:372
msgid "Accepted offers are green"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan takliflar yashil"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:373
msgid "The state should not be visible anymore"
msgstr "Holat endi ko'rinmasligi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:377
msgid "Keep in mind that **all** fields used in attributes must be in the view!"
msgstr "Atributlarda ishlatiladigan **barcha** maydonlar ko'rinishda bo'lishi kerakligini yodda tuting!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:378
msgid ""
"If you want to test the color of the \"Offer Received\" and \"Offer "
"Accepted\" states, add the field in the form view and change it manually "
"(we'll implement the business logic for this later)."
msgstr ""
"\"Taklif qabul qilindi\" va \"Taklif tasdiqlandi\" holatlarining rangini "
"sinab ko'rmoqchi bo'lsangiz, forma ko'rinishiga maydonni qo'shing va "
"uni qo'lda o'zgartiring (buning biznes mantiqini keyinroq amalga oshiramiz)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:384
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this section can be found in "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/search` and "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/search/defaults`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: bu bo'lim bilan bog'liq hujjatlarni "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/search` va "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/search/defaults` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:389
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section, the available properties will be "
"filtered by default, and searching on the living area returns results "
"where the area is larger than the given number."
msgstr ""
"**Maqsad**: bu bo'lim oxirida mavjud mulklar standart bo'yicha "
"filtrlanadi va yashash maydoni bo'yicha qidiruv berilgan raqamdan katta "
"maydonga ega natijalarni qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst
msgid "Default filters and domains"
msgstr "Standart filtrlar va domenlar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:397
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Last but not least, there are some tweaks we would like to apply when "
"searching. First of all, we want to have our 'Available' filter applied "
"by default when we access the properties. To make this happen, we need to"
" use the ``search_default_{$name}`` action context, where ``{$name}`` is "
"the filter name. This means that we can define which filter(s) will be "
"activated by default at the action level."
msgstr ""
"Oxirgi, lekin muhim: qidiruv paytida qo'llashni xohlagan ba'zi "
"sozlamalar mavjud. Avvalo, mulklarga kirganimizda 'Mavjud' filtri "
"standart bo'yicha qo'llanilishini xohlaymiz. Buning uchun ``{$name}`` "
"filtr nomi bo'lgan ``search_default_{$name}`` amal kontekstidan "
"foydalanishimiz kerak. Bu amal darajasida qaysi filtr(lar) standart "
"bo'yicha faollashtirilishini aniqlashimiz mumkinligini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:402
msgid ""
"Here is an example of an `action "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/6decc32a889b46947db6dd4d42ef995935894a2a/addons/crm/report/crm_opportunity_report_views.xml#L115>`__"
" with its `corresponding filter "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/6decc32a889b46947db6dd4d42ef995935894a2a/addons/crm/report/crm_opportunity_report_views.xml#L68>`__."
msgstr ""
"Mana `tegishli filtri "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/6decc32a889b46947db6dd4d42ef995935894a2a/addons/crm/report/crm_opportunity_report_views.xml#L68>`__ "
"bilan `amal "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/6decc32a889b46947db6dd4d42ef995935894a2a/addons/crm/report/crm_opportunity_report_views.xml#L115>`__ misoli."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:407
msgid "Add a default filter."
msgstr "Standart filtr qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:409
msgid ""
"Make the 'Available' filter selected by default in the "
"``estate.property`` action."
msgstr "``estate.property`` amali da 'Mavjud' filtrini standart bo'yicha tanlangan qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:411
msgid ""
"Another useful improvement in our module would be the ability to search "
"efficiently by living area. In practice, a user will want to search for "
"properties of 'at least' the given area. It is unrealistic to expect "
"users would want to find a property of an exact living area. It is always"
" possible to make a custom search, but that's inconvenient."
msgstr ""
"Modulimizdagi yana bir foydali yaxshilanish yashash maydoni bo'yicha "
"samarali qidirish imkoniyati bo'ladi. Amalda foydalanuvchi berilgan "
"maydonga 'kamida' ega bo'lgan mulklarni qidirmoqchi bo'ladi. "
"Foydalanuvchilar aniq yashash maydoniga ega mulkni topmoqchi bo'lishini "
"kutish mantiqsiz. Maxsus qidiruv amalga oshirish har doim mumkin, "
"lekin bu noqulay."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:416
msgid ""
"Search view ``<field>`` elements can have a ``filter_domain`` that "
"overrides the domain generated for searching on the given field. In the "
"given domain, ``self`` represents the value entered by the user. In the "
"example below, it is used to search on both ``name`` and ``description`` "
"fields."
msgstr ""
"Qidiruv ko'rinishidagi ``<field>`` elementlari berilgan maydon bo'yicha "
"qidirish uchun yaratilgan domenni bekor qiladigan ``filter_domain`` ga "
"ega bo'lishi mumkin. Berilgan domenda ``self`` foydalanuvchi kiritgan "
"qiymatni ifodalaydi. Quyidagi misolda u ``name`` va ``description`` "
"maydonlari bo'yicha qidirish uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:428
msgid "Change the living area search."
msgstr "Yashash maydoni qidiruvini o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:430
msgid ""
"Add a ``filter_domain`` to the living area to include properties with an "
"area equal to or greater than the given value."
msgstr ""
"Berilgan qiymatga teng yoki undan katta maydonga ega mulklarni qo'shish "
"uchun yashash maydoniga ``filter_domain`` qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:434
msgid "Stat Buttons"
msgstr "Stat tugmalari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:438
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section, there will be a stat button on the "
"property type form view which shows the list of all offers related to "
"properties of the given type when it is clicked on."
msgstr ""
"**Maqsad**: bu bo'lim oxirida mulk turi forma ko'rinishida bosilganda "
"berilgan turdagi mulklarga tegishli barcha takliflar ro'yxatini ko'rsatadigan "
"stat tugmasi bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst
msgid "Stat button"
msgstr "Stat tugmasi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:445
msgid ""
"If you've already used some functional modules in Odoo, you've probably "
"already encountered a 'stat button'. These buttons are displayed on the "
"top right of a form view and give a quick access to linked documents. In "
"our real estate module, we would like to have a quick link to the offers "
"related to a given property type as depicted in the **Goal** of this "
"section."
msgstr ""
"Agar siz allaqachon Odoo da ba'zi funksional modullardan foydalangan bo'lsangiz, "
"siz ehtimol allaqachon 'stat tugmasi' bilan tanishgansiz. Bu tugmalar forma "
"ko'rinishining yuqori o'ng qismida ko'rsatiladi va bog'liq hujjatlarga tezkor "
"kirish imkonini beradi. Ko'chmas mulk modulimizda bu bo'limning **Maqsadi** da "
"ko'rsatilganidek berilgan mulk turi bilan bog'liq takliflarga tezkor havola "
"bo'lishini xohlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:450
msgid ""
"At this point of the tutorial we have already seen most of the concepts "
"to do this. However, there is not a single solution and it can still be "
"confusing if you don't know where to start from. We'll describe a step-"
"by-step solution in the exercise. It can always be useful to find some "
"examples in the Odoo codebase by looking for ``oe_stat_button``."
msgstr ""
"Darslikning ushbu nuqtasida buni amalga oshirish uchun ko'pchilik "
"tushunchalarni allaqachon ko'rdik. Biroq yagona yechim yo'q va qayerdan "
"boshlashni bilmasangiz hali ham chalkash bo'lishi mumkin. Mashqda qadam-"
"baqadam yechimni tavsiflaymiz. ``oe_stat_button`` ni qidirish orqali "
"Odoo kod bazasida ba'zi misollarni topish har doim foydali bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:455
msgid ""
"The following exercise might be a bit more difficult than the previous "
"ones since it assumes you are able to search for examples in the source "
"code on your own. If you are stuck there is probably someone nearby who "
"can help you ;-)"
msgstr ""
"Quyidagi mashq oldingilardan biroz qiyinroq bo'lishi mumkin, chunki u "
"manba kodida o'z betingizcha misollarni qidira olishingizni taxmin qiladi. "
"Agar qisilsangiz, yaqin atrofda sizga yordam bera oladigan kimdir bor ;-)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:459
msgid ""
"The exercise introduces the concept of :ref:`reference/fields/related`. "
"The easiest way to understand it is to consider it as a specific case of "
"a computed field. The following definition of the ``description`` field:"
msgstr ""
"Mashq :ref:`reference/fields/related` tushunchasini tanishtiradi. Uni "
"tushunishning eng oson usuli - uni hisoblangan maydonning maxsus holati "
"sifatida ko'rib chiqish. Quyidagi ``description`` maydoni ta'rifi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:470
msgid "is equivalent to:"
msgstr "ekvivalent:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:484
msgid "Every time the partner name is changed, the description is modified."
msgstr "Hamkor nomi o'zgartirilgan har safar tavsif o'zgartiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:486
msgid "Add a stat button to property type."
msgstr "Mulk turiga stat tugmasini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:488
msgid ""
"Add the field ``property_type_id`` to ``estate.property.offer``. We can "
"define it as a related field on ``property_id.property_type_id`` and set "
"it as stored."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.offer`` ga ``property_type_id`` maydonini qo'shing. Uni "
"``property_id.property_type_id`` bo'yicha bog'liq maydon sifatida "
"aniqlashimiz va saqlangan deb belgilashimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:491
msgid ""
"Thanks to this field, an offer will be linked to a property type when "
"it's created. You can add the field to the list view of offers to make "
"sure it works."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu maydon tufayli taklif yaratilganda u mulk turiga bog'lanadi. "
"Ishlayotganligini tekshirish uchun takliflar ro'yxat ko'rinishiga maydonni qo'shishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:494
msgid ""
"Add the field ``offer_ids`` to ``estate.property.type`` which is the "
"One2many inverse of the field defined in the previous step."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.type`` ga avvalgi bosqichda aniqlangan maydonning "
"One2many teskarisi bo'lgan ``offer_ids`` maydonini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:497
msgid ""
"Add the field ``offer_count`` to ``estate.property.type``. It is a "
"computed field that counts the number of offers for a given property type"
" (use ``offer_ids`` to do so)."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.type`` ga ``offer_count`` maydonini qo'shing. Bu berilgan "
"mulk turi uchun takliflar sonini hisoblaydigan hisoblangan maydon "
"(buning uchun ``offer_ids`` dan foydalaning)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:500
msgid ""
"At this point, you have all the information necessary to know how many "
"offers are linked to a property type. When in doubt, add ``offer_ids`` "
"and ``offer_count`` directly to the view. The next step is to display the"
" list when clicking on the stat button."
msgstr ""
"Bu nuqtada mulk turiga qancha taklif bog'langanligini bilish uchun zarur "
"bo'lgan barcha ma'lumotlarga egasiz. Shubhalanganingizda, ``offer_ids`` va "
"``offer_count`` ni to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ko'rinishga qo'shing. Keyingi "
"qadam stat tugmasi bosilganda ro'yxatni ko'rsatish."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:504
msgid ""
"Create a stat button on ``estate.property.type`` pointing to the "
"``estate.property.offer`` action. This means you should use the "
"``type=\"action\"`` attribute (go back to the end of :doc:`09_actions` if"
" you need a refresher)."
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.offer`` amaliga ishora qiladigan ``estate.property.type`` "
"da stat tugmasini yarating. Bu ``type=\"action\"`` atributidan "
"foydalanishingiz kerakligini anglatadi (eslatma kerak bo'lsa, "
":doc:`09_actions` ning oxiriga qayting)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:508
msgid ""
"At this point, clicking on the stat button should display all offers. We "
"still need to filter out the offers."
msgstr ""
"Bu nuqtada stat tugmasini bosish barcha takliflarni ko'rsatishi kerak. "
"Hali takliflarni filtrlab chiqarishimiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:511
msgid ""
"On the ``estate.property.offer`` action, add a domain that defines "
"``property_type_id`` as equal to the ``active_id`` (= the current record,"
" `here is an example "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/df37ce50e847e3489eb43d1ef6fc1bac6d6af333/addons/event/views/event_views.xml#L162>`__)"
msgstr ""
"``estate.property.offer`` amalida ``property_type_id`` ni ``active_id`` ga "
"(= joriy yozuv) teng deb aniqlaydigan domen qo'shing "
"(`mana bir misol "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/df37ce50e847e3489eb43d1ef6fc1bac6d6af333/addons/event/views/event_views.xml#L162>`__)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/11_sprinkles.rst:515
msgid ""
"Looking good? If not, don't worry, the :doc:`next chapter "
"<12_inheritance>` doesn't require stat buttons ;-)"
msgstr ""
"Yaxshi ko'rinyaptimi? Agar yo'q bo'lsa, tashvishlanmang, :doc:`keyingi bob "
"<12_inheritance>` stat tugmalarini talab etmaydi ;-)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 12: Inheritance"
msgstr "12-bob: Meros"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:5
msgid ""
"A powerful aspect of Odoo is its modularity. A module is dedicated to a "
"business need, but modules can also interact with one another. This is "
"useful for extending the functionality of an existing module. For "
"example, in our real estate scenario we want to display the list of a "
"salesperson's properties directly in the regular user view."
msgstr ""
"Odoo ning kuchli jihati uning modulligidir. Modul biznes ehtiyojiga "
"bag'ishlangan, ammo modullar bir-biri bilan ham o'zaro ta'sir qilishi "
"mumkin. Bu mavjud modulning funksionalligini kengaytirish uchun foydali. "
"Masalan, ko'chmas mulk stsenariyimizda savdo vakilining mulklari ro'yxatini "
"to'g'ridan-to'g'ri odatiy foydalanuvchi ko'rinishida ko'rsatishni xohlaymiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:10
msgid ""
"But before going through the specific Odoo module inheritance, let's see "
"how we can alter the behavior of the standard CRUD (Create, Retrieve, "
"Update or Delete) methods."
msgstr ""
"Ammo maxsus Odoo moduli merosiga o'tishdan oldin, standart CRUD "
"(Yaratish, O'qish, Yangilash yoki O'chirish) metodlarining xatti-harakatini "
"qanday o'zgartirishimiz mumkinligini ko'raylik."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:14
msgid "Python Inheritance"
msgstr "Python merosi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:20
msgid ""
"It should not be possible to delete a property which is not new or "
"cancelled."
msgstr "Yangi yoki bekor qilinmagan mulkni o'chirish mumkin bo'lmasligi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:26
msgid ""
"When an offer is created, the property state should change to 'Offer "
"Received'"
msgstr "Taklif yaratilganda mulk holati 'Taklif qabul qilindi' ga o'zgarishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:27
msgid ""
"It should not be possible to create an offer with a lower price than an "
"existing offer"
msgstr "Mavjud taklifdan past narxda taklif yaratish mumkin bo'lmasligi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst
msgid "Create"
msgstr "Yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:33
msgid ""
"In our real estate module, we never had to develop anything specific to "
"be able to do the standard CRUD actions. The Odoo framework provides the "
"necessary tools to do them. In fact, such actions are already included in"
" our model thanks to classical Python inheritance::"
msgstr ""
"Ko'chmas mulk modulimizda standart CRUD amallarini amalga oshirish uchun "
"hech qachon maxsus narsa ishlab chiqishga majbur bo'lmadik. Odoo freymvorki "
"ularni amalga oshirish uchun zarur vositalarni taqdim etadi. Aslida, "
"bunday amallar klassik Python merosi tufayli allaqachon modelimizda mavjud::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:46
msgid ""
"Our ``class TestModel`` inherits from :class:`~odoo.models.Model` which "
"provides :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.create`, "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.read`, :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.write` and "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink`."
msgstr ""
"Bizning ``class TestModel`` :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.create`, "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.read`, :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.write` va "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` metodlarini taqdim etadigan "
":class:`~odoo.models.Model` dan meros oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:50
msgid ""
"These methods (and any other method defined on "
":class:`~odoo.models.Model`) can be extended to add specific business "
"logic::"
msgstr ""
"Bu metodlar (va :class:`~odoo.models.Model` da aniqlangan har qanday boshqa "
"metod) maxsus biznes mantiqini qo'shish uchun kengaytirilishi mumkin::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:68
msgid ""
"The decorator :func:`~odoo.api.model` is necessary for the "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.create` method because the content of the "
"recordset ``self`` is not relevant in the context of creation, but it is "
"not necessary for the other CRUD methods."
msgstr ""
":func:`~odoo.api.model` dekoratori :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.create` metodi "
"uchun zarur, chunki ``self`` yozuvlar to'plami mazmuni yaratish "
"kontekstida tegishli emas, lekin boshqa CRUD metodlari uchun zarur emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:72
msgid ""
"It is also important to note that even though we can directly override "
"the :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` method, you will almost always want"
" to write a new method with the decorator :func:`~odoo.api.ondelete` "
"instead. Methods marked with this decorator will be called during "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` and avoids some issues that can occur "
"during uninstalling the model's module when "
":meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` is directly overridden."
msgstr ""
"Shuningdek, :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` metodini to'g'ridan-to'g'ri "
"bekor qilishimiz mumkin bo'lsa-da, siz deyarli har doim buning o'rniga "
":func:`~odoo.api.ondelete` dekorator bilan yangi metod yozmoqchi bo'lasiz. "
"Bu dekorator bilan belgilangan metodlar :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` "
"paytida chaqiriladi va :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.unlink` to'g'ridan-to'g'ri "
"bekor qilingan holda model modulini o'rnatish olib tashlanayotganda yuzaga "
"kelishi mumkin bo'lgan ba'zi muammolardan qochadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:78
msgid ""
"In Python 3, ``super()`` is equivalent to ``super(TestModel, self)``. The"
" latter may be necessary when you need to call the parent method with a "
"modified recordset."
msgstr ""
"Python 3 da ``super()`` ``super(TestModel, self)`` ga ekvivalent. "
"O'zgartirilgan yozuvlar to'plami bilan ota-ona metodini chaqirish kerak "
"bo'lganda ikkinchisi zarur bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:83
msgid ""
"It is very important to **always** call ``super()`` to avoid breaking the"
" flow. There are only a few very specific cases where you don't want to "
"call it."
msgstr ""
"Oqimni buzmashlik uchun ``super()`` ni **har doim** chaqirish juda muhim. "
"Uni chaqirmoqchi bo'lmaydiganingiz uchun faqat bir nechta juda maxsus holat mavjud."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:85
msgid ""
"Make sure to **always** return data consistent with the parent method. "
"For example, if the parent method returns a ``dict()``, your override "
"must also return a ``dict()``."
msgstr ""
"Ota-ona metodi bilan izchil ma'lumotlarni **har doim** qaytarishiga ishonch "
"hosil qiling. Masalan, ota-ona metodi ``dict()`` qaytarsa, sizning "
"bekor qilishingiz ham ``dict()`` qaytarishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:88
msgid "Add business logic to the CRUD methods."
msgstr "CRUD metodlariga biznes mantiqini qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:90
msgid "Prevent deletion of a property if its state is not 'New' or 'Cancelled'"
msgstr "Holati 'Yangi' yoki 'Bekor qilingan' bo'lmasa mulkni o'chirishning oldini oling"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:92
msgid ""
"Tip: create a new method with the :func:`~odoo.api.ondelete` decorator "
"and remember that ``self`` can be a recordset with more than one record."
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: :func:`~odoo.api.ondelete` dekorator bilan yangi metod yarating "
"va ``self`` bir nechta yozuvga ega yozuvlar to'plami bo'lishi mumkinligini yodda tuting."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:95
msgid ""
"At offer creation, set the property state to 'Offer Received'. Also raise"
" an error if the user tries to create an offer with a lower amount than "
"an existing offer."
msgstr ""
"Taklif yaratishda mulk holatini 'Taklif qabul qilindi' ga o'rnating. "
"Shuningdek, foydalanuvchi mavjud taklifdan kam miqdorda taklif yaratmoqchi "
"bo'lsa xato ko'taring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:98
msgid ""
"Tip: the ``property_id`` field is available in the ``vals``, but it is an"
" ``int``. To instantiate an ``estate.property`` object, use "
"``self.env[model_name].browse(value)`` (`example "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/136e4f66cd5cafe7df450514937c7218c7216c93/addons/gamification/models/badge.py#L57>`__)"
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: ``property_id`` maydoni ``vals`` da mavjud, lekin u ``int``. "
"``estate.property`` ob'ektini yaratish uchun "
"``self.env[model_name].browse(value)`` dan foydalaning (`misol "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/136e4f66cd5cafe7df450514937c7218c7216c93/addons/gamification/models/badge.py#L57>`__)"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:103
msgid "Model Inheritance"
msgstr "Model merosi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:105
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
":ref:`reference/orm/inheritance`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: bu mavzu bilan bog'liq hujjatlarni "
":ref:`reference/orm/inheritance` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/12_inheritance.rst:108
msgid ""
"In our real estate module, we would like to display the list of "
"properties linked to a salesperson directly in the Settings / Users & "
"Companies / Users form view. To do this, we need to add a field to the "
"``res.users`` model and adapt its view to show it."
msgstr ""
