msgid "6% of the selling price"
msgstr "Sotish narxining 6%"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/13_other_module.rst:163
msgid "an additional 100.00 from administrative fees"
msgstr "ma'muriy to'lovlar uchun qo'shimcha 100.00"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/13_other_module.rst:165
msgid ""
"Tip: Add the ``invoice_line_ids`` at creation following the example "
"above. For each line, we need a ``name``, ``quantity`` and "
"``price_unit``."
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: Yuqoridagi misol bo'yicha yaratilishida ``invoice_line_ids`` "
"qo'shing. Har bir satr uchun ``name``, ``quantity`` va ``price_unit`` kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/13_other_module.rst:168
msgid ""
"This chapter might be one of the most difficult that has been covered so "
"far, but it is the closest to what Odoo development will be in practice. "
"In the :doc:`next chapter <14_qwebintro>`, we will introduce the "
"templating mechanism used in Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Bu bob hozirgacha ko'rib chiqilgan eng qiyinlaridan biri bo'lishi mumkin, "
"lekin u Odoo ishlanmasining amalda qanday bo'lishiga eng yaqin. "
":doc:`Keyingi bobda <14_qwebintro>`, Odoo da ishlatiladigan "
"shablon mexanizmini taqdim etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 14: A Brief History Of QWeb"
msgstr "14-bob: QWeb ning qisqacha tarixi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:5
msgid ""
"So far the interface design of our real estate module has been rather "
"limited. Building a list view is straightforward since only the list of "
"fields is necessary. The same holds true for the form view: despite the "
"use of a few tags such as ``<group>`` or ``<page>``, there is very little"
" to do in terms of design."
msgstr ""
"Hozirgacha ko'chmas mulk modulimizning interfeys dizayni juda cheklangan "
"edi. Ro'yxat ko'rinishini qurish oddiy, chunki faqat maydonlar ro'yxati "
"zarur. Xuddi shu narsa forma ko'rinishi uchun ham amal qiladi: ``<group>`` "
"yoki ``<page>`` kabi bir nechta teglarning ishlatilishiga qaramay, "
"dizayn nuqtai nazaridan qiladigan narsa juda oz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:10
msgid ""
"However, if we want to give a unique look to our application, it is "
"necessary to go a step further and be able to design new views. Moreover,"
" other features such as PDF reports or website pages need another tool to"
" be created with more flexibility: a templating_ engine."
msgstr ""
"Biroq ilovamizga noyob ko'rinish bermoqchi bo'lsak, bir qadam oldinga "
"qo'yib yangi ko'rinishlarni loyihalash imkoniyatiga ega bo'lish kerak. "
"Bundan tashqari, PDF hisobotlar yoki veb-sayt sahifalari kabi boshqa "
"xususiyatlar ko'proq moslashuvchanlik bilan yaratilishi uchun boshqa "
"vositani talab qiladi: shablon_ mexanizmi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:14
msgid ""
"You might already be familiar with existing engines such as Jinja "
"(Python), ERB (Ruby) or Twig (PHP). Odoo comes with its own built-in "
"engine: :ref:`reference/qweb`. QWeb is the primary templating engine used"
" by Odoo. It is an XML templating engine and used mostly to generate HTML"
" fragments and pages."
msgstr ""
"Siz allaqachon Jinja (Python), ERB (Ruby) yoki Twig (PHP) kabi mavjud "
"mexanizmlar bilan tanish bo'lishingiz mumkin. Odoo o'zining o'rnatilgan "
"mexanizmiga ega: :ref:`reference/qweb`. QWeb Odoo tomonidan ishlatiladigan "
"asosiy shablon mexanizmi. Bu XML shablon mexanizmi va asosan HTML "
"fragmentlar va sahifalarni yaratish uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:19
msgid ""
"You probably already have come across the `kanban board`_ in Odoo where "
"the records are displayed in a card-like structure. We will build such a "
"view for our real estate module."
msgstr ""
"Siz ehtimol allaqachon Odoo da yozuvlar karta ko'rinishida ko'rsatiladigan "
"`kanban taxtasi`_ bilan tanishgansiz. Biz ko'chmas mulk modulimiz uchun "
"bunday ko'rinish quramiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:23
msgid "Concrete Example: A Kanban View"
msgstr "Aniq misol: Kanban ko'rinishi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/kanban`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: bu mavzu bilan bog'liq hujjatlarni "
":ref:`reference/view_architectures/kanban` da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:30
msgid ""
"**Goal**: at the end of this section a Kanban view of the properties "
"should be created:"
msgstr "**Maqsad**: bu bo'lim oxirida mulklarning Kanban ko'rinishi yaratilishi kerak:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:36
msgid ""
"In our estate application, we would like to add a Kanban view to display "
"our properties. Kanban views are a standard Odoo view (like the form and "
"list views), but their structure is much more flexible. In fact, the "
"structure of each card is a mix of form elements (including basic HTML) "
"and QWeb. The definition of a Kanban view is similar to the definition of"
" the list and form views, except that their root element is ``<kanban>``."
" In its simplest form, a Kanban view looks like:"
msgstr ""
"Ko'chmas mulk ilovamizda mulklarimizni ko'rsatish uchun Kanban ko'rinishini "
"qo'shmoqchimiz. Kanban ko'rinishlari standart Odoo ko'rinishi (forma va "
"ro'yxat ko'rinishlari kabi), ammo ularning tuzilishi ancha moslashuvchan. "
"Aslida, har bir kartaning tuzilishi forma elementlari (asosiy HTML ni "
"o'z ichiga olgan) va QWeb aralashmasi. Kanban ko'rinishining ta'rifi "
"ro'yxat va forma ko'rinishlari ta'rifiga o'xshash, faqat ularning "
"ildiz elementi ``<kanban>``. Eng oddiy shaklda Kanban ko'rinishi quyidagicha:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:55
msgid "Let's break down this example:"
msgstr "Ushbu misolni tahlil qilaylik:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:57
msgid ""
"``<templates>``: defines a list of :ref:`reference/qweb` templates. "
"Kanban views *must* define at least one root template ``card``, which "
"will be rendered once for each record."
msgstr ""
"``<templates>``: :ref:`reference/qweb` shablonlar ro'yxatini belgilaydi. "
"Kanban ko'rinishlari har bir yozuv uchun bir marta ko'rsatiladigan "
"kamida bitta ``card`` ildiz shablonini *belgilashi* shart."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:59
msgid ""
"``<t t-name=\"card\">``: ``<t>`` is a placeholder element for QWeb "
"directives. In this case, it is used to set the ``name`` of the template "
"to ``card``"
msgstr ""
"``<t t-name=\"card\">``: ``<t>`` QWeb direktivalari uchun to'ldiruvchi "
"element. Bunday holda, u shablonning ``name`` ini ``card`` ga o'rnatish "
"uchun ishlatiladi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:61
msgid "``<field name=\"name\"/>``: this will add the ``name`` field to the view."
msgstr "``<field name=\"name\"/>``: bu ko'rinishga ``name`` maydonini qo'shadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:63
msgid "Make a minimal kanban view."
msgstr "Minimal kanban ko'rinishini yarating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:65
msgid ""
"Using the simple example provided, create a minimal Kanban view for the "
"properties. The only field to display is the ``name``."
msgstr ""
"Taqdim etilgan oddiy misoldan foydalanib, mulklar uchun minimal Kanban "
"ko'rinishini yarating. Ko'rsatilishi kerak bo'lgan yagona maydon ``name``."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:68
msgid ""
"Tip: you must add ``kanban`` in the ``view_mode`` of the corresponding "
"``ir.actions.act_window``."
msgstr ""
"Maslahat: tegishli ``ir.actions.act_window`` ning ``view_mode`` ga "
"``kanban`` qo'shishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:71
msgid ""
"Once the Kanban view is working, we can start improving it. If we want to"
" display an element conditionally, we can use the ``t-if`` directive (see"
" :ref:`reference/qweb/conditionals`)."
msgstr ""
"Kanban ko'rinishi ishlayotgan bo'lsa, uni yaxshilashni boshlashimiz mumkin. "
"Agar elementni shartli ravishda ko'rsatmoqchi bo'lsak, ``t-if`` direktivisidan "
"foydalanishimiz mumkin (:ref:`reference/qweb/conditionals` ga qarang)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:90
msgid "We added a few things:"
msgstr "Bir nechta narsa qo'shdik:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:92
msgid "``t-if``: the ``<div>`` element is rendered if the condition is true."
msgstr "``t-if``: shart to'g'ri bo'lsa ``<div>`` elementi ko'rsatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:93
msgid ""
"``record``: an object with all the requested fields as its attributes. "
"Each field has two attributes ``value`` and ``raw_value``. The former is "
"formatted according to current user parameters and the latter is the "
"direct value from a :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.read`."
msgstr ""
"``record``: barcha so'ralgan maydonlari atribut sifatida bo'lgan ob'ekt. "
"Har bir maydon ``value`` va ``raw_value`` ikkita atributga ega. "
"Birinchisi joriy foydalanuvchi parametrlariga ko'ra formatlangan, "
"ikkinchisi esa :meth:`~odoo.models.Model.read` dan to'g'ridan-to'g'ri qiymat."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:97
msgid ""
"In the above example, the field ``name`` was added in the ``<templates>``"
" element, but ``state`` is outside of it. When we need the value of a "
"field but don't want to display it in the view, it is possible to add it "
"outside of the ``<templates>`` element."
msgstr ""
"Yuqoridagi misolda ``name`` maydoni ``<templates>`` elementida qo'shilgan, "
"lekin ``state`` uning tashqarisida. Maydon qiymatini kerak bo'lganda, "
"lekin uni ko'rinishda ko'rsatmoqchi bo'lmaganda, uni ``<templates>`` "
"elementidan tashqarida qo'shish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:101
msgid "Improve the Kanban view."
msgstr "Kanban ko'rinishini yaxshilang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:103
msgid ""
"Add the following fields to the Kanban view: expected price, best price, "
"selling price and tags. Pay attention: the best price is only displayed "
"when an offer is received, while the selling price is only displayed when"
" an offer is accepted."
msgstr ""
"Kanban ko'rinishiga quyidagi maydonlarni qo'shing: kutilayotgan narx, "
"eng yaxshi narx, sotish narxi va teglar. Diqqat: eng yaxshi narx faqat "
"taklif qabul qilinganda ko'rsatiladi, sotish narxi esa faqat taklif "
"tasdiqlanganda ko'rsatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:107
#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:118
msgid "Refer to the **Goal** of the section for a visual example."
msgstr "Vizual misol uchun bo'limning **Maqsadi** ga qarang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:109
msgid ""
"Let's give the final touch to our view: the properties must be grouped by"
" type by default. You might want to have a look at the various options "
"described in :ref:`reference/view_architectures/kanban`."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishimizga yakuniy tegizamiz: mulklar standart bo'yicha tur bo'yicha "
"guruhlangan bo'lishi kerak. :ref:`reference/view_architectures/kanban` da "
"tasvirlangan turli opsiyalarga nazar tashlashni xohlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:113
msgid "Add default grouping."
msgstr "Standart guruhlashni qo'shing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:115
msgid ""
"Use the appropriate attribute to group the properties by type by default."
" You must also prevent drag and drop."
msgstr ""
"Mulklarni standart bo'yicha tur bo'yicha guruhlash uchun tegishli "
"atributdan foydalaning. Shuningdek, sudrab-tashlab qo'yishning oldini olishingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/14_qwebintro.rst:120
msgid ""
"Kanban views are a typical example of how it is always a good idea to "
"start from an existing view and fine tune it instead of starting from "
"scratch. There are many options and classes available, so... read and "
"learn!"
msgstr ""
"Kanban ko'rinishlari noldan boshlash o'rniga mavjud ko'rinishdan "
"boshlash va uni sozlashning har doim yaxshi fikr ekanligining tipik "
"misoli. Ko'plab opsiyalar va klasslar mavjud, shuning uchun... o'qing va o'rganing!"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:3
msgid "Chapter 15: The final word"
msgstr "15-bob: So'nggi so'z"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:6
msgid "Coding guidelines"
msgstr "Kod yozish qoidalari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:8
msgid ""
"We will start refactoring the code to match to the Odoo coding "
"guidelines. The guidelines aim to improve the quality of the Odoo Apps "
"code."
msgstr ""
"Kodni Odoo kod yozish qoidalariga moslashtirish uchun refaktoringni "
"boshlaymiz. Qoidalar Odoo Ilovalari kodi sifatini oshirishga qaratilgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:11
msgid ""
"**Reference**: you will find the Odoo coding guidelines in "
":doc:`/contributing/development/coding_guidelines`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: Odoo kod yozish qoidalarini "
":doc:`/contributing/development/coding_guidelines` da topasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:14
msgid "Polish your code."
msgstr "Kodingizni sayqallang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:16
msgid ""
"Refactor your code to respect the coding guidelines. Don't forget to run "
"your linter and respect the module structure, the variable names, the "
"method name convention, the model attribute order and the xml ids."
msgstr ""
"Kod yozish qoidalariga rioya qilish uchun kodni qayta yozing. "
"Linterni ishga tushirishni va modul tuzilishi, o'zgaruvchi nomlari, "
"metod nomlash konventsiyasi, model atribut tartibi va xml id lariga "
"rioya qilishni unutmang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:21
msgid "Test on the runbot"
msgstr "Runbot da test qilish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:23
msgid ""
"Odoo has its own :abbr:`CI (Continuous integration)` server named `runbot"
" <https://runbot.odoo.com/>`__. All commits, branches and PR will be "
"tested to avoid regressions or breaking of the stable versions. All the "
"runs that pass the tests are deployed on their own server with demo data."
msgstr ""
"Odoo ning `runbot <https://runbot.odoo.com/>`__ nomli o'zining "
":abbr:`CI (Uzluksiz integratsiya)` serveri bor. Barcha commitlar, "
"branchlar va PR regressiyalar yoki barqaror versiyalarning buzilishidan "
"qochish uchun sinovdan o'tkaziladi. Testlardan o'tgan barcha ishga "
"tushirishlar o'z serverlarida demo ma'lumotlar bilan joylashtiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:27
msgid "Play with the runbot."
msgstr "Runbot bilan o'ynang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/server_framework_101/15_final_word.rst:29
msgid ""
"Feel free to go to the runbot website and open the last stable version of"
" Odoo to check out all the available applications and functionalities."
msgstr ""
"Runbot veb-saytiga kirib, barcha mavjud ilovalar va funksiyalarni ko'rish "
"uchun Odoo ning so'nggi barqaror versiyasini ochishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:3
msgid "Setup guide"
msgstr "O'rnatish qo'llanmasi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:5
msgid ""
"Depending on the intended use case, there are multiple ways to install "
"Odoo. For developers of the Odoo community and Odoo employees alike, the "
"preferred way is to perform a source install (:dfn:`running Odoo from the"
" source code`)."
msgstr ""
"Mo'ljallangan foydalanish holatiga qarab, Odoo ni o'rnatishning bir necha "
"usuli mavjud. Odoo hamjamiyati dasturchilari va Odoo xodimlari uchun ham "
"afzallik berilgan usul - manba o'rnatishni amalga oshirish "
"(:dfn:`Odoo ni manba kodidan ishga tushirish`)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:10
msgid ""
"Follow the :ref:`contributing/development/setup` section of the "
"contributing guide to prepare your environment for pushing local changes "
"to the Odoo repositories."
msgstr ""
"Mahalliy o'zgarishlarni Odoo omborlariga yuborish uchun muhitingizni "
"tayyorlash uchun hissa qo'shish qo'llanmasining "
":ref:`contributing/development/setup` bo'limiga amal qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:14
msgid "Adapt the environment for the tutorials"
msgstr "Muhitni darsliklar uchun moslashtirilg"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:16
msgid ""
"By now, you should have downloaded the source code into two local "
"repositories, one for `odoo/odoo` and one for `odoo/enterprise`. These "
"repositories are set up to push changes to pre-defined forks on GitHub. "
"This will prove to be convenient when you start contributing to the "
"codebase, but in the scope of following a tutorial, we want to avoid "
"polluting them with training material. Let's then push your changes in a "
"third repository: `odoo/tutorials`. Like the first two repositories, it "
"will be part of the `addons-path` that references all directories "
"containing Odoo modules."
msgstr ""
"Hozir siz manba kodini ikkita mahalliy omborga, biri `odoo/odoo` va biri "
"`odoo/enterprise` uchun yuklab olgan bo'lishingiz kerak. Bu omborlar "
"GitHub da oldindan belgilangan fork larga o'zgarishlarni yuborish uchun "
"sozlangan. Kod bazasiga hissa qo'shishni boshlaganingizda bu qulay bo'ladi, "
"lekin darslikni bajarishda ularni o'quv materiallari bilan ifloslantirmaslikni "
"xohlaymiz. Keyin o'zgarishlaringizni uchinchi omborga yuboramiz: "
"`odoo/tutorials`. Birinchi ikkita ombor kabi, u Odoo modullarini o'z ichiga "
"olgan barcha kataloglarga murojaat qiladigan `addons-path` ning bir qismi bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:24
msgid ""
"Depending on the tutorial that you are following, you might not need to "
"install all the modules that this repository contains."
msgstr ""
"Bajarayotgan darsliqingizga qarab, ushbu ombor o'z ichiga olgan barcha "
"modullarni o'rnatish shart bo'lmasligi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:27
msgid ""
"Following the same process as with the `odoo/odoo` and `odoo/enterprise` "
"repositories, clone the `odoo/tutorials` repository on your machine with:"
msgstr ""
"`odoo/odoo` va `odoo/enterprise` omborlari bilan bir xil jarayondan so'ng, "
"mashiningizda `odoo/tutorials` omborini quyidagi bilan klonlang:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:34
msgid ""
"Configure your fork and Git to push changes to your fork rather than to "
"the main codebase. If you work at Odoo, configure Git to push changes to "
"the shared fork created on the account **odoo-dev**."
msgstr ""
"Fork ingizni va Gitni asosiy kod bazasiga emas, fork ingizga o'zgarishlarni "
"yuborish uchun sozlang. Agar Odoo da ishlasangiz, **odoo-dev** hisobida "
"yaratilgan umumiy fork ga o'zgarishlarni yuborish uchun Gitni sozlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:39
msgid "Link Git with your fork"
msgstr "Gitni fork ingiz bilan bog'lang"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:41
msgid ""
"Visit `github.com/odoo/tutorials <https://github.com/odoo/tutorials>`_ "
"and click the :guilabel:`Fork` button to create a fork of the repository "
"on your account."
msgstr ""
"`github.com/odoo/tutorials <https://github.com/odoo/tutorials>`_ ga kiring "
"va hisobingizda ombor fork ini yaratish uchun :guilabel:`Fork` tugmasini bosing."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:44
msgid ""
"In the command below, replace `<your_github_account>` with the name of "
"the GitHub account on which you created the fork."
msgstr ""
"Quyidagi buyruqda `<your_github_account>` ni fork yaratgan GitHub "
"hisobining nomi bilan almashtiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:52
msgid "Link Git with odoo-dev"
msgstr "Gitni odoo-dev bilan bog'lang"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:60
msgid ""
"That's it! Your environment is now prepared to run Odoo from the sources,"
" and you have successfully created a repository to serve as an addons "
"directory. This will allow you to push your work to GitHub."
msgstr ""
"Hammasi shu! Muhitingiz endi Odoo ni manbadan ishga tushirishga tayyor "
"va siz muvaffaqiyatli addon katalogi bo'lib xizmat qiladigan ombor yaratdingiz. "
"Bu sizga GitHub ga ishingizni yuborish imkonini beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:65
msgid "**For Odoo employees only:**"
msgstr "**Faqat Odoo xodimlari uchun:**"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:67
msgid ""
"Make sure to read very carefully :ref:`contributing/development/first-"
"contribution`. In particular, your branch name must follow our "
"conventions."
msgstr ""
":ref:`contributing/development/first-contribution` ni juda diqqat bilan "
"o'qishga ishonch hosil qiling. Xususan, branch nomingiz bizning "
"konventsiyalarimizga amal qilishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:70
msgid ""
"Once you have pushed your first change to the shared fork on **odoo-"
"dev**, create a :abbr:`PR (Pull Request)`. Please put your quadrigram in "
"the PR title (e.g., \"abcd - Technical Training\")."
msgstr ""
"**odoo-dev** da umumiy fork ga birinchi o'zgarishingizni yuborgach, "
":abbr:`PR (Pull Request)` yarating. PR sarlavhasiga to'rt harfli "
"qisqartmangizni qo'ying (masalan, \"abcd - Texnik o'quv\")."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:74
msgid ""
"This will enable you to share your upcoming work and receive feedback "
"from your coaches. To ensure a continuous feedback loop, we recommend "
"pushing a new commit as soon as you complete a chapter of the tutorial. "
"Note that the PR is automatically updated with commits you push to "
"**odoo-dev**, you don't need to open multiple PRs."
msgstr ""
"Bu sizga kelgusi ishingizni ulashish va murabbiylaringizdan fikr-mulohaza "
"olish imkonini beradi. Uzluksiz fikr-mulohaza tsiklini ta'minlash uchun, "
"darsliqning har bir bobini tugatgach, yangi commit yuborishni tavsiya etamiz. "
"PR **odoo-dev** ga yuborganingiz commitlar bilan avtomatik yangilanishini, "
"bir nechta PR ochish shart emasligini e'tibor bering."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:79
msgid ""
"At Odoo we use `Runbot <https://runbot.odoo.com>`_ extensively for our "
":abbr:`CI (Continuous Integration)` tests. When you push your changes to "
"**odoo-dev**, Runbot creates a new build and test your code. Once logged "
"in, you will be able to see your branches `Tutorials project "
"<https://runbot.odoo.com/runbot/tutorials-12>`_."
msgstr ""
"Odoo da biz :abbr:`CI (Uzluksiz integratsiya)` testlarimiz uchun "
"`Runbot <https://runbot.odoo.com>`_ dan keng foydalanishimiz. "
"**odoo-dev** ga o'zgarishlaringizni yuborganingizda, Runbot yangi "
"qurish va kodingizni sinovdan o'tkazish yaratadi. Tizimga kirganingizdan "
"so'ng `Darsliklar loyihasi "
"<https://runbot.odoo.com/runbot/tutorials-12>`_ da branchlaringizni ko'ra olasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:86
msgid ""
"The specific location of the repositories on your file system is not "
"crucial. However, for the sake of simplicity, we will assume that you "
"have cloned all the repositories under the same directory. If this is not"
" the case, make sure to adjust the following commands accordingly, "
"providing the appropriate relative path from the `odoo/odoo` repository "
"to the `odoo/tutorials` repository."
msgstr ""
"Fayl tizimidagi omborlarning aniq joylashuvi muhim emas. Biroq "
"soddalik uchun barcha omborlarni bir xil katalog ostida klonlaganingizni "
"taxmin qilamiz. Agar bunday bo'lmasa, `odoo/odoo` omboridan `odoo/tutorials` "
"omboriga tegishli nisbiy yo'lni taqdim etib, quyidagi buyruqlarni "
"mos ravishda sozlashga ishonch hosil qiling."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:93
msgid "Run the server"
msgstr "Serverni ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:96
msgid "Launch with `odoo-bin`"
msgstr "`odoo-bin` bilan ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:98
msgid ""
"Once all dependencies are set up, Odoo can be launched by running `odoo-"
"bin`, the command-line interface of the server."
msgstr ""
"Barcha bog'liqliklar o'rnatilgach, Odoo server buyruq qatori interfeysi "
"bo'lgan `odoo-bin` ni ishga tushirish orqali ishga tushirilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:106
msgid ""
"There are multiple :ref:`command-line arguments "
"<reference/cmdline/server>` that you can use to run the server. In this "
"training you will only need some of them."
msgstr ""
"Serverni ishga tushirish uchun foydalanishingiz mumkin bo'lgan bir nechta "
":ref:`buyruq qatori argumentlari <reference/cmdline/server>` mavjud. "
"Ushbu o'qitishda faqat ularning bir qismiga muhtoj bo'lasiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:111
msgid "The database that is going to be used."
msgstr "Foydalaniladigan ma'lumotlar bazasi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:115
msgid ""
"A comma-separated list of directories in which modules are stored. These "
"directories are scanned for modules."
msgstr ""
"Modullar saqlanadigan vergul bilan ajratilgan kataloglar ro'yxati. "
"Bu kataloglar modullar uchun skanlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:120
msgid ""
"Prevent the worker from using more than <limit> CPU seconds for each "
"request."
msgstr "Ishchini har bir so'rov uchun <limit> dan ortiq CPU soniyasidan foydalanishdan to'xtating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:124
msgid ""
"Prevent the worker from taking longer than <limit> seconds to process a "
"request."
msgstr "Ishchini so'rovni qayta ishlash uchun <limit> soniyadan ko'proq vaqt olishdan to'xtating."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:127
msgid ""
"The :option:`--limit-time-cpu` and :option:`--limit-time-real` arguments "
"can be used to prevent the worker from being killed when debugging the "
"source code."
msgstr ""
":option:`--limit-time-cpu` va :option:`--limit-time-real` argumentlari "
"manba kodini disk raskadrovka paytida ishchining o'ldirilishining oldini "
"olish uchun ishlatilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst
msgid ""
"You may face an error similar to `AttributeError: module '<MODULE_NAME>' "
"has no attribute '<$ATTRIBUTE'>`. In this case, you may need to re-"
"install the module with :command:`$ pip install --upgrade --force-"
"reinstall <MODULE_NAME>`."
msgstr ""
"`AttributeError: module '<MODULE_NAME>' has no attribute '<$ATTRIBUTE'>` "
"ga o'xshash xatoga duch kelishingiz mumkin. Bunday holda modulni "
":command:`$ pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall <MODULE_NAME>` "
"bilan qayta o'rnatishingiz kerak bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst
msgid ""
"If this error occurs with more than one module, you may need to re-"
"install all the requirements with :command:`$ pip install --upgrade "
"--force-reinstall -r requirements.txt`."
msgstr ""
"Agar bu xato bir nechta modulda yuzaga kelsa, barcha talablarni "
":command:`$ pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall -r requirements.txt` "
"bilan qayta o'rnatishingiz kerak bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst
msgid "You can also clear the python cache to solve the issue:"
msgstr "Muammoni hal qilish uchun Python keshini ham tozalashingiz mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:141
msgid "Other commonly used arguments are:"
msgstr "Boshqa keng ishlatiladigan argumentlar:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:143
msgid ""
":option:`-i <odoo-bin --init>`: Install some modules before running the "
"server (comma-separated list). This is equivalent to going to "
":guilabel:`Apps` in the user interface, and installing the module from "
"there."
msgstr ""
":option:`-i <odoo-bin --init>`: Serverni ishga tushirishdan oldin ba'zi "
"modullarni o'rnating (vergul bilan ajratilgan ro'yxat). Bu foydalanuvchi "
"interfeysidagi :guilabel:`Ilovalar` ga o'tish va u yerdan modulni "
"o'rnatishga ekvivalent."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:146
msgid ""
":option:`-u <odoo-bin --update>`: Update some modules before running the "
"server (comma-separated list). This is equivalent to going to "
":guilabel:`Apps` in the user interface, selecting a module, and upgrading"
" it from there."
msgstr ""
":option:`-u <odoo-bin --update>`: Serverni ishga tushirishdan oldin ba'zi "
"modullarni yangilang (vergul bilan ajratilgan ro'yxat). Bu foydalanuvchi "
"interfeysidagi :guilabel:`Ilovalar` ga o'tish, modulni tanlash va "
"u yerdan yangilashga ekvivalent."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:151
msgid "Log in to Odoo"
msgstr "Odoo ga kirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:153
msgid ""
"Open http://localhost:8069/ on your browser. We recommend using `Chrome "
"<https://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/>`_, `Firefox "
"<https://www.mozilla.org/firefox/new/>`_, or any other browser with "
"development tools."
msgstr ""
"Brauzeringizda http://localhost:8069/ ni oching. `Chrome "
"<https://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/>`_, `Firefox "
"<https://www.mozilla.org/firefox/new/>`_ yoki ishlab chiqish vositalari "
"bilan boshqa brauzerdan foydalanishni tavsiya etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:157
msgid "To log in as the administrator user, use the following credentials:"
msgstr "Administrator foydalanuvchisi sifatida kirish uchun quyidagi hisob ma'lumotlaridan foydalaning:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:159
msgid "email: `admin`"
msgstr "elektron pochta: `admin`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:160
msgid "password: `admin`"
msgstr "parol: `admin`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:163
msgid "Enable the developer mode"
msgstr "Dasturchi rejimini yoqing"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:165
msgid ""
"The developer or debug mode is useful for training as it gives access to "
"additional (advanced) tools. :ref:`Enable the developer mode <developer-"
"mode>` now. Choose the method that you prefer; they are all equivalent."
msgstr ""
"Dasturchi yoki disk raskadrovka rejimi qo'shimcha (ilg'or) vositalarga "
"kirish imkonini bergani uchun o'qitish uchun foydali. Hozir "
":ref:`dasturchi rejimini yoqing <developer-mode>`. O'zingiz afzal "
"ko'rgan usulni tanlang; ularning barchasi ekvivalent."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:170
msgid "Extra tools"
msgstr "Qo'shimcha vositalar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:173
msgid "Useful Git commands"
msgstr "Foydali Git buyruqlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:175
msgid "Here are some useful Git commands for your day-to-day work."
msgstr "Mana kundalik ishingiz uchun ba'zi foydali Git buyruqlari."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst
msgid "Switch branches:"
msgstr "Branchlarni almashtirish:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst
msgid ""
"When you switch branches, both repositories (odoo and enterprise) must be"
" synchronized, i.e. both need to be in the same branch."
msgstr ""
"Branchlarni almashtirganda, ikkala ombor ham (odoo va enterprise) "
"sinxronlangan bo'lishi kerak, ya'ni ikkalasi ham bir xil branchda bo'lishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:189
msgid "Fetch and rebase:"
msgstr "Olish va qayta asoslash:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:202
msgid "Code Editor"
msgstr "Kod muharriri"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:204
msgid ""
"If you are working at Odoo, many of your colleagues are using `VSCode "
"<https://code.visualstudio.com>`_, `VSCodium <https://vscodium.com>`_ "
"(the open source equivalent), `PyCharm "
"<https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/download/#section=linux>`_, or "
"`Sublime Text <https://www.sublimetext.com>`_. However, you are free to "
"choose your preferred editor."
msgstr ""
"Agar Odoo da ishlasangiz, ko'pgina hamkasblaringiz `VSCode "
"<https://code.visualstudio.com>`_, `VSCodium <https://vscodium.com>`_ "
"(ochiq manbali ekvivalent), `PyCharm "
"<https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/download/#section=linux>`_, yoki "
"`Sublime Text <https://www.sublimetext.com>`_ dan foydalanadi. Biroq, "
"siz o'zingiz afzal ko'rgan muharririni tanlashda erkinssiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:209
msgid ""
"It is important to configure your linters correctly. Using a linter helps"
" you by showing syntax and semantic warnings or errors. Odoo source code "
"tries to respect Python's and JavaScript's standards, but some of them "
"can be ignored."
msgstr ""
"Linterlaringizni to'g'ri sozlash muhim. Linterdan foydalanish sintaksis "
"va semantik ogohlantirishlar yoki xatolarni ko'rsatish orqali yordam beradi. "
"Odoo manba kodi Python va JavaScript standartlariga rioya qilishga harakat "
"qiladi, lekin ularning ba'zilari e'tiborga olinmasligi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:213
msgid "For Python, we use PEP8 with these options ignored:"
msgstr "Python uchun biz PEP8 dan ushbu parametrlar e'tiborga olinmagan holda foydalanamiz:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:215
msgid "`E501`: line too long"
msgstr "`E501`: satr juda uzun"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:216
msgid "`E301`: expected 1 blank line, found 0"
msgstr "`E301`: 1 ta bo'sh satr kutilgan, 0 ta topildi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:217
msgid "`E302`: expected 2 blank lines, found 1"
msgstr "`E302`: 2 ta bo'sh satr kutilgan, 1 ta topildi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:219
msgid ""
"For JavaScript, we use ESLint and you can find a `configuration file "
"example here <https://github.com/odoo/odoo/wiki/Javascript-coding-"
"guidelines#use-a-linter>`_."
msgstr ""
"JavaScript uchun ESLint dan foydalanamiz va `konfiguratsiya fayl misolini "
"bu yerda <https://github.com/odoo/odoo/wiki/Javascript-coding-"
"guidelines#use-a-linter>`_ topishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:223
msgid "Administrator tools for PostgreSQL"
msgstr "PostgreSQL uchun administrator vositalari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:225
msgid ""
"You can manage your PostgreSQL databases using the command line as "
"demonstrated earlier or using a GUI application such as `pgAdmin "
"<https://www.pgadmin.org/download/pgadmin-4-apt/>`_ or `DBeaver "
"<https://dbeaver.io/>`_."
msgstr ""
"PostgreSQL ma'lumotlar bazalaringizni avval ko'rsatilganidek buyruq "
"qatori yordamida yoki `pgAdmin "
"<https://www.pgadmin.org/download/pgadmin-4-apt/>`_ yoki `DBeaver "
"<https://dbeaver.io/>`_ kabi GUI ilovasi yordamida boshqarishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:229
msgid ""
"To connect the GUI application to your database we recommend you connect "
"using the Unix socket."
msgstr ""
"GUI ilovasini ma'lumotlar bazasiga ulash uchun Unix socket orqali "
"ulanishni tavsiya etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:231
msgid "Host name/address: `/var/run/postgresql`"
msgstr "Xost nomi/manzil: `/var/run/postgresql`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:232
msgid "Port: `5432`"
msgstr "Port: `5432`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:233
msgid "Username: `$USER`"
msgstr "Foydalanuvchi nomi: `$USER`"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:236
msgid "Python Debugging"
msgstr "Python disk raskadrovkasi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:238
msgid ""
"When facing a bug or trying to understand how the code works, simply "
"printing things out can go a long way, but a proper debugger can save a "
"lot of time."
msgstr ""
"Xato bilan yuzlashganda yoki kodning qanday ishlashini tushunishga "
"harakat qilganda, narsalarni shunchaki chop etish uzoq yo'l olishi mumkin, "
"lekin to'g'ri disk raskadrovchi ko'p vaqt tejashi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:241
msgid ""
"You can use a classic Python library debugger (`pdb "
"<https://docs.python.org/3/library/pdb.html>`_, `pudb "
"<https://pypi.org/project/pudb/>`_ or `ipdb "
"<https://pypi.org/project/ipdb/>`_), or you can use your editor's "
"debugger."
msgstr ""
"Klassik Python kutubxona disk raskadrovchisidan (`pdb "
"<https://docs.python.org/3/library/pdb.html>`_, `pudb "
"<https://pypi.org/project/pudb/>`_ yoki `ipdb "
"<https://pypi.org/project/ipdb/>`_) yoki muharriringizning disk raskadrovchisidan "
"foydalanishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:245
msgid ""
"In the following example we use ipdb, but the process is similar with "
"other libraries."
msgstr "Quyidagi misolda ipdb dan foydalanamiz, lekin jarayon boshqa kutubxonalar bilan o'xshash."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:247
msgid "Install the library:"
msgstr "Kutubxonani o'rnating:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:253
msgid "Place a trigger (breakpoint):"
msgstr "Trigger (to'xtash nuqtasi) joylashtiring:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:272
msgid "Here is a list of commands:"
msgstr "Mana buyruqlar ro'yxati:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:276
msgid ""
"Print the list of available commands if not argument is supplied. With a "
"command as an argument, print the help about that command."
msgstr ""
"Agar argument berilmasa, mavjud buyruqlar ro'yxatini chop eting. "
"Argument sifatida buyruq berilsa, o'sha buyruq haqida yordam chop eting."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:281
msgid "The value of the `expression` is pretty-printed using the `pprint` module."
msgstr "`expression` ning qiymati `pprint` moduli yordamida chiroyli chop etiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:285
msgid "Print a stack trace with the most recent frame at the bottom."
msgstr "Eng so'nggi kadr pastda bo'lgan stek izini chop eting."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:289
msgid ""
"Move the current frame one level down in the stack trace (to a newer "
"frame)."
msgstr "Joriy kadrni stek izida bir daraja pastga (yangi kadrga) siljiting."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:293
msgid ""
"Move the current frame one level up in the stack trace (to an older "
"frame)."
msgstr "Joriy kadrni stek izida bir daraja yuqoriga (eski kadrga) siljiting."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:297
msgid ""
"Continue the execution until the next line in the current function is "
"reached or it returns."
msgstr ""
"Joriy funksiyaning keyingi satriga yetilguncha yoki u qaytgunga qadar "
"bajarilishni davom ettiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:301
msgid "Continue the execution and only stop when a breakpoint is encountered."
msgstr "Bajarilishni davom ettiring va faqat to'xtash nuqtasiga duch kelganda to'xtang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:305
msgid ""
"Execute the current line. Stop at the first possible occasion (either in "
"a function that is called or on the next line in the current function)."
msgstr ""
"Joriy satrni bajaring. Birinchi mumkin bo'lgan holatda to'xtang "
"(chaqirilayotgan funksiyada yoki joriy funksiyaning keyingi satrida)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/setup_guide.rst:310
msgid "Quit the debugger. The program being executed is aborted."
msgstr "Disk raskadrovchidan chiqing. Bajarilayotgan dastur to'xtatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:10
msgid ""
"**Reference**: `Odoo's Test Framework: Learn Best Practices "
"<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JEIscps0OOQ>`__ (Odoo Experience 2020) "
"on YouTube."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: YouTube dagi `Odoo Test Freymvorki: Eng yaxshi "
"amaliyotlarni o'rganing "
"<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JEIscps0OOQ>`__ (Odoo Experience 2020)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:14
msgid ""
"Writing tests is a necessity for multiple reasons. Here is a non-"
"exhaustive list:"
msgstr "Testlar yozish bir necha sabablarga ko'ra zaruriyat. Mana to'liq bo'lmagan ro'yxat:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:16
msgid "Ensure code will not be broken in the future"
msgstr "Kelajakda kod buzilmasligini ta'minlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:17
msgid "Define the scope of your code"
msgstr "Kodingiz doirasini aniqlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:18
msgid "Give examples of use cases"
msgstr "Foydalanish holatlari misollarini keltirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:19
msgid "It is one way to technically document the code"
msgstr "Bu kodni texnik hujjatlashtirishning bir usuli"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:20
msgid "Help your coding by defining your goal before working towards it"
msgstr "Maqsadingizni unga erishishdan oldin belgilash orqali kodlashda yordam berish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:23
msgid "Running Tests"
msgstr "Testlarni ishga tushirish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:25
msgid "Before knowing how to write tests, we need to know how to run them."
msgstr "Testlarni qanday yozishni bilishdan oldin, ularni qanday ishga tushirishni bilishimiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:77
msgid "Integration Bots"
msgstr "Integratsiya botlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:79
msgid ""
"This section is only for Odoo employees and people that are contributing "
"to `github.com/odoo`. We highly recommend having your own CI otherwise."
msgstr ""
"Bu bo'lim faqat Odoo xodimlari va `github.com/odoo` ga hissa qo'shayotgan "
"odamlar uchun. Aks holda o'zingizning CI ga ega bo'lishni kuchli tavsiya etamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:82
msgid ""
"When a test is written, it is important to make sure it always passes "
"when modifications are applied to the source code. To automate this task,"
" we use a development practice called Continuous Integration (CI). This "
"is why we have some bots running all the tests at different moments. "
"Whether you are working at Odoo or not, if you are trying to merge "
"something inside `odoo/odoo`, `odoo/enterprise`, `odoo/upgrade` or on "
"odoo.sh, you will have to go through the CI. If you are working on "
"another project, you should think of adding your own CI."
msgstr ""
"Test yozilganda, manba kodga o'zgartirishlar qo'llanilganda u har doim "
"o'tishiga ishonch hosil qilish muhim. Bu vazifani avtomatlashtirish uchun "
"biz Uzluksiz integratsiya (CI) deb ataladigan ishlab chiqish amaliyotidan "
"foydalanamiz. Shuning uchun turli vaqtlarda barcha testlarni bajaradigan "
"ba'zi botlarimiz mavjud. Odoo da ishlaganingizdan qat'i nazar, "
"`odoo/odoo`, `odoo/enterprise`, `odoo/upgrade` yoki odoo.sh da biror "
"narsani birlashtirmoqchi bo'lsangiz, CI dan o'tishingiz kerak bo'ladi. "
"Boshqa loyihada ishlayotgan bo'lsangiz, o'z CI ni qo'shish haqida o'ylashingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:91
msgid "Runbot"
msgstr "Runbot"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:93
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
"`Runbot FAQ <https://runbot.odoo.com/doc>`__."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: bu mavzu bilan bog'liq hujjatlarni "
"`Runbot FAQ <https://runbot.odoo.com/doc>`__ da topish mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:96
msgid ""
"Most of the tests are run on `Runbot <https://runbot.odoo.com>`__ every "
"time a commit is pushed on GitHub."
msgstr ""
"GitHub ga commit yuklab bo'linganda ko'pgina testlar "
"`Runbot <https://runbot.odoo.com>`__ da bajariladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:99
msgid ""
"You can see the state of a commit/branch by filtering on the runbot "
"dashboard."
msgstr "Runbot boshqaruv panelida filtrlash orqali commit/branch holatini ko'rishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:101
msgid ""
"A **bundle** is created for each branch. A bundle consists of a "
"configuration and batches."
msgstr ""
"Har bir branch uchun **to'plam** yaratiladi. To'plam konfiguratsiya va "
"paketlardan iborat."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:104
msgid ""
"A **batch** is a set of builds, depending on the parameters of the "
"bundle. A batch is green (i.e. passes the tests) if all the builds are "
"green."
msgstr ""
"**Paket** to'plam parametrlariga qarab qurishlar to'plami. Barcha "
"qurishlar yashil bo'lsa, paket yashil (ya'ni testlardan o'tgan)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:107
msgid ""
"A **build** is when we launch a server. It can be divided in sub-builds. "
"Usually there are builds for the community version, the enterprise "
"version (only if there is an enterprise branch but you can force the "
"build), and the migration of the branch. A build is green if every sub-"
"build is green."
msgstr ""
"**Qurish** server ishga tushganda. U kichik qurishlarга bo'linishi mumkin. "
"Odatda hamjamiyat versiyasi uchun qurishlar, enterprise versiyasi uchun "
"(faqat enterprise branch mavjud bo'lsa, lekin qurishni majburlashingiz mumkin) "
"va branch migratsiyasi mavjud. Har bir kichik qurish yashil bo'lsa, qurish yashil."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:112
msgid ""
"A **sub-build** only does some parts of what a full build does. It is "
"used to speed up the CI process. Generally it is used to split the post "
"install tests in 4 parallel instances. A sub-build is green if all the "
"tests are passing and there are no errors/warnings logged."
msgstr ""
"**Kichik qurish** to'liq qurish qiladigan narsalarning faqat ba'zi qismlarini "
"bajaradi. U CI jarayonini tezlashtirish uchun ishlatiladi. Odatda "
"o'rnatishdan keyingi testlarni 4 ta parallel instancega bo'lish uchun "
"ishlatiladi. Barcha testlar o'tsa va xatolar/ogohlantirishlar ro'yxatga "
"olinmasa, kichik qurish yashil."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:117
msgid ""
"All tests are run regardless of the modifications done. Correcting a typo"
" in an error message or refactoring a whole module triggers the same "
"tests. All modules will be installed as well. This means something might "
"not work even if the Runbot is green, i.e. your changes depend on a "
"module that the module the changes are in doesn't depend on."
msgstr ""
"Qilingan o'zgartirishlardan qat'i nazar barcha testlar bajariladi. "
"Xato xabarida matn xatosini to'g'rilash yoki butun modulni refaktoring "
"qilish bir xil testlarni ishga tushiradi. Barcha modullar ham o'rnatiladi. "
"Bu Runbot yashil bo'lsa ham biror narsa ishlamasligi mumkinligini anglatadi, "
"ya'ni o'zgarishlaringiz o'zgarishlar mavjud bo'lgan modul bog'liq bo'lmagan "
"modulga bog'liq."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:121
msgid ""
"The localization modules (i.e. country-specific modules) are not "
"installed on Runbot (except the generic one). Some modules with external "
"dependencies can also be excluded."
msgstr ""
"Lokalizatsiya modullari (ya'ni mamlakat-spetsifik modullar) Runbot da "
"o'rnatilmaydi (umumiy modul bundan mustasno). Tashqi bog'liqliklarga "
"ega ba'zi modullar ham chiqarib tashlanishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:123
msgid ""
"There is a nightly build running additional tests: module operations, "
"localization, single module installs, multi-builds for nondeterministic "
"bugs, etc. These are not kept in the standard CI to shorten the time of "
"execution."
msgstr ""
"Qo'shimcha testlarni bajaradigan tungi qurish mavjud: modul operatsiyalari, "
"lokalizatsiya, bitta modul o'rnatishlari, deterministik bo'lmagan xatolar "
"uchun ko'p qurishlar va h.k. Bajarilish vaqtini qisqartirish uchun ular "
"standart CI da saqlanmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:127
msgid ""
"You can also login to a build built by Runbot. There are 3 users usable: "
"`admin`, `demo` and `portal`. The password is the same as the login. This"
" is useful to quickly test things on different versions without having to"
" build it locally. The full logs are also available; these are used for "
"monitoring."
msgstr ""
"Runbot tomonidan qurilgan qurishga ham kirishingiz mumkin. Foydalanish "
"mumkin bo'lgan 3 ta foydalanuvchi mavjud: `admin`, `demo` va `portal`. "
"Parol kirishga o'xshash. Bu mahalliy ravishda qurish shart bo'lmay turib "
"turli versiyalarda narsalarni tezda sinovdan o'tkazish uchun foydali. "
"To'liq jurnallar ham mavjud; ular monitoring uchun ishlatiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:133
msgid "Robodoo"
msgstr "Robodoo"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:135
msgid ""
"You will most likely have to gain a little bit more experience before "
"having the rights to summon robodoo, but here are a few remarks anyways."
msgstr ""
"Robodoo ni chaqirish huquqiga ega bo'lishdan oldin biroz ko'proq tajriba "
"orttirish kerak bo'ladi, lekin mana baribir bir nechta izoh."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:138
msgid ""
"Robodoo is the guy spamming the CI status as tags on your PRs, but he is "
"also the guy that kindly integrates your commits into the main "
"repositories."
msgstr ""
"Robodoo PR larda teglar sifatida CI holatini spamlaydigan, lekin u shu "
"bilan birga commitlaringizni asosiy omborlarga samimiy ravishda "
"integrasiyalaydigan odamdir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:141
msgid ""
"When the last batch is green, the reviewer can ask robodoo to merge your "
"PR (it is more a `rebase` than a `merge`). It will then go to the "
"mergebot."
msgstr ""
"So'nggi paket yashil bo'lganda, ko'rib chiquvchi robodoo dan PR ni "
"birlashtirish (bu `merge` dan ko'ra `rebase` ga o'xshaydi) so'rashi mumkin. "
"Keyin mergebot ga o'tadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:145
msgid "Mergebot"
msgstr "Mergebot"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:147
msgid ""
"`Mergebot <https://mergebot.odoo.com>`__ is the last testing phase before"
" merging a PR."
msgstr "`Mergebot <https://mergebot.odoo.com>`__ PR ni birlashtirish oldidan oxirgi sinov bosqichi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:149
msgid ""
"It will take the commits in your branch not yet present on the target, "
"stage it and rerun the tests one more time, including the enterprise "
"version even if you are only changing something in community."
msgstr ""
"U maqsadda hali mavjud bo'lmagan branchingizdagi commitlarni oladi, "
"ularni bosqichga qo'yadi va testlarni yana bir marta qayta bajaradi, "
"faqat hamjamiyatda biror narsani o'zgartirayotgan bo'lsangiz ham enterprise "
"versiyasini o'z ichiga oladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:153
msgid ""
"This step can fail with a `Staging failed` error message. This could be "
"due to"
msgstr "Bu bosqich `Staging failed` xato xabari bilan muvaffaqiyatsiz bo'lishi mumkin. Bu quyidagilarga bog'liq bo'lishi mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:155
msgid ""
"a nondeterministic bug that is already on the target. If you are an Odoo "
"employee, you can check those here: https://runbot.odoo.com/runbot/errors"
msgstr ""
"maqsadda allaqachon mavjud bo'lgan deterministik bo'lmagan xato. "
"Agar Odoo xodimi bo'lsangiz, ularni bu yerda tekshirishingiz mumkin: https://runbot.odoo.com/runbot/errors"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:157
msgid ""
"a nondeterministic bug that you introduced but wasn't detected in the CI "
"before"
msgstr "siz kiritgan, lekin avval CI da aniqlanmagan deterministik bo'lmagan xato"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:158
msgid ""
"an incompatibility with another commit merged right before and what you "
"are trying to merge"
msgstr "oldinroq birlashtirilgan boshqa commit va birlashtirmoqchi bo'lganingiz bilan moslik yo'qligi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:159
msgid ""
"an incompatibility with the enterprise repository if you only did changes"
" in the community repo"
msgstr "faqat hamjamiyat omborida o'zgarishlar qilgan bo'lsangiz enterprise ombori bilan moslik yo'qligi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:161
msgid ""
"Always check that the issue does not come from you before asking the "
"merge bot to retry: rebase your branch on the target and rerun the tests "
"locally."
msgstr ""
"Birlashtirish botidan qayta urinishni so'rashdan oldin muammo sizdan "
"emasligini tekshiring: branchingizni maqsadga qayta bazalang va testlarni "
"mahalliy qayta ishga tushiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:167
msgid ""
"Because Odoo is modular, the tests need to be also modular. This means "
"tests are defined in the module that adds the functionality you are "
"adding in, and tests cannot depend on functionality coming from modules "
"your module doesn't depend on."
msgstr ""
"Odoo modulli bo'lganligi sababli, testlar ham modulli bo'lishi kerak. Bu "
"testlar qo'shilayotgan funksionallikni qo'shadigan modulda aniqlanishini va "
"testlar modulingiz bog'liq bo'lmagan modullardan keladigan funksionallikka "
"bog'liq bo'lolmasligini anglatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:171
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
":ref:`Special Tags<reference/testing/tags>`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: ushbu mavzuga tegishli hujjatlar "
":ref:`Maxsus teglar<reference/testing/tags>` bo'limida topilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:192
msgid ""
"If the behavior you want to test can be changed by the installation of "
"another module, you need to ensure that the tag `at_install` is set; "
"otherwise, you can use the tag `post_install` to speed up the CI and "
"ensure it is not changed if it shouldn't."
msgstr ""
"Agar siz test qilmoqchi bo'lgan xatti-harakat boshqa modul o'rnatish orqali "
"o'zgartirilishi mumkin bo'lsa, `at_install` tegi o'rnatilganligini ta'minlashingiz "
"kerak; aks holda, CI ni tezlashtirish va o'zgarmasligi kerak bo'lsa "
"o'zgarmasligini ta'minlash uchun `post_install` tegidan foydalanishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:197
msgid "Writing a test"
msgstr "Test yozish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:199
msgid ""
"**Reference**: the documentation related to this topic can be found in "
"`Python unittest <https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html>`__ and"
" :ref:`Testing Odoo<reference/testing>`."
msgstr ""
"**Ma'lumotnoma**: ushbu mavzuga tegishli hujjatlar "
"`Python unittest <https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html>`__ va "
":ref:`Odoo testlash<reference/testing>` bo'limlarida topilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:203
msgid "Here are a few things to take into consideration before writing a test"
msgstr "Test yozishdan oldin e'tiborga olish kerak bo'lgan bir necha narsalar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:205
msgid ""
"The tests should be independent of the data currently in the database "
"(including demo data)"
msgstr ""
"Testlar ma'lumotlar bazasidagi joriy ma'lumotlardan (demo ma'lumotlar ham) "
"mustaqil bo'lishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:206
msgid ""
"Tests should not impact the database by leaving/changing residual data. "
"This is usually done by the test framework by doing a rollback. "
"Therefore, you must never call ``cr.commit`` in a test (nor anywhere else"
" in the business code)."
msgstr ""
"Testlar qoldiq ma'lumotlarni qoldirish/o'zgartirish orqali ma'lumotlar "
"bazasiga ta'sir qilmasligi kerak. Bu odatda test tizimi tomonidan orqaga "
"qaytarish (rollback) qilish orqali amalga oshiriladi. Shu sababli, testda "
"(yoki biznes kodning boshqa joyida) hech qachon ``cr.commit`` ni "
"chaqirmasligingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:209
msgid ""
"For a bug fix, the test should fail before applying the fix and pass "
"after."
msgstr ""
"Xato tuzatish uchun, test tuzatishni qo'llashdan oldin muvaffaqiyatsiz "
"bo'lishi va keyin o'tishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:210
msgid ""
"Don't test something that is already tested elsewhere; you can trust the "
"ORM. Most of the tests in business modules should only test the business "
"flows."
msgstr ""
"Boshqa joyda allaqachon sinovdan o'tkazilgan narsani tekshirmang; ORM ga "
"ishonishingiz mumkin. Biznes modullardagi testlarning aksariyati faqat "
"biznes oqimlarini tekshirishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:212
msgid "You shouldn't need to flush data into the database."
msgstr "Ma'lumotlarni ma'lumotlar bazasiga yo'q qilishingiz shart emas."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:214
msgid ""
"Remember that ``onchange`` only applies in the Form views, not by "
"changing the attributes in python. This also applies in the tests. If you"
" want to emulate a Form view, you can use ``odoo.tests.Form``."
msgstr ""
"Esda tuting, ``onchange`` faqat Form ko'rinishlarida qo'llaniladi, "
"Python-da atributlarni o'zgartirish orqali emas. Bu testlarda ham "
"qo'llaniladi. Forma ko'rinishini simulyatsiya qilmoqchi bo'lsangiz, "
"``odoo.tests.Form`` dan foydalanishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:218
msgid ""
"The tests should be in a ``tests`` folder at the root of your module. "
"Each test file name should start with `test_` and be imported in the "
"``__init__.py`` of the test folder. You shouldn't import the test "
"folder/module in the ``__init__.py`` of the module."
msgstr ""
"Testlar modulingizning ildizidagi ``tests`` papkasida bo'lishi kerak. Har "
"bir test fayli nomi `test_` bilan boshlanishi va test papkasining "
"``__init__.py`` fayliga import qilinishi kerak. Test papkasini/modulini "
"modulning ``__init__.py`` fayliga import qilmasligingiz kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:234
msgid ""
"All the tests should extend ``odoo.tests.common.TransactionCase``. You "
"usually define a ``setUpClass`` and the tests. After writing the "
"`setUpClass`, you have an `env` available in the class and can start "
"interacting with the ORM."
msgstr ""
"Barcha testlar ``odoo.tests.common.TransactionCase`` ni kengaytirishi kerak. "
"Odatda ``setUpClass`` va testlarni aniqlanadi. `setUpClass` yozilgandan "
"so'ng, sinfda `env` mavjud bo'ladi va ORM bilan muloqotni boshlashingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:238
msgid "These test classes are built on top of the ``unittest`` python module."
msgstr "Ushbu test sinflari ``unittest`` Python moduli asosida qurilgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:281
msgid ""
"For better readability, split your tests into multiple files depending on"
" the scope of the tests. You can also have a Common class that most of "
"the tests should inherit from; this common class can define the whole "
"setup for the module. For instance, in `account "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/account/tests/common.py>`__."
msgstr ""
"Yaxshiroq o'qilish uchun, testlarni qamrab olish doirasiga qarab bir nechta "
"faylga bo'ling. Ko'pgina testlar meros olishi kerak bo'lgan umumiy sinf ham "
"bo'lishi mumkin; bu umumiy sinf modul uchun butun sozlamani belgilashi mumkin. "
"Masalan, `account "
"<https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/19.0/addons/account/tests/common.py>`__ da."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:286
msgid "Update the code so no one can:"
msgstr "Hech kim quyidagilarni qila olmasligi uchun kodni yangilang:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:288
msgid "Create an offer for a sold property"
msgstr "Sotilgan mulk uchun taklif yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:289
msgid "Sell a property with no accepted offers on it"
msgstr "Qabul qilingan takliflari bo'lmagan mulkni sotish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:291
msgid ""
"and create tests for both of these cases. Additionally check that selling"
" a property that can be sold is correctly marked as sold after selling "
"it."
msgstr ""
"va ushbu holatlarning ikkalasi uchun testlar yarating. Bundan tashqari, "
"sotilishi mumkin bo'lgan mulkni sotgandan so'ng to'g'ri ravishda sotilgan "
"deb belgilanganligini tekshiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:295
msgid ""
"Someone keeps breaking the reset of Garden Area and Orientation when you "
"uncheck the Garden checkbox. Make sure it doesn't happen again."
msgstr ""
"Kimdir Garden katagini olib tashlaganingizda Bog' Maydoni va Yo'nalishini "
"doimiy ravishda buzib qo'yadi. Buni yana sodir bo'lmasligi uchun ta'minlang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/unit_tests.rst:298
msgid "Tip: remember the note about `Form` a little bit above."
msgstr "Maslahat: yuqoridagi `Form` haqidagi eslatmani eslang."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:5
msgid "Customizing the web client"
msgstr "Veb mijozni sozlash"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:14
msgid "This guide is about creating modules for Odoo's web client."
msgstr "Ushbu qo'llanma Odoo veb mijozi uchun modullar yaratish haqida."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:16
msgid ""
"To create websites with Odoo, see :doc:`website_theme`; to add business "
"capabilities or extend existing business systems of Odoo, see "
":doc:`backend`."
msgstr ""
"Odoo bilan veb-saytlar yaratish uchun :doc:`website_theme` ga qarang; "
"biznes imkoniyatlarini qo'shish yoki Odoo ning mavjud biznes tizimlarini "
"kengaytirish uchun :doc:`backend` ga qarang."

