#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1647
msgid "Existing web components"
msgstr "Mavjud veb komponentlar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1650
msgid "The Action Manager"
msgstr "Amal menejeri"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1652
msgid ""
"In Odoo, many operations start from an :doc:`action "
"<../reference/backend/actions>`: opening a menu item (to a view), "
"printing a report, ..."
msgstr ""
"Odoo da, ko'pgina amallar :doc:`amaldan <../reference/backend/actions>` "
"boshlanadi: menyu elementini ochish (ko'rinishga), hisobot chop etish, ..."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1655
msgid ""
"Actions are pieces of data describing how a client should react to the "
"activation of a piece of content. Actions can be stored (and read through"
" a model) or they can be generated on-the fly (locally to the client by "
"javascript code, or remotely by a method of a model)."
msgstr ""
"Amallar mijozning kontent qismini faollashtiruvga qanday munosabatda bo'lishini "
"tavsiflovchi ma'lumot qismlaridir. Amallar saqlanishi (va model orqali o'qilishi) "
"yoki tezda yaratilishi mumkin (mahalliy ravishda mijozga javascript kodi orqali "
"yoki masofadan model metodi orqali)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1660
msgid ""
"In Odoo Web, the component responsible for handling and reacting to these"
" actions is the *Action Manager*."
msgstr ""
"Odoo vebda, ushbu amallarga munosabatda bo'lish va ularni boshqarish uchun "
"mas'ul komponent *Amal menejeri* dir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1664
msgid "Using the Action Manager"
msgstr "Amal menejeridan foydalanish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1666
msgid ""
"The action manager can be invoked explicitly from javascript code by "
"creating a dictionary describing :doc:`an action "
"<../reference/backend/actions>` of the right type, and calling an action "
"manager instance with it."
msgstr ""
"Amal menejeri to'g'ri turdagi :doc:`amalni <../reference/backend/actions>` "
"tavsiflovchi lug'at yaratish va amal menejer namunasini u bilan chaqirish "
"orqali javascript kodidan aniq chaqirilishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1670
msgid ""
":func:`~odoo.Widget.do_action` is a shortcut of :class:`~odoo.Widget` "
"looking up the \"current\" action manager and executing the action::"
msgstr ""
":func:`~odoo.Widget.do_action` \"joriy\" amal menejerini qidiradigan va "
"amalni bajara- :class:`~odoo.Widget` ning yorligidir::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1686
msgid ""
"The most common action ``type`` is ``ir.actions.act_window`` which "
"provides views to a model (displays a model in various manners), its most"
" common attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Eng keng tarqalgan amal ``type`` - bu modellarga ko'rinishlar taqdim etadigan "
"``ir.actions.act_window`` (modelni turli usullarda ko'rsatadi), uning eng "
"keng tarqalgan atributlari:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1691
msgid "The model to display in views"
msgstr "Ko'rinishlarda ko'rsatiladigan model"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1693
msgid "For form views, a preselected record in ``res_model``"
msgstr "Forma ko'rinishlari uchun ``res_model`` da oldindan tanlangan yozuv"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1695
msgid ""
"Lists the views available through the action. A list of ``[view_id, "
"view_type]``, ``view_id`` can either be the database identifier of a view"
" of the right type, or ``false`` to use the view by default for the "
"specified type. View types can not be present multiple times. The action "
"will open the first view of the list by default."
msgstr ""
"Amal orqali mavjud ko'rinishlarni ro'yxatlaydi. ``[view_id, view_type]`` "
"ro'yxati, ``view_id`` to'g'ri turdagi ko'rinishning ma'lumotlar bazasi "
"identifikatori yoki belgilangan tur uchun standart ko'rinishni ishlatish "
"uchun ``false`` bo'lishi mumkin. Ko'rinish turlari bir necha marta mavjud "
"bo'lolmaydi. Amal standart bo'yicha ro'yxatning birinchi ko'rinishini ochadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1701
msgid "``target``"
msgstr "``target``"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1701
msgid ""
"Either ``current`` (the default) which replaces the \"content\" section "
"of the web client by the action, or ``new`` to open the action in a "
"dialog box."
msgstr ""
"Veb mijozning \"kontent\" bo'limini amal bilan almashtiruvchi ``current`` "
"(standart) yoki amalni muloqot oynasida ochish uchun ``new`` bo'lishi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1704
msgid "Additional context data to use within the action."
msgstr "Amal ichida ishlatish uchun qo'shimcha kontekst ma'lumotlari."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1706
msgid "Jump to Product"
msgstr "Mahsulotga o'tish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1708
msgid ""
"Modify the ``PetToysList`` component so clicking on a toy replaces the "
"homepage by the toy's form view."
msgstr ""
"``PetToysList`` komponentini o'yinchoqni bosish bosh sahifani o'yinchoqning "
"forma ko'rinishi bilan almashtirishi uchun o'zgartiring."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1755
msgid "Client Actions"
msgstr "Mijoz amallari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1757
msgid ""
"Throughout this guide, we used a simple ``HomePage`` widget which the web"
" client automatically starts when we select the right menu item. But how "
"did the Odoo web know to start this widget? Because the widget is "
"registered as a *client action*."
msgstr ""
"Bu qo'llanma davomida, biz to'g'ri menyu elementini tanlaganimizda veb mijoz "
"avtomatik ishga tushiradigan oddiy ``HomePage`` vidjetidan foydalandik. Lekin "
"Odoo veb bu vidjetni ishga tushirishni qanday bildi? Chunki vidjet *mijoz "
"amali* sifatida ro'yxatdan o'tgan."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1762
msgid ""
"A client action is (as its name implies) an action type defined almost "
"entirely in the client, in javascript for Odoo web. The server simply "
"sends an action tag (an arbitrary name), and optionally adds a few "
"parameters, but beyond that *everything* is handled by custom client "
"code."
msgstr ""
"Mijoz amali (nomidan ko'ringanidek) deyarli to'liq mijozda, Odoo veb uchun "
"javascript da aniqlangan amal turidir. Server shunchaki amal tegi (ixtiyoriy "
"nom) yuboradi va ixtiyoriy ravishda bir necha parametr qo'shadi, lekin bundan "
"tashqari *hamma narsa* maxsus mijoz kodi tomonidan boshqariladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1767
msgid ""
"Our widget is registered as the handler for the client action through "
"this::"
msgstr "Bizning vidjetimiz mijoz amali uchun ishlovchi sifatida shu orqali ro'yxatdan o'tgan::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1772
msgid ""
"``instance.web.client_actions`` is a :class:`~odoo.web.Registry` in which"
" the action manager looks up client action handlers when it needs to "
"execute one. The first parameter of :class:`~odoo.web.Registry.add` is "
"the name (tag) of the client action, and the second parameter is the path"
" to the widget from the Odoo web client root."
msgstr ""
"``instance.web.client_actions`` - bu amal menejeri birini bajarish kerak "
"bo'lganda mijoz amal ishlovchilarini qidiruvchi :class:`~odoo.web.Registry`. "
":class:`~odoo.web.Registry.add` ning birinchi parametri mijoz amalining nomi "
"(tegi), ikkinchi parametri esa Odoo veb mijoz ildizidan vidjetga yo'l."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1778
msgid ""
"When a client action must be executed, the action manager looks up its "
"tag in the registry, walks the specified path and displays the widget it "
"finds at the end."
msgstr ""
"Mijoz amali bajarilishi kerak bo'lganda, amal menejeri registrda uning tegini "
"qidiradi, ko'rsatilgan yo'lni bosib o'tadi va oxirida topgan vidjetni ko'rsatadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1782
msgid ""
"a client action handler can also be a regular function, in which case "
"it'll be called and its result (if any) will be interpreted as the next "
"action to execute."
msgstr ""
"mijoz amal ishlovchisi oddiy funksiya ham bo'lishi mumkin, bu holda u "
"chaqiriladi va uning natijasi (mavjud bo'lsa) bajarish uchun keyingi amal "
"sifatida talqin qilinadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1786
msgid "On the server side, we had simply defined an ``ir.actions.client`` action:"
msgstr "Server tomonida biz oddiygina ``ir.actions.client`` amali aniqladik:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1794
msgid "and a menu opening the action:"
msgstr "va amalni ochadigan menyu:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1802
msgid "Architecture of the Views"
msgstr "Ko'rinishlar arxitekturasi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1804
msgid ""
"Much of Odoo web's usefulness (and complexity) resides in views. Each "
"view type is a way of displaying a model in the client."
msgstr ""
"Odoo vebning foydaliligining (va murakkabligining) ko'p qismi ko'rinishlarda "
"joylashgan. Har bir ko'rinish turi mijozda modelni ko'rsatish usuli."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1808
msgid "The View Manager"
msgstr "Ko'rinish menejeri"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1810
msgid ""
"When an ``ActionManager`` instance receive an action of type "
"``ir.actions.act_window``, it delegates the synchronization and handling "
"of the views themselves to a *view manager*, which will then set up one "
"or multiple views depending on the original action's requirements:"
msgstr ""
"``ActionManager`` namunasi ``ir.actions.act_window`` turidagi amal qabul "
"qilganda, u ko'rinishlarning o'zini sinxronlashtirish va boshqarishni *ko'rinish "
"menejeriga* topshiradi, u so'ngra asl amalning talablariga qarab bir yoki bir "
"nechta ko'rinishni o'rnatadi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1820
msgid "The Views"
msgstr "Ko'rinishlar"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1822
msgid ""
"Most :doc:`Odoo views <../reference/user_interface/view_records>` are "
"implemented through a subclass of :class:`odoo.web.View` which provides a"
" bit of generic basic structure for handling events and displaying model "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Ko'pgina :doc:`Odoo ko'rinishlari <../reference/user_interface/view_records>` "
"hodisalarni boshqarish va model ma'lumotlarini ko'rsatish uchun umumiy asosiy "
"tuzilmani biroz taqdim etadigan :class:`odoo.web.View` kichik sinfi orqali "
"amalga oshiriladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1826
msgid ""
"The *search view* is considered a view type by the main Odoo framework, "
"but handled separately by the web client (as it's a more permanent "
"fixture and can interact with other views, which regular views don't do)."
msgstr ""
"*Qidiruv ko'rinishi* asosiy Odoo tizimi tomonidan ko'rinish turi sifatida "
"qabul qilinadi, lekin veb mijoz tomonidan alohida boshqariladi (u ancha doimiy "
"o'rnatma bo'lib, oddiy ko'rinishlar qilmaydigan boshqa ko'rinishlar bilan "
"o'zaro ta'sir qilishi mumkin)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1830
msgid ""
"A view is responsible for loading its own description XML (using "
":py:class:`~odoo.models.Model.fields_view_get`) and any other data source"
" it needs. To that purpose, views are provided with an optional view "
"identifier set as the :attr:`~odoo.web.View.view_id` attribute."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinish o'zining tavsif XML ini (:py:class:`~odoo.models.Model.fields_view_get` "
"yordamida) va zarur bo'lgan boshqa ma'lumot manbalarini yuklash uchun mas'ul. "
"Shu maqsadda, ko'rinishlarga :attr:`~odoo.web.View.view_id` atributi sifatida "
"o'rnatilgan ixtiyoriy ko'rinish identifikatori taqdim etiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1835
msgid ""
"Views are also provided with a :class:`~odoo.web.DataSet` instance which "
"holds most necessary model information (the model name and possibly "
"various record ids)."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishlarga shuningdek zarur model ma'lumotlarining ko'pini (model nomi va "
"ehtimol turli yozuv id'lari) saqlaydigan :class:`~odoo.web.DataSet` namunasi "
"taqdim etiladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1839
msgid ""
"Views may also want to handle search queries by overriding "
":func:`~odoo.web.View.do_search`, and updating their "
":class:`~odoo.web.DataSet` as necessary."
msgstr ""
"Ko'rinishlar shuningdek :func:`~odoo.web.View.do_search` ni bekor qilish va "
"zarur holda :class:`~odoo.web.DataSet` ni yangilash orqali qidiruv so'rovlarini "
"boshqarishni ham xohlashi mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1844
msgid "The Form View Fields"
msgstr "Forma ko'rinishi maydonlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1846
msgid ""
"A common need is the extension of the web form view to add new ways of "
"displaying fields."
msgstr ""
"Keng tarqalgan ehtiyoj - bu maydonlarni ko'rsatishning yangi usullarini qo'shish "
"uchun veb forma ko'rinishini kengaytirish."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1849
msgid ""
"All built-in fields have a default display implementation, a new form "
"widget may be necessary to correctly interact with a new field type (e.g."
" a :term:`GIS` field) or to provide new representations and ways to "
"interact with existing field types (e.g. validate "
":py:class:`~odoo.fields.Char` fields which should contain email addresses"
" and display them as email links)."
msgstr ""
"Barcha o'rnatilgan maydonlarning standart ko'rsatish amalga oshirilishi bor, "
"yangi forma vidjeti yangi maydon turi (masalan, :term:`GIS` maydoni) bilan "
"to'g'ri o'zaro ta'sir qilish yoki mavjud maydon turlari bilan o'zaro ta'sir "
"qilishning yangi ko'rinishlari va usullarini taqdim etish uchun zarur bo'lishi "
"mumkin (masalan, email manzillarni o'z ichiga olishi kerak bo'lgan "
":py:class:`~odoo.fields.Char` maydonlarini tekshirish va ularni email "
"havolalar sifatida ko'rsatish)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1856
msgid ""
"To explicitly specify which form widget should be used to display a "
"field, simply use the ``widget`` attribute in the view's XML description:"
msgstr ""
"Maydonni ko'rsatish uchun qaysi forma vidjetidan foydalanish kerakligini "
"aniq belgilash uchun, ko'rinishning XML tavsifida ``widget`` atributidan "
"foydalaning:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1865
msgid ""
"the same widget is used in both \"view\" (read-only) and \"edit\" modes "
"of a form view, it's not possible to use a widget in one and an other "
"widget in the other"
msgstr ""
"bir xil vidjet forma ko'rinishining \"ko'rish\" (faqat o'qish) va \"tahrirlash\" "
"rejimlarida ham ishlatiladi, birida vidjet va boshqasida boshqa vidjetdan "
"foydalanish mumkin emas"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1868
msgid "and a given field (name) can not be used multiple times in the same form"
msgstr "va berilgan maydon (nom) bir xil formada bir necha marta ishlatilishi mumkin emas"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1869
msgid ""
"a widget may ignore the current mode of the form view and remain the same"
" in both view and edit modes"
msgstr ""
"vidjet forma ko'rinishining joriy rejimini e'tiborsiz qoldirishi va ko'rish "
"hamda tahrirlash rejimlarida bir xil bo'lib qolishi mumkin"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1872
msgid "most of this should probably move to an advanced form view guide"
msgstr "bularning aksariyati ehtimol ilg'or forma ko'rinishi qo'llanmasiga ko'chirilishi kerak"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1874
msgid ""
"Fields are instantiated by the form view after it has read its XML "
"description and constructed the corresponding HTML representing that "
"description. After that, the form view will communicate with the field "
"objects using some methods. These methods are defined by the "
"``FieldInterface`` interface. Almost all fields inherit the "
"``AbstractField`` abstract class. That class defines some default "
"mechanisms that need to be implemented by most fields."
msgstr ""
"Maydonlar forma ko'rinishi tomonidan XML tavsifini o'qib, ushbu tavsifni "
"ifodalovchi tegishli HTML ni qurilgandan so'ng yaratiladi. Shundan so'ng, "
"forma ko'rinishi maydon ob'ektlari bilan ba'zi metodlar yordamida muloqot "
"qiladi. Bu metodlar ``FieldInterface`` interfeysi tomonidan aniqlanadi. "
"Deyarli barcha maydonlar ``AbstractField`` abstrakt sinfidan meros oladi. "
"Bu sinf ko'pgina maydonlar tomonidan amalga oshirilishi kerak bo'lgan ba'zi "
"standart mexanizmlarni aniqlaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1882
msgid "Here are some of the responsibilities of a field class:"
msgstr "Mana maydon sinfining ba'zi mas'uliyatlari:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1884
msgid ""
"The field class must display and allow the user to edit the value of the "
"field."
msgstr "Maydon sinfi maydon qiymatini ko'rsatishi va foydalanuvchiga tahrirlashga ruxsat berishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1885
msgid ""
"It must correctly implement the 3 field attributes available in all "
"fields of Odoo. The ``AbstractField`` class already implements an "
"algorithm that dynamically calculates the value of these attributes (they"
" can change at any moment because their value change according to the "
"value of other fields). Their values are stored in *Widget Properties* "
"(the widget properties were explained earlier in this guide). It is the "
"responsibility of each field class to check these widget properties and "
"dynamically adapt depending of their values. Here is a description of "
"each of these attributes:"
msgstr ""
"U Odoo ning barcha maydonlarida mavjud 3 maydon atributini to'g'ri amalga "
"oshirishi kerak. ``AbstractField`` sinfi allaqachon ushbu atributlar qiymatini "
"dinamik ravishda hisoblaydigan algoritmni amalga oshirgan (ular istalgan "
"vaqtda o'zgarishi mumkin, chunki ularning qiymati boshqa maydonlar qiymatiga "
"qarab o'zgaradi). Ularning qiymatlari *Vidjet xususiyatlari* da saqlanadi "
"(vidjet xususiyatlari ushbu qo'llanmada ilgari tushuntirilgan). Har bir maydon "
"sinfi ushbu vidjet xususiyatlarini tekshirish va ularning qiymatlariga qarab "
"dinamik ravishda moslashish mas'uliyatini o'z zimmasiga oladi. Mana ushbu "
"atributlarning har birining tavsifi:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1895
msgid ""
"``required``: The field must have a value before saving. If ``required`` "
"is ``true`` and the field doesn't have a value, the method ``is_valid()``"
" of the field must return ``false``."
msgstr ""
"``required``: Saqlashdan oldin maydonda qiymat bo'lishi kerak. Agar "
"``required`` ``true`` bo'lsa va maydonda qiymat bo'lmasa, maydonning "
"``is_valid()`` metodi ``false`` qaytarishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1898
msgid ""
"``invisible``: When this is ``true``, the field must be invisible. The "
"``AbstractField`` class already has a basic implementation of this "
"behavior that fits most fields."
msgstr ""
"``invisible``: Bu ``true`` bo'lganda, maydon ko'rinmas bo'lishi kerak. "
"``AbstractField`` sinfi allaqachon ko'pgina maydonlarga mos keladigan ushbu "
"xatti-harakatning asosiy amalga oshirilishiga ega."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1901
msgid ""
"``readonly``: When ``true``, the field must not be editable by the user. "
"Most fields in Odoo have a completely different behavior depending on the"
" value of ``readonly``. As example, the ``FieldChar`` displays an HTML "
"``<input>`` when it is editable and simply displays the text when it is "
"read-only. This also means it has much more code it would need to "
"implement only one behavior, but this is necessary to ensure a good user "
"experience."
msgstr ""
"``readonly``: ``true`` bo'lganda, maydon foydalanuvchi tomonidan tahrirlanmasligi "
"kerak. Odoo dagi ko'pgina maydonlar ``readonly`` qiymatiga qarab butunlay "
"boshqacha xatti-harakatga ega. Masalan, ``FieldChar`` tahrirlash mumkin "
"bo'lganda HTML ``<input>`` ko'rsatadi va faqat o'qish rejimida shunchaki matnni "
"ko'rsatadi. Bu shuningdek faqat bitta xatti-harakatni amalga oshirish uchun "
"ancha ko'proq kod kerakligini anglatadi, lekin bu yaxshi foydalanuvchi tajribasini "
"ta'minlash uchun zarur."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1909
msgid ""
"Fields have two methods, ``set_value()`` and ``get_value()``, which are "
"called by the form view to give it the value to display and get back the "
"new value entered by the user. These methods must be able to handle the "
"value as given by the Odoo server when a ``read()`` is performed on a "
"model and give back a valid value for a ``write()``.  Remember that the "
"JavaScript/Python data types used to represent the values given by "
"``read()`` and given to ``write()`` is not necessarily the same in Odoo. "
"As example, when you read a many2one, it is always a tuple whose first "
"value is the id of the pointed record and the second one is the name get "
"(ie: ``(15, \"Agrolait\")``). But when you write a many2one it must be a "
"single integer, not a tuple anymore. ``AbstractField`` has a default "
"implementation of these methods that works well for simple data type and "
"set a widget property named ``value``."
msgstr ""
"Maydonlarda ikkita metod bor, ``set_value()`` va ``get_value()``, ular forma "
"ko'rinishi tomonidan ko'rsatish uchun unga qiymat berish va foydalanuvchi "
"kiritgan yangi qiymatni qaytarib olish uchun chaqiriladi. Bu metodlar model "
"ustida ``read()`` bajarilganda Odoo serveri tomonidan berilgan qiymatni "
"boshqara olishi va ``write()`` uchun yaroqli qiymat qaytara olishi kerak. "
"Esda tuting, ``read()`` tomonidan berilgan va ``write()`` ga berilgan "
"qiymatlarni ifodalash uchun ishlatiladigan JavaScript/Python ma'lumot turlari "
"Odoo da bir xil bo'lmasligi mumkin. Masalan, many2one ni o'qisangiz, u har "
"doim birinchi qiymati ko'rsatilgan yozuv id si va ikkinchisi olingan nom "
"bo'lgan demakdir (ya'ni: ``(15, \"Agrolait\")``). Lekin many2one ga yozganda "
"u bitta butun son bo'lishi kerak, endi demak. ``AbstractField`` ushbu "
"metodlarning oddiy ma'lumot turi uchun yaxshi ishlaydigan va ``value`` nomli "
"vidjet xususiyatini o'rnatadigan standart amalga oshirilishiga ega."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1923
msgid ""
"Please note that, to better understand how to implement fields, you are "
"strongly encouraged to look at the definition of the ``FieldInterface`` "
"interface and the ``AbstractField`` class directly in the code of the "
"Odoo web client."
msgstr ""
"E'tibor bering, maydonlarni qanday amalga oshirishni yaxshiroq tushunish "
"uchun, Odoo veb mijoz kodida to'g'ridan-to'g'ri ``FieldInterface`` interfeysi "
"va ``AbstractField`` sinfining ta'rifiga qarishingiz qo'llab-quvvatlanadi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1929
msgid "Creating a New Type of Field"
msgstr "Yangi maydon turi yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1931
msgid ""
"In this part we will explain how to create a new type of field. The "
"example here will be to re-implement the ``FieldChar`` class and "
"progressively explain each part."
msgstr ""
"Bu qismda biz yangi maydon turi qanday yaratilishini tushuntiramiz. Bu "
"yerdagi misol ``FieldChar`` sinfini qayta amalga oshirish va har bir qismni "
"bosqichma-bosqich tushuntirish bo'ladi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1936
msgid "Simple Read-Only Field"
msgstr "Oddiy faqat o'qish maydoni"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1938
msgid ""
"Here is a first implementation that will only display text. The user will"
" not be able to modify the content of the field."
msgstr ""
"Mana faqat matn ko'rsatadigan birinchi amalga oshirish. Foydalanuvchi "
"maydon tarkibini o'zgartira olmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1955
msgid ""
"In this example, we declare a class named ``FieldChar2`` inheriting from "
"``AbstractField``. We also register this class in the registry "
"``instance.web.form.widgets`` under the key ``char2``. That will allow us"
" to use this new field in any form view by specifying "
"``widget=\"char2\"`` in the ``<field/>`` tag in the XML declaration of "
"the view."
msgstr ""
"Bu misolda, biz ``AbstractField`` dan meros oluvchi ``FieldChar2`` nomli "
"sinf e'lon qilamiz. Biz shuningdek bu sinfni ``char2`` kaliti ostida "
"``instance.web.form.widgets`` registrida ro'yxatdan o'tkazamiz. Bu bizga "
"ko'rinishning XML deklaratsiyasidagi ``<field/>`` tegida ``widget=\"char2\"`` "
"ni belgilash orqali har qanday forma ko'rinishida ushbu yangi maydondan "
"foydalanishga imkon beradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1961
msgid ""
"In this example, we define a single method: ``render_value()``. All it "
"does is display the widget property ``value``.  Those are two tools "
"defined by the ``AbstractField`` class. As explained before, the form "
"view will call the method ``set_value()`` of the field to set the value "
"to display. This method already has a default implementation in "
"``AbstractField`` which simply sets the widget property ``value``. "
"``AbstractField`` also watch the ``change:value`` event on itself and "
"calls the ``render_value()`` when it occurs. So, ``render_value()`` is a "
"convenience method to implement in child classes to perform some "
"operation each time the value of the field changes."
msgstr ""
"Bu misolda, biz bitta metod aniqlaymiz: ``render_value()``. U qiladigan "
"yagona narsa ``value`` vidjet xususiyatini ko'rsatish. Bular ``AbstractField`` "
"sinfi tomonidan aniqlangan ikkita vosita. Ilgari tushuntirilganidek, forma "
"ko'rinishi ko'rsatish uchun qiymat o'rnatish uchun maydonning ``set_value()`` "
"metodini chaqiradi. Bu metod allaqachon ``AbstractField`` da ``value`` "
"vidjet xususiyatini shunchaki o'rnatadigan standart amalga oshirilishiga ega. "
"``AbstractField`` shuningdek o'zida ``change:value`` hodisasini kuzatadi va "
"u yuz berganda ``render_value()`` ni chaqiradi. Shunday qilib, "
"``render_value()`` maydon qiymati har safar o'zgarganda ba'zi amalni bajarish "
"uchun bola sinflarda amalga oshirish uchun qulay metoddir."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1971
msgid ""
"In the ``init()`` method, we also define the default value of the field "
"if none is specified by the form view (here we assume the default value "
"of a ``char`` field should be an empty string)."
msgstr ""
"``init()`` metodida biz shuningdek agar forma ko'rinishi tomonidan hech qanday "
"ko'rsatilmasa, maydonning standart qiymatini ham aniqlaymiz (bu yerda biz "
"``char`` maydonining standart qiymati bo'sh qator bo'lishi kerak deb "
"taxmin qilamiz)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1976
msgid "Read-Write Field"
msgstr "O'qish-yozish maydoni"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1978
msgid ""
"Read-only fields, which only display content and don't allow the user to "
"modify it can be useful, but most fields in Odoo also allow editing. This"
" makes the field classes more complicated, mostly because fields are "
"supposed to handle both editable and non-editable mode, those modes are "
"often completely different (for design and usability purpose) and the "
"fields must be able to switch between modes at any moment."
msgstr ""
"Faqat tarkibni ko'rsatadigan va foydalanuvchiga uni o'zgartirishga ruxsat "
"bermaydigan faqat o'qish maydonlari foydali bo'lishi mumkin, lekin Odoo "
"dagi ko'pgina maydonlar tahrirlashga ham ruxsat beradi. Bu maydon sinflarini "
"murakkabroq qiladi, asosan maydonlar tahrir qilinadigan va tahrirlanmaydigan "
"rejimlarning ikkalasini ham boshqarishi zarur bo'lganligi sababli, bu rejimlar "
"ko'pincha butunlay boshqacha (dizayn va foydalanuvchanlik maqsadida) va "
"maydonlar istalgan vaqtda rejimlar o'rtasida almasha olishi kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:1985
msgid ""
"To know in which mode the current field should be, the ``AbstractField`` "
"class sets a widget property named ``effective_readonly``. The field "
"should watch for changes in that widget property and display the correct "
"mode accordingly. Example::"
msgstr ""
"Joriy maydon qaysi rejimda bo'lishi kerakligini bilish uchun ``AbstractField`` "
"sinfi ``effective_readonly`` nomli vidjet xususiyatini o'rnatadi. Maydon "
"o'sha vidjet xususiyatidagi o'zgarishlarni kuzatishi va shunga mos ravishda "
"to'g'ri rejimni ko'rsatishi kerak. Misol::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2033
msgid ""
"In the ``start()`` method (which is called immediately after a widget has"
" been appended to the DOM), we bind on the event "
"``change:effective_readonly``. That allows us to redisplay the field each"
" time the widget property ``effective_readonly`` changes. This event "
"handler will call ``display_field()``, which is also called directly in "
"``start()``. This ``display_field()`` was created specifically for this "
"field, it's not a method defined in ``AbstractField`` or any other class."
" We can use this method to display the content of the field depending on "
"the current mode."
msgstr ""
"``start()`` metodida (DOM ga vidjet qo'shilgandan so'ng darhol chaqiriladi), "
"biz ``change:effective_readonly`` hodisasiga bog'laymiz. Bu bizga ``effective_readonly`` "
"vidjet xususiyati har safar o'zgarganda maydonni qayta ko'rsatishga imkon beradi. "
"Bu hodisa ishlovchisi ``display_field()`` ni chaqiradi, u shuningdek "
"``start()`` da to'g'ridan-to'g'ri chaqiriladi. Bu ``display_field()`` "
"maxsus ushbu maydon uchun yaratilgan, u ``AbstractField`` yoki boshqa "
"sinfda aniqlangan metod emas. Biz bu metoddan joriy rejimga qarab maydon "
"tarkibini ko'rsatish uchun foydalanishimiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2042
msgid ""
"From now on the conception of this field is typical, except there is a "
"lot of verifications to know the state of the ``effective_readonly`` "
"property:"
msgstr ""
"Bundan buyon bu maydonning tushunchasi odatiy, faqat ``effective_readonly`` "
"xususiyatining holatini bilish uchun ko'p tekshiruvlar mavjud:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2045
msgid ""
"In the QWeb template used to display the content of the widget, it "
"displays an ``<input type=\"text\" />`` if we are in read-write mode and "
"nothing in particular in read-only mode."
msgstr ""
"Vidjet tarkibini ko'rsatish uchun ishlatiladigan QWeb shablonida, agar biz "
"o'qish-yozish rejimida bo'lsak ``<input type=\"text\" />`` ko'rsatiladi va "
"faqat o'qish rejimida hech narsa ko'rsatilmaydi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2048
msgid ""
"In the ``display_field()`` method, we have to bind on the ``change`` "
"event of the ``<input type=\"text\" />`` to know when the user has "
"changed the value. When it happens, we call the ``internal_set_value()`` "
"method with the new value of the field. This is a convenience method "
"provided by the ``AbstractField`` class. That method will set a new value"
" in the ``value`` property but will not trigger a call to "
"``render_value()`` (which is not necessary since the ``<input "
"type=\"text\" />`` already contains the correct value)."
msgstr ""
"``display_field()`` metodida biz foydalanuvchi qiymatni qachon o'zgartirganligi "
"haqida bilish uchun ``<input type=\"text\" />`` ning ``change`` hodisasiga "
"bog'lashimiz kerak. Bu yuz berganda, biz maydonning yangi qiymati bilan "
"``internal_set_value()`` metodini chaqiramiz. Bu ``AbstractField`` sinfi "
"tomonidan taqdim etilgan qulay metoddir. Bu metod ``value`` xususiyatida "
"yangi qiymat o'rnatadi, lekin ``render_value()`` ga chaqiruvni ishga "
"tushirmaydi (bu zarur emas, chunki ``<input type=\"text\" />`` allaqachon "
"to'g'ri qiymatni o'z ichiga oladi)."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2056
msgid ""
"In ``render_value()``, we use a completely different code to display the "
"value of the field depending if we are in read-only or in read-write "
"mode."
msgstr ""
"``render_value()`` da biz faqat o'qish yoki o'qish-yozish rejimida "
"ekanligimizga qarab maydon qiymatini ko'rsatish uchun butunlay boshqacha "
"kodni ishlatamiz."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2059
msgid "Create a Color Field"
msgstr "Rang maydoni yaratish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2061
msgid ""
"Create a ``FieldColor`` class. The value of this field should be a string"
" containing a color code like those used in CSS (example: ``#FF0000`` for"
" red). In read-only mode, this color field should display a little block "
"whose color corresponds to the value of the field. In read-write mode, "
"you should display an ``<input type=\"color\" />``. That type of ``<input"
" />`` is an HTML5 component that doesn't work in all browsers but works "
"well in Google Chrome. So it's OK to use as an exercise."
msgstr ""
"``FieldColor`` sinfi yarating. Bu maydonning qiymati CSS da ishlatiladigan "
"rang kodi o'z ichiga olgan qator bo'lishi kerak (misol: qizil uchun ``#FF0000``). "
"Faqat o'qish rejimida, bu rang maydoni rangi maydon qiymatiga mos keladigan "
"kichik blok ko'rsatishi kerak. O'qish-yozish rejimida, ``<input type=\"color\" />`` "
"ko'rsatishingiz kerak. ``<input />`` ning bu turi barcha brauzerlarda ishlamaydigan, "
"lekin Google Chrome da yaxshi ishlaydigan HTML5 komponentidir. Shuning uchun "
"mashq sifatida foydalanish yaxshi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2069
msgid ""
"You can use that widget in the form view of the ``message_of_the_day`` "
"model for its field named ``color``. As a bonus, you can change the "
"``MessageOfTheDay`` widget created in the previous part of this guide to "
"display the message of the day with the background color indicated in the"
" ``color`` field."
msgstr ""
"Ushbu vidjetni ``message_of_the_day`` modelining ``color`` nomli maydoni "
"uchun forma ko'rinishida ishlatishingiz mumkin. Bonus sifatida, kunning "
"xabarini ``color`` maydonida ko'rsatilgan fon rangi bilan ko'rsatish uchun "
"ushbu qo'llanmaning oldingi qismida yaratilgan ``MessageOfTheDay`` vidjetini "
"o'zgartirishingiz mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2134
msgid "The Form View Custom Widgets"
msgstr "Forma ko'rinishining maxsus vidjetlari"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2136
msgid ""
"Form fields are used to edit a single field, and are intrinsically linked"
" to a field. Because this may be limiting, it is also possible to create "
"*form widgets* which are not so restricted and have less ties to a "
"specific lifecycle."
msgstr ""
"Forma maydonlari bitta maydonni tahrirlash uchun ishlatiladi va mohiyatan "
"maydon bilan bog'liq. Bu cheklovchi bo'lishi mumkinligi sababli, unchalik "
"cheklanmagan va muayyan hayot tsikli bilan kamroq bog'langan *forma "
"vidjetlari* yaratish ham mumkin."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2141
msgid ""
"Custom form widgets can be added to a form view through the ``widget`` "
"tag:"
msgstr "Maxsus forma vidjetlari ``widget`` tegi orqali forma ko'rinishiga qo'shilishi mumkin:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2147
msgid ""
"This type of widget will simply be created by the form view during the "
"creation of the HTML according to the XML definition. They have "
"properties in common with the fields (like the ``effective_readonly`` "
"property) but they are not assigned a precise field. And so they don't "
"have methods like ``get_value()`` and ``set_value()``. They must inherit "
"from the ``FormWidget`` abstract class."
msgstr ""
"Bu turdagi vidjet XML ta'rifiga muvofiq HTML yaratilayotganda forma "
"ko'rinishi tomonidan oddiygina yaratiladi. Ularda maydonlar bilan umumiy "
"xususiyatlar bor (masalan, ``effective_readonly`` xususiyati), lekin ularga "
"aniq maydon belgilanmaydi. Shuning uchun ularda ``get_value()`` va "
"``set_value()`` kabi metodlar yo'q. Ular ``FormWidget`` abstrakt sinfidan "
"meros olishlari kerak."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2154
msgid ""
"Form widgets can interact with form fields by listening for their changes"
" and fetching or altering their values. They can access form fields "
"through their :attr:`~odoo.web.form.FormWidget.field_manager` attribute::"
msgstr ""
"Forma vidjetlari forma maydonlari bilan ularning o'zgarishlarini tinglash va "
"qiymatlarini olish yoki o'zgartirish orqali o'zaro ta'sir qilishi mumkin. "
"Ular forma maydonlariga :attr:`~odoo.web.form.FormWidget.field_manager` "
"atributi orqali kirishlari mumkin::"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2174
msgid ""
":attr:`~odoo.web.form.FormWidget` is generally the "
":class:`~odoo.web.form.FormView` itself, but features used from it should"
" be limited to those defined by "
":class:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin`, the most useful being:"
msgstr ""
":attr:`~odoo.web.form.FormWidget` odatda :class:`~odoo.web.form.FormView` "
"ning o'zidir, lekin undan ishlatiladigan xususiyatlar "
":class:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin` tomonidan aniqlanganlari bilan "
"cheklanishi kerak, eng foydalilar:"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2179
msgid ""
":func:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin.get_field_value(field_name)` "
"which returns the value of a field."
msgstr ""
":func:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin.get_field_value(field_name)` "
"maydon qiymatini qaytaradi."

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2181
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":func:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin.set_values(values)` sets multiple"
" field values, takes a mapping of ``{field_name: value_to_set}``"
msgstr ""
":func:`~odoo.web.form.FieldManagerMixin.set_values(values)` bir nechta "
"maydon qiymatlarini o'rnatadi, ``{field_name: value_to_set}`` xaritasini oladi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2183
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"An event :samp:`field_changed:{field_name}` is triggered any time the "
"value of the field called ``field_name`` is changed"
msgstr ""
":samp:`field_changed:{field_name}` hodisasi ``field_name`` deb atalgan "
"maydon qiymati har safar o'zgarganda ishga tushadi"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2186
msgid "Show Coordinates on Google Map"
msgstr "Google Xaritada koordinatalarni ko'rsatish"

#: ../../content/developer/tutorials/web.rst:2188
msgid ""
"Add two fields to ``product.product`` storing a latitude and a longitude,"
" then create a new form widget to display the latitude and longitude of a"
